(72, '', 'From 66 West: Take the exit for Rt 123 South towards Fairfax In approx 2 miles, you\'ll approach North St (there will be a sign that says to Rt 236 West) Turn right there, it will swerve you to the left and then you\'ll be on Rt 236. About a block down on the right is an office/apartment complex and Bridges is in there From 66 East and other points west: Take the exit for Rt 50 East The intersection where you\'ll see Rt 50 and Rt 29 going to the left, you\'ll be staying straight and getting on Rt 236. In about a mile (soon after the light for Judicial Drive), there will be an office/apartment complex on the left and Bridges is in there From the Beltway: Take 66 West and follow the first set of directions if you\'re coming from the north, but if you\'re coming from the south, take: The exit for Little River Turnpike (Rt. 236) West towards Fairfax In about 5 miles, you\'ll be in Old Towne Fairfax (you\'ll know b/c you\'ll be forced to swerve to the right, then soon you\'ll be swerving back to the left in order to stay on Rt. 236). In about a block after you pass Old Towne, there will be an office/apartment complex on the right and Bridges is in there ', 'Bridges (duh, that is why you park there)', '', 'Parking lot of Bridges Billiards and Grill 10560 Main Street, Fairfax ', ''),
(74, '', 'Capitol beltway exit 44 heading west on 193. go approx. .7 miles. As you descend to the bottom of the hill, there will be a sign for Betty Cooke Memorial Bridge. There will also be a pink house on the left. Take a right into Scott\'s run at that point. There will be a walkers\' trail provided.\r\n\r\nIf you\'re coming from Rt. 7, head (who said head?) east on 193.  Go past our normal stop at Difficult Run.  Trail will be on the left.  Apparently, it\'ll be somewhere near the bridge and some pink house.  ', '', 'There is a Scott\'s run nature preserve with a parking lot right off the highway.  <b>Do not go here</b>.  Go to the bottom of the hill and turn in right before (after, if coming from Rt. 7) the Cooke bridge.\r\n\r\nSign-up begins at 6:30, hares away at 7:00.\r\n\r\nRemember... it\'s freakin\' <b><font color="blue">cold</font></b>!  Wear warm clothes!', '', ''),
(75, '', 'From I-66, exit onto Fairfax County Parkway North. Make Left at first light onto Fair Lakes Parkway. Make Left onto Stringfellow Rd. Turn right into commuter lot before I-66 overpass. From Sterling, take Rt 28 South. Exit onto Rt 50 East. Make right onto Stringfellow Rd. Make right into commuter lot before I-66 overpass. ', 'TBD (probably O\'Toole\'s)', 'Sign-up begins at 6:30, hares away at 7:00.\r\n\r\nRemember... it\'s freakin\' <b><font color="blue">cold</font></b>!  Wear warm clothes!', 'Commuter lot on Stringfellow Rd, near Fair Lakes ', ''),
(76, '<P><B><I>In Catholicism ', '<P class=western style="MARGIN-TOP: 0in; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0in"><FONT face="Times New Roman, serif"><STRONG><FONT face="Georgia, MS Reference Serif, serif"><FONT color=#ff0000>From Sterling:</FONT></STRONG><SPAN>Take Atlantic Boulevard, North towards Route 7, Atlantic Boulevard turns into Algonkian Parkway. Continue on Algonkian Parkway through the lights at Cascades Boulevard, Potomac Falls Road and Hardwood Forest. Take RIGHT at next light into shopping Center. Look for deviants in parking lot</SPAN></FONT><FONT face="Georgia, MS Reference Serif, serif">.</FONT></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=western style="MARGIN-TOP: 0in; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0in"><FONT face="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT face="Georgia, MS Reference Serif, serif">Or: Take Cascades Boulevard towards Algonkian Park. Take RIGHT at light onto Algonkian Parkway. Go through the lights at </FONT><SPAN><FONT face="Georgia, MS Reference Serif, serif">Potomac Falls Road and Hardwood Forest. Take RIGHT at next light into shopping Center. Look for deviants in parking lot</FONT></SPAN><FONT face="Georgia, MS Reference  erif, serif">.</FONT></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=western style="MARGIN-TOP: 0in; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0in"><FONT face="Times New Roman, serif"><FONT face="Georgia, MS Reference Serif, serif">Or: Take Sterling Boulevard, North towards Route 7. Take a RIGHT onto Route 7 towards Tysons Corner. Take the ramp to Algonkian Parkway / Fairfax County Parkway. Take a LEFT at the top of the ramp onto Algonkian Parkway. Continue on Algonkian Parkway for approx. (2) miles to shopping center on your LEFT. </FONT><SPAN><FONT face="Georgia, MS Reference Serif, serif">Look for deviants in parking lot</FONT></SPAN><FONT face="Georgia, MS Reference Serif, serif">.</FONT></FONT></P>\r\n<P class=western style="MARGIN-TOP: 0in; MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0in"><FONT face="Times New Roman, serif"><STRONG><FONT face="Georgia, MS Reference Serif, serif"><FONT color=#ff0000>From Reston / Herndon Area:</FONT> </STRONG><SPAN>F