(79, '<P style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align=center><FONT face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt">Eddie Money and John Bon Jovi Birthday Extravaganzaa where you can </SPAN><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: black; mso-bidi-font-size: 10.0pt">run, run so far awaaaaay, run all night and daaaaay<?xml:namespace prefix = o ns = "urn:schemas-microsoft-com:office:office" /><o:p></o:p></SPAN></FONT></P><SPAN style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-fareast-font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><FONT face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, Serif">Come dressed as your favorite 80s rocker and win prizes!</FONT></SPAN> ', '<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, Serif" size=3>From the East:</FONT></P>\r\n<OL style="MARGIN-TOP: 0in" type=1>\r\n<LI class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in"><FONT face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT size=3>Get out of my dreams and into your car and make your way to 66 West.</FONT> </FONT>\r\n<LI class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-list: l1 level1 lfo1; tab-stops: list .5in"><FONT face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><FONT size=3>Until you can', 'You just can', '', '<P class=MsoNormal style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><FONT face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, Serif" size=3>The Orbital Parking Lot in Sterling', ''),
(80, '<br />', '<p><font face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, Serif">From 66:  </font></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><font face="Georgia">Head (who said head?) north on 28.  </font>\r\n</li><li><font face="Georgia">Take a right on Frying Pan Rd.</font> \r\n</li><li><font face="Georgia">Take a left on Centreville Road. </font>\r\n</li><li><font face="Georgia">Take your second left onto McNair Farms</font> \r\n</li><li><font face="Georgia">Take your second right onto Isham Randolph. </font>\r\n</li><li><font face="Georgia">Park wherever you can find it.  </font>\r\n</li><li><font face="Georgia">Go behind FOC\'s house and hash</font></li></ol>\r\n<p><font face="Georgia">From inside the beltway:</font></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><font face="Georgia">Take the toll road west. </font>\r\n</li><li><font face="Georgia">Take the exit for Elden St. and head south. </font>\r\n</li><li><font face="Georgia">Take a right on McNair Farms</font> \r\n</li><li><font face="Georgia">Take the second right onto McNair Farms</font> \r\n</li><li><font face="Georgia">Park where you can find it. </font>\r\n</li><li><font face="Georgia">Go behind FOC\'s house and hash</font></li></ol>\r\n<p>From the North:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>Take 28 South \r\n</li><li>Turn left on Frying Pan Rd. (just past the toll road) \r\n</li><li><font face="Georgia">Take a left on Centreville Road. </font>\r\n</li><li><font face="Georgia">Take your second left onto McNair Farms</font> \r\n</li><li><font face="Georgia">Take your second right onto Isham Randolph. </font>\r\n</li><li><font face="Georgia">Park wherever you can find it.  </font>\r\n</li><li><font face="Georgia">Go behind FOC\'s house and hash</font></li></ol>', 'Ned Devine\'s', 'Parking will be tight on Isham Randolph.  You\'ll probably have better luck parking on McNair Farms', '<p><font face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, Serif">Behind FOC\'s House</font><br /><font face="Georgia"><a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/map.adp?country=US&countryid=250&addtohistory=&address=2514+isham+randolph+Drive&city=herndon&state=va&zipcode=+&submit=Get+Map">2514 Isham Randolph Dr.</a></font><br /><font face="Georgia"><a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/map.adp?country=US&countryid=250&addtohistory=&address=2514+isham+randolph+Drive&city=herndon&state=va&zipcode=+&submit=Get+Map">Herndon, VA  20171</a></font></p>', ''),
(82, '', 'From toll Road<br />Take route 28 towards Sterling and after the toll both take a left at Old Ox Road (2nd light, route 606)). Follow Old Ox for a few yards then take a right onto Pacific followed by a right onto Indian Circle. Start is around the back of the unoccupied building on your right, after the Fairfield Inn. Look for wankers and Hash. <p>From route 7<br />Take 28 towards Dulles and after Sterling Parkway take a right onto Old Ox Road (route 606). Take the next right onto Pacific and go past the Fairfield Inn. Turn right into the parking lot of the unoccupied office building and go towards the back. Look for wankers and Hash. </p>', 'Jimmy\'s in Herndon', '', '', ''),
(81, '<br />\r\n', '\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="3"><font face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><span><strong>From Sterling</strong>:</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span>Get to Route 7 East towards Tysons. Take a LEFT onto Georgetown Pike  and go a few miles until you pass Great Falls Park on your left. Soon after downhill see right before turn immediate right into Difficult Run Stream Park and look for miscreants milling about &quot;with bad intent&quot; amongst the wankers.</span></font></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font size="3"><font face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><span><strong>From Reston / Herndon Area/Springfield / Burke</strong>:</span><span>&nbsp;</span><span>Find your way to Fairfax County Parkway, (Route 7100) North. Follow Fairfax County Parkway to the bridge at Route 7. Take a Right onto Route 7, East (towards Tyson\'s)<span>Or: Find your way to Route 7, East. Proceed on Route 7, East, then a left onto Georgetown Pike. </span></span><span> Go a few miles until you pass Great Falls Park on your left. Soon after downhill see right before turn immediate right into Difficult Run Stream Park and look for miscreants milling about &quot;with bad intent&quot; amongst the wankers.</span></font></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span><font size="3"><font face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><strong>From the Beltway</strong>: Take the Georgetown Pike (193) exit and go Northwest outside the beltway for 3.5 miles. Make abrupt, challenging turn left in valley bottom into Difficult Run Park and look for miscreants milling about &quot;with bad intent&quot; amongst the wankers. </font></font></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font size="3"><font face="Georgia, Times New Roman, Times, Serif"><span class="header2"><span>Or check with map', '<br />\r\n', '<br />\r\n', '\r\n<p align="center"><font size="3" face="Georgia"><span>&quot;Little &quot; Difficult Run Streeeeaaam Park directly abutting Great Falls Park on Georgetown Pike</span></fo