(87, '<font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">After perusing for hours for some theme for this weeks', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">From the Beltway: Take the I-66, West toward Manassas/Winchester. Take the exit for Route 50, West toward Chantilly/Winchester. Continue on Route 50 past the exits for Fair Oaks Shopping Center; Fairfax County Parkway; Stringfellow Road. After going through the light at Metrotech Drive (at Sully Place Shopping Center) take a RIGHT onto Centreville Road. Continue on Centreville Road for approx. ', '<p><!--StartFragment --><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Damon\'s Grill<br />3980 Corsair Court<br />Chantilly, VA 20151<br />(703) 481-9384<br /><br />From Route 50 West: RIGHT onto Centerview Drive. LEFT onto Thunderbolt Lane. LEFT onto Corsair Court.<br /><br />From Centreville Road: (From Herndon... RIGHT onto Skyhawk; From Route 50 LEFT onto Skyhawk) LEFT onto Centerview Road. RIGHT onto Thunderbolt Lane. LEFT onto Corsair Court.</font></p>', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">This trail is guaranteed to be short', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Behind the Camber building at:<br /><a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/map.adp?ovi=1&zoom=7&mapdata=IgGhLx%2bMihCnQqp0P8YMx5zIm5m0%2f8PO6WNZQko4zzgAOTK1G93b3tomqLmwt91RbJJvZB2mbtZpjzhMBzT6%2fXWnIZNvSRWGm%2byG%2be%2fJoUi21nwyhU28P29OzcQWGAW8AKMBvHfM8kGLok20%2b9ZR3ip1P%2fKkN5w68qPW7qNmAscZ41XphjNYg%2fXNNsLmSbMo5iai5SOtmvvDZiwlhBXgqNkqROjHXxaxWhx6KeNbVf6BfoApxchw9BlhwL001bcgJ7hIKAT9O%2bf8aj9640GUb3Y74WBpuURqd4QuIH14A9fsbYeWIqf6dwCjxQ%2bIN3ttFmRITNWHNMh51ghBO7sjxUXq0rhWGidizCAC8kRmemfbm%2f1WHtzlpw%3d%3d">3855 Centerview Drive; Chantilly, VA</a></font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">(at the intersection of Centerview Drive and Skyhawk Drive', ''),
(88, '<!--StartFragment --><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Those of you that know me know I\'ve been dreading this moment for quite some time and the terrible event is now upon me. My 30th birthday. (Cue huge bolts of lightning and terrible crashes of thunder.) I can think of nowhere else I\'d rather be than haring a trail as my youth slips away into oblivion. (More lightning and thunder.) So come out and help me mourn the end of my 20\'s (I\'ll be wearing black to mark the occasion, feel free to join me). Trail is guaranteed to be short (I\'m old now and can\'t run far), flat (I\'m old now and can\'t run hills), dry (I\'m old now and hate running with wet feet), and poison ivy free (I\'m old now and don\'t heal very quickly). (End with one final crack of thunder then the ominous silence of a graveyard.)</font>', '<p><!--StartFragment --><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">From Webster City, Iowa (where I was born 30 years ago): Head east. Cross into Wisconsin, drop into Illinois, then go through Indiana, Ohio, Pennsylvania and Maryland. Head south on 270 to 495 toward Northern VA/Tyson\'s Corner. Take the LEFT exit for the 66 east connector (also east 267). Take first exit, Chain Bridge Road to Tyson\'s corner. Proceed straight through stoplight at the end of the ramp (Anderson Rd.). Continue about .3 miles, Safeway is on your right. Look for wankers, park and hash. Should take you about 16 hours. </font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">From Sterling/Reston: Take the toll road east. Pass under the beltway. Take the first exit (Chain Bridge Road to Tyson\'s Corner). Proceed straight through stoplight at the end of the ramp (Anderson Rd.). Continue about .3 miles, Safeway is on your right. Look for wankers, park and hash. If there\'s an accident on the toll road it could take you about 16 hours. </font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">From 66: Take 66 east. Exit on 495 north toward Baltimore. Continue to exit 46B, take Ramp onto SR-123 [Dolley Madison Blvd] towards VA-123 / Chain Bridge Rd / McLean. At the third light take a right (Anderson Rd.). Do not get confused. You will pass Colshire Dr. at the second light. Don\'t take it, it will screw you up. Take Anderson (3rd light). Continue about .3 miles, Safeway is on your right. Look for wankers, park and hash. If there\'s an accident on 66 it could take you about 16 hours. </font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">From DC: HOV restrictions lift on 66 west at 6:30. Then it becomes a parking lot for the next 2 hours. I would take The George Washington Parkway north about 5.5 miles. Exit at 123 Chain Bridge Road and take a right at the end of the ramp (toward McLean). Continue 4.3 miles to Anderson Road and take a left. Continue about .3 miles, Safeway is on your right. Look for wankers, park and hash. If there\'s an accident on the Parkway it could take you about 16 hours. </font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">From Points South: Get on the Beltway toward Tyson\'s Corner. Continue to exit 46B, take Ramp onto SR-123 [Dolley Madison Blvd] towards VA-123 / Chain Bridge Rd / McLean. At the third light take a right (Anderson Rd.). Do not get confused. You will pass Colshire Dr. at the second light. Don\'t take it, it will screw you up. Take Anderson (3rd light). Continue about .3 miles, Safeway is on your right. Look for wankers, park and hash. If there\'s an accident on the beltway it could take you about 16 hours. </font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><b>Metro:</b> Nearest Metro is West Falls Church - about 1.5 to 2 miles away from start. Could take you about 16 hours if you get lost. </font></p>', '<!--StartFragment --><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Mr. Smith\'s of Georgetown (703) 893-5500 (on Leesburg Pike/Route 7) less than a mile west of the beltway (in Tyson\'s Corner)</font>', '<br />', '<!--StartFragment --><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><a href="http://mappoint.msn.com/(qx5f02454o3vba55z1wpea45)/map.aspx?L=USA&C8.92401,-77.20100&A=7.16667&P=|38.92401,-77.20100|1|7401+Colshire+Dr,+McLean,+VA+22102|L1|">Safeway at the corner of Anderson Rd. and Colshire Dr., McLean</a> </font>', ''),
