(117, '<center><h1><font face="Chiller">THIRD ANNUAL HALLOWEENIE PUB CRAWL<br />(A.K.A. TOUR DE BASURA BLANCA)<br />octoBEER 26, 2004<br />Sign-in at 6:30pm, Hares Away at 7:00pm<br /></font></h1><font face="Chiller">&nbsp;</font> </center><font size="7" face="Chiller">&nbsp;</font><p><font size="7" face="Chiller"><b>SPECIAL NOTE FROM THE HARES</b><br /></font></p><center><font size="7" face="Chiller"><font size="5" face="Chiller">** Cost for this special trail is $11 (pre-reg), $13 at the door in a costume and $15 if youre not! **<br />(Please see the following examples) </font></font></center><center><table><tbody><tr><td valign="top" align="center"><font size="6" face="Chiller">Costume!</font><br /><img src="/images/hall3_1.jpg" /> </td><td valign="top" align="center"><font size="6" face="Chiller">Not a costume...</font><br /><img src="/images/hall3_2.jpg" /> </td></tr><tr><td valign="top" align="center"><font size="6" face="Chiller">Costume!</font><br /><img src="/images/hall3_3.jpg" /> </td><td valign="top" align="center"><font size="6" face="Chiller">Not a costume...?</font><br /><img src="/images/hall3_4.jpg" /> </td></tr></tbody></table></center>', '<font size="4">&nbsp;</font><font size="4"><font face="Chiller"><b><b>From the Dulles Toll Road:</b><br />Take exit 9B (28 North), turn right on Sterling Blvd, turn right on East Poplar. Park on the street near #103 (first house on the left).<br /><br /><b>From Route 7 (either direction):</b><br />Turn onto Sterling Blvd, go through several lights, turn left on East Poplar. Park on the street near #103 (first house on the left).<br /><br />Mapquest: 103 East Poplar Road, Sterling, VA 20164</b></font> </font>', '<br />', '<font size="6"><font face="Chiller">Costumes, costumes, costumes!</font> </font>', '<!--StartFragment --><font size="5" face="Chiller"><font size="6"><b>TUPPERWARES MOMS HOUSE</b></font></font> <br />', ''),
(130, '', 'From Dulles Airport Direction:<br /><ul><li>Take RT 28 Sully Rd NORTH </li><li>Turn left on Waxpool rd. </li><li>Turn right on Smith Switch Rd </li><li>Should be first road after Loudon County Pky </li></ul><p>From the north:<br /></p><ul><li>Take RT 28 Sully Rd SOUTH </li><li>Turn left on Waxpool rd. </li><li>Turn right on Smith Switch Rd </li><li>Should be first road after Loudon County Pky </li></ul><p>look for <a href="http://pages.loudouncounty.com/sports/ash_ice4.jpg">this building</a> with curved roof &amp; giant skater silhouette</p>', '<font size="3"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Hell if I know. What\'s in Two Creeks?</span></font>', '<span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Dog friendly. And bring a flashlight! And some WARM clothes!<br /></span>', 'Ashburn Ice House parking lot<br />21595 Smiths Switch Road<br />Ashburn, VA 20147', ''),
(111, '<br />', '<span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><font size="3"><span style="font-weight: bold;">From outside of Arlington<br /><span style="font-weight: bold;"></span></span>Take route 66 to Fairfax Dr., Exit 71.  Stay on Fairfax Drive (at the stop light for Glebe) and continue on about a mile.  Take a right onto Monroe St. and go past the Virginia Square Metro and over Wilson Blvd.  Bear to your left at the traffic circle then take your immediate left onto 6<sup>th</sup> St.  Park on the street (or nearby).  Udder Ho\'s house is the only one on the right.  Walk around back and look for wankers.<br /><br /><span style="font-weight: bold;">Or... take Metro:</span><br />Get off at Virginia Square.  Clean yourself up and then walk towards Wilson Blvd.  Cross Wilson and follow Monroe for 1 1/2 blocks.  Bear left at the traffic circle and take the next left onto 6<sup>th</sup> St.  House is the only one on the right.  Go around back and look for wankers.<br /><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-weight: bold;"></span><br /></span></font></span>', '<font size="3"><span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">Clarendon Grill</span></font><br />', '<font size="3"><span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">Bring a partner and something to tie yourselves together, or take the luck of the draw on who you get attached to all night!  Any tether is acceptable, so show some imagination as you keep your legs together.  </span></font>', '<font size="3"><span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">Udder Ho\'s House</span><br style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" />3508 6<sup>th</sup> St<br />Arlington, VA<br style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" /></font>', ''),
