(132, 'Welcome to the first annual So Happy It\'s Fat Tuesday Hash, brought to you , as is every Tuesday, by the So Happy It\'s Tuesday Hash House Harriers!<p>Registration starts at 6:30, hares away at 7:00.</p>', '<b>From the west</b>: Take 66 east.  Exit 71 (Fairfax Dr / VA-120 / VA-237 / Glebe Rd).  Continue straight on Fairfax Dr. about 0.8 miles.  Left on Quincy for about .4 miles.  Turn left on N. 15th St. and then take an immediate left into the parking structure.  Look for wankers, park and hash.\r\n\r\n \r\n<p>\r\n<b>From the east</b>: Take 66 west.  Exit 71 (Fairfax Dr / VA-120 / VA-237 / Glebe Rd).  Left on Glebe Road.  Left on Fairfax Drive about .4 miles.  Left on Quincy for about .4 miles.  Turn left on N. 15th St. and then take an immediate left into the parking structure.  Look for wankers, park and hash.\r\n\r\n \r\n</p><p>\r\n<b>Metro</b>: Exit at Ballston Station (orange line).  Walk north on Stafford Street 4 blocks.  Pass Washington-Lee High School on your right and look for the parking structure over 66 directly behind the school.  Look for wankers and hash.</p>', 'Chevy\'s, in Ballston', 'Come dressed for your Mardi Gras festivities, even if it\'s just a string of beads!\r\n<p>\r\nBear in mind that this is a real hash... it is <i>not</i> a pub crawl.  Weather is supposed to be warmer than it has been, but still, be smart (or as smart as you can be).  And don\'t forget flashlights!\r\n</p><p>\r\nToetag Beads to the first 60 people.</p>', 'Ballston-MU Metro Parking Lot', ''),
(133, '<span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">Sign-in at 6:30, hares away at 7:00<br /></span>', '<span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">From the east:</span><br /></span><ul><li>Take 66 to the toll road and follow toll road.<br /></li><li>Take lucky exit 13 (Wiehle) and take a right onto Wiehle (Note:  $0.75 toll!)<br /></li><li>Go through the intersection with Baron Cameron and take a left on Center Harbor Road</li><li>Follow Center Harbor to Reston Parkway, and the shopping center should be right in front of you. <br /></li><li>Take a left behind the Blockbuster and start looking for love</li></ul><span style="font-weight: bold;">From Sterling:<br /></span><ul><li>Take Rt. 7 to Reston Parkway and take a right</li><li>Go through one stop light, and the shopping center should be at the next light</li><li>Turn right and follow behind the Blockbuster.  Look for whatever love is left.</li></ul><span style="font-weight: bold;">From the South:<br /></span><ul><li>Take 28N to the toll road</li><li>Follow the toll road towards Reston ($0.35 toll)</li><li>Take the exit for Reston Parkway and turn left</li><li>About a mile after the intersection with Baron Cameron, the shopping center will be on your left</li><li>Turn left and maneuver your way behind Blockbuster.  Look for some miniscule scraps of love.  <br /></li></ul>', 'TBD', '<br />', '<span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">Behind the Blockbuster<br />North Shore Shopping Center<br />Reston, VA<br /></span>', ''),
(134, 'Then we can ', '<strong><span style="color: red; font-family: Georgia;"><o:p /></span></strong>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><font size="3"><strong><span style="color: red; font-family: Georgia;">From Sterling/Herndon/Reston: </span></strong><strong><span style="font-weight: normal; font-family: Georgia;">Make your way to the Beltway (I-495', 'Grevey', 'Live trail (as usual)', 'At Lurie Park; Falls Church, VA\r\n<p>\r\n(at the intersection of Holmes Run Drive and Executive Avenue)<br />\r\n(ADC Map: Northern VA 15, D-09, Fac)</p>', ''),
(135, '<br />', '<font color="red">From the east</font>:<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Find your way to 66 West</li>\r\n<li>Take exit 55 (7100) North, towards Reston</li>\r\n<li>At the first light, turn left onto Fair Lakes Parkway</li>\r\n<li>After about a miie, turn left onto Fair Lakes Blvd.</li>\r\n<li>At the next light, turn left into Fair Lakes Shopping Center</li>\r\n<li>The Food Lion is right in front of you.  Find the wankers, park and hash</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n<font color="red">From the north</font>:<br />\r\n</p><ul>\r\n<li>Take Fairfax County Parkway (7100) South</li>\r\n<li>Just before 66, turn left on Fair Lakes Parkway</li>\r\n<li>After about a mile, turn left on Fair Lakes Blvd</li>\r\n<li>At the light, turn left into Fair Lakes Shopping Center</li>\r\n<li>The Food Lion is right in front of you.  Find the wankers, park and hash</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>\r\n<font color="red">From the west</font>:<br />\r\n</p><ul>\r\n<li>Find your way to 66 East</li>\r\n<li>Take exit 55 (7100) North... hey, this looks familiar... follow the directions as above</li>\r\n</ul>', 'TBD', 'Yada, yada, dress warm, bring a flashlight, beautiful young female virgins, etc.', 'Fair Lakes Shopping Center in the Food Lion parking lot<br />\r\n<a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/map.adp?country=US&addtohistory=&formtype=address&searchtype=address&cat=&address=13065%20Fair%20Lakes%20Shopping%20Ctr&city=Fairfax&state=VA&zipcode=22033%2d5179&searchtab=home">13065 Fair Lakes Shopping Ctr<br />\r\nFairfax, VA 22033</a><br />', ''),
(136, '', '<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="COLOR: rgb(204,0,0)">From </span><place style="COLOR: rgb(204,0,0)" w:st="on"><city w:st="on">Manassas</city></place> take Rt 28 North to west on <street w:st="on"><address w:st="on">Waxpool Rd.</address></street> (new on ramp from the right lane).<span>', '<span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Kilpatricks</span>', '<span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif">It\'s still cold -- wear warm clothes. And bring a flashlight. And virgins.<br /></span>', '<span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Home Depot in Ashburn<br /></span><a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/map.adp?country=US&addtohistory=&formtype=address&searchtype=address&cat=&address=%5b21500%2d21531%5d%20Shellhorn%20Rd&city=Ashburn&state=VA&zipcode=20147&searchtab=home"><font class="TDheaderGRAY"><font size="+0"><font class="GRAYcontent">21421 Shellhorn Road<br />Ashburn, VA 20147</font></font></font></a><br />', ''),
(137, '', 'From the South: <br />From the Beltway (you can find that, right?), take the VA-620 W/BRADDOCK RD WEST exit- EXIT 54A. <br />Go to the first light and Turn LEFT onto PORT ROYAL RD. <br />Go to the right rear on shopping center next to the 7-11<br />Find Wankers and Hash.<br /><br />From the North:<br />Take the Beltway to VA-620W/Braddock Rd., exit 54A.', '', 'You better have your green on or 14 O\'Karat C*ck will find you!', 'Ravensworth Shopping Center Behind 7-11', ''),
(138, '', '<font size="2"><b>From Points West</b><i>:</i>\r\n 66 East to Rte. 110 South to Rte. 1 South. After you come across the\r\ns-curve bridge over the railroad tracks, continue through three more\r\nlights and turn RIGHT on Wythe for one block, then RIGHT on N.\r\nFayette for a half-block. We are the four-story brick townhouses on\r\nyour RIGHT; 727 is located at the far left corner of the courtyard\r\n(end unit). <b>Please park on the street.</b></font>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><font size="2"><b>From Points South</b><i>:</i>\r\nGet yourself to Route 1 North, which becomes N. Patrick Street as you\r\ndrive through Old Town. LEFT on Wythe for two blocks; RIGHT on N.\r\nFayette for a half-block. We are the four-story brick townhouses on\r\nyour RIGHT; 727 is located at the far left corner of the courtyard\r\n(end unit). <b>Please park on the street.</b></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><font size="2"><b>From Points North</b><i>:</i>\r\nGet yourself to 395 South, then exit GW Parkway (take the exit marked\r\nReagan National Airport), which becomes N. Washington St. as you\r\nenter Old Town. RIGHT on Wythe for five blocks, RIGHT on N. Fayette\r\nfor a half-block. We are the four-story brick townhouses on your\r\nRIGHT; 727 is located at the far left corner of the courtyard (end\r\nunit). <b>Please park on the street.</b></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><font size="2">Or ', 'TBD', '', '<p style="margin-bottom: 0in; font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><font size="2">Porta-Potter &amp; Dead\r\nHare', ''),
(139, 'Yes folks... that\'s right... \'Porn To Fail\' makes his debut haring here at So Happy It\'s Tuesday Hash House Harriers!! He\'s already named... so there\'s no \'Gets Off Easy\' this time!!\r\n\r\n<p>\r\nActually... \'Gets Off Easy\' was suppose to hare, but she called in a sub... \'Lube Me Up Scottie\'. And as we were \'downing\' a few ales last night... we decided &quot;What the f*ck... \'Holy F*ck\' should hare too... so we conveniently volunteered him.\r\n\r\n</p><p>\r\nHence... \'Bound to Fail\' trail... (oops... now we won\'t see \'Watergate\'!!)</p>', '<font color="red">From Sterling/Herndon/Reston:</font> Make your way toward the Beltway (I-495... via Dulles Toll Road; Route 7). If you are cumming via Dulles Toll Road, take the Route 7 East toward Tysons, McLean, Vienna... and if cumming straight down Route 7 East, cross over the Dulles Toll Road. Take a RIGHT onto Westwood Center Drive (a left would take you onto Tyco Road... if you get to Spring Hill Road, you\'ve gone too far). Proceed to the dead-end of Westwood Center Drive to office building parking lot on your left and look for deviants. \r\n\r\n \r\n<p>\r\n\r\n<font color="red">From the Beltway:</font>\r\n</p><p>\r\n\r\n<font color="red">Option A:</font> Take Route 7 West. Go through a million lights (approximately 1 ', 'Mr. Smith\'s (<i>another favorite bar!!</i>)', 'Live trail (as usual)... It\'s dark but not as dark as yesterday... so... BRING A FLASHLIGHT, you numbnuts!!\r\n\r\n \r\n<p>\r\nOh... and don\'t forget to bring those... \'Beautiful Young Female Virgins\'!!</p>', 'At Office Building Parking Lot; Tysons Corner, VA\r\n<p>\r\n(dead-end of Westwood Center Drive, which is across Route 7 from Tyco Road)<br />\r\n(ADC Map: Northern VA (some page), (A thru Z-with some #, Fac)</p>', ''),
(140, '<p align="center" class="MsoNormal" style="text-align: center;"><span>Dig out your old sheets and your crowns of\r\nlaurel', '<p style="text-decoration: underline;">From points south &amp; southwest</p>\r\n\r\n<ol type="1" style="margin-top: 0in; font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" start="1"><li class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Take\r\n     66-E to exit 53 (Route 28 North/Dulles Airport).<o:p /></span></li><li class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Go 11\r\n     miles or so and turn right onto <st1:street w:st="on"><st1:address w:st="on">Sterling\r\n       Blvd.</st1:address></st1:street><o:p /></span></li><li class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Go\r\n     about a mile and turn right onto East Poplar.<o:p /></span></li><li class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Park\r\n     on the street and meet us in the back yard, pay and hash.<o:p /></span></li></ol>\r\n\r\n<p style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-decoration: underline;">From points west (like, Leesburg)</p>\r\n\r\n<ol type="1" style="margin-top: 0in; font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" start="1"><li class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Take\r\n     Route 7 East (Leesburg Pike) to Route 28 South.<o:p /></span></li><li class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Go 4\r\n     miles or so and turn left onto <st1:street w:st="on"><st1:address w:st="on">Sterling\r\n       Blvd.</st1:address></st1:street><o:p /></span></li><li class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Go\r\n     about a mile and turn right onto East Poplar.<o:p /></span></li><li class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Park\r\n     on the street and meet us in the back yard, pay and hash.<o:p /></span></li></ol>\r\n\r\n<p style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style="text-decoration: underline;">From points east</p>\r\n\r\n<ol type="1" style="margin-top: 0in; font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" start="1"><li class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Take\r\n     66-W to exit 67 (Dulles Toll Road/I-495 North).<o:p /></span></li><li class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">From\r\n     the toll road, take exit 9B (Route 28 North/Dulles Airport).<o:p /></span></li><li class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Go\r\n     about 2 miles and turn right onto <st1:street w:st="on"><st1:address w:st="on">Sterling Blvd.</st1:address></st1:street><o:p /></span></li><li class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Go\r\n     about a mile and turn right onto East Poplar.<o:p /></span></li><li class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Park\r\n     on the street and meet us in the back yard, pay and hash.<o:p /></span></li></ol>', '<span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">Duh, the Barefoot Pelican!</span>', '<p style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" class="MsoBodyText">Yes, just like last year, you gotta wear a toga.<span>&nbsp;</span>We might have prizes and we might not.<span>&nbsp;</span>The Pelican will be giving special\r\nfood/beverage discounts to anyone wearing theirs at the OnOnOn, and that', '<span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">Duh, Tuppy\'s Mom\'s house<br /><a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/map.adp?country=US&addtohistory=&formtype=address&searchtype=address&cat=&address=103%20E%20Poplar%20Rd&city=Sterling&state=VA&zipcode=20164%2d3303&searchtab=home">103 East Poplar Rd.<br />Sterling, VA  20164</a><br /></span>', ''),
(141, '', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><b><span style="font-size: 11pt;"> From Rt.\r\n66:<o:p /></span></b><br /><span style="font-size: 11pt;">Take Rt. 66 E to exit 71 (<st1:street w:st="on"><st1:address w:st="on">Fairfax Dr./Glebe Rd</st1:address></st1:street>). Turn right onto <st1:street w:st="on"><st1:address w:st="on">Glebe Rd</st1:address></st1:street>, which is\r\njust past Holiday Inn. Go through multiple lights (seems like forever). <o:p><br />After you cross over <st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Columbia</st1:place></st1:city>\r\npike, turn right onto <st1:street w:st="on"><st1:address w:st="on">Walter Reed\r\n  Dr</st1:address></st1:street>.<o:p><br />As you', '<span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">Bungalow Billiards<br />2766 South Arlington Mill Dr. <br /></span>', '', '<span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">Fort Barnard Park<br /><a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/map.adp?searchtype=address&country=US&addtohistory=&searchtab=home&address=2101+South+Pollard+St&city=Arlington&state=VA&zipcode=">2101 S. Pollard St. <br />Arlington, VA</a><br /></span>', ''),
(142, '', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(204, 0, 0);">From Tysons Corner</span>: take 495 south to <st1:street w:st="on"><st1:address w:st="on">Braddock Rd.</st1:address></st1:street> exit.\r\nGo west on <st1:street w:st="on"><st1:address w:st="on">Braddock Rd.</st1:address></st1:street>\r\nTake a left on Rt 123, then a left into University Mall. Look for wankers between Giant and the M &amp; T Bank.<o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="color: rgb(204, 0, 0);">From Centreville</span>: take Rt 28 south to a left on <st1:street w:st="on"><st1:address w:st="on">Braddock Rd.</st1:address></st1:street> Go\r\nabout 7 miles and take a right on Rt 123. Go left into University Mall, look\r\nfor wankers between Giant and the M &amp; T Bank.</p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">And there is always <a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/map.adp?city=Fairfax&state=VA&address=10673+Braddock+Road+(University+Mall)&zoom=8">MAP QUEST</a>!!!!!!!</p>', '<span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">Fat Tuesday\'s</span>', '', '<span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">University Mall in <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:city w:st="on">Fairfax</st1:city></st1:place></span>', ''),
(143, '<font face="Tahoma" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">I<span class="853324413-20042005">t\'s the 19th anniversary of Chernobyl, and we decided \r\nwe\'d celebrate by heading to Centreville...</span></font>', '<div style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">From points east of Centreville.... take 66 to the Rt.29 \r\nexit in Centreville (exit 52 I think).  Take right on Rt.29 (Lee Highway) \r\nand take second right into the commuter parking lot at the intersection of Stone \r\nRoad and Rt. 29.</div>\r\n<div style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">If coming from north or south on Rt.28 we\'ll see you at \r\nthe on-on-on.... Nah, just take 28 towards Centreville until you get to Rt.29 \r\nLee highway.  Take Rt.29 West.  You\'ll go through a few lights (3 or \r\n4).  Once you pass underneath 66, take second right into the commuter \r\nparking lot at the intersection of Stone Road and Rt. 29.</div>', '<span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">TBA</span>', 'Make sure you are there for Hares away, as there will be \r\nspecial instructions at start.<br /><br /><u>Things you may want <span class="853324413-20042005"> to <span class="853324413-20042005"><em>SERIOUSLY </em></span></span>consider \r\nhaving:</u><span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><br /></span>Change of clothes, dry shoes, towel, flashlight, up<span class="853324413-20042005"><font size="2" color="#0000ff"> - </font></span>to<span class="853324413-20042005"><font size="2" color="#0000ff"> - </font></span>date tetanus shots, floatation \r\ndevice, snake-bite-kit,<span class="853324413-20042005">  tick spray,</span> \r\na geiger counter, and a bullet proof vest.<span class="853324413-20042005">&nbsp;</span>\r\n<div style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span class="853324413-20042005"><br />And, of course, be prepared \r\nfor any &quot;accidents&quot; that may happen at the local nuclear power \r\nplant.</span></div>', '<span class="853324413-20042005" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">The Commuter Lot in Centreville</span>', ''),
(144, '<font size="2" face="Arial" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 10pt;">So here it is again - my 30<sup>th</sup> birthday! \r\nThank God this year I have someone else to join in the misery of leaving my 20\'s\r\n- Just Matthew!  We\'ve put together a fun trail - not too\r\nlong, not too short that should keep you entertained while Just Matthew and I\r\ndrown our sorrows in our <st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Sparks</st1:place></st1:city>\r\nand Jello Shooters - we might even share...  Poison Ivy factor is\r\nzero (of course) since it\'s a Lube trail!</span></font>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><font size="2"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">From Webster City, Iowa\r\n(where Lube was born 30ish years ago):</span> Head east. Cross into Wisconsin, drop\r\ninto <st1:state w:st="on">Illinois</st1:state>, then go through <st1:state w:st="on">Indiana</st1:state>, <st1:state w:st="on">Ohio</st1:state>, <st1:state w:st="on">Pennsylvania</st1:state> and <st1:state w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Maryland</st1:place></st1:state>.\r\nHead south on 270 to 495 toward Northern VA/Tyson\'s Corner. At exit 47A, RIGHT\r\ntowards VA-7.  Keep LEFT to stay on Ramp towards <st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Falls Church</st1:place></st1:city>.  At exit 47B, take Ramp\r\n(RIGHT) towards VA-7/ <st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Falls Church</st1:place></st1:city>. \r\nGo 1.2 miles.  Turn RIGHT (South-West) onto Pimmit Dr (2nd to last\r\nstoplight before you cross under 66).  Go to the third (I think) right and\r\nturn in (there should be a Subway on your left as you enter the parking\r\nlot).  Go all the way straight back in that parking lot (up a little hill)\r\nto a hidden parking section behind the stores.  Look for wankers, park and\r\nhash. Should take you about 16 hours.<o:p /></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><font size="2"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">From GW Hospital (where Just\r\nMatthew was born 30ish years ago):</span> Go South on <st1:street w:st="on"><st1:address w:st="on">23rd St NW</st1:address></st1:street>.  Take RIGHT onto\r\nI-66.  At exit 66B, take Ramp (RIGHT) onto SR-7 [Leesburg Pike] towards\r\nTyson\'s Corner.  Turn LEFT (South-West) onto Pimmit Dr (second stoplight). \r\nGo to the third (I think) right and turn in (there should be a Subway on your\r\nleft as you enter the parking lot).  Go all the way straight back in that\r\nparking lot (up a little hill) to a hidden parking section behind the\r\nstores.  Look for wankers, park and hash.<o:p /></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><font size="2"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">From </span><st1:place style="font-weight: bold;" w:st="on"><st1:city w:st="on">Sterling</st1:city></st1:place><span style="font-weight: bold;"> via Route 7:</span>  Take Route 7 east. \r\nCross under the beltway.  Go<o:p> 1.2 miles.  Turn RIGHT\r\n(South-West) onto Pimmit Dr (2nd to last stoplight before you cross under\r\n66).  Go to the third (I think) right and turn in (there should be a\r\nSubway on your left as you enter the parking lot).  Go all the way\r\nstraight back in that parking lot (up a little hill) to a hidden parking\r\nsection behind the stores.  Look for wankers, park and hash.<o:p /></o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><font size="2"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Cumming in via the </span><st1:street style="font-weight: bold;" w:st="on"><st1:address w:st="on">Toll Road</st1:address></st1:street><span style="font-weight: bold;">: </span>\r\nTake the exit for 495 south (outer loop).  At exit 47A, turn RIGHT onto\r\nRamp towards VA-7 / Leesburg Pike / Tysons Corner / <st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Falls Church</st1:place></st1:city>.  Keep LEFT to stay on Ramp\r\ntowards VA-7 / Leesburg Pike / <st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Falls\r\n  Church</st1:place></st1:city>.  At exit 47B, take Ramp (RIGHT) onto SR-7\r\n[Leesburg Pike] towards VA-7 / Leesburg Pike / <st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Falls Church</st1:place></st1:city>.  Go 1.2 miles.  Turn\r\nRIGHT(South-West) onto Pimmit Dr (2nd to last stoplight before you cross under\r\n66).  Go to the third (I think) right and turn in (there should be a\r\nSubway on your left as you enter the parking lot).  Go all the way\r\nstraight back in that parking lot (up a little hill) to a hidden parking\r\nsection behind the stores.  Look for wankers, park and hash.<o:p /></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><font size="2"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">Cumming in via 66:</span>  At\r\nexit 66, turn RIGHT onto Ramp towards VA-7 / Leesburg Pike / <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:city w:st="on">Falls Church</st1:city></st1:place>.  Keep LEFT to stay on Ramp\r\ntowards VA-7 going to Tyson\'s.  Turn LEFT (South-West) onto Pimmit Dr (2nd\r\nstoplight).  Go to the third (I think) right and turn in (there should be\r\na Subway on your left as you enter the parking lot).  Go all the way\r\nstraight back in that parking lot (up a little hill) to a hidden parking\r\nsection behind the stores.  Look for wankers, park and hash.<o:p /></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<font size="2" face="Courier New" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><span style="font-weight: bold;">From points South:</span>  Get\r\non the beltway heading north toward Tyson\'s Corner (inner loop).  At exit\r\n49B, get on I-66 toward <st1:state w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Washington</st1:place></st1:state>. \r\nAt exit 66, turn RIGHT onto Ramp towards VA-7 / Leesburg Pike / <st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Falls Church</st1:place></st1:city>.  Keep\r\nLEFT to stay on Ramp towards VA-7 going to Tyson\'s.  Turn LEFT\r\n(South-West) onto Pimmit Dr 2nd stoplight).  Go to the third (I think)\r\nright and turn in (there should be a Subway on your left as you enter the\r\nparking lot).  Go all the way straight back in that parking lot (up a\r\nlittle hill) to a hidden parking section behind the stores.  Look for\r\nwankers, park and hash.</span></font>', '<font size="2" face="Arial" color="#333333" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);">Mark\'s Pub </span></font><font size="2" face="Arial" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">(</span></font><font size="2" face="Arial" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 10pt;">2190\r\nEast Pimmit Drive , <st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Falls Church</st1:place></st1:city>,\r\nVA 703-356-3822) </span></font>', '', '<font size="2" face="Arial" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Behind Mark\'s Pub (</span></font><font size="2" face="Arial" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span lang="EN" style="font-size: 10pt;">2190 East\r\nPimmit Drive , Falls Church, VA 703-356-3822)  (Roughly located near Route\r\n7 and 66 in <st1:city w:st="on"><st1:place w:st="on">Falls Church</st1:place></st1:city>)</span></font>', ''),
(146, '<div style="text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><img src="/images/obrother.jpg" /></span><br /><span style="font-size: 10pt;"></span></div><p class="MsoNormal" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Please join\r\nthe So Happy Its Tuesday gang for its first ever Hillbilly Hash. White\r\nKane, a native WV\'er has brought his family\'s annual hash out of the\r\nmountains and put it right where it belongs in <st1:place w:st="on">Reston</st1:place>!\r\n!<o:p /></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p>This is a themed hash, please come dressed in Hillbilly getups -- no city slicker doodads, or I reckon y\'all gonna be tarred and feathered!</p><p>&nbsp;</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">There will\r\nbe a Hatfields (<i>runners</i>) trail &amp;\r\na McCoys (<i>walkers</i>) trail <o:p /></span></p>', '<p style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" class="MsoNormal"><strong style="color: rgb(204, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">From\r\n495 Beltway</span></strong><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><o:p><br />Take 267\r\ntoll road towards Reston <o:p><br />Take <st1:street w:st="on"><st1:address w:st="on">Weihle Ave</st1:address></st1:street> exit <o:p><br />Turn left\r\nonto Weihle<o:p><br />When Weihle ends, turn\r\nleft onto <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:placename w:st="on">Sunrise</st1:placename>\r\n <st1:placetype w:st="on">Valley</st1:placetype></st1:place><o:p><br />Turn right\r\nonto <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:placename w:st="on">South</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st="on">Lakes (second light)<br />Take a right into the shopping center on your right.<br /></st1:placetype></st1:place></o:p></o:p></o:p></o:p></o:p></span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Park in the main lot<i>&nbsp;</i><em><span style="font-style: normal;">and walk around back of Safeway, look for Wankers, that is the official\r\nstart.</span></em></span><br /></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" class="MsoNormal"><strong style="color: rgb(204, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">From 28</span></strong><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><o:p><br />Take 267\r\ntoll road towards Reston<o:p><br /></o:p></o:p></span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Take <st1:street w:st="on"><st1:address w:st="on">Weihle Ave</st1:address></st1:street> exit <o:p><br />\r\nTurn right onto Weihle<o:p><br />\r\nWhen Weihle ends, turn\r\nleft onto <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:placename w:st="on">Sunrise</st1:placename>\r\n <st1:placetype w:st="on">Valley</st1:placetype></st1:place><o:p><br />\r\nTurn right\r\nonto <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:placename w:st="on">South</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st="on">Lakes (second light)<br />\r\nTake a right into the shopping center on your right.<br />\r\n</st1:placetype></st1:place></o:p></o:p></o:p></span><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Park in the main lot<i>&nbsp;</i><em><span style="font-style: normal;">and walk around back of Safeway, look for Wankers, that is the official\r\nstart.</span></em></span></p>', 'Lakeside Inn, just right across the parking lot from the start!', 'Make sure you bring a dry pair of shoes!  Also, this is <i>not</i> a dog or city slicker friendly trail.<br /><br />GIT-R-Done!!<br />', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Safeway, <st1:place w:st="on"><st1:placename w:st="on">South</st1:placename> <st1:placetype w:st="on">Lakes</st1:placetype></st1:place>\r\nShopping Plaza <o:p /></span><st1:address w:st="on"><st1:street w:st="on"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><br /><a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/map.adp?searchtype=address&country=US&addtohistory=&searchtab=home&address=11120+S.+Lakes+Dr&city=reston&state=va&zipcode=">11120 S. Lakes Dr.</a></span></st1:street><a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/map.adp?searchtype=address&country=US&addtohistory=&searchtab=home&address=11120+S.+Lakes+Dr&city=reston&state=va&zipcode="><br /><st1:city w:st="on"><span style="font-size: 10pt;">Reston</span></st1:city><span style="font-size: 10pt;">, <st1:state w:st="on">VA</st1:state>\r\n <st1:postalcode w:st="on">22091</st1:postalcode></span></a>\r\n</st1:address><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><o:p /></span></p>', ''),
(147, '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-family: Georgia;"><font size="3">Hummm', '<b><span style="font-family: Georgia;"><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="color: red; font-family: Georgia;"><font size="3">From Sterling/Herndon:<o:p /></font></span></p>\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><font size="3"><span style="color: red; font-family: Georgia;">Option 1:</span><strong><span style="font-weight: normal; font-family: Georgia;">&nbsp;</span></strong><st1:street><st1:address><strong><span style="font-weight: normal; font-family: Georgia;">Take Route</span></strong></st1:address></st1:street><strong><span style="font-weight: normal; font-family: Georgia;"> 7, East towards Tysons Corner. Turn RIGHT onto Baron Cameron. Take LEFT onto </span></strong><st1:street><st1:address><strong><span style="font-weight: normal; font-family: Georgia;">Wiehle Avenue</span></strong></st1:address></st1:street><strong><span style="font-weight: normal; font-family: Georgia;"> (wave to Watergate on your right!!)', '<span style="font-family: Georgia;"><span style="font-family: Georgia;"><font size="3">TBD <em>(I want to go to Jimmy', '<span style="font-family: Georgia;"><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-family: Georgia;"><font size="3">Live trail, as usual', '<div style="text-align: left;"><span style="font-family: Georgia;"><address style="background: white none repeat scroll 0% 50%; -moz-background-clip: initial; -moz-background-origin: initial; -moz-background-inline-policy: initial; text-align: center;"><font size="3"><span style="font-family: Georgia;">Commuter </span><st1:place><span style="font-family: Georgia;">Lot</span></st1:place><span style="font-family: Georgia;"> on </span><st1:street><st1:address><span style="font-family: Georgia;">Sunset Hills Road</span></st1:address></st1:street><span style="font-family: Georgia;">; </span><st1:place><st1:city><span style="font-family: Georgia;">Reston</span></st1:city><span style="font-family: Georgia;">, </span><st1:state><span style="font-family: Georgia;">VA</span></st1:state><span style="font-family: Georgia;"><span>&nbsp;</span></span><st1:postalcode><span style="font-family: Georgia;">20194</span></st1:postalcode></st1:place><span style="font-family: Georgia;"><o:p /></span></font></address>\r\n<p align="center" class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: center;"><span style="font-size: 8pt; font-family: Georgia;">(just off of </span><st1:street><st1:address><span style="font-size: 8pt; font-family: Georgia;">Wiehle Avenue</span></st1:address></st1:street><span style="font-size: 8pt; font-family: Georgia;"> between Wiehle<span>&nbsp;</span>and </span><st1:street><st1:address><span style="font-size: 8pt; font-family: Georgia;">Reston Parkway</span></st1:address></st1:street><span style="font-size: 8pt; font-family: Georgia;">)<o:p /></span></p>\r\n<p align="center" class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: center;"><span></span></p></span><br /><span style="font-family: Georgia;"><p align="center" class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-align: center;"><span><font size="3">(ADC Map: </font></span><font size="3"><st1:place><span style="font-family: Georgia;">Northern VA</span></st1:place><span style="font-family: Georgia;">', ''),
(149, '', '<div style="COLOR: rgb(0,0,0); FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><p class="MsoNormal"><font size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; COLOR: rgb(204,0,0)">From Points North</span>:</span></font><p><font size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"><p /></span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><br /></span></font></p></p><ul><li><font size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Travel 7100 South </span></font></li><li><font size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Turn right onto Fair Lakes Parkway</span></font></li><li><font size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Travel On FL Parkway until Stringfellow Rd, then turn left</span></font></li><li><font size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Travel under Rt 66, then turn left at second traffic light onto Autumn Willow Drive</span></font></li><li><font size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Turn at the first left into the Soccer Field parking lot and look for the wankers.</span></font></li></ul><p class="MsoNormal"><font size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"><p /></span><br /><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; COLOR: rgb(204,0,0)">From Points South/East/West</span>:</span></font><p><font size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"><p /></span><br /></font></p></p><ul><li><font size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Travel 7100 North</span></font></li><li><font size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Turn left onto Fair Lakes Parkway</span></font> </li><li><font style="COLOR: rgb(0,0,0); FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif" face="Arial" color="#0000ff" size="2">**Follow rest of directions from Points North.</font></li></ul></div>', '<span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif">TBD</span>', '<span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Start is at soccer fields, so bring your minivans. </span>', 'Soccer fields off Autumn Willow Dr.', ''),
(188, '', 'Easiest ', 'Mr. Smith', '', '<p>Tysons Corner<br />Avalon Crescent Apartments<br />1669 Onyx Drive<br />Corner of Park Run and Tysons Blvd<br />McLean, VA 22102<br /></p>', ''),
(148, 'When <i>Tuppy</i> speaks', '<font color="red"><b>From Sterling/Herndon: </b></font>\r\n<br />\r\n<font color="red"><b>Option 1:</b></font>\r\n Take Route 7, West towards Leesburg. Turn RIGHT onto Countryside Boulevard. Continue past the Countryside Shopping Center and take your first RIGHT onto Cromwell Road. Plenty of street parking', 'Where else? The Barefoot Pelican Bar &amp; Karaoke; 156 Enterprise Street; Sterling, VA  20164; Telephone: 703-444-2208. \r\n<br />Web site: <a href="http://thebarefootpelican.com">TheBarefootPelican.com</a>', '<p>Live trail, as usual', 'Off of Cromwell Road; Sterling, VA  20165<br />\r\n(just off of Countryside Boulevard past the Countryside Shopping Mall)<br />\r\n<br />\r\n(ADC Map: Loudoun VA', ''),
(150, '', '<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="color: rgb(204, 0, 0);">Directions from parts east</span>: Take Rt. 66 west to exit 52,\r\ntake a right on Rt. 29 to a right on Stone Rd. Travel approximately ', 'O\'Tooles', '', '<p class="MsoNormal">Centreville, Stone Road Giant Parking lot.</p>', ''),
(151, '<span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold">Note the special date and time!!!!!</span>', '<font style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif" face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><p /></span></font>Get yourself to Route 66 West (you\'re on your own to this point).<p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><br /></span>Route 66 West to Route 15 SOUTH (LEFT) (Haymarket - exit #40).<p><br />Take Route 15 until it dead ends at Route 29. <p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><br /></span>Turn RIGHT onto Rte. 29.<p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><br /></span>Almost immediately (1/16th of a mile) turn RIGHT onto <street w:st="on"><address w:st="on">Cerro Gordo Road</address></street> - the very first paved road on the right! <p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><br /></span>(The road sign is in the median on the left). If you cross over Broad Run you\'ve missed it; turn around and try again.<p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><br /></span>Take <place w:st="on">Cerro Gordo</place> about a mile to 7708 (on the LEFT); look for the trampoline and the ridiculously tall swing set in the front yard.<p><font size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><br /></span>Sign-in starts at 1pm</span></font></p></p></p></p></p></p></p>', '', '<font style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif" face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><p /></span></font><p class="MsoNormal" style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><font size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Bring dry clothes <p><br />BBQ to follow trail<p><br />Bonfire<p><br />Live entertainment<p><br />Option to spend the night - bring a tent<p>', '<font style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif" face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><address w:st="on"><street w:st="on">7708 Cerro Gordo Rd</street>,<city w:st="on">Gainesville</city>,<state w:st="on">VA.<br /></state></address></span></font><font style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif" face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt"><p /></span></font><p class="MsoNormal" style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><font size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Here\'s a link for MapQuest: <a href="http://mappoint.msn.com/(xn1sha45en30mk55moqzvlvr)/map.aspx?L=USA&C=38.78672%2c-77.67782&A=7.16667&P=%7C38.78672%2c-77.67782%7C1%7C7708+Cerro+Gordo+Rd%2c+Gainesville%2c+VA+20155%7CL1%7C">Directions for June 18th</a></span></font></p><br style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif" />', ''),
(232, '<div>**Note** any missspellings are part of a government consperacy.</div><div>', '<div>Directions:</div><div>From 66 - Take the exit for route 123 toward George Mason University (I\'m sure it has a number but I\'ve never looked).', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://www.yellowpages.com/sp/moreinfo/index.jsp;jsessionid=NGA0C1B0XEAY1QFI4A1BNWQ?id=5544193&q=Fat%20Tuesday\'s%20Resturant">Fat Tuesday\'s Restaurant</a></p>', '<p>A to A trail. The weather should be in the mid to upper 80\'s but will probably be in the 30\'s. Bring the sun tan lotion and bug spray if you think you are going to need it.</p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://www.yellowpages.com/sp/moreinfo/index.jsp;jsessionid=NGA0C1B0XEAY1QFI4A1BNWQ?id=5544193&q=Fat%20Tuesday\'s%20Resturant">Fat Tuesday\'s Restaurant</a>', ''),
(152, '', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><font size="3"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="color: rgb(204, 0, 0);">From 495</span> (North from Tyson', 'The Old Brogue, unless we change our collective minds.', 'Trail could be dry, flat and wet but don', 'Great Falls Grange Park<br />Great Falls, VA<br />', ''),
(153, '', '<span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; COLOR: rgb(204,0,0)">From Points West</span><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold"> (Reston/Herndon/Sterling/Leesburg/Iowa) </span><br />Take Route 7 or the Dulles Toll Road (whichever works best for you) to Route 495 East toward Springfield/Richmond. Get off 495 onto Route 50 East toward Washington/Falls Church. Take Route 50 East to the 5th traffic light (one of them is a pedestrian crossover in front of Loehmann\'s Plaza) and turn right onto Annandale Rd. Immediately after the 2nd light at Kerns Road, turn left onto Holloman Road. Take Holloman until it bends to the left in front of the 1st United Methodist Church (Korean) and turn right onto Taynton Rd. Park anywhere on Taynton or in the church parking lot and look for Sh*tty wankers. <p><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; COLOR: rgb(204,0,0)">From Centreville/Chantilly/Fairfax </span><br />Take Route 66 east to Route 495 East toward Springfield/Richmond. Get off 495 onto Route 50 East toward Washington/Falls Church. Take Route 50 East to the 5th traffic light (one of them is a pedestrian crossover in front of Loehmann\'s Plaza) and turn right onto Annandale Rd. Immediately after the 2nd light at Kerns Road, turn left onto Holloman Road. Take Holloman until it bends to the left in front of the 1st United Methodist Church (Korean) and turn right onto Taynton Rd. Park anywhere on Taynton or in the church parking lot and look for Sh*tty wankers. </p><p><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; COLOR: rgb(204,0,0)">From Alexandria/Springfield </span><br />Take Route 495 West toward Tysons Corner/Rockville. Get off 495 onto Route 50 East toward Washington/Falls Church. Take Route 50 East to the 5th traffic light (one of them is a pedestrian crossover in front of Loehmann\'s Plaza) and turn right onto Annandale Rd. Immediately after the 2nd light at Kerns Road, turn left onto Holloman Road. Take Holloman until it bends to the left in front of the 1st United Methodist Church (Korean) and turn right onto Taynton Rd. Park anywhere on Taynton or in the church parking lot and look for Sh*tty wankers. </p><p><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; COLOR: rgb(204,0,0)">From Arlington/DC </span><br />Take Route 50 West toward Fairfax. After going under the Route 7 underpass in Seven Corners take a left at the 2nd traffic light onto Annandale Rd. Immediately after the 2nd light at Kerns Road, turn left onto Holloman Road. Take Holloman until it bends to the left in front of the 1st United Methodist Church (Korean) and turn right onto Taynton Rd. Park anywhere on Taynton or in the church parking lot and look for Sh*tty wankers. </p><p><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold">ADC Map Page 15 - H9</span><br style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold" />(Note - ADC map book shows the church as Holy Spirit United Methodist)</p>', 'Grevey\'s', '<pre style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif">PI Factor - moderate<br />Dog and Stroller Friendly (yes 14K you can bring Mustard Gas with you)</pre>', '1st United Methodist Church<br />Falls Church, VA<br />', ''),
(154, '', '<span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><span style="COLOR: rgb(204,0,0)">From the North</span>: <br />Take Fairfax County Parkway South to Burke Center Parkway.? Take a left on BCP.? Go approximately 2 miles and take a left on Roberts Parkway.? Take a right at the next light.? VRE will be on the right. <br /><br /><span style="COLOR: rgb(204,0,0)">From the South</span>:<br />Take Fairfax County Parkway North to Burke Center parkway (BCP).? Take a right on to BCP. Go approximately 2 miles, take a left on to Roberts Parkway. Take a right at the next light.? VRE will be on the right. </span><br /><br style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif" />', '<span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Glory Days Grill</span>', '', '<span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Burke Center VRE, Burke, VA</span><br style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif" />', '');
