(145, '<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="3" face="Georgia"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="3" face="Georgia"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia;">Since my birthday is Friday, May 13<sup>th</sup>\r\nit\'s only appropriate that we celebrate our trail this week in honor of\r\nMother\'s Day (held on May 8<sup>th</sup> this year). So... expect\r\ntotal debauchery this Tuesday and do something nice for your mother...\r\nbring her to the hash!!<o:p><br /></o:p></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font size="3" face="Georgia"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia;">Here\'s a few historical facts\r\nabout...<o:p /></span></font><font size="3" face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br /></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="3" face="Georgia"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia;"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><font size="3" face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Origin</span></font><font size="3" face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-family: Georgia;"><o:p /></span><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><br /></span></font></p><p><font size="3" face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">The first known observance of Mother\'s Day in the </span></font><font size="6" face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 24pt;"><a href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/u/un/united_states.html" title="United States"><font size="3"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">U.S</span></font></a></span></font><font face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"> occurred in </font><font size="6" face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 24pt;"><a href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/a/al/albion__michigan.html" title="Albion, Michigan"><font size="3"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Albion,\r\nMichigan</span></font></a></span></font><font face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"> on </font><font size="6" face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 24pt;"><a href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/m/ma/may_13.html" title="May 13"><font size="3"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">May 13</span></font></a></span></font><font face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">, </font><font size="6" face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 24pt;"><a href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/1/18/1877.html" title="1877"><font size="3"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">1877</span></font></a></span></font><font face="Verdana"><span style="font-family: Verdana;"><span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">, the second\r\nSunday of the month. According to local legend... Albion pioneer, Juliet\r\nCalhoun Blakeley, stepped up to complete the sermon of the Rev. Myron\r\nDaughterty, who was distraught because an anti-temperance group had forced his\r\nson and two other temperance advocates to spend the night in a saloon and\r\nbecome publicly drunk. In the pulpit, Blakeley called on other mothers to join\r\nher. Blakeley\'s two sons, both travelling salesmen, were so moved that they\r\nvowed to return each year to pay tribute to her and embarked on a campaign to\r\nurge their business contacts to do likewise</span>. <o:p /></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<ul type="disc"><li class="MsoNormal"><font size="6" face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 24pt;"><a href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/1/19/1908.html" title="1908"><font size="3"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">1908</span></font></a></span></font><font face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"> - </font><font size="6" face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 24pt;"><a href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/m/mo/mother_s_day.html" title="Mother\'s Day"><font size="3"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Mother\'s\r\n     Day</span></font></a></span></font><font face="Verdana"><span style="font-family: Verdana;"><span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"> is observed for the first\r\n     time (Andrew\'s Methodist Church in </span><u1:place style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><u1:city>Grafton</u1:city>, <u1:state>West\r\n     Virginia</u1:state></u1:place><span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">... where everyone is a mother!!).</span> <o:p /></span></font></li></ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><font size="3" face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 12pt;"><span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">Mother\'s Day is a </span><a style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/h/ho/holiday.html" title="Holiday">holiday</a><span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"> in several nations around the world, celebrated in\r\nthe </span><a style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/u/un/united_states.html" title="United States">United States</a><span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">, </span><a style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/c/ca/canada.html" title="Canada">Canada</a><span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">, </span><a style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/a/au/australia.html" title="Australia">Australia</a><span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"> and several other countries on the second </span><a style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/s/su/sunday.html" title="Sunday">Sunday</a><span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"> in </span><a style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/m/ma/may.html" title="May">May</a><span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">,\r\nto celebrate </span><a style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/m/mo/mother.html" title="Mother">motherhood</a><span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">. Often the mother receives </span><a style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/g/gi/gift.html" title="Gift">gifts</a>.<o:p /></span></font></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n<a style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;" name="Origin"><font size="3"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Historians claim that this day emerged\r\nfrom the custom of mother worship in ancient </span></font></a><font size="6" face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 24pt;"><a href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/g/gr/greece.html" title="Greece"><font size="3"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Greece</span></font></a></span></font><font face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">. Mother\r\nworship which kept a festival to </font><font size="6" face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 24pt;"><a href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/c/cy/cybele.html" title="Cybele"><font size="3"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Cybele</span></font></a></span></font><font face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">, a great\r\nmother of gods, and </font><font size="6" face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 24pt;"><a href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/r/rh/rhea__mythology_.html" title="Rhea (mythology)"><font size="3"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Rhea</span></font></a></span></font><font face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">, the wife of </font><font size="6" face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 24pt;"><a href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/c/cr/cronus.html" title="Cronus"><font size="3"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Cronus</span></font></a></span></font><font face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;">, was held on </font><font size="6" face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 24pt;"><a href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/m/ma/march_15.html" title="March 15"><font size="3"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">March 15</span></font></a></span></font><font face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"> to </font><font size="6" face="Verdana" style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"><span style="font-size: 24pt;"><a href="http://www.brainyencyclopedia.com/encyclopedia/m/ma/march_18.html" title="March 18"><font size="3"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">March 18</span></font></a></span></font><font face="Verdana"><span style="font-family: Verdana;"><span style="font-family: georgia,times new roman,times,serif;"> around Asia\r\nMinor. They insist that this custom spread around the world</span>.</span></font