(155, '', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; COLOR: rgb(204,0,0)">Directions from parts east</span>: Take Rt. 66 west to exit 52, take a left on Rt. 29. Proceed about 1 mile and look for the bowling ally on the left. If you pass a CVS you have gone to far. Look for wankers in the rear parking lot.</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; COLOR: rgb(204,0,0)">Directions from </span><place style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; COLOR: rgb(204,0,0)" w:st="on" /><city w:st="on" />Sterling</city /></place />: Go south on Rt. 28 to the 2<sup>nd</sup> Rt. 29 exit. You will be heading east for about </p>', '<span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif">O\'Toole\'s</span>', '', '<span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Centreville, AMF Bowling Alley</span><br style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif" /><a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/map.adp?searchtype=address&country=US&addtohistory=&searchtab=home&address=13814+Lee+Highway&city=&state=&zipcode=20120"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif">13814 Lee Highway</span><br style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif" /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Centreville, VA 20120</span></a><br style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif" /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif">(703) 830-3700</span><br style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif" />', ''),
(156, 'It\'s Just Becky\'s birthday, so come celebrate by joining the SH*T for our first ever pajama party trail! Make sure you show up in your PJ\'s or your birtday suit (although for legal reasons, anyone in their birthday suit will be confined to my car). Prizes will be awarded on a whim! <p>Sign-in at 6:30, hares away at 7:00!</p>', '<pre style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; COLOR: rgb(204,0,0)">From Fairfax</span>:<br /></pre><ul><li>North on Fairfax County Parkway</li><li>Left onto Fox Mill RD / VA-665</li><li>Right onto Monroe St.</li><li>Monroe St. becomes Van Buren St.</li><li>The entrance to the parking lot is on the left-hand side, 1 block before<span style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif"> </span>Herndon Parkway<br /></li></ul><pre style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><br /><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; COLOR: rgb(204,0,0)">From Sterling</span>:<br /></pre><ul><li>South on Fairfax County Parkway</li><li>Bear right onto Spring Street ramp</li><li>Right on Spring Street</li><li>Left onto Herndon Parkway</li><li>Right onto Van Buren St</li><li>Go down to the next light and make a right into the parking lot</li></ul>', '', '', '<pre style="FONT-FAMILY: georgia,times new roman,times,serif">The parking lot on the southwest corner of Van Buren and Herndon Parkway.<br />205 Van Buren St<br />Herndon, VA 20170</pre>', ''),
(157, 'Wear your coolest sleeveless shirt and come celebrate Grevey�s new, improved sleeveless shirt policy!', '<b><font color="#cc0000">From Points West (Reston/Herndon/Sterling/Leesburg/Iowa)</font></b>:<br />Take Route 7 or the Dulles Toll Road (whichever works best for you) to Route 495 South (East?) toward Springfield/Richmond. Get off 495 onto Route 50 East toward Washington/Falls Church. Immediately take the exit for Fairview Park <b>SOUTH</b> and make the first right into the parking lot for 3110 Fairview Park Drive. Park and look for Sh*tty wankers. <p><b><font color="#cc0000">From Centreville/Chantilly/Fairfax</font></b>:<br />Take Route 66 east to Route 495 South (East?) toward Springfield/Richmond. Get off 495 onto Route 50 East toward Washington/Falls Church. Immediately take the exit for Fairview Park <b>SOUTH</b> and make the first right into the parking lot for 3110 Fairview Park Drive. Park and look for Sh*tty wankers. </p><p><b><font color="#cc0000">From Alexandria/Springfield</font></b>:<br />Take Route 495 North (West?) toward Tysons Corner/Rockville. Get off 495 onto Route 50 East toward Washington/Falls Church. Get in the right lane and follow the signs to Fairview Park <b>SOUTH</b> and make the first right into the parking lot for 3110 Fairview Park Drive. Park and look for Sh*tty wankers. </p><p><b><font color="#cc0000">From Arlington/DC</font></b>:<br />Take Route 50 West toward Fairfax. Just before reaching Route 495 take the Fairview Park exit and stay ion the left lane. At the traffic light, turn left onto Fairview Park Dr and cross over Route 50. Make the first right into the parking lot for 3110 Fairview Park Drive. Park and look for Sh*tty wankers. </p><p>ADC Map Page 15-C8</p>', 'Grevey\'s', 'PI Factor - moderate<br />Dog and Stroller Friendly - yes (well as friendly as any Sh*tty Trail is)', '<a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?q=3110+Fairview+Park+Drive,+Falls+Church,+VA&spn=0.022126,0.044072&t=h&hl=en">3110 Fairview Park Drive</a><br /><font size="-2"><a href="/map/157.kmz">Click here for Google Earth</a></font>', ''),
(158, '<p align="center"><!--StartFragment --><strong><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><span style="COLOR: maroon"><font size="5">The ?Virgin Twins, plus One? Trail<br /></font></span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: maroon; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">(?Genius is one per cent inspiration and ninety-nine per cent perspiration. Accordingly, a ?genius? is often merely a talented person who has done all of his or her homework? ? Thomas Edison)</span></font></strong><span style="COLOR: maroon"><br /><br /></span></p><p align="center"><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3"><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">This week?s trail will be dedicated to all those like? <b><i>?I Faked Them All?, ?You Must Be This Tall To Ride?</i></b> and <b><i>?Just John C.?</i></b>. A) They agreed to hare? and B) They did a wonderful job in preparing for this trail!!</font></font></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3"><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">My virgin twins, <b><i>?I Faked Them All?</i></b> and <b><i>?You Must Be This Tall To Ride?</i></b> obviously have been ?included? in a previous trail as ?hares? hence their namings. But after talking with them and learning that one was shown her ?small? part the day before and the other had not been on trail? I was proud of their dedication to come out? not once, but twice to ?scout? their trail from start to finish (a third ?review? may be done closer to the date of the trail).</font></font></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3"><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Have you seen either these two in the winter or in the rain? On our second scouting session? it absolutely poured on us. <b><i>?I Faked Them All?</i></b> trying to keep the ?map? dry and <b><i>?You Must Be This Tall To Ride?</i></b> trying to keep her ?hair? from getting wet!! But? alas? they completed the trail.</font></font></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3"><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Also? look for <b><i>?Just John C.?</i></b>. on trail this week? he?ll have a big part and with his impending departure <i>??it will be one of his last trails with us so I?m sure he?s wanting it to be extra special?.</i></font></font></span></p><p /><p /><p />', '<font color="#cc0000"><b>From Sterling/Herndon</b></font>:<br /><font color="#cc0000"><b>Option 1</b></font>: Take Route 7, East towards Tysons Corner. Take the exit for Fairfax County Parkway/Algonkian Parkway. At the top of the Ramp take a LEFT back over Route 7 onto Algonkian Parkway. Continue on Algonkian Parkway for about 1 ? miles and take a RIGHT onto Great Falls Forest, second LEFT onto Yorktown Drive and second RIGHT onto Brockman Lane. Proceed to the deadend and look for wankers.<br /><br /><font color="#cc0000"><b>Option 2 (from Countryside/Cascades)</b></font>: Take Algonkian Parkway, East towards Lowes Island. After you pass Great Falls Plaza, continue past Whitewater Drive and take a LEFT onto Great Falls Forest. Take the second LEFT onto Yorktown Drive and second RIGHT onto Brockman Lane. Proceed to the deadend and look for wankers.<br /><br /><br /><font color="#cc0000"><b>From Reston</b></font>: Find your way to Fairfax County Parkway, North. Continue on Fairfax County Parkway, North over Route 7 onto Algonkian Parkway. Continue on Algonkian Parkway for about 1 ? miles and take a RIGHT onto Great Falls Forest, second LEFT onto Yorktown Drive and second RIGHT onto Brockman Lane. Proceed to the deadend and look for wankers.<br /><br /><br /><font color="#cc0000"><b>From the beltway</b></font>:<br /><br /><font color="#cc0000"><b>Option 1</b></font>: Take Dulles Toll Road (a $.75 pre-hash contribution). Take the first exit onto Route 7, West. Continue on Route 7, West for approx. 7 miles to the Fairfax County Parkway/Algonkian Parkway exit. Bear to the RIGHT onto Algonkian Parkway. Continue on Algonkian Parkway for about 1 ? miles and take a RIGHT onto Great Falls Forest, second LEFT onto Yorktown Drive and second RIGHT onto Brockman Lane. Proceed to the deadend and look for wankers.<br /><br /><font color="#cc0000"><b>Option 2</b></font>: Take Dulles Toll Road (a $.75 pre-hash contribution). Take the first exit onto Route 7, West. Continue on Route 7, West for approx. 6 ? miles to the Georgetown Pike. Take a RIGHT onto Georgetown Pike and the first LEFT onto Seneca Road. Continue on Seneca Road for approx. 1 ? miles and take a LEFT onto Brockman Lane (it reads Beach Mill Road to the right) and proceed to the deadend and look for wankers.<br /><br /><font color="#cc0000"><b>Option 3</b></font>: Take Georgetown Pike, West through Great Falls just before you get onto Route 7, take a RIGHT onto Seneca Road. Continue on Seneca Road for approx. 1 ? miles and take a LEFT onto Brockman Lane (it reads Beach Mill Road to the right) and proceed to the deadend and look for wankers.<br /><br /><br />Brockman Lane from the Fairfax County side (off of Seneca Road) is being mentioned as an option because it has more room to park, however, to get to the OnOnOn if you are going to drive? you will have to take Brockman Lane back to Seneca Road to Route 7 to Algonkian Parkway. Where on the Loudoun County side you are a little more than a ? of mile to food and more beer.', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><font size="3"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Fox Chase Tavern? 20789 </span><place /><placename /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Great Falls</span></placename /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">?</span><placetype /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Plaza</span></placetype /></place /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">; </span><city /><place /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Sterling</span></place /></city /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">, VA<span>? </span>20165</span></font></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3">(703) 444-8666</font></span></p>', '<!--StartFragment --><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3">Live trail, as usual? It?s still light out? <b><i>LEAVE THOSE FLASHLIGHTS AT HOME!! BRING VIRGINS INSTEAD!!</i></b></font></span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></i></b></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3">This will be like a walk in the park (or? near a park!!)? no shiggy? no streams, rivers, lakes or oceans. No poison ivy of any kind. In fact? you may not even need a ?Hash Bag?!! Cum thirsty? or don?t cum at all!!</font></span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3">Oh? and don?t forget to bring those? ?Beautiful Young Female Virgins?!!</font></span></p><p /><p><font size="3">?</font></p><p /><p><font size="3">?</font></p>', '<p><!--StartFragment --><street /></p><address><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/map.adp?formtype=address&searchtype=address&country=US&addtohistory=&1ahXX=&address=Brockman+Ln+and+Brockman+Ct&city=Great+Falls&state=VA&zipcode=" target="_blank">Brockman Lane</a></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">; </span><place /><city /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Lowes Island</span></city /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">, </span><state /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">VA</span></state /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">?</span><postalcode /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">20165</span></postalcode /></place /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> or </span><place /><city /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Great Falls</span></city /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">, </span><state /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">VA</span></state /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><span>? </span></span><postalcode /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">22066</span></postalcode /></place /></address><p /><p><place /><postalcode /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></postalcode /></place /><font size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><strong>(It?s at the dead end from either direction)</strong></span></font></p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><!--StartFragment --><font size="2"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">(ADC Map: </span><place /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Northern VA</span></place /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">? B2 on Page 02, Fac)</span><font face="Times New Roman">?</font></font></span></p><p><font size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Or, click <a href="/map/158.kmz">here</a> for Google Earth</span></font></p>', ''),
(160, 'Even though the SH*T seems to have a lot of theme hashes (pimpin\' sleeveless hillbilly pirates and all), but not this week! That\'s right, this week, show up in your favorite normal hashing gear and have absolutely no costumes at all for the &quot;It\'s not a theme hash&quot; hash!', '<b><font color="#cc0000">From the North</font></b>:<br /><ul><li>Head (who said head?) South on 28 </li><li>Turn right on Westfields </li><li>Westfields will become Poplar Tree, and then Stone Road </li><li>Turn left at Braddock Rd. </li><li>Take the first right into the shopping center. Turn left and go around behind the shopping center. Look for the wankers. Park and hash. </li></ul><p><b><font color="#cc0000">From the East</font></b>:<br /></p><ul><li>Get thee to 66 West </li><li>Take the exit for 29 South </li><li>Turn right at Stone Road </li><li>Go about a mile. <i>After</i> the light at Sully Park Dr., turn right into the shopping center. Go behind the stores, find the wankers, park and hash </li></ul><p><b><font color="#cc0000">From anywhere else</font></b>:<br /></p><ul><li><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?q=Braddock+Rd+%26+stone+rd,+Centreville,+VA+20120&spn=0.021113,0.038935&hl=en">Google Maps.</a> </li></ul>', '', '', 'Behind the shopping center at the corner of <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?q=Braddock+Rd+%26+stone+rd,+Centreville,+VA+20120&spn=0.021113,0.038935&hl=en">Braddock and Stone Road</a><br /><br />Click <a href="/map/160.kmz">here</a> for a Google Earth placemark.', ''),
