(164, '', '<font color="#CC0000"><b>From Points West</b></font>\r\n:  66 East to Rte. 110 South to Rte. 1 South. After you come across the s-curve bridge over the railroad tracks, continue through three more lights and turn RIGHT on Wythe for one block, then RIGHT on N. Fayette for a half-block. We are the four-story brick townhouses on your RIGHT; 727 is located at the far left corner of the courtyard (end unit). Please park on the street.\r\n<p>\r\n<font color="#CC0000"><b>From Points South</b></font>\r\n: Get yourself to Route 1 North, which becomes N. Patrick Street as you drive through Old Town. LEFT on Wythe for two blocks; RIGHT on N. Fayette for a half-block. We are the four-story brick townhouses on your RIGHT; 727 is located at the far left corner of the courtyard (end unit). Please park on the street.\r\n<p>\r\n<font color="#CC0000"><b>From Points North</b></font>\r\n: Get yourself to 395 South, then exit GW Parkway (take the exit marked Reagan National Airport), which becomes N. Washington St. as you enter Old Town. RIGHT on Wythe for five blocks; RIGHT on N. Fayette for a half-block. We are the four-story brick townhouses on your RIGHT; 727 is located at the far left corner of the courtyard (end unit). Please park on the street.\r\n<p>\r\nOr ', 'Murphy', 'Just a reminder: it', 'Dead Hare and Split Pussynality', ''),
(162, 'n(This is a Metro accessible trail)', '<p><font color="#cc0000"><b>Via Metro (Orange Line) </b></font><br />Take Metro to the East Falls Church Metro station. After exiting Metro onto Roosevelt Blvd./Sycamore St. turn left and walk 3 blocks (crossing Lee Hwy.) to Tuckahoe Park. Look for Sh*tty wankers. </p><p><font color="#cc0000"><b>From Points West (Reston/Herndon/Sterling/Leesburg/Iowa) </b></font><br />Get on the Dulles Toll Road (Rte 267) East toward Washington by whatever is the easiest route for you. Take 267E until it merges into I-66 East. Get off I-66 at the Washington Blvd./Lee Hwy exit (Exit 69) then turn left onto Lee Hwy (Rte 29). Follow Lee Hwy to the 2nd traffic light and turn left onto Sycamore St. ', 'IRELAND', 'PI Factor - low <br />Dog and Stroller Friendly - yes (well as friendly as any Sh*tty Trail is)', 'Tuckahoe Park <p>ADC Northern Virginia Map Page 16-A2</p><p>Click <a href="/map/162.kmz">here</a> for a Google Earth placemark.</p>', ''),
(159, 'You Know You are from Buffalo if: <ul><li>You hate the Miami Dolphins </li><li>You save Canadian coins ... to use at toll booths and parking meters. </li><li>You flinch when you hear the words &quot;wide right!&quot; </li><li>While living out of town, you\'ve said to your friends ... </li><li>back home, you could get a case of Labatts for twelve bucks!&quot; <ul><li>&quot;back home, this house would go for only 80K!&quot; </li><li>&quot;you call this snow?&quot; </li><li>&quot;you call this a supermarket?&quot; </li><li>&quot;you call these wings?&quot; </li><li>&quot;you call this pizza?&quot; </li><li>&quot;they\'re closing the schools for this?&quot; </li></ul></li><li>You know how to pronounce Scajaquada, Cheektowaga and Depew. </li><li>You get mad when you get stuck in ', '<b><font color="#cc0000">From 66, Beltway or points east</font></b>: Get yourself to 50 and go West. Take 50 West to Stringfellow and make a Left onto Stringfellow. Make a right onto Poplar Tree. Take Poplar Tree to Walney. Go straight through the intersection. Take your first right onto Newbrook. Take your next right onto Parkeast (it', '', 'Don\'t forget to bring out those young beautiful male virgins', 'St. Paul Travelers Building<br /><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?q=parkeast+circle,+chantilly,+va&spn=0.019394,0.037753&hl=en">Parkeast Circle</a><br /><p><font size="-1">Click <a href="/map/159.kmz">here</a> for Google Earth</font> </p>', ''),
(163, '<p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Ok Kiddies its time to sharpen your pencils and grab your Trapper-Keepers \'cause school is in session!', '<p class="MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Make your way to Rt. 28 (Sully Road)</span></font></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">From the North, travel South on Rt. 28 to Rt.50 (Lee Jackson Memorial Highway)<br />Take Rt. 50 West for three lights to Stonecroft Blvd.<br />Take a left on Stonecroft (at <place w:st="on" /><placename w:st="on" />Chantilly</placename /> <placename w:st="on" />Auto</placename /> <placetype w:st="on" />Park</placetype /></place />)<br />Go about 3/4 mile to Bogle Drive.</street /><br />Turn Right onto Bogle and follow it all the way straight back to the end of the road.<br />Look for Wankers, park and hash.</span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span></font><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">From the South, travel north on Rt. 28 to Rt.50 (Lee Jackson Memorial Highway)<br />Take Rt. 50 West for three lights to Stonecroft Blvd.</street /><br />Take a left on Stonecroft (at <place w:st="on" /><placename w:st="on" />Chantilly</placename /> <placename w:st="on" />Auto</placename /> <placetype w:st="on" />Park</placetype /></place />)<br />Go about 3/4 mile to Bogle Drive</street /><br />Turn Right onto Bogle and follow it all the way straight back to the end of the road.<br />Look for Wankers, park and hash.</span></font></p>', 'TBD', '<!--StartFragment --><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">This will be a VIRGIN FRIENDLY HASH.', '<p>14998 Bogle Drive<br />Chantilly, VA 20151</p><p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">If you miss the bus you can find the rest of the class by following these directions....</span></font></p><address />', ''),
(165, '', '<p>\r\n<b>\r\n<font color="#CC0000">\r\nFrom 495\r\n</font>\r\n</b>\r\n:\r\n\r\nTake the Route 50 (Arlington Blvd) exit toward Fairfax. At approximately 5th light (1.7 miles) turn left on Barkley Drive (the light just prior to Barkley is Cedar Lane).  Once on Barkley, immediately turn right down the service road. Take the second entrance to the temple, go all the way to the back end of parking lot, look for wankers, park and hash.\r\n\r\n \r\n<p>\r\n<b>\r\n<font color="#CC0000">\r\nFrom points north\r\n</font>\r\n</b>\r\n:  Get to 66. Head east.  If you run into the beltway use the directions above.  Take the Nutley Street exit toward Fairfax (going south right by the Vienna Metro stop).  At 4th light take Left on RT 50 Arlington BLVD. Go through one light, down a hill, then turn right onto service RD. (If you come to light at Barkley Dr you\'ve gone to far turn right and head back down service rd.)  You\'ll be right in front of temple, go all the way to the back end of parking lot, look for wankers, park and hash.', 'TBD', 'In case you haven\'t noticed, <i>it\'s getting dark earlier</i>!!  Make sure you bring a flashlight!!', 'Kena Shriners Temple (back parking lot)<br>\r\n\r\n9001 Arlington BLVD (Rt 50)<br>\r\n\r\nFairfax VA 22031', ''),
(166, 'Required Equipment:\r\n<p>\r\nYour breasticles and/or testicles.  \r\n<br>\r\n(Special note to the men: if your girlfriend/wife is currently in charge of your balls, that\'s ok - you can still come.)', '<font color="#CC0000"><b>\r\nFrom the Sterling area via Route 7</b></font>:\r\n\r\nTake Route 7 east for a while.  Pass over the beltway.  Go about a mile and turn RIGHT on Pimmit Drive.  (You\'ve gone too far if you pass under I-66. Turn around.)   Take your third RIGHT into the parking lot for Mark\'s Pub (there will be a Subway on your left as you turn into the parking lot).  Go all the way straight back, up a small hill and into the back parking lot.  Look for wankers, park and hash.\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<font color="#CC0000"><b>\r\nFrom the Reston area via the toll road (267)</b></font>:\r\n\r\nTake the toll road east.  Exit Route 7 east.  Pass over the beltway.  Go about a mile and turn RIGHT on Pimmit Drive.  (You\'ve gone too far if you pass under I-66. Turn around.)   Take your third RIGHT into the parking lot for Mark\'s Pub (there will be a Subway on your left as you turn into the parking lot).  Go all the way straight back, up a small hill and into the back parking lot.  Look for wankers, park and hash.\r\n\r\n <p>\r\n<font color="#CC0000"><b>\r\nFrom the West via 66</b></font>:\r\n\r\nTake 66 east.  Cross over the beltway and take the next exit (exit 66, Leesburg Pike, Rt. 7 and make the left on the ramp to go toward Tyson\'s).  Merge onto Route 7.  Take a LEFT at the second light onto Pimmit Drive.  Take your third RIGHT into the parking lot for Mark\'s Pub (there will be a Subway on your left as you turn into the parking lot).  Go all the way straight back, up a small hill and into the back parking lot.  Look for wankers, park and hash.\r\n\r\n <p>\r\n<font color="#CC0000"><b>\r\nFrom Points South</b></font>:\r\n\r\nHead up 495 toward Tyson\'s corner.  Exit Route 7 east (exit 47B toward Falls Church).  Go about a mile and turn RIGHT on Pimmit Drive.  (You\'ve gone too far if you pass under I-66. Turn around.)   Take your third RIGHT into the parking lot for Mark\'s Pub (there will be a Subway on your left as you turn into the parking lot).  Go all the way straight back, up a small hill and into the back parking lot.  Look for wankers, park and hash.\r\n\r\n <p>\r\n<font color="#CC0000"><b>\r\nFrom Points East</b></font>:  Get to Route 7.  (Be mindful of HOV restrictions on 66 west...)  After passing under 66, take a LEFT at the second light onto Pimmit Drive.  Take your third RIGHT into the parking lot for Mark\'s Pub (there will be a Subway on your left as you turn into the parking lot).  Go all the way straight back, up a small hill and into the back parking lot.  Look for wankers, park and hash.', 'Mark\'s Pub<br>\r\n2190 East Pimmit Dr.<br>\r\nFalls Church, VA<br>\r\n703-356-3822\r\n<p>  \r\n<a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/map.adp?country=US&addtohistory=&formtype=address&searchtype=address&cat=&address=2190%20Pimmit%20Dr&city=Falls%20Church&state=VA&zipcode=22043%2d2806&searchtab=home">\r\nMapQuest to Mark\'s Pub</a>', 'Bring a flashlight or a head lamp - you\'re going to need it. <br>\r\n\r\nPI factor: probably, but shouldn\'t be much.  Dog friendly: sure.  Strollers: In the SH*T hash?  Yeah right.', 'Mark\'s Pub<br>\r\n2190 East Pimmit Dr.<br>\r\nFalls Church, VA<br>\r\n703-356-3822\r\n<p>\r\n<a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/map.adp?country=US&addtohistory=&formtype=address&searchtype=address&cat=&address=2190%20Pimmit%20Dr&city=Falls%20Church&state=VA&zipcode=22043%2d2806&searchtab=home">\r\nMapQuest to Mark\'s Pub</a>', '');
