(260, '<div class="MsoNormal" style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 22pt; FONT-FAMILY: & #39"><font face="Times New Roman">NO MORE PAPERS</font></span></div><div class="MsoNormal" style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 22pt; FONT-FAMILY: & #39"><font face="Times New Roman">NO MORE BOOKS</font></span></div><div class="MsoNormal" style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 22pt; FONT-FAMILY: & #39"><font face="Times New Roman">NO<span>', '<div class="MsoNormal"><font size="3"><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Falls Church</span></strong><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">:</span></strong><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></b></font></div><div class="MsoNormal"><font size="3"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">This part of </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Falls Church</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> is not very easy to get to', '<div class="MsoNormal" style="LINE-HEIGHT: 14.4pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #333333; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font face="Times New Roman" color="#000000" size="3"></font><p style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 0in"><a href="http://www.google.com/maps?f=l&hl=en&q=Sunset+Grille&near=7250+Columbia+Pike&sll=38.83232,-77.195113&sspn=0.007121,0.014462&ie=UTF8&latlng=38830892,-77195105,7256122419844528615&ei=Qop2RujLPIvarQK8_tSTCA&cd=1"><font color="#000080"><u><font face="Georgia, serif"><b>Sunset</b></font></u></font><font color="#000080"><u><font face="Georgia, serif">', '<p>Live A to A\' trail. Plan for shiggy, pavement, PI, biting insect,and tom foollery(it is a B$ trail)... plan ahead</p><p>and don\'t for get to bring an apple for the teacher.</p><p />', '<p class="western"><font face="Times New Roman, serif"><font color="#000000"><font face="Georgia, serif">', ''),
(262, '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><strong><font size="4"><font color="#ff0000">Looking</font> <font color="#0000ff">to</font> <font color="#ff0000">prelube</font> <font color="#0000ff">for</font> <font color="#ff0000">the</font> <font color="#0000ff">Fourth</font> <font color="#ff0000">of</font> <font color="#0000ff">July</font><font color="#ff0000">?</font>', '<font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">From Sterling/Herndon/<wbr />Reston:<br />Take Rt.28 to Waxpool Rd (West of 28 its Waxpool, East of 28 is Church St) Continue heading west, the road changes names 3 times but continue on strait until you reach Belmont Ridge Road. Take a Left onto Belmont Ridge Rd. Stay on this road till you hit Ryan Rd, take a Left on Ryan Road. You will see a strip mall on your right just after you turn on to Ryan Rd, Harris Teeter is in that shopping center, take a Right in to the Bramble shopping center and look for wankers. <br />', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">BBQ &amp; Camp-Over at Dixie Queen\'s!<br />', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Live trail. Plan for everything except snow.</font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">NOTE: There will be a vehicle at start to throw all your overnight gear into.</font></p>', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><a title="Start Location" href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&hl=en&q=42415+Ryan+Road,+Ashburn,+Va.+20148&sll=37.0625,-95.677071&sspn=32.885543,59.238281&ie=UTF8&ll=38.987751,-77.534809&spn=0.007872,0.014462&z=16&iwloc=addr&om=1">Brambleton Town Center<br />42415 Ryan Road, Ashburn, Va. 20148</a></font></p>', ''),
(261, '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Anybody feeling creative?', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><strong>From West of Herndon (Centreville, West Virginia, Purcellville, etc...):</strong><br />Find your way to Rt 28, head towards Herndon.<br />Exit onto Frying Pan Rd. </font><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Take a Left on to Sunrise Valley Drive.<br /></font><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Take a Right on to Dulles Technology Drive.<br />Take Second Left into parking lot and Look for Wankers.</font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><strong>From East of Herndon (Reston, McLean, Anacostia, etc...):</strong><br />Find your way to 495 heading towards Tyson\'s Corner.<br />Take the Toll Road heading West.<br />Take exit number 10 Centreville Rd, at the end of the off ramp head South (Left).<br />Take a Right onto Sunrise Valley Drive.<br />Take 1st Left onto Dulles Technology Drive.<br />Take 5th Right into parking lot and look for wankers.</font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><strong>From South of Herndon (Springfield, Woodbridge, Richmond, etc...):</strong><br /></font><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Head North on Fairfax County Parkway.<br />Take a left onto Sunrise Valley Drive<br />After crossing Centreville Road, take 1st Left onto Dulles Technology Drive.<br />Take 5th Right into parking lot and look for wankers.</font></p>', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Ned Divines</font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Village Center at Dulles (by the Clock Tower)<br />2465 Centreville Road<br />Herndon, VA 20171 </font></p><p><font face="Georgia">703-793-7376</font></p>', '<p><font face="Georgia">Dixie Queen is one of the hares, need I say more?</font></p><p><font face="Georgia">If you don\'t know what this means, you should hash more often...', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,seri