(290, '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; tab-stops: 180.75pt"><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif" size="2">This will be Nuclear Jism\'s first haring since his most recent hash injury. Let me take a few words to remind you half minds that it takes approximately 20 people to carry an incapacitated person a mile over uneven terrain (shiggy). Basically we are going to need every man, woman, and illegitimate child (SH*Tters) in the DC metropolitan area to make sure Jism &amp; Udder get to the bar so we can buy them birthday drinks.   </font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif" size="2">Live Wintery trail and remember a warm beer is better than no beer!</font></p>', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font face="Times New Roman" color="#000000" size="3">The Herndon-Monroe Park &amp; Ride is at the intersection of Sunset Valley Drive &amp; Roark Drive. If one is driving west (from Fairfax County Parkway) one makes a right at Roark. The map we have is a little off -- It\'s actually not right there at the intersection of Fairfax County Parkway and Sunset Valley Drive -- there\'s a couple blocks and a light to go past once you turn off the parkway. </font></span></font></p><div><font color="#000000">Directions:</font></div><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">From DC: take toll road to 7100 Fairfax Co. Parkway</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font color="#000000"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">                </span></font><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Take a left onto 7100 and drive 0.4 miles to the 2nd stop light.</span></font></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font color="#000000"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"> 