(297, '<p>It\'s a little known fact that Wook\'n Pa Nub is considering converting to <span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ">Judaism.  Nub being the oversexed hasher that he is doesn\'t want to limit himself to just one sex so he has recruited what he believes to be two very attractive and available hashers to assist him in his conversion to &quot;The Chosen People&quot;. </span></p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ">Nub being Nub has made two fundamental mistakes... Cradle 2 Dreidel is not Jewish and The Hebrew SlamHer is not single. In fact The Hebrew SlamHer is Friendly Thighs Man Toy!!   </span></p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ">Live A to A\' Trail.  It is going to be warmer than it has been but the RA is calling for rain. Bring a life jackect, rain coat, flash light, and a small stack of $20 for the webmaster.</span></p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ">Now about parking... it is going to be a bee-atch. I would park at the metro lot over 66 or take the metro. </span></p>', '<blockquote><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&hl=en&q=1060+N+Taylor+St,+Arlington,+Arlington,+Virginia+22201,+United+States&sll=38.893104,-77.090507&sspn=0.017402,0.036263&ie=UTF8&cd=1&geocode=0,38.883073,-77.112822&ll=38.883567,-77.112823&spn=0.008702,0.018132&z=16&iw"><font color="#0000ff">Trail# 296 Start</font></a></p></blockquote>(Metro)<br />Ballston Metro stop. Cross Fairfax drive toward 7/11. Turn Left, walk one block turn Left on N Taylor. Park is half block down on your right. Start location will be marked from the Ballston Metro Stop. <br /><p>(Driving) <br />Parking in Ballston sucks, good luck. <br />66 to exit 71 Fairfax Drive/Glebe Rd. Stay on Fairfax Dr cross Glebe Rd. Go about 3 blocks, Turn Left at N Taylor St. small park will be on right between two buildings. </p><blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote><blockquote> </blockquote></blockquote><blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote> </blockquote><br />', '<b>Buffalo D\'s</b> &amp; Food Factory back bar, directly across the street from Ballston Metro stop, to right of 7/11 at 4221 Fairfax Dr, Arlington, VA 22203<span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold"><br /></span><b>Buffalo D\'s Happy Hour prices 4pm to 9pm</b>. Cheapest in Ballston.<br />Rail Drinks …3.00$!!!<br />Buffalo D\'s Pilsner ….. 2.00$!!!!<br />Draft Bud, Bud Light, Miller Light….. 2.50$<br />Sam Adams, Yuengling, Blue Moon…3.50$<br />Guinness, NewCastle ….4.50$<b><br />For Hashers Happy Hour starts back up for us at 9:30</b>, runs till 11:30pm. Hmmmm that\'s convenient, why is anyone going to do trail…. <blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote> </blockquote><blockquote> </blockquote>', ' ', '<p>1060 N Taylor St, Arlington, VA 22201. In a small park behind the Nature Conservancy Headquarters across from the Ballston Metro. 1 block left of the 7/11 and Buffalo D\'s.</p>', ''),
(298, '<p>I know this is a Permenently Screwed trail but after looking at the hare list... I\'m thinking it should be named the Endless Just Hash.  The hareraiser B$ was very hesitant to permit three virgin hares to run but after B$ was injured when Chasing the Beast was riding him at the last OnOnOn his senses seemed to leave him. Screwed, the meticulous planner has promised to give the pack Herpes if any of his hares get snared.  Start will be at the corner of Rolling Rd and Old Keene Mill Rd at Cardinal Forest Plaza In FRONT of the Giant. In the BACK of the parking lot. </p><p>Live Trail! It\'s getting warmer but it is still going to be dark. Bring a whistle, flashlight, and don\'t forget those Ben Franklins for the Webmaster.</p>', 'Old ADC Map Grid 21 K-10<br />If you have a New ADC Map LOOK IT UP!!!!!!<br /><br />Cuming from I495, I95, I395 you would take the Springfield/Franconia<br />Exit. Then Take Old Keene Mill Rd west for so many miles the<br />shopping center is on the Right before the intersection of Rolling Rd.<br /><br />Cuming from Fairfax County Parkway, you would turn on to Old Keene Mill Rd. You<br />would go East for so many miles. The shopping Center is on the Left after the<br />intersection of Rolling Rd. If you are Cuming off the Subway at Franconia Springfield. GOOD LUCK!!<br />It would be a very long walk.....<br /><br />', '<font color="#000000"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><font size="2"><span style="FONT-STYLE: normal"><span><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; tab-stops: 271.5pt"><a href="http://www.yellowpages.com/info-LMS62402144/Hard-Times-Cafe/maps?back_to=/name/VA/hard-times?search_mode=all&search_terms=hard+times"><font face="Times New Roman" color="#0000ff" size="3">Hard Times Cafe</font></a></p>at Springfield Plaza on the corner of Amherst Ave. and Old Keene Mill Rd</span></span></font></font></font>', ' ', '  <p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=q&hl=en&q=Rolling