(301, '<p>On this day we will be celebrating the 300th trail of the So Happy It\'s Tuesday Hash House Harriers with a Shots Gone Wild Toga Hash. MisManagement has granted us a generous budget and Buffalo D\'s has promised us great drink prices till late in the evening.</p><p>The evening\'s entertainment will feature shots from the Shot Gone Wild Girls and a live A to B trail. Plan for a typical SH*T trail by bringing a whistle, flashlight, PI stuff, and a change of shoes.  Both trails will have a minimal amount of sticker bushes so you can wear your togas on trail or you can just change before the end circle.</p>', '<p>From the Ballston Metro Station - walk 3-4 block West on N Fairfax Dr. Turn left onto the Bluemont Junction Bike Trail. Walk a block and there we\'ll be.  </p><p>If you are driving click this <a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&sp=Point.qgd0n88k60m2_300th%20Start___&encType=1">300th Start</a> </p><p>You should be able to park on the streets around the park.</p>', ' <span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/4221+Fairfax+Dr+Arlington+VA+22203-1606/"><font color="#800080">Buffalo D\'s</font></a></span>', '<p>Bag vehicle will be provided.</p>', '<p> <a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&sp=Point.qgd0n88k60m2_300th%20Start___&encType=1">300th Start</a> </p><p>The start is in the middle of Fields Park.</p>', ''),
(302, '<span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: red; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font color="#000000">Ok, it is April first! You know what that means! Nobody is safe from the twisted minds of the hares, including the hares themselves. We all saw what some unsuspecting co-hares had happen to them last year right? SO come on out but be on your toes or you could find yourself sitting in a bar all by yourself with 5 pitches of beer in front of you telling the bartender that “no really, there are 40 people right behind me!”</font></span>', '<p>Metro:  Franconia-Springfied Metro - Start is less than 1 mile</p><p>Driving:</p><p /><p>Make your way to the outer loop of I-495.</p><p>Go to the Springfield mixing bowl, then take exit 57A</p><p>-&gt; Merge on to Franconia Rd/VA-644 E</p><p>-&gt; Make a right on Frontier Dr.</p><p>-&gt;Turn left onto Springfiled Pkwy/VA-7900 E</p><p>-&gt; Make left at the light at Beulah St.</p><p>-&gt; Take a left onto Walker Lane.</p><p>-&gt; Take first Right into parking lot.</p><p>-&gt; Go to the back of the parking lot - park - hash</p>', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lucky’s Sports Theatre and Grille</span></font><font face="Tahoma" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">7027 Manchester Blvd</span></font><font face="Tahoma" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Alexandria</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">, VA 22310</span></font><font face="Tahoma" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"></span></font></p>', 'Live trail that could end anywhere. Bring $5, whistle, change of clothes, flash light, PI stuff, bug spray, sun tan lotioin, small flask, at least two condoms, dark glasses, and a rubber chicken', '<p>Back right corner of the o<font face="Georgia" color="#660000"><span style="COLOR: #660000; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">ffice parking lot off of Walker Lane. </span></font></p><p><font face="Georgia" color="#660000"><span style="COLOR: #660000; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/%5B6348-6348%5D+Walker+Ln+Alexandria+VA+22310/#a/maps/l::[6348-6348]+Walker+Ln:Alexandria:VA:22310:US:38.7689:-77.1597:street:Fairfax+County/m:hyb:12:38.7689:-77.1597:0::/io:0:::::f:EN:M:/e"><font face="Times New Roman">Trail #301 Start</font></a></span></font></p><font face="Georgia" color="#660000"><span style="COLOR: #660000; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">6348 Walker Lane</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Alexandria</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">, VA 22310</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Start is in Springfield although it technically is Alexandria </span></font></p></span></font>', ''),
(303, '<p>This week we must first start with a question...</p><p>What are the top ten motivations for B$ to want to hare two weeks in a row?</p><p>10. He sucks as a hareraiser and is incapable to recruit competent hares.</p><p>9. He is trying to prove that his knee injury has healed and he is not a feable old man.</p><p>5. He is an attention whore.</p><p>4. He can\'t find a date to save his life so he has lots of time on his hands.</p><p>2. He is using the ruse of haring a trail to get to know She Finger Me &amp; Air Spanker One better.</p><p>1. Money is trying to prove that he can match last week\'s excellent trail!</p><p>Now that we\'ved thrown B$ under the bus, it is time to recognize a MOMENTOUS occasion!  We have NOT ONLY the newly named Grand Master of OTH haring for us, She Spankered Me One , we ALSO have the outgoing Grand Master of OTH haring for us, She Spankered Me One.  (I can\'t tell them apart.)  </p><p>This week will be a live A to B trail. I really have no idea what to expect. Be sure to bring a major credit card, medical id, 5 quarters, and a loaf of white bread. </p>', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><b><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Metro</span></font></b></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Metro:  You can take the Orange Line to West Falls Church.  It is about a mile to two walk.  Take a Left on Haycock, Left on Great Falls, Right On Kirby and cut through the park to the fields.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><b><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Driving</span></font></b></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Directions: (From South or West, East)  Take any route you choose to 66E.  Take Exit 66 onto Rte 7 West. Immediately get into the right lane, so that once you go under the overpass, you can take the next right turn on Idylwood.  Idylwood turns into Kirby Road, once you go over the Toll Road.  Make a Left turn on Westmoreland St. and Go until you see the Baseball parks on the left (about .33 miles). You will find the Wankers there.  </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">You can also take the GW Parkway north or South until Kirby Road or 123.  if you Take 123, you will need to take the Chain Bridge split to meet up with Westmoreland.  Kirby runs directly to Westmoreland<b><i><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-STYLE: italic"></span></i></b></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p>', '<p><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-STYLE: italic"><font face="Arial" size="3">Mark\'s Pub</font></span></p>', '', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">2024 Kirby Road</span></font><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">, </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Mclean</span></font><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">, VA 22101</span></font><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p>', '');
