(304, '<p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">If you\'re not bleeding from paying taxes, you will be after doing this trail!</span></p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Live A to Q trail. Bring dried fruit, gorp, compass, topo map, clean underwear, ivy block, bug spray, whistle,  &amp; flash light (serious about the flash light)</span></p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span></p>', '<div><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">From the Beltway,</span></font></p></div><div><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Take the Dulles Toll Road west and take Exit 17.  Turn right onto Spring Hill Road.  At the first traffic light take a right onto Lewinsville Road.  Take your first left onto Artnauman Ct and an immediate left into the parking lot.  Park and hash.</span></font></p></div><div><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">From points west:</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span></font><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Take the Dulles Toll Road east and take Exit 17.  Turn left onto Spring Hill Road.  At the first traffic light take a right onto Lewinsville Road.  Take your first left onto Artnauman Ct and an immediate left into the parking lot.  Park and hash.</span></font></p></div>', '<p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">The Pub</span>  </p><p><span class="EC_street-address"><font face="Garamond" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Garamond">6827 Redmond Drive</span></font></span><font face="Garamond"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Garamond">, <span class="EC_locality">McLean</span>, <span class="EC_region">VA</span></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Garamond"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Garamond"><span class="EC_region"></span></span></font><span class="EC_tel"><span id="EC_sxphone"><font face="Garamond" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Garamond">(703) 448-0928</span></font></span></span><font face="Garamond"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Garamond"></span></font></p>', '', '<span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Spring</span> Hill Recreation Center in Tysons Corner, VA', ''),
(305, '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Bodoni" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni"><font size="3"></font></span></font></p><font face="Bodoni" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni"><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font size="3"><font face="times new roman,times,serif">Once again the SH*T is repeating itself. Once again the SH*T is repeating itself. We are letting the same hare hare two weeks in a row row row.</font></font></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span></p><p /><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font size="3"><font face="times new roman,times,serif">I know you are thinking this must be the hareraiser\'s fault... but we threw him under the bus bus last week and while it is always fun fun to throw BB$$ under under the bus (and we we do it as often as we can as often as we can), we\'ve decided to give it a rest rest for this week.  </font></font></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span></p><p /><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font size="3"><font face="times new roman,times,serif">So even though even though there is some repetition in this week\'s\'s\'s trail, we will not not not, I repeat not not not, throw the current harrrreraiserrr under the bus.  It really isn\'t his fault anywayyy.</font></font></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span></p><p /><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font size="3"><font face="times new roman,times,serif">Who’s fault is is it?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Who cares?<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>(Fire in the Cornhole Fire in the Cornhole)</font></font></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span></p><p /><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font size="3"><font face="times new roman,times,serif">The real point is that we’re going to be in some cool new territory.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Or or at least territory that we we we we we haven’t been to in a long long long time.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Of course the last few times times we we we’ve come out to this area area area there has been a major weather event event.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>But don’t let let that stop stop stop stop stop you.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>I think we will will be safe from an ice stormmmmmm this time.</font></font></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span></p><p /><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font size="3"><font face="times new roman,times,serif">Live trail with at least a little shiggy (or a SH*T-ton of shiggy). Bring a flash light, bug spray, PI stuff, a change of cloths, eraser, rubber chicken, and syphon.  </font></font></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span></p><p /><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font size="3"><font face="times new roman,times,serif">There will be Karaoke at the on-on-on! So come on out and sing to your SH*T-ty hearts content.</font> </font></span></p><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /><p /></span></font>', '<p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Find your way to the Dulles Greenway</p><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Take exit 5 for Claiborne Parkway</p><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Take a left on Claiborne Parkway</p><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Take a left on Broadlands Blvd.</p><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Turn left into shopping center and look for wankers.</p><p /><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Or (if you don’t want to pay $3.50 in tolls)</p><p /><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Take the Dulles Toll Road to Rt. 28 North</p><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Exit onto Waxpool Rd. West</p><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Waxpool turns into Farmwell which turns into Ashburn Farm Parkway</p><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Take a left onto Claiborne Parkway</p><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Take a left on Broadlands Blvd.</p><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Turn left into shopping center and look for wankers.</p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://www.merchantcircle.com/business/The.Original.Steakhouse.And.Sports.Theater.571-223-0100" target="_blank">The Original Steakhouse &amp; Sports Theater</a>  </p><p /><p class="ecmsonormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">43150 <place /><placename />Broadlands</placename /> <placetype />Center</placetype /></place /> <place /><city />Plz<br />Broadlands</city />, <state />VA</state /> <postalcode />20148</postalcode /></place /><br />571-223-0100</p>', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><b><font face="Times New Roman" size="5"><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 20pt">TRAIL NOTES: Have you seen how much rain we have gotten in the last couple days?! Guess what that means? Bring a dry change of cloths, YOU ARE GOING TO GET WET. Also as a S.H.I.T. first, the hares have requested that if you have a personal flotation devise, i.e. inner tube, life jacket, boogie board, flotsam, jetsam etc., please bring it out. No, I am not joking here, there will be a section of trail that you will want a flotation devise. Hares will provide an air compressor if you need it.  </span></font></b></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><b><font face="Times New Roman" size="5"><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 20pt">You do NOT have to go tubing if you don\'t want!!!</span></font></b></p>', '<font face="Bodoni" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni"><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><font size="3"><place /><placename />Broadlands</placename /> <placetype />Shopping Center</font></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><font size="3">43150</font> <font size="3">Broadlands</font> <font size="3">Center</font> <font size="3">Pl</font>.</p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><font size="3">Broadlands</city />, <state />VA</state /> <postalcode />20148</postalcode /></font></place /><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni"> </span></p></span></font>', ''),
(306, 'Considering what we have been through in the last couple weeks; 3.45 miles of tunnels, shiggy up the ying yang, copious amounts of shots, sneaker sucking mud, flooded river crossings, midgets midgets midgets, 2 AHHB trails, a 300th b-day, tubing (not really), leaches, angry police officers, scared citizens, barking dogs, and Permanently Screwed incessant whining.- Permanently Screwed has assured me that this week will be a relaxing stroll through some beautiful, flat, dry cuntryside. Of course he has also promised that pigs will fly, cats and dogs will live together in harmony, and that Chasing the Beast will get a clue. HUH? WHHHAT? <br /><br /><b>In other words</b>, expect more of the same. Bring a dry bag, flash light, ivy block, band aids, Van Halen album, and a frozen French bread pizza.<br />', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Metro</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">After Cumming out of Van Dorn Metro Turn right and walk about two blocks maybe 3.. Parking lot is on the left side. </span></i></b></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Driving</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Cumming off of I495 take exit 173 Van Dorn St Exit. Take left onto <street w:st="on" /></span></i></b></p><address w:st="on">Van Dorn St</address><p></street />about a half mile turn right onto Eisenhower.</p><p>If you miss the turn on Eisenhower to the next exit it circles back to Eisenhower.</p><p>Go past the metro station parking lot is on the left…. <br style="mso-special-character: line-break" /><br style="mso-special-character: line-break" /></p><p /><p> </p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Nick’s Restaurant &amp; Night Club </span></i></b></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" /><address w:st="on"><street w:st="on" /><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">642 S. Pickett St.</span></i></b></street /><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> <city w:st="on" />Alexandria</city /></span></i></b></address><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><p /></span></i></b>', '', '<p>Parking lot accross the street from 5200 Eisenhower Ave. </p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=F779229D335CABAE!106"><font color="#800080">Trail #305</font></a></p>', ''),
(307, '<font face="Georgia">Holy Crapoli!  It\'s that time of the year again!  I\'m turning 30 one more time!!  It\'s at this point that I really wish I had started this when I was 29. 29 sounds so much better than 30...  Dammit... </font> <font face="Georgia">Sometimes I wish I could just go backward in time - don\'t you????</font>', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">From the Beltway: Exit 46A (123 South/Chain Bridge Road toward Tyson\'s Corner).  Go about 3.3 miles and turn right on Mill Street.  Go one block and turn left on Church Street.  Go one block and the Red Caboose is on your right.  Park where you can find a spot - street or parking lot.</font></p>', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><span lang="FR" style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: "><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif" size="3"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&ss=ypid.YN886x33185350&encType=1">Vienna Inn</a></font></span><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&ss=ypid.YN886x33185350&encType=1"><span lang="FR" style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "> <br /></span><font size="3"><span lang="FR" style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: "><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">120 Maple Ave E, Vienna, VA</font></span><span lang="FR" style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "> </span></font></a></font><font face="Georgia"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&ss=ypid.YN886x33185350&encType=1"> 703-938-9548</a></font></p><p><font face="Georgia">(The Vienna Inn is half a block from start...)</font></p>', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">A to A trail.  No tunnels (probably).  No water (probably).  No poison ivy (probably).  Then again, I don\'t know - as of this posting, I haven\'t scouted yet so I don\'t really know what\'s going to be on trail.  All I can promise is that there will be a trail.  And it will be good.  And there will be much rejoicing.  ;-)</font></p><p><font face="Georgia">If I\'m feeling nice I might update this later with more info.  But I probably won\'t.</font></p>', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&sp=Point.qghj848jv236_5%2F6%2F08%20Trail%20Start____&encType=1" target="_blank">Vienna, VA</a></font></p><p><font face="Georgia">Circle up by the Red Caboose on the W&amp;OD trail at the corner of Church Street and Dominion Road.  </font></p>', ''),
(308, 'Once Again SH*Tters are getting older.  This week the infamous And How\'s Her Bush will be turning 50. I know what you are thinking... AHHB doesn\'t look a day over 49! of course to prove AHHB still has game he had to recruit two recently aged hotties to do all the work. The SH*T will give anyone a beer if they can guess Drunk\'n &amp; Diswhorederly &amp; SaskatewSnatch\'s ages.', '<p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><font size="3"><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">From </span></strong><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Arlington</span></strong><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> (and Points East and North):</span></strong></font></p><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><font size="3"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">If Cumming via… </span><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">George Washington Memorial Parkway, North</span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> (heading TOWARD I495)… take the <b><i>Spout Run</i></b> exit. Take the FIRST <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT</span></b> onto </span><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Lorcom Lane</span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Take a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT</span></b> onto </span><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Nellie Custis Drive</span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Nellie </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Custis Drive</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> bears<b><span style="COLOR: #3366ff"> </span><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT</span></b> and turns into <b><i>Military Road</i></b>. Take a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT</span></b> (at the light) onto </span><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Marcey Road</span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Continue on </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Marcey Road</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> to </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Marcey</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Park</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> all the way to the end. If your car goes into the </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Potomac River</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">… you’ve gone too far, but at least you’ll be on trail!! Park (or have you car towed from the river) and look for wankers milling around doing 16oz curls.</span></font></p><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3"> </font></span></p><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3">And finally… from the Beltway:</font></span></strong></p><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><font size="3"><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">via </span></strong><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">George Washington Memorial Parkway</span></strong><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">:</span></strong></font></p><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><font size="3"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Find your way to the beltway and take the appropriate exit for <b><i>Interstate 495, North</i></b> towards </span><span style="COLOR: red"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Rockville<span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">, </span><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">MD</span></span></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">.</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> Take <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT 43</span></b> for<b><i> </i></b></span><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">George Washington Memorial Parkway, South</span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> towards </span><span style="COLOR: red"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Washington<span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">, </span><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">DC</span></span></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Take the <b><span style="COLOR: blue">SECOND EXIT</span></b> for <b><i>Route 123, </i></b></span><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Dolly Madison Boulevard</span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> and continue all the way until it dead ends into a “T” intersection with </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Glebe Road</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Take a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT</span></b> onto </span><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Glebe Road</span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">… and you will start a monstrous climb (start thinking about what the trail is going to be like!!)… follow the signs and bear </span><b><span style="COLOR: blue"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">RIGHT</span></span></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> FOR Military Road</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> (this will be… </span><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">North Old Glebe Road</span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">). Go through the first stop sign and take a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> on the bridge over </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Glebe Road</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Take your first <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Military Road</i></b>. Continue on </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Military Road</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> for approx. 1½ miles… and take a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Marcey Road</i></b> (at the light) and continue to </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Marcey</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Park</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> all the way to the end. Park and look for wankers milling around doing 16oz curls.</span></font></p><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3"> </font></span></p><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3">Alternate Route:</font></span></strong></p><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3">via Interstate 66, North:</font></span></strong></p><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><font size="3"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Take the SPOUT </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">RUN</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> exit onto Route 29, North. Turn <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Spout Run</i></b> and then your FIRST <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Lorcom Lane</i></b> and follow the directions above.</span></font></p><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3"> </font></span></p><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><font size="3"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Obviously… there are MANY other ways to get there… however… </span><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Metro</span></strong><strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></strong><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">is not one of them.</span></strong></font></p><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3"> </font></span></strong></p>', '<p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><font size="3"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Cowboy Café … they have ½ price burgers on Tuesdays and parking is limited. (Address for Cowboy Café: </span><span class="EC_EC_street-address1"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">4792 Lee Hwy</span></span><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">, </span><span class="EC_EC_street-address1"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Arlington</span></span><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">, </span><span class="EC_EC_street-address1"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">VA</span></span><span class="EC_EC_street-address1"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">)</span></span></font></p>', '<p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; mso-fareast-font-family: ">Live A to A\' trail. Plan on encountering poison ivy, sticker bushes, diseased insects, wild animals, homeless people, and Mormons. Oh &amp; for some reason the hares said to bring a flashlight. </span></font></span></p>', '<strong><font face="Georgia"> </font></strong><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&q=2845+Marcey+Rd,+Arlington,+VA+22207,+USA&um=1&ie=UTF-8&sa=X&oi=geocode_result&resnum=1&ct=title" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><font face="Georgia" color="#800080" size="3"><strong>Marcey Park</strong></font></a><strong><font face="Georgia" size="3"> (old </font><font size="3"><span>Potomac Overlook) in Arlington<span>, VA</span></span></font></strong><span style="COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><br /></span><strong><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">(off of </span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Military Road</span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> Between </span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Old Glebe Road</span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> and Route 29)</span></i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></strong>', ''),
(309, '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">That’s right, you will be teamed up with a fellow hasher and one of each of your legs will be tied together. You will run or attempt to run the entire trail like this! This is going to be more fun than watching Nub compete in the </span></font><font face="Tahoma" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"><a href="http://www.spellingbee.com/" target="_blank"><font color="#000000"><span style="COLOR: windowtext">Scripps National Spelling Bee</span></font></a>! There will be the same shiggy that you have come to expect and enjoy on a regular basis from the S.H.I.T. but now it will just be that much more difficult/fun to navigate. Look at it this way, you are going to get to know the person you are tied too really, really well (for better or for worse) by the end of the trail.  Extra beer and ear muffs will be provided to the poor unfortunate soul that gets chained to Herpes. </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">It is going to be fun, I promise. If it isn’t you can take the Hare Raiser out back and shoot him.</span></span></font></p>', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal" style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12pt"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Find your way to Route 7 and look for a little place call <i><span style="FONT-STYLE: italic">Sterling</span></i>, where the women flow like the salmon of Capistrano. We will be in the shopping center with the Don Pablo’s and the Pacific Restaurant – right across from the NOVA Community College. </span></font></p>', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">O’Faolain’s Irish Pub</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span></font><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">20921 Davenport Drive</span></font><font face="Tahoma" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"> Sterling, VA 20165</span></font></p>', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">A-A’ trail with all the trimmings!  Come prepared for a typical S.H.I.T. trail with the standard water, mud, and shiggy.  Make sure to not go light on the deodorant either cause you are going to be getting very familiar with some wanker. </span></font><font face="Tahoma" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"> </span></font><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Aren’t you glad you use dial. Don’t you wish everyone did? </span></font><font face="Tahoma" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"> </span></font><font face="Tahoma" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"></span></font></p>', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">46280 Potomac Run Plz</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span></font><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Sterling</span></font><font face="Tahoma" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma">, VA 20164</span></font></p><font face="Times New Roman" color="#0000ff" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/46280+Potomac+Run+Plz+Sterling+20164/#a/maps/l::46280+Potomac+Run+Plz:Sterling:VA:20164-6608:US:39.027161:-77.399002:address:Loudoun+County/m::12:39.027161:-77.399002:0:0:/io:0:::::f:EN:M:/e">Three Legged Start</a></p></span></font><font face="Tahoma" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"></span></font><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"> </span></font><font face="Tahoma" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"></span></font></p>', ''),
(310, 'Not sure who\'s idea this trail was but I assure you that a great deal of planning and practice has gone into this soon-to-be-called &quot;work of art&quot;. Seriously, when was the last time these half-minds actually ran a trail instead of drinking a four pack of Sparks on the walker\'s trail?  Should be fun times tonight! ', '<span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: ">Cumming from the </span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: ">Fairfax County Parkway </span></street /><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: ">turn onto </span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: ">Sunrise Valley Drive </span></street /><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: ">heading West for about 1.5 miles turn left onto </span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: ">Wood Oak Drive.  </span></street /><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: ">Look for Wankers in the parking lot.</span>', 'TBA', 'Live A to A\' trail. The weather should be perfect for a shiggy run. Plan for poison ivy, tics, &amp; unpleasant body odor.', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><font size="2"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Parking Lot across the street from this address: <strong><a href="http://tinyurl.com/3s5a46">http://tinyurl.com/3s5a46</a> </strong></span></font></p></street />', ''),
(311, 'As many of you know Target Practise is being re-deported again. Personally I believe if the government would stop buying her round trip airline tickets this wouldn\'t be a recurring problem. But I digress... Come out, wish TP farewell, shower her with expensive gifts, and remind her that wherever she gets sent there will be more men than woman.', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">(Metro)</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Soooooo not even close. If coming by metro leave yesterday. </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">(Driving)</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"><font color="#000000">Take Rt 66 West to the Rout 29 Exit <font face="times new roman,times,serif">the second is Exit 43A – Gainesville/Warrenton.</font></font> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Take Rt 29 West</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Turn left onto Linton Hall Rd. </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span></font><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Take a left at second light into shopping center. (1<sup>st</sup> left turn you can make)<font face="Georgia"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></font></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Look for wanker (s),  park,  hash<br /><br /></span></font></p>', '<p>Joes Pizza</p><p><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">14085 John Marshall Hwy</span></font> </p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Gainesville</span></font>, VA 20155</p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p>', 'Be prepared for anything. I am not kidding, we are so far off the grid that I wouldn’t be surprised to see big foot. The Shiggy is gonna be kickin so make sure to come prepared. On a side note, Fire in the Cornhole can actually walk to start this week!', '<p><font color="#000000">The <font face="Arial" size="2">Gateway Center</font> at the corner of Rt 29 (Lee Highway) and Linton Hall Road</font> </p><p><font face="times new roman,times,serif" color="#000000">start on the side of AJ Carpet and Flooring which is located at 7617 Linton Hall Rd</font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.live.com/default.aspx?wip=2&v=2&rtp=~&FORM=MSNH#JnE9eXAuNzYxNytMaW50b24rSGFsbCtSZCtnYWluc3ZpbGxlJTJjK3ZhJTdlc3N0LjAlN2VwZy4xJmJiPTU3Ljg0NDc1MDk5Mjg5MSU3ZS02NS41NjY0MDYyNSU3ZTI1LjQ4Mjk1MTE3NTM1NTMlN2UtMTMzLjc2OTUzMTI1"><font color="#0000ff">Trail #311</font></a></p>', ''),
(312, '<font color="#0000ff"><font face="times new roman,times,serif" color="#000000">The Annual Mary-Kate and Ashley Olsen Birthday Trail. The bitches are back and legal! Many of the trail’s exploits revolve around the idea of three &quot;swinging-dick&quot; hares trying to rein in the precocious antics of these girls, who frequently get the best of them. As is the case with many trails, these bitches ignore the rules, only to learn their lesson afterward. The trails usually end with a hug or kiss and with the girls sometimes admitting their wrongs and working out a compromise with 14K, B$, or Corn. There is always a beer towards the end of the trail. The girls grow up (and out) as their waistline progresses, and various (boy)friends are introduced, notably Udder Ho, Mary Kate’s  steady Pimp for Seasons 6 &amp; 7. They later break up, though in the final episode, Big Daddy U.H. returns to escort ‘dem bitches. to their senior prom.</font></font>', '<span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 7.5pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps/7512+Old+Keene+Mill+Road%2C++Springfield%2C++VA+22150/"><font face="Times New Roman" color="#800080" size="3">Trail #311</font></a></p></span>', 'Kate’s Irish Pub <br />6131 N. Backlick Rd, <br />Springfield, VA <br />(703) 866-0860<br />', '<p>Unusally when the hares make last minutes changes to a trail it is a bad sign but this time it\'s going to be different &amp; the check is in the mail &amp; I won\'t cum in your mouth.</p><p>From the Hareraiser who happens to be a hare, &quot;Tonight\'s trail is going to be really good!&quot;</p><p>Now to be serious... It is hot! &amp; it will be hot for trail. Hydrate before trail. </p>', '<p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font color="#000000"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Start  is at the back of the Church at the corner of </span><font face="Arial" size="3"><span style="COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font color="#000000">Byron Ave. and Old Keene Mill Road (7512 Old Keene Mill Rd, Springfield, VA 22150).  Make a left into the parking lot before you enter Byron Park</font></span></font></font></span></p>', ''),
(313, '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="times new roman,times,serif" color="#000000" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font face="Times New Roman" color="#000000" size="3">I\'m not sure why Lance Armstrong gave up cycling for hashing. Maybe Lance just needed a real challenge. Whatever his reasons, he is taking his training for the Tour duh Hash very seriously. Pictured is Lance running the NYC Marathon in 2:46:43. After the race Lance commented, &quot;I would have gotten a better time if it hadn\'t taken me so freakin\' long to find the Beer Check&quot;.<br /> <br />Well, Lance, you aren\'t going to have that problem at the SH*T. The SH*T is known for having the best hash beer in the DC area.  (Except Great Falls... F*ck Them!)   <br /> <br />This week\'s trail, the fourth leg of the Tour will have a little something for everyone. We will have a nice, relaxing walker\'s trail for those who choose to save themselves for future Tour legs &amp; a nice 4-5 mile shiggy filled stroll through scenic Fairfax for those that are looking for a truly SH*Tty trail.<br /> <br />Bring $5, a whistle, ivy block, bug spray, sun screen, head lamp, change of clothing, and a shaved poodle.</font></span></font></p>', '<font face="times new roman,times,serif" color="#000000" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font face="times new roman,times,serif" color="#000000" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font color="#000000"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font face="times new roman,times,serif"><font size="3"><font color="#000000">Trail starts <a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&sp=Point.qgbbfx8jvf3f_SHIT%20Trail%20Start____&encType=1">behind</a> the Pan Am Shopping Center at the corner of Lee Highway (Rt 29) and Nutley St</font>.</font></font></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font color="#000000"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font face="times new roman,times,serif" color="#000000" size="3">Coming from the north, south, east and/or the beltway: Take Route 50 (Arlington Blvd) WEST.  From the beltway, go just over 2 miles to a RIGHT on Nutley street.  Go less than half a mile and turn RIGHT into the Pan Am Shopping Center.  Drive all the way around to the BACK of the shopping center.  Look for wankers, park and hash.</font></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font color="#000000"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font face="times new roman,times,serif" color="#000000" size="3">From the west: Take 66 EAST.  Exit Nutley Street SOUTH.  Pan Am Shopping Center is ahead on your LEFT after you cross over Lee Highway.  Drive all the way around to the BACK of the shopping center.  Look for wankers, park and hash.</font></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font color="#000000"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font face="times new roman,times,serif"><font size="3"><font color="#000000">From the Metro: Exit at the</font> </font></font><a href="http://www.wmata.com/metrorail/Stations/station.cfm?station=103"><font face="times new roman,times,serif" size="3">Vienna/Fairfax-GMU</font></a><font face="times new roman,times,serif" size="3"> <font color="#000000">Station and walk 3/4 of a mile SOUTH to the Pan Am Shopping Center.  Walk around to the BACK of the shopping center.  Look for wankers and hash</font>.</font></span></font></p></span></font></span></font>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-outline-level: 5"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold"><a href="http://www.glorydaysgrill.com/"><span style="COLOR: black; TEXT-DECORATION: none; text-underline: none">Glory Days Grill</span></a> (in the Pan Am Shopping Center - same as start)</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-outline-level: 5"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold">3059 Nutley St</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-outline-level: 5"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold">Fairfax VA</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-outline-level: 5"><span style="mso-bidi-font-weight: bold">703-204-0900</span></p>', '', '<font face="times new roman,times,serif" color="#000080" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font face="times new roman,times,serif" color="#000000" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><font color="#000000"><font face="times new roman,times,serif" size="3">Pan Am Shopping Center BACK parking lot: <a title="Link to Trail Start" href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&sp=Point.qgbbfx8jvf3f_SHIT%20Trail%20Start____&encType=1">Link to Trail Start</a> (scroll out when you get to the map)</font></font></p></span></font></span></font></span></font>', ''),
(314, '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" color="#444444" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: #444444">Trail notes; Ok so some of you may be asking yourself, “Who is Cockspur?” and “Why have I never heard of this Corn on the Cock guy”. Well let you tell me, that these guys go way back and are sure to lay an old school classic S.H.I.T. trail. Come prepared for anything especially Cockspur chicken dancing like a MoFo. </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" color="#444444" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: #444444">Make sure to bring a change of clothes, Ivy Blocker, sun screen, bug spray, sarcastic comments, wounds and scars from last weeks trail, mangled pride, broken egos, and a giant laser machine that can turn a house into a giant popcorn popper from space. </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><b><font face="Times New Roman" color="#444444" size="3"><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: #444444">Hey Norm, little know fact. Never go in against Cockspur in flip cup when Rum is on the line!</span></font></b></p>', '<p class="EC_ecmsonormal"><font face="Times New Roman" color="#444444" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: #444444">From Leesburg and points northwest, take Rt 7 East, follow signs to CHAIN BRIDGE RD/VA-123 S. Continue to follow MAPLE AVE/VA-123 S.  Look for Wendy’s on your left.</span></font></p><p class="EC_ecmsonormal"><font face="Times New Roman" color="#444444" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: #444444"> From Manassas and points west: take I-66 E toward Washington.  Follow VA-243 N/NUTLEY ST via EXIT 62 toward VIENNA.  Turn RIGHT onto MAPLE AVE W/VA-123 N.    Look for Wendy’s on your right. </span></font></p><p class="EC_ecmsonormal"><font face="Times New Roman" color="#444444" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: #444444">From DC and points east: Take VA-123 East toward CHAIN BRIDGE/MCLEAN directly into Vienna, OR I-66 W toward Manassas.  Follow VA-243 N/NUTLEY ST via EXIT 62 toward VIENNA.  Turn RIGHT onto MAPLE AVE W/VA-123 N, OR take 50 West to 495 and follow “Beltway” directions below. </span></font></p><p class="EC_ecmsonormal"><font face="Times New Roman" color="#444444" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: #444444">From anywhere on the BELTWAY: Take 495 to VA-123 S via EXIT 46A toward TYSONS CORNER.  Continue to follow MAPLE AVE/VA-123 S.  Look for Wendy’s on your left </span></font></p>', '<font color="#444444">Vienna Inn, 120 Maple Ave E</font>', '', '<span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/default.aspx?wip=2&v=2&rtp=~&FORM=MSNH#JnE9eXAuNDExK01hcGxlK0F2ZStFK1ZpZW5uYSUyYytWQSU3ZXNzdC4wJTdlcGcuMSZiYj01Ny4wODg1MTUzMjc4ODY1JTdlLTM5LjYzODY3MTg3NSU3ZTE0Ljc3NDg4MjUwNjUxNjMlN2UtMTE0LjYwOTM3NQ==">Trail Start</a> Parking lot behind Wendy\'s, 411 Maple Ave E, Vienna, VA</span>', ''),
(315, '<p>Wear your favorite Blue/Hawaiin/Elvis whatever to this weeks trail. Expect fantastic prizes &amp; strange blue beverages. You may not get SH*T but you entitled half-minds should expect something. </p><p>Bring ivy block, tecnu, bug spray, head lamp, whistle, change of cloths, something that goes well with a lei, and unrealistic expectations.</p>', 'Find your way to Route 7 just outside the beltway (exit 47 on 495)<br />Turn left to go south on Gallows Road.<br />Go approximately .7 miles and turn left onto Science Application Ct.<br />Go all the way to the back parking lot and look for wankers.<br /> <br />', 'On the Border<br />8053 Leesburg Pike<br />', '', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&where1=7980%20Science%20Applications%20Ct%2C%20Vienna%2C%20VA%2022182-4015&encType=1"><font color="#800080">Trail Start</font></a> Far back parking lot at 7980 Science Application Court, Vienna VA </p>', ''),
(316, '&nbsp;', '<div><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><u><font size="3" face="Arial"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">Metro</span></font></u><font face="Arial"><span style="font-family: Arial;">: Not really metro accessible.  Start is 1.5 miles south from the Crystal City metro (straight down Rt. 1/Jefferson Davis Hwy).</span></font></p></div><div><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><u><font size="3" face="Arial"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">Driving</span></font></u><font face="Arial"><span style="font-family: Arial;">: Get yourself to 395. Take the Glebe Road exit.  Travel south and stay on South Glebe Road (do not get on West Glebe Rd.) for a little over 1.5 miles.  Take a right onto Rt. 1 (Jefferson Davis Hwy).  Take first available left into the Potomac Yards shopping center.  Look for wankers hanging out in front of Shoppers Food Warehouse.</span></font></p></div><div><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font size="3" face="Arial"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;">&nbsp;</span></font></p></div>', '<p>Hops Brewery (same shopping center as Start)</p><p>3625 Jefferson Davis Hwy</p><p>No Hasher food specials because the hares refused to blow the manager!!</p><p>But they do have cheap beer...</p><p>$1.79 for a mug, $2.29 for a pint &amp; $3.29 for a 20 oz schooner</p><p>Who knows it might even taste good.</p>', '<p /><p />', '<p>Shoppers Food Warehouse (front parking lot)</p><p>Potomac Yards shopping center (Crystal City\'ish)</p><p>3801 Jefferson Davis Hwy, Alexandria, VA</p><p><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Arial;"><a target="_blank" href="http://www.gmap-pedometer.com/?r=2027382">http://www.gmap-pedometer.com/?r=2027382</a></span></p><p />', ''),
(317, '<p>Sorry Half-Minds I have no idea what to expect this week! I mean seriously who the hell is Gay Station &amp; no I\'m not sure if PSA is under indictment along with his hos at the metro. I know Jism has dedicated his life\'s work to making medicines that save lives but can he hare? I can\'t remember because I got drunk at all the other trails he led. The only thing I know for certain is that Sir Shaves A Lot was at least an hour late every time they got together to scout.</p><p>Personally I would bring a whistle, PI stuff, flash light, change of clothes, a good sense of direction and cab fare.  <font color="#cc0000"><strong>PLEASE NOTE: NO DOGS ALLOWED THIS WEEK AS A CONDITION OF THE HOMEOWNER AT THE BEER CHECK AND END LOCATION </strong></font></p><p />', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Drive to <a href="http://maps.live.com/default.aspx?wip=2&v=2&rtp=~&FORM=MSNH#JnE9eXAuNDY0MStEdWtlK1N0JTJjK0FsZXhhbmRyaWElMmMrVkElN2Vzc3QuMCU3ZXBnLjEmYmI9NTcuMDg4NTE1MzI3ODg2NSU3ZS0zOS42Mzg2NzE4NzUlN2UxNC43NzQ4ODI1MDY1MTYzJTdlLTExNC42MDkzNzU=">Fox Chase Plaza</a> </p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Or Metro to Van Dorn Station and call a generous fellow hasher, car pool, take a cab, ride a bicycle, scooter, segway, roller blade, unicycle, skitch, run, walk, limp, pub crawl, hitch hike the 1.2 miles or be a true champion and have your pimp drop you off.</p>', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">At this time the On-On-On is at Shooter McGees, 5239 Duke St.<br /><br /></span></font></p>', '<img hspace="0" src="http://www.apysl.org/images/nodogs.gif" align="baseline" border="0" />', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.live.com/default.aspx?wip=2&v=2&rtp=~&FORM=MSNH#JnE9eXAuNDY0MStEdWtlK1N0JTJjK0FsZXhhbmRyaWElMmMrVkElN2Vzc3QuMCU3ZXBnLjEmYmI9NTcuMDg4NTE1MzI3ODg2NSU3ZS0zOS42Mzg2NzE4NzUlN2UxNC43NzQ4ODI1MDY1MTYzJTdlLTExNC42MDkzNzU=">Fox Chase Plaza</a> off Duke Street in front of Harris Teeter.</p><p>4641 Duke St, Alexandria, VA</p><p />', '');
