(318, '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">This week the SH*T will be back on our home turf! That\'s right, outside the beltway!! One would think this would guarantee a good shiggilicious trail.  And it might...  Who knows?  We\'ve traveled far outside the beltway and run pavement pounders and we\'ve hashed inside the beltway and spent most of the trail underground in tunnels, so I wouldn\'t recommend trying to figure out a trail by the location...  Instead, let\'s examine this week\'s hares for clues as to the type of trail they may lay.  (It\'s more fun to pick on our friends anyway.)  First, we have a lead hare who Vegas oddsmakers are only giving 69 to 1 that he\'ll even make his own trail start.  Then you have his wife, a directionally challenged chronic DFL.  Next down the line is a fresh post-op patient (he says he had knee surgery but we know it was really just the last stage of his female to male conversion - now he really is just one of the boys!).  Last (and least) we have a no name hasher and a mystery hare.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Hmmm…<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>we could be in for it this week.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Might I recommend a 500 watt flashlight, survival kit, bloodhound, catamaran, pocket knife and MacGyver to put it all together for you.</p>', '<p>(Metro)<br />Take Metro to WFC station, then Fairfax Connector #980 to Herndon-Monroe<br />Park and Ride (about 20 minutes). Walk half a mile East to start.<br /> </p><p>(Driving)<br />From the West:<br />Go East on VA-267 E<br />Take the VA-7100/FAIRFAX CNTY PKWY exit- exit number 11 to Herndon.<br />Turn RIGHT onto FAIRFAX CNTY PKWY.<br />Turn RIGHT onto SUNRISE VALLEY DR.<br />Turn RIGHT at the light with the Sprint sign.<br />Drive around back, look for wankers.<br /><br />From the East<br />Take GEORGE WASHINGTON MEMORIAL PKWY N.<br />Take the ramp towards I-495 S and merge onto I-495 S.<br />Take the ramp towards VA-267 W (Portions toll)<br />Take the VA-7100/FAIRFAX CNTY PKWY exit- exit number 11 to Herndon.<br />Turn LEFT at the end of the ramp onto FAIRFAX CNTY PKWY.<br />Turn RIGHT onto SUNRISE VALLEY DR.<br />Turn RIGHT at the light with the Sprint sign.<br /></p>', 'Buffalo Wings House<br />13005 Worldgate Dr, Herndon<br />', '', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.live.com/default.aspx?wip=2&v=2&rtp=~&FORM=MSNH#JnE9eXAuMTI1MjQrU3VucmlzZStWYWxsZXkrRHJpdmVSZXN0b24lMmMrVkErMjAxOTElN2Vzc3QuMCU3ZXBnLjEmYmI9NTMuOTA0MzM4MTU2Mjc0NyU3ZS00My4xNTQyOTY4NzUlN2UyMC4wNTU5MzEyNjUxOTQ0JTdlLTExMC45MTc5Njg3NQ=="><font color="#0000ff">Behind Sprint Buildings</font></a> on Sunrise Valley Drive</p><p>12524 Sunrise Valley Drive<br />Reston, VA 20191<br /></p>', ''),
(319, '', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: "Arial","sans-serif"; mso-themecolor: text1">Take 66 or other assorted methods to Rte. 50 or 28.<p /></span></i></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: "Arial","sans-serif"; mso-themecolor: text1"><p> </p></span></i></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: "Arial","sans-serif"; mso-themecolor: text1">From 28, head north or south, Make a turn right if you are coming north, make a left if you are coming south onto Rte 50 (Lee Jackson Memorial Highway).<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Turn Onto Metrotech drive from 50.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Once you pass the Lowes, make a right turn to go as if you were going behind it.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>From there, go behind the Babies R Us, as the parking lot is a little bigger.<p /></span></i></b></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: "Arial","sans-serif""><p> </p></span></i></b></p>', 'Bungalow Billiards in Sully Plaza Shopping Center', '', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #444444; FONT-FAMILY: "Verdana","sans-serif""><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?f=d&hl=en&geocode=&saddr=38.893429,-77.422489&daddr=&mra=mi&mrsp=0&sz=17&sll=38.893438,-77.423701&sspn=0.003958,0.006609&ie=UTF8&t=h&z=17"><font color="#800080">Behind Babies R US</font></a><p /></span></p><p>Sully Plaza Shopping Center</p><p>13954 Metrotech Dr.</p><p>Chantilly, VA</p>', ''),
(320, '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><font size="2">Some people feel the two best things to cum out of Canada are Pam Anderson\'s breasts, but those at the SH*T know better.  The two best things to cum out of Canada are</font><font color="#000000"> </font></font><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#000000"><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Areola Borealis and Saskatchewsnatch...  Ahhhh - feel the love!  </font></font></font></p><p><font face="Arial" size="2"><font color="#000000"><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">That was your warm fuzzy for the day, now we will get down the point of this missive: to sh*t on Canada, the 51st state.  Oh wait!  First we need to SH*T on the honorary Canadian, Can\'t Find Pussy in a Haystack.  It has come to our attention that Haystack has broken his hand in a tragic masturbation accident.  The dude hasn\'t been laid in so long his hand finally wore out and broke.  Now that his primary form of entertainment has been sidelined for the next 4-6 weeks you better hide your sisters, mothers, grandmothers and warm apple (American) pies.</font></font></font></p><p><font face="Georgia" size="2">Now, on to Blaming Canada!</font></p><p><img hspace="0" src="http://www.canadasucks.com/images/c1.jpg" align="baseline" border="0" /></p><p><font size="2"><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Have you ever done a google search using the search string &quot;Canada sucks?&quot;  The first thing that pops up is a website </font><a href="http://www.canadasucks.com/"><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">www.canadasucks.com</font></a><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">.  </font><a href="http://mail.canadasucks.com/email/scripts/loginuser.pl"><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Click here to get your own canadasucks.com email address.</font></a><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">  Interestingly, on this website is a tactical map of the US invasion of Canada in 1775:</font></font></p><p><a href="http://www.canadasucks.com/americanrevolution.htm"><img hspace="0" src="/images/canadainvasion_copy.jpg" align="baseline" border="0" /></a></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif" size="2">As quoted on the candasucks.com website: Professional cartographer, </font><a href="mailto:hash@canadasucks.com"><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif" size="2">JP</font></a><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif" size="2">, has provided me with this detailed tactical map of the US invasion of Canada (click picture for larger image). This is proof to all you unbelieving Hosers out there that yes, the US did conquer Canada during the American Revolution. Now that I\'ve proved all you Hosers wrong, your next step would be to e-mail me about your supposed &quot;victory&quot; in the War of 1812. Sorry, you lost that war too.   Note from the webmaster: apparently Canada wasn\'t good enough to keep, but apparently its a good place to be FROM, just ask Areola Borealis and Saskatchewsnatch. </font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><font size="2"><font color="#000000">This week\'s trail would be a typical trail if we were hashing in Canada. Unfortunately, we are not.  Because</font> we are in NOVA, the hares have promised to lay a SH*Tty trail. I haven\'t a clue what that means, so I would plan for anything. Bring snow shoes, hand warmers, heavy winter coat, scarf, long underwear, and passport because we are heading North. </font></font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif" size="2">One note from the hares: no dogs - sorry - you can bring your dogs back to the hash next week.</font></p>', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif" size="2">Metro:<br />Not very metro accessible but if you take the metro here are the connecting buses to take:<br />Van Dorn Metro station: 25B direction Ballston or the Dash 5 direction Braddock Metro<br />King Street Metro station: Dash 5 bus direction Van Dorn Metro. </font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif" size="2">Driving:<br />From points south:<br />Take 395 north to the Seminary exit east.  Merge to the left as the first left, Library Lane, is where you need to turn.  Go down the road and turn left into the parking lot about a block and a half down and park behind the strip mall.</font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif" size="2">From points west:<br />Take 66 east and follow signs for 395 south.  Take 395 south to Seminary exit east.  Merge to the left as the first left, Library Lane, is where you need to turn.  Go down the road and turn left into the parking lot about a block and a half down and park behind the strip mall.</font></p>', 'TBA', '', '<p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; LINE-HEIGHT: 115%; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://www.gmap-pedometer.com/?r=2126370"><font color="#800080">Blame Canada Start</font></a></span> </p><p>(off Library Road behind strip mall between Kenmore and Library)</p>', ''),
(326, '<p>So we got a little wet at the AGM. Did that stop us from having a good time? </p><p><strong>HELL NO!</strong> It was a blast. Thanks to everyone who helped out and turning what could have been a disaster into a great and memorable party that I am sure people will be talking about for years!</p><p>Special thanks goes out to Permanently Screwed for letting us use his yard.</p><p>Now onto this weeks trial...</p><p>Dixie Queen will be leading this adventure into the wilds of Ashburn. Dixie being the competive bastard that he is has recruited the gold medal team from the OlympDicks.  Udder believes that superior intellect, positive attitude, &amp; love for beer will enable the hares to out whit the pack.</p><p>The hares suggest that you eat a hardy meal &amp; drink a few cold ones before trail... you are going to need the carbs. </p><p>Due to the AGM all water crossings have been removed!!!<strong> BRING A FLASH LIGHT!</strong>  It is going to be dark before you finish trail.</p><p> </p><p>  </p>', 'Hi', '<p>Nick\'s Corner Grill in Brmbleton Town Center</p><p>42395 Ryan Road, #130</p>', '', '<p>Back of Harris Teeter in Brambleton Town Center</p><p>42415 Ryan Road</p><p>Ashburn, VA 20148</p>', ''),
