(328, '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><font face="Calibri">And I cannot lie! Not that I am bitter about my trail being scooped….</font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><font face="Calibri">After numerous scouting missions to the area (okay I mountain biked the area twice) I presented the trail to the Hareraiser for the SH*Tty Tour-Da-Hash trail. I was denied because the location was too close to <city /><place />Great Falls</place /></city />’ home turf &amp; besides CornHole had a better trail in mind. I now know this to be BULL SH*T. I hate big tits!</font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><font face="Calibri">The Hareraiser was saving the trail for personal gain. He was just waiting for some curvy vixen to come along saying I sooo want to lead my own trail but I need a really cool place to do it. I hate big tits! <span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><font face="Calibri">To top things off, the said vixen bragged about having an old school hasher to plow through all the SH*T and a wide eyed blonde virgin that is too naïve to realize that she is just being used for her body. I hate big tits! <span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </span><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">    </span><span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><font face="Calibri">The trail starts near the Colvin Run Mill at one of the trail heads for the Cross County Connecter Trail. This is a truly beautifully wooded area with miles of single track riding (advance beginner level). The trees are giant with lots of open areas to hash. I hate harriettes that use their feminine wiles to scoop my trail</font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 10pt"><font face="Calibri">But I’m not bitter</font></p><p />', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: "><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&sp=Point.qgv44x8jsb39_Trail%20327%20Start_Fairfax%20County%20Pumping%20Station___&encType=1"><em><font color="#c50000"><strong>Fairfax County Pumping Station</strong></font></em></a> <font size="2"><font color="#000000"><font face="Arial">PScrewed, click link for MSN map, use aerial view to see unnamed road</font></font></font></span></span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: ">From DC Area </span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span>Get yourself to VA-267 W</span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: ">Take exit 19B-A for US-267 W toward I-495</span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: ">Slight left at VA-267 W (Partial toll road)</span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: ">Take exit 16 to merge onto Leesburg Pike/VA-7 toward Leesburg</span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: ">Turn right at Colvin Run Rd</span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: ">Bare right immediately after turn onto Colvin Run Rd and follow road to dead end (parking lot)</span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: "></span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt"><font face="Arial">From East Bygod</font></span></p><p> </p><p /><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: "></span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: ">Merge onto I-66 E via the ramp to Washington</span></p><p /><p /