(332, '<p>This week\'s SH*Tty Jacka$$ of the week is Summer\'s Eve.</p><p>How does one become The SH*Tty Jack$$ of the week? By not giving the Hareraiser the trail directions a week in advance.</p><p>Now to be perfectly honest it is possible that a variety of things could have gone wrong. The internet could be down, the power may have been out for days, a beer could have been spilled into the keyboard or the Hareraiser &amp; Webmaster could be the guilty procrastinators. Like all good mis-managers we do not accept any of the blame or responsibility. </p><p>Ice the Hares!!</p><p>And remember, if you have to ask you don\'t know.</p><p> </p><p /><p />', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ">D-erections:</span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: "></span><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">From DC and Inside the Beltway</b></p><p /><p> Route 495 or 66 West to the Dulles Toll Road (267 West). Exit 11 for Fairfax County Parkway (Route 7100) North. (Right turn off the exit ramp to go North).<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Once you cross over Route 7, this road changes names to Algonkian Parkway. Continue 2.2 miles and make a LEFT into Great Falls Plaza. (directly across from Lowes Island Blvd.)</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Make a Right once in the plaza, and a left at the day care to continue around the back of the plaza. Look for wankers.</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" /><p>(Note:<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>If coming from Tysons Corner area, take Route 7 West and make a right onto Algonkian Pkwy North. Follow directions above.)</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" /><p> </p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">From Fairfax / Chantilly and South</b></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Fairfax 