(334, '<p>Because I know nothing about this week\'s trail, I\'ll have to focus on the hares.</p><p>First we have Fud Mucker (Fud). He was the RA at my very first Dayton Hash. The only advice that the pack gave me was... Don\'t follow Fud!!</p><p>Cop S Interuptus (CSI) - when he is around so are the police. My advice... Don\'t follow CSI!! </p><p>Davey Crotch Itch (Davey) - got lost laying his own trail or maybe it was the pack that got lost. Either way the pack did not see Davey for what seemed like hours. Again my advice: don\'t follow Davey!!</p><p>All The Way In - A tall mofo that can run like SH*T through a goose. I assume this FRB was recruited to do most of the work. My advice... don\'t even try to catch this guy because it\'s not going to happen. </p><p>Soft Serve Custer (Custer) - rescues people for a living. My advice... we keep Custer with the pack so that he can coordinate the rescue of the hares.</p><p>Bring flash light, compass, GPS, cell phone, CB radio and flippers. Wear long pants, multi layered synthetic clothing and a good luck charm because you are going to need them.</p><p>What is the difference between Sarah Palin\'s mouth &amp; her vagina?</p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ">From the east (via Capital Beltway/Woodrow Wilson Bridge S/ 1-95 S/I-495S/I-495 Innerloop). Exit at 177 B-A, take ramp for US-1 South/Richmond Highway toward Fort Belvoir. Arrive at 7690 Richmond Highway VA. </span></i></b></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: "></span></i></b><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: ">From the west (via Capital Beltway / I-95 E / I-495 N / I-495 Outerloop)</span></i></b></p><p />