(336, '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Not that we need a theme for each of our trails… so… sometimes it’s just a title!! So… perusing what significantly happened on this day… you may find that:</span></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><ul type="square"><li class="EC_MsoNormal" style="tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">In 1307, according to legend, William Tell shoots an apple off his son’s head!! Now… that’s significant… right?</span></li><li class="EC_MsoNormal" style="tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Or… maybe it’s because in 1918 </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Latvia</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> won it’s independence from </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Russia</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">!!</span></li><li class="EC_MsoNormal" style="tab-stops: list .5in"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Oh… I know… it’s because Jacques-Alexandre Laffon de Ladebat, a French shipbuilder and merchant, died on this day in 1797?</span></li></ul><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">No? Well… come out for a really sh*tty trail. We’ll fill you up with some real sh*tty beer… till the point that you could give a (crap) to what happened on this day!!</span></p>', '<p class="EC_ecmsonormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Metro</span></p><p class="EC_ecmsonormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span><strong><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Q: When will construction begin? When will the Metro open? </span></strong><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p class="EC_NormalWeb1"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">A: Construction on the first phase of the Metrorail will begin in March 2009. Phase 1 will branch off the Orange Line just beyond East Falls Church Station, goes through Tysons Corner (4 stops) to </span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Wiehle Avenue</span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> (1 stop) in </span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Reston</span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. It is scheduled to be completed by 2013. The project is currently in the middle of a major utility relocation program involving 21 different utilities along Route 7 between the </span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Dulles Toll Road</span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: windowtext; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> and Route 123.</span></p><p class="EC_ecmsonormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Driving</span></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Get yourself to the <b><i>Beltway (I-495)</i></b>. Take <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT 45</span></b> for the <b><i>Route 267, </i></b></span><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Dulles Toll Road</span></i></b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. As soon as you go through the main toll plaza… take the first <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT</span></b> for Route 7. On the ramp to Route 7… stay on your <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> and turn <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Route 7, East</i></b>. You will pass back over the </span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Dulles Toll Road</span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> and take your first <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT</span></b> onto </span><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Westwood Center Drive</span></i></b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Continue to the end of the cul-de-sac pull into the parking lot slightly on your <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b>. Look for wankers milling around for beer.</span></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Alternate direction from the <b><i>Beltway (I-495)</i></b>. Take <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT 47B-A</span></b> for the <b><i>Route 7, West</i></b>. Continue on Route 7 for approx. 2½ miles and turn <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Westwood Center Drive</i></b> (</span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Tyco Road</span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> will be on your right). Continue to the end of the cul-de-sac pull into the parking lot slightly on your <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b>. Look for wankers milling around for beer.</span></p>', '<p>O Malley’s Pubý (located behind the Marriott at Route 123 and International Drive) </p><p>1960 Chain Bridge Rd, Mclean, VA 22102-4001</p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "></span></p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!198"><font color="#0000ff">Trail 335</font></a></span></p>', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Live A to A’ trail. </span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">If you haven’t noticed yet… it’s DARK!! That would mean… BRING A FLASHLIGHT!! As usual, bring dry clothes and shoes and virgins (but the virgins can be ‘wet’)</span></p>', '<p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!198"><font color="#0000ff">Trail 335</font></a></span></p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ">8699 Westwood Center Dr, Vienna, VA 22182-2235</span></p>', ''),
(337, '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" />', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!203">Trail 336</a> </p>', '<p><font face="Arial">Runs With Bull\'s house, Falls Church, VA</font> </p><p>The hares will provide food at the on-after: burgers and accompaniment.</p>', '<p>Live A to A trail. <font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">You will get wet, you will get dirty, you will have fun. Remember your flash light and a change of cloths.</span></font></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!203">Trail 336</a></p><p>Kirby Park Baseball Field</p><p>1898 Westmoreland St, McLean, VA </p>', ''),
(338, '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">We haven’t run one of these in a while so we are going to give it a shot and see how bad we can mess it up. Here is the concept: there is no hares at the start of the trail. Someone is randomly selected to start and is handed the bag of flour and is given a 5 minute (maybe) head start. This person can lay trail where ever they see fit. This person will get snared. At that point the flour is handed off to the next random person and they are given a 2 minute head start. This continues for however long we decide to run for. There is a end destination so the hare razor will be gently guiding people in that direction if we get too far away. It is a fun time and can be a real rush for people who don’t hare all too often. So come on out and give it a shot. </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">There will be a separate walkers trail……</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p>', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">From the Dulles area<br />Take Rt 28 (Sully Rd) north to Rt 7 (Leesburg Pike), east on Rt 7 past Dulles Towne Center and Cascades Parkway 1mile, right onto Bartholomew Fair Dr, then 1st right into Potomac Run Plaza.<br /><br />From Leesburg<br />Go east on Rt 7 past Dulles Towne Center and Cascades Pkwy 1 mile, make a right onto Bartholomew Fair Dr, then 1st right into Potomac Run Plaza.</span></font></p>', '<p>Don Pablos Restaurant</p><p>46280 Potomac Run Plaza</p><p>Sterling, VA 20164</p><p>703-421-9524</p>', 'The pack tends to run a little faster on Pick-Up trails which means you need to pay more attention to the kinds of clothing that you are wearing. I prefer high tech synthetics for the under layer and at least a wind proof outer layer. Be sure to bring a head lamp and it might be smart if you print a map of the area just incase you have trouble finding the end circle. ', '<p align="left"><table class="EC_MsoNormalTable" style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" border="0"><tbody><tr><td style="PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; PADDING-TOP: 0in"><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "Times New Roman","serif"; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!207">Trail 337</a></span></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">46301 Potomac Run Plaza<br />Sterling, VA 20164</span></font></p></td></tr></tbody></table></p>', ''),
(339, '', '<p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!211"><font color="#0000ff">Trail 338</font></a></span></p>', '<span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><div class="bizAddr"><span id="ctl00_PageContent_lvInArea_ctrl0_Listing5_lblAddress">Blue Iguana</span></div><div class="bizAddr"><span>12727 Shoppes Lane<span class="addressSpacer">, </span><br />Fairfax, VA 22033-3834</span> </div><div class="bizPhone"><div class="call"><a title="Click to call: Local Phone Number" onclick="function anonymous()\r\n{\r\nreturn GB_c2c(\'\', this.href);\r\n}" href="http://www.yellowbook.com/clicktocall/call.aspx?listingId=1820964839&addressId=1&phoneType=Local"><font color="#0066cc">703-502-9877</font></a><br /><br /></div></div></span><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!211"><font color="#0000ff">Trail 338</font></a></span></p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "></span></p>', 'Live A to A trail. Bring extra warm cloths, flash light and a festive spirit.<br />', '<p>Fairfax Government Center </p><p>12000 Government Center Pkwy</p><p>Fairfax, VA 22030<br /></p><p>Start is in the front parking lot of the Fx government center near the parked school buses.</p>', '');
INSERT INTO `shit_directions` (`TRL_ID`, `TIDBIT`, `DIRECTIONS`, `ONONON`, `NOTES`, `ADDRESS`, `MAPLINK`) VALUES
(340, '<p /><p />', '<p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">From the east: Get to I-66 west. Take I-66 west to exit 53B (Rt.-28/ Sully Rd. north). Merge onto 28 north. After about 1.7 miles get on the ramp for the exit to Westfields Blvd. Take the first exit on the ramp to get on Westfields Blvd. headed west. As soon as you are on Westfields, get left immediately. Make a left at the intersection of Westfields and Park Meadow Dr. towards the construction site. Turn right into the small parking lot just off of Westfields.<br /><br />From Herndon/ Reston: Make your way to Rt-28 south. Take 28 south to the exit for Westfields Blvd. headed west. As soon as you are on Westfields, get left immediately. Make a left at the intersection of Westfields and Park Meadow Dr. towards the construction site. Turn right into the small parking lot just off of Westfields.<br /><br />From the south: Make your way to 28 north. About 2 miles north of I-66 get on the ramp for the exit to Westfields Blvd. Take the first exit on the ramp to get on Westfields Blvd. headed west. As soon as you are on Westfields, get left immediately. Make a left at the intersection of Westfields and Park Meadow Dr. towards the construction site. Turn right into the small parking lot just off of Westfields.</span></p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span></p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span></p><p><br /></p>', '<p><span class="EC_locationlist"><font face="Arial"><span id="EC_chantillydetails">Bungalow Billiards</span></font></span></p><p><span class="EC_locationlist"><font face="Arial"><span>13891 Metrotech Drive</span><span class="EC_locationlist"> </span><br /><span class="EC_locationlist">Chantilly</span><span class="EC_locationlist">, Virginia 20151</span><span class="EC_locationlist"> </span><br /><span class="EC_locationlist">Phone: 703-502-3925</span></font></span><span class="EC_locationlist"><font face="Arial"><span class="EC_locationlist"></span></font></span></p>', '', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!215">Trail 339</a> <span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Chek out the Aerial view. The destination parking lot is very obvious. </span></span></p><p />', ''),
(341, '<p>OTH (deep Southern NOVA hash) has givrn the SH*T a wonderful Christmas present! A present you say. What useful thing could one hash give another...You gessed it OTH is giving us their left over kegs. In typical OTH fashion the beer is of high quality but I can\'t remember what kind?</p><p>Good luck &amp; have a Merry Christmas </p>', 'Take 123 North or South from whatever way you have to get there.  Use the address above if you have a GPS.  Head towards George Mason University, that would be north/west from 95, east/south from 66.  If you are coming from 95, up 123, look for the Sikh Temple, on the left, the shopping center will be just past the temple on the right side.  Make the turn, as if you were going to Giant, go right around the back side of the building.  Look for arrows and the pack.<div><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font size="3" face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">From 66 directions:  At the intersection of 123 and Braddock, either continue on Braddock and make your first right into the shopping center, or make your first left off Rte. 123 into the Giant parking area.  Following the building down and around the back.  Look for the wankers.</span></font></p></div><div><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font size="3" face="Times New Roman"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Clue:  The start will be near the Fat Tuesday\'s Bar.</span></font></p></div>', '<p>Fat Tuesdays\'s Bar</p><p>10673 Braddock Road, </p><p>Fairfax, VA 22032</p>', 'Live A to B trail. It might be really F\'n cold. Don\'t forget your shorts and sun screen.', '<p><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!219">Trail 340</a></p><p>University Shopping Center, Intersection of Braddock Road and Rte. 123 (near GMU)</p>', ''),
(342, '<div><div>Happy Holidaze you wankers!! Firstly we would like to thank the half minds from OTH3 for bringing delicious hot food and tasty kegs to last weeks SH*Tty Christmas trail. </div><div> </div><div></div><div></div><div>Enough sap now onto this weeks hashtertainment...</div><div> </div><div></div><div></div><div>We\'ve selected yummy seasonal shots -- one to represent each season --  to get you reminiscing about years\' past and the upcumming year.  Please be advised that this is not for you overachieving runners ... trail will be for shot-worthy walkers only!  (But overachieving runners who choose to walk are welcome.)  Yes, this means that there will not be a runners trail but we\'ve got you walking though the hills (and shiggy!) of Wakefield Park.<br /></div></div><div> </div>', 'Get yourself to the Braddock Road exit off 495 (between Annandale and Springfield).  Enter Wakefield Park at the intersection of Braddock Road &amp; Wakefield Park Road.  (note: Wakefield Park Road is not well advertised.  The road splits at Braddock so one half is Wakefield Park Road and the other part is Queensberry Avenue).  Once you\'re in the park, go about 1/4 mile (or where the paved road ends).  You\'ll see the RECenter on the left ... so turn left and then go as far right as you can.  Wankers should meet at the far right part of the parking lot.', '<p>Kilroy\'s</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!223">Trail 341</a></p><p />', '<p>Nice &amp; relaxing shot &amp; shiggy filled walking trail. Where warm cloths and don\'t forget your flash light. </p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!223">Trail 341</a></p><p /><p>Wakefield Park\'s Audrey Moore RECenter </p><p />', ''),
(343, '<p> Happy Birthday F*ck you Udder &amp; Nuclear!! </p><p>Actually it is more of a f*ck you Little C*ck That Won\'t. You see Little C was bragging about running his first two 5K\'s within a week of each other at just under a 7 minutes/mile pace. Unfortunitely for Little C he was bragging to this weeks hares who really wanted to focus more on their birthdays than running... So they signed him up.  Of course that was before they realized that he is practically a virgin hare (only hared once over three years ago)</p><p>In all seriousness Udder is one of the most experienced SH*Tty hares, Nuclear is an overly maticulous detail oriented super geek, and at least in his mind Little C is one fast SH*Tter.   </p><p>Cum out and help us snare two virgin hares Just Jolie and Just Little C*ck That Won\'t.</p>', 'from the east:<br />Take 267 W to 28N<br />Go West on 606<br />Make a right on Moran Rd<br />You\'ll see the lot on your left<br />Park and look for wankers<br /><br />Cheapskate directions from the east:<br />Take route 7 W to 28 S<br />Go West on 606<br />Make a right on Moran Rd<br />You\'ll see the lot on your left<br /> Park and look for wankers<br /><br />Directions from the south:<br />Take 28 N<br />Go West on 606<br />Make a right on Moran Rd<br />You\'ll see the lot on your left<br />Park and look for wankers<br /><br />Directions from the west:<br />Take 7 E to 28 S<br />Go West on 606<br />Make a right on Moran Rd<br />You\'ll see the lot on your left<br /> Park and look for wankers<br /><br />Alternative directions from the west:<br />Take 50 E to 28 S<br />Go West on 606<br />Make a right on Moran Rd<br />You\'ll see the lot on your left<br />Park and look for wankers<br /><br />', '', 'Live A to A trail. Cold? probably, Rain? maybe, Dark? absolutely. Bring flashlights, something warm to change into and what ever undrinkable beers in your fridge that you can\'t bring yourself to throw out... We have birthdays to toast.', '<p>Start is at the commuter lot on 606 in Sterling, VA. The intersection of Lockridge &amp; Moran Rd.</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!235"><font color="#0000ff">Trail 342</font></a></p>', ''),
(344, '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><font face="Calibri">Now listen you half-minds there is no reason to be concerned that Dixie is haring this week. He promised there will be no swimming on trail and Cock Spur assures me there will be no hockey. <span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </span>I didn’t bother to ask Free P*ssy or Socket what they have planned because they are woman and lord knows you can’t trust woman. If I were a gambling man I’d bet that we should have some concerns about Sock &amp; Free P*ssy. It is well known that Socket is a racist and this could be a training run to make sure she is ready for the year’s first half-marathon. Free P*ssy has spent the past few months doing god knows who (have you seen her?) so I’m sure she is ready to get her hash on. I suggest we all start carbo loading early.  I know I am!!</font></p><p />', '<div>From the East </div><div> </div><div>Dulles Toll Road West to Fairfax County Parkway. <br />Left at Toll Road exit to head South on Parkway.<br />Right onto Sunrise Valley Drive<br />Right into Park-and-Ride<br />Right into uncovered parking lot (NOT the parking garage)<br />Look for wankers in the south-east corner of the lot.</div><div> </div><div>From the West</div><div> </div><div>Dulles Toll Road East to Fairfax County Parkway. <br />Right at Toll Road exit to head South on Parkway.<br />Right onto Sunrise Valley Drive<br />Right on Roark into Park-and-Ride<br />Right into uncovered parking lot (NOT the parking garage)<br />Look for wankers in the south-east corner of the lot.</div><div> </div><div>From the South</div><div> </div><div>Fairfax County Parkway North <br />Left onto Sunrise Valley Drive<br />Right into Park-and-Ride<br />Right into uncovered parking lot (NOT the parking garage)<br />Look for wankers in the south-east corner of the lot.</div><div> </div><div>From the North</div><div> </div><div>Fairfax County Parkway South <br />Right onto Sunrise Valley Drive<br />Right into Park-and-Ride<br />Right into uncovered parking lot (NOT the parking garage)<br />Look for wankers in the south-east corner of the lot.</div>', '<p>Chili\'s, 11840 Sunrise Valley Dr Reston, VA 20191-3326 </p><div>Make a left out of park-and-ride. Drive East on Sunrise Valley Drive for about 2 miles. Chili\'s is on the left.</div>', 'Live A to A Trail. Temperatures could be in the mid to upper 80\'s. Bring sunscreen, bug spray,&amp; ivy block but unexpected things could happen... like normal January weather!! Dry shoes and a heavey Winter coat for circle might be a good idea. ', '<p>Herndon-Monroe Park-and-Ride </p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!238">Trail 343</a></span></p>', ''),
(345, '', 'From DC: Ha!<br />From Metro: Ha Ha!<br />From the Beltway:Not as funny but if you\' re able to make it to the toll road take it to route 28 and head toward Sterling.  Take the first exit to Ox Road and bear right.  Follow Old Ox to Herndon Parkway and take a left at the light.  Take a left at the next light onto Crestview road and take a right into the Trailside Park parking lot. Look for the usual cast of misfits and Hash, but be sure to park first.<br /><br />From Sterling: Drive down the road take a left and park.<br />From Herndon: Cross Herndon Parkway and revers the Sterling directions<br /><br />', '', '', '<span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "Times New Roman","serif"; mso-fareast-font-family: "Times New Roman"; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!243">Trail 344</a></span>', ''),
(346, 'You have to ask yourself if Porn is up to his old tricks or has he come up with something new. Porn has recruited a veteran crew of hares to do his bidding. Again you have to ask yourself if this is a good thing! It\'s going to be cold, dark and maybe wet but Porn has arranged to have circle indoors &amp; promises to have his world famous chili to warm your hash worthy soles. ', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">From DC/Arlington: </span></u></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Take 395 South to Exit 1B Franconia/Rt 644/Springfield exit and stay left to exit 169A for Va 644 - Franconia Rd/Franconia.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Follow Franconia Rd for approximately 2 miles and turn right onto Villa St (last turn before you hit Van Dorn Street). Look for wankers, park and hash.</span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><br /><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><u>From Lorton/Woodbridge: </u></b></span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Take 95 North to Exit 169A toward Rt 644 East Franconia Rd.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>At the traffic light at the end of the exit ramp turn left onto Loisdale Rd.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Turn right at the next intersection onto Franconia Rd and follow it for approximately 2 miles.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Turn right onto Villa St (last turn before Van Dorn Street) look for wankers, park and hash.</span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">From Herndon/Tysons Corner: </span></u></b></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Take 495 South to Exit 173 – Van Dorn Street/ Rt 613 toward Franconia.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>At the traffic light at the end of the exit ramp turn right onto Van Dorn Street.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Turn right at onto Franconia Rd/Rt 644.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span>Make immediate left onto Villa Street, look for wankers, park and hash.</span></p><p /><p />', 'TBD', 'Live Trail. It\'s still January! plan a head... bring flashlight, warm cloths for circle and a commerative Obama dollar.  Additional Notes:  there will be chili provided again this week and POSSIBLY some type of non-vegetarian offering to be sacrificed to Gispert and the Hash Gods on the grill.', '<p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: "><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">The start is across the street from The <span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA">Latter Day Saints Church at </span>6219 Villa St, Alexandria, VA 22310</span></span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: "><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"></span></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!248"><font color="#0000ff">Trail 345</font></a></span></p><p />', ''),
(347, '<p>It\'s a Crotch Itch trail, and he\'s hoping that by this time he has a reputation for having shiggtastic runner trails, pedestrian walker trails, and lots of good alcohol.</p><p>Davy being of sound mind and afraid of Poon has planned for two different trails. One for good weather &amp; one if it\'s SH*Tty<br /> <br /></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!259"><font color="#0000ff">Trail 346</font></a></p>', '<p>Is dependent on the weather &amp; will be announced at ther beginning of trail.</p>', 'Live trail. Bring a dry bag, flash light and pray to the weather gods that we get a descent night to hash.', '<p>13894 Redskin Drive<br />Herndon, VA</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!259"><font color="#0000ff">Trail 346</font></a></p><p><br /></p>', ''),
