(351, 'Okay so it is not quite Spring yet but the temp is just barely below freezing... Perfect for an e<span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: ">xhilarating</span> run. The hares have gone to a great deal of trouble covering the ground with sparkling white stuff &amp; the RA has arranged for clear skies. It\'s going to be a great night to hash!! ', '<p>From the Dulles Toll Road or I-66:</p><p>North onto Route 28 (Shaw Rd)</p><p>Right onto Sout Sterling Blvd. (Route 846)</p><p>Left onto Sliverbrook Center Dr. Siliverbrook Dr. may not appear on some maps.</p><p>Take second right and look for wankers.</p><p>Silverbrook Dr. is the next street past Terminal Dr. Silverbrook drive is brand new (shows up on google earth); its only about a 100 yards long; there are 3 brand new buildings along silverbrook on the right hand side; we\'ll circle up between the last two buildings</p>', 'TBA', 'Live A to A\' trail. Don\'t forget your flashlight &amp; warm stuff for circle.', '<p><font face="Arial">Google: 510 Shaw Road Sterling, VA</font></p><p><strong><font face="Arial"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&tab=wl">http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&amp;tab=wl</a></font></strong></p><font face="Arial"><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: ">MSN maps:Terminal Dr &amp; Shaw Rd Sterling, VA</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!292"><font face="Times New Roman">Trail 350</font></a></span></p><p /></font>', ''),
(352, '<p>From the lead hare Spike...</p><p><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><font color="#000000">I don’t think you will have any problem with the right training.  What else is needed?</font> </font></p><p><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="2">Don\'t know what that means either.</font></p>', '<p><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!314">Trail 351</a></p><p />', '<span class="Title">Blue Iguana Restaurant &amp; Bar</span><br /><b>Fair Lakes<br />12727 Shoppes Lane<br />Fairfax, VA 22033</b><br />', 'Live A to B trail. Bring a flash light &amp; try to stay out of the water. It\'s not warm enough for a swim!! ', '<p><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2">Dicks Sporting Goods</font></p><p><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2">12501 Fair Lakes Cir, Fairfax, VA 22033-3803</font></p>', ''),
(353, '<p>With the exception of our virgins most SH*Tters have slept with at least one person of Irish Descent!!</p><p>Because of this unique phenomena, we the SH*T, have decided to schedule Saint Patty\'s Day on a Tuesday.</p><p>To help the hashing world celebrate this special SH*T day And How\'s Her Bush has agreed to let us party at his place in warm and cheerful Vienna. Please be respectful of the neighbors and property.</p><p>The hares will be laying live A to A runner\'s and walker\'s trails. Expect some shiggy but the main focus for of the evening is to show the Irish how to drink.</p><p>Bring your id on trail... there may be a special beer check on trail.</p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!319">Trail 352</a></span></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">From the Beltway…<br /></span></b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Get yourself to the <b><i>Beltway (I-495)</i></b>. Take <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT 47B-A</span></b> for the <b><i>Route 7, Leesburg Pike, West</i></b>. Continue on Route 7, Leesburg Pike, West through Tysons Corner and take the <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT</span></b> for <b><i>Route 123, </i></b></span><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Chain Bridge Road</span></i></b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> south</span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> toward </span><span style="COLOR: red"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Vienna</span></span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Continue on Route 123, </span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Chain Bridge Road</span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">&nbsp;</span><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">(which turns into </span></i></b><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Maple Avenue</span></i></b><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">)</span></i></b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> and take a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Park Street</i></b>. Go to the first stop sign and turn <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Monroe Avenue</i></b>. Go to the first stop sign and turn <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT</span></b> onto </span><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Ninovan Road</span></i></b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> then take your first <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Fellini Court</i></b>. My house will be the one directly at the end of the court. If you drive into my living room, you’ve gone too far. Back up and park in the cul-de-sac!!</span></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Otherwise… if you’re cumming from the North:</span></b></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">You can take <b><i>Route 66, West</i></b> towards <span style="COLOR: red">Front Royal</span>. Take the <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT</span></b> for </span><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Nutley Street</span></i></b><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">…</span></i></b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> (first exit outside of the beltway) and take a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT </span></b>onto </span><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Nutley Street</span></i></b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Take a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT </span></b>at the second light onto </span><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Tapawingo Road</span></i></b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Continue on </span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Tapawingo Road</span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> for appox. </span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">1.4 miles</span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. You will go through five or six stop signs… the last being at the intersection with </span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Park Street</span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Continue on </span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Tapawingo Road</span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> and take a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto </span><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Ninovan Road</span></i></b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> and then your first <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT</span></b> onto <b><i>Fellini Court</i></b>. My house will be the one directly at the end of the court. If you drive into my living room, you’ve gone too far. Back up and park in the cul-de-sac!!</span></p>', '', 'Live A to A trail. If you want we can lock your hash bag in a random virgin\'s car &amp; then loose said virgin on trail.', 'And How\'s Her Bush\'s house... I mean No Name Nyet\'s house <br />410 Fellini Ct SE, Vienna, VA 22180-5827', ''),
(354, '<p>Some may say that it seems like just yesterday when we hashed this SH*T. Others can\'t remember what they had for lunch. Perhaps the hares noticed unrealized hashing potential in the area or maybe this week\'s Justs just think they are better hares. Who knows and who really cares.</p><p>Winter is officially over so anything goes!! </p>', '<span style="mso-fareast-font-family: "><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><font color="#0000ff"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Technical">Address: 4401 Fair Lakes Ct, Fairfax VA 22033<br /><br />East or West: 66 to exit 55, take 7100 North and make the first available right onto Fair Lakes Pkwy. Make a left at the light onto Fair Lakes Ct. First available right into 4401 and park at the rear left portion of the parking lot.<br /><br />North: 7100 South and make a left onto Fair Lakes Pkwy. Make a left at the light onto Fair Lakes Ct. First available right into 4401 and park at the rear left portion of the parking lot.<br /><br />South: 95 to 123 North then 7100 North. Make a left at the light onto Fair Lakes Ct. First available right into 4401 and park at the rear left portion of the parking lot.<br /><br />Backup parking lot will be Dick\'s sporting goods, for a worse case scenario (cops, bears, etc.).</span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><font color="#0000ff"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Technical"></span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><font color="#0000ff"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: Technical"><font color="#660000"><span style="COLOR: #660000"></span></font></span></font></p></span>', '<p>TGI Friday\'s </p><p>12249 Fair Lakes Promenade Dr<br />Fairfax VA 22033 </p>', 'Live A to B trail. The hares are pretty hardcore. I\'d bring a pillow and someone comfortable to sleep on... you are going to need a nap after this trail. Flash light, ivy block, bug spray and a change of clothes might be a good idea.', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!336"><font color="#0000ff">Trail 353</font></a></p><p>Parking lot at 4401 Fair Lakes Ct, Fairfax VA 22033</p>', '');
INSERT INTO `shit_directions` (`TRL_ID`, `TIDBIT`, `DIRECTIONS`, `ONONON`, `NOTES`, `ADDRESS`, `MAPLINK`) VALUES
(355, '<p>Ok, it\'s April first, well; it will be at midnight damn it! You know what that means! Nobody is safe from the twisted minds of the hares, including the hares themselves. We all saw what some unsuspecting wankers had happen to them in the past right? Tunnels galore, mud, pricker bushes that just won\'t quit! Hell, we even had 3.2 wankers swear that they would never again do a SH*T trail after last years foolish trail. So come on out but be on your toes or you could find yourself sitting in a bar all by yourself with eight pitchers of beer in front of you telling the bartender that &quot;no, really, there are 40 people right behind me!&quot;</p>', '<p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "Times New Roman","serif"; mso-fareast-font-family: "Times New Roman"; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!340">Trail 354</a></span></p>', '<p>The Pub</p><p>6827 Redmond D.</p><p>Mclean, VA 22101</p><p>Hey Normy, little known fact... The Pub serves really good Chinese food</p>', 'Flashlights and a change of cloths are very necessary unless you plan to be naked at circle. It is Spring time and that means mud, mud and more mud. Please be prepared to fully change your clothes after trail. This goes for walkers as well. You will be getting dirty Sally boys &amp; sissies should stay home.', '<p>Office parking lot at:</p><p>7601 Lewinsville Rd.</p><p>Mclean, VA 22102</p>', ''),
(356, '<p>The SH*T will be following another one of our sh*tty traditions by bouncing our way through warm and cheerful Herdon on this SoHappy Easter. Trail could be short, flat and dry but I wouldn\'t count on it.</p><p>This could be a very special day for the SH*T... Moroccan Mole might actually have to run on trail!</p><p>Mole claims to have been in the Marines, claims to have run multiple marathons and claims to wear women\'s clothing on landry day but has anyone ever seen him run? Personally I\'ve never even seen Mole do a slow jog.</p><p>Cum out to see history in the making.</p><p /><p />', 'From the Dulles toll road get onto Fairfax County Parkway(7100) heading towards Herndon/Reston.  Take the right exit to Herndon/Reston and take a left turn onto Elden Street.  Go through 5-7 lights (watch your speed) and take a right onto Station Street (Jimmy\'s Tavern will be on your left).  Park in the lot on your left.  Start will be at the red caboose on the hill.', 'TBA', 'Live A to B trail. Bring flash light, Ivy block, bug spray, $5, change of clothes and a small but tastefully expensive gift for the webmaster.', '<p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!344">Trail 355</a></span></p><p>The little red caboose near the Herndon Town hall.</p><p>Near the Intersection of Elden &amp; Station St.</p><p>Herndon, VA</p><p><br /></p>', ''),
(357, '<p>Porn has agreed to the one condition that has been imposed on his trail this week...</p><p>The trail will be live!!</p><p>Bring bug spray (tics &amp; chiggers, oh my), Ivy Block &amp; whatever poison ivy preventer you might have, flash light, change of clothes, $5 and a pissy attitude. </p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!347">Trail 356</a></span></p><p />', '<p>Hard Times Cafe <br />6362 Springfield Plz, <br />Springfield, VA 22150-3431</p>', 'Live A to A\' trail.', '<p>Backlick VRE</p><p>6900 Hechinger Drive, Springfield, Virginia 22151</p><p>Parking is free</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!347">Trail 356</a></span></p>', ''),
(358, '<p />', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal" style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12pt"><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="1"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">The Nottoway park may be reached by taking Beltway Exit 49 (Route 66) west to exit at Route 243 or Nutley Street north. Turn left on Courthouse Road from Nutley Street and the park entrance will be on the left.</span></font></p>', '<font face="Arial">Glory Days<br />3059 Nutley Street<br />Fairfax, VA 22031</font>', '<p><font face="Arial">Live A-A\' trail with all the trappings of a B$/Fire trail, hills, water, mud, posion ivy, barking spiders, rabid midgets, you know, the works. </font><font face="Arial">Bring a flashlight and a change of cloths as usual and remember, a warm beer is better than no beer.</font> </p>', '<span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt"><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!354"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Trail 357</font></a></span></p><p /><p>NOTTOWAY <span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">PARK</span><font face="Arial" color="#000000" size="1"><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font><font face="Verdana" color="#444444" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #444444; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"></span></font><font size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt"> </span></font> </p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Verdana" color="#444444" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: #444444; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana"> </span></font>9601 Courthouse Road</p><p><font size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt"></span></font><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Fairfax</span></font>, VA 22181</p></span></span>', ''),
(359, '<p>Look at the map! Click on Aerial view. I know you can only see trees, trees and more trees.</p><p>If I was you I would expect to be running through the woods.</p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!359">Trail 358</a></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: "></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: "></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: ">Details from Davey Jock Itch:</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: "></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: ">From the East and or West: <br />  <br />Get your a$$ to I 66 – take in the proper direction (east if you’re coming from the west, west if you’re coming from the east)  and head for EXIT 53 – ROUTE 28 NORTH. <br />  <br />Has confuZed?  Just wait…. <br />  <br />At your FIRST LIGHT on 28, make a RIGHT onto WALNEY ROAD.  Look for parking and wankers on your left near the pond. <br />  <br />From the South: <br />  <br />Get your a$$ to RT 28 North, as you cross RT 29 in Centreville, pay attention.  After crossing I-66, make RIGHT onto WALNEY ROAD.  Look for parking and wankers on your left near the pond. <br />  <br />From the North: <br />  <br />You’re screwed.  Take 28 South past the light at Braddock/Walney Road.  You CANNOT make a left there, so don’t try. <br />  <br />Continue SOUTH on 28, exit at RT 29 EAST to FAIRFAX – stay in exit lane over RT 28, and continue to exit onto 28 NORTH.  After crossing I-66, make RIGHT onto WALNEY ROAD.  Look for parking and wankers on your left near the pond. <br /></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: "></span></p><p />', 'TBD', 'Live A to A trail. High chance of mud, stickers, PI and flowing water. Don\'t forget your flashlights. It gets darker earlier in the woods.', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!359">Trail 358</a></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: "></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: ">Ellanor C Lawrence Park <br />5040 Walney Road (not exact address)<br />Chantilly, VA 20151 </span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="mso-fareast-font-family: "></span></p><p />', ''),
(360, '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><font color="#ff0000" size="7">It\'s Cinco de Mayo!!!</font>  </font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif" color="#0000cc" size="7">And Lube\'s birthday!  Whoo-hoooo!!!!!</font></p><p align="center"><img hspace="0" src="http://i234.photobucket.com/albums/ee85/JackedUpOnDew/Happy%20Birthday/beer_candles.jpg" align="baseline" border="0" /></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">What does that mean?  It means Tequila for everyone!  And by Tequila I mean Sparks, and by everyone I mean me!  Hurray!  </font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Yes, this is a birthday/Cinco de Mayo trail, but don\'t forget your standard hash accoutrements: dry shoes, change of clothes, bug spray, ivy block, whistle, personal flotation device, Sawzall, N95 mask, Sparks, oragami, Spanish-English dictionary, pygmy goat and extra toilet paper.</font></p>', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">From the North: Use the link above</font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">From the South: Use the link above</font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">From the East: Use the link above</font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">From the West: Use the link above</font></p>', '<font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Cowboy Café: <span class="EC_EC_street-address1"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">4792 Lee Hwy</span></span><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">, </span><span class="EC_EC_street-address1"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Arlington</span></span><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">, </span><span class="EC_EC_street-address1"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">VA</span></span></font>', 'Live trail lead by alzheimer afflicted half minds. Please don\'t be offended if the hares introduce themselves. They probably don\'t remember any of you. In fact, it will be just luck if they remember that they are the hares this week', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">2840 Marcey Road,  Arlington, VA</font> 22207  (Drive in as far as you can go and park near the picnic pavilion.  Park on the street if the parking lot is full.  Do not park in the first parking lot just inside the park - it is a private lot.)</p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "Times New Roman","serif"; mso-fareast-font-family: "Times New Roman"; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!362">Trail 359</a></span></p><p />', ''),
(361, '<p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">You know… sometimes you just have to say, “What the F***!!” So… “What the F***!!” as in… “F U AHHB” See how ‘fun’ that word is!?! Be sure to give the birthday boy a warm F U!!</span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">So… we’re going back to our roots!! That’s right (“KP”) suck it up and cum on out to </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Sterling</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">“… why? Because… ‘big kids drive’!!</span></p>', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font size="3"><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Metro…<br /></span></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Yea… like some time in 2013!!</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3"> </font></span></b></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3">Driving:</font></span></b></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font size="3"><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">From ALL points EAST of </span></b><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Sterling</span></b><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">!! </span></b></font><b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">(after all… it’s NOT like we have any more ‘Dirty </span></b><b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Sterling</span></b><b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> Girls’!!)</span></b><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3">…<br /><br /></font></span></b></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font size="3"><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">From the Beltway…<br /></span></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Get yourself to the <b><i>Beltway (I-495)</i></b>. Take <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT 45</span></b> for the </span><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Dulles Toll Road</span></i></b><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">, Route 267, West</span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3"> </font></span></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3">Option One…</font></span></b></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3">Go through the main toll plaza </font></span><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">(a $ .75 pre-hash contribution)</span></i></b><font size="3"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> and continue on the </span><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Dulles Toll Road</span></i></b><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">, Route 267, West</span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> to <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT 9B</span></b> </span></font><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">(another $ .50 pre-hash contribution)</span></i></b><font size="3"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> for <b><i>Route 28, </i></b></span><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Sully Road, North</span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Continue on Route 28, </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Sully Road</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> for approx. 4½ miles and take a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT</span></b> onto </span><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Severn Way</span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Take a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto </span><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Atlantic Boulevard</span></i></b><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">and then a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT</span></b> into the shopping center at <b><i>Dulles Eastern Plaza</i></b>. Start will be on your <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> in front of the now defunct “Scan Furniture Store”. Park and look for wankers doing 16oz curls.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3"> </font></span></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3">Option Two…</font></span></b></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3">Go through the main toll plaza </font></span><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">(a $ .75 pre-hash contribution)</span></i></b><font size="3"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> and take the FIRST <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT</span></b> for <b><i>Route 7, West</i></b>. At the end of the ramp… take a right on Route 7, West and continue for approx. 10½ miles. Take the <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT</span></b> onto <b><i>Cascades Parkway</i></b>, toward </span><span style="COLOR: red"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Sterling</span></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> and make a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT </span></b>onto <b><i>Nokes Boulevard</i></b>. Take a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT </span></b>onto </span><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">City Center Boulevard</span></i></b><b><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">…</span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> and continue onto <b><i>Dulles Eastern Plaza</i></b>.<span>  </span>Start will be on your <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT</span></b> in front of the now defunct “Scan Furniture Store”. Park and look for wankers doing 16oz curls.</span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><font size="3"> </font></span></p>', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal" style="BACKGROUND: #e5e3df"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font size="3"></font></span></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal" style="BACKGROUND: #e5e3df"><font size="3"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal" style="BACKGROUND: #e5e3df"><font size="3"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal" style="BACKGROUND: #e5e3df"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font size="3"></font></span></p><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><div><font size="4">Red Robin Gourmet Burgers</font></div><div><font size="3"></font> </div><div><span> <span dir="ltr">21045 Dulles Town Cir</span><a style="TEXT-DECORATION: underline" target="_blank"><span></span></a><div><span dir="ltr">Sterling, VA 20166</span></div><div><span dir="ltr">703.421.0038</span></div></span></div></span>', 'Live Trail! PI, stickers, mud and water is highly likely. Flash lights are still a good idea. If you haven\'t gotten AHHB a birthday present yet... bright colored thongs are always well received.', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!374"><font color="#0000ff">Trail 360</font></a></p><strong>45633 Dulles Eastern Plaza, Sterling, VA 20166<span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></strong>', ''),
(362, '', '<span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!379">Trail 361</a></span>', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal">Glory Days Grill</p><p class="EC_MsoNormal">13850 Braddock Rd</p><p class="EC_MsoNormal">Centreville, VA 20121</p><p class="EC_MsoNormal">(703) 266-4100</p>', 'Live trail! Plan for anything that naturally occurs in NOVA. Please permit me to list them for those of you with below average intelligence:  Wild Dogs, Faro Cats, Ravenous Deer, Coyotes, Eastern Timber Wolves, Badgers, Bears, Bobcats, Mountain Lions, Snakes, Chiggers, Tall Grass, Sticker Bushes, <span style="mso-spacerun: yes"> </span>Poison Ivy, Mud, Water, Rocks and there might even be Tics on trail. And a special note… the sun will be setting while you are still on trail.<p />', '<p>The Centreville commuter lot at the intersection of Rt 29 (Lee Hwy) and Stone Rd. </p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!379">Trail 361</a></span> </p><p />', ''),
(363, '<p>Air Spanker One has out done himself this week by finding what could be the coolest hash friendly bar in Mclean. I know the only competition in Mclean is the Pub but you have to give the half-mind credit for finding a place that has chics, wings, and karaoke on a Tuesday.</p><p>Pre-gamming will start at 4 PM with half price wings &amp; drink specials. As always the chics are going to cost you. Happy Hour ends and trail starts at 7PM</p><p>Now about the trail... be sure to use cups at the start!</p><p />', 'From Sterling:  Take the Dulles Toll Road or Rte. 7 East Towards Tyson\'s Corner.  <font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"> </span></font><div><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Toll Road Riders:  Get off at the Spring Hill Road Exit and go north on Spring Hill Road (take a left to go under the toll road).  Spring Hill Road splits into Lewinsville Road, so stay right at the split.</span></font></p></div><div><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Rte. 7 Cheapskates:  At the intersection of Rte. 7 and Lewinsville Road, take a left onto Lewinsville and follow that to the park.  The parking lot we will use is located just off the road, Do Not Use the actual Rec Center Lot.</span></font></p></div><div><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Directions from Southish:</span></font></p></div><div><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Get on the Inner Loop (495 towards Tysons Corner) and get off at Rte. 123, away from Tysons (east I believe).  Once you cross under the Toll Road (just past Anderson Rd.) Get into the Far left set of turning lanes.  Make the left onto Lewinsville Road.  Follow Lewinsville until you hit the park on your right.</span></font></p></div>', '<p>Chics and Wings </p><p>8119 Watson Street, </p><p>Mclean, VA 22102</p>', '<p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt">Live Trail. If you don\'t have a trust fund you probably shouldn\'t be here.</span></p>', '<p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!391">Trail 362</a></span></p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "></span>Spring Hill District Park, </p><p>8108 Lewinsville, Rd, </p><p>McLean, Va </p>', ''),
(364, '<p>CornHole has been wanting to hare this trail ever since he nailed his first harriette. His mother was so proud... she thought her son was gay. But I digress. This is going to be a classic SH*T trail. Runner\'s trail is only 3.8 miles with almost no pavement. There will be a walker\'s trail but CornHole was so excited when describing the trail he talked way to much &amp; honestly the only thing I heard was blah blah blah!!</p><p>In celebration of such a potentially classic trail the SH*T Mis-Management will be kicking in few bucks for pizza at the OnOnOn. </p>', '<font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!400">Trail 363</a></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Start is in the parking lot of a new three story office building.</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Take exit 43B, go straight throught light &amp; take the first left that actual goes somewhere.</p></span></font>', '<p>Joe\'s Pizza &amp; Subs</p><p><span class="EC_street-address"><font face="Arial" color="#555555" size="1"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: #555555; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">14085 John Marshall Hwy</span></font></span><font face="Arial" color="#555555" size="1"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 9pt; COLOR: #555555; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><br /><span class="EC_locality">Gainesville</span>, <span class="EC_region">VA</span> <span class="EC_postal-code">20155</span></span></font></p>', '<p>Live A to B trail with usual shiggy type hazzards.</p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><a href="http://maps.live.com/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!400">Trail 363</a></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">13575 Heathcote Blvd <br />Gainesville, VA <br /></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">next to</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Conway-Robinson</span></font><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> Memorial State Forest</span></font></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p>', ''),
(365, '<p>This week the hares have put togeher the perfect drinking trail. The start is close to the metro, close to the pre-game location (Glory Days) and close to the OnOnOn.</p><p>My first thought... Brilliant!!</p><p>&amp; then I realized... most of the hares are virgins. Well only virgins if saddlebacking doesn\'t count.</p><p>Now about the trail. Hope that wasn\'t too much information.</p><p>See ya Tuesday</p><p />', '<p>Only a couple of blocks from the Vienna Metro Station.</p><p>From 66 E or W: Take exit 62 Nutley St towards Fairfax.  Stay on Nutley pass 29 and hang a left into Pan Am Shopping center and go behind the Micro Center building.</p>', '<div><span><span dir="ltr"><div>Glory Days</div><div><span><span dir="ltr">3059 Nutley St</span><a style="DISPLAY: none; TEXT-DECORATION: underline" href="http:///" target="_blank"><span></span></a> <div><span dir="ltr">Fairfax, VA 22031</span></div></span></div></span></span></div>', 'Live trail! Expect Ticks, PI, T-Rex\'s and the usual village idiots. Flashlights, change of clothes and deodorant also recommended. ', '<p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://www.bing.com/maps/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!408">Trail 364</a></span></p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><div><span><div><span dir="ltr">Glory Day\'s</span></div><div><span dir="ltr">3059 Nutley St</span><a style="DISPLAY: none; TEXT-DECORATION: underline" href="http:///" target="_blank"><span></span></a></div><div><span dir="ltr">Fairfax, VA 22031</span></div></span></div><div>Parking lot behind &quot;Micro Center&quot;!</div></span>', ''),
(366, '<p>Basically the only thing that our SH*Tty Hare Raiser has done this year is obsess about how to top last year\'s SH*Tty Tour Duh Hash trail.</p><p>Personally I think he wasted his time. Last year\'s trail was superb but who am I to judge.</p><p />', '<table class="barlink" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" border="0"><tbody><tr><td><font face="Georgia"><p>Metro:  Franconia-Springfied Metro - Start is less than 1 mile</p><p>Driving:</p><p /><p>Make your way to the outer loop of I-495.</p><p>Go to the Springfield mixing bowl, then take exit 57A</p><p>-&gt; Merge on to Franconia Rd/VA-644 E</p><p>-&gt; Make a right on Frontier Dr.</p><p>-&gt;Turn left onto Springfiled Pkwy/VA-7900 E</p><p>-&gt; Make left at the light at Beulah St.</p><p>-&gt; Take a left onto Walker Lane.</p><p>-&gt; Take first Right into parking lot.</p><p>-&gt; Go to the back of the parking lot - park - hash</p></font></td></tr><tr><td> </td></tr></tbody></table>', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Lucky’s Sports Theatre and Grille</span></font><font face="Tahoma" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">7027 Manchester Blvd</span></font><font face="Tahoma" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Alexandria</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">, VA 22310</span></font><font face="Tahoma" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"></span></font></p>', '<font face="Georgia">Live trail that could end anywhere. Bring $5, whistle, change of clothes, flash light, PI stuff, bug spray, sun tan lotioin, small flask, at least two condoms, dark glasses, and a rubber chicken</font>', '<span style="COLOR: #660000; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "Times New Roman","serif"; mso-fareast-font-family: Calibri; mso-fareast-theme-font: minor-latin; mso-ansi-language: EN-US; mso-fareast-language: EN-US; mso-bidi-language: AR-SA"><a href="http://www.bing.com/maps/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!413">Trail 365</a></span><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">6348 Walker Lane</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> </span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Alexandria</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">, VA 22310</span></font><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" color="#000080" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: navy; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Start is in Springfield although it technically is Alexandria </span></font></p></span>', ''),
(367, '<p>Once again the SH*T will be hosting Hermie\'s favorite theme. </p><p>Why you might ask? because Hermie has refused to leave NOVA until he gets to hare his brown bag hash. </p><p>What is the brown bag hash? Everyone is to bring a<strong> CLEAN </strong>article of clothing sealed in a bag. Perhaps something that you are too embarrassed to wear in public &amp; you don\'t care if you get back.</p><p>You only need to bring one bag to participate but it would be nice if you brought extra... remember charity starts at the hash.</p><p>How do you participate?  Give your brown bags to the sign in people. At some point Nub will instruct the pack to retrieve a brown bag from the pile. Next you are to put on the article of clothing in a manner that best suites you... Then we hash! </p><p /><p>WTF is the reason for so many hares? Because there will be many, something like seven, beverage checks on trail.  </p><p>Special Note: The trail start is heavily patrolled. Please be polite &amp; discrete.</p>', '<span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://www.bing.com/maps/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!417">Trail 366</a></span>', '<p>Brion\'s Grille</p><p>10659 Braddock Road</p><p>Fairfax, VA 22032</p><p>Half priced burgers &amp; happy hour drinks before trail.</p>', 'Live A to B trail. Walker\'s trail not stroller or dog friendly. Bring ivy block, bug spray, flash light, and a bologna sandwhich', '<p><span class="street-address"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: "><a href="http://www.bing.com/maps/?v=2&encType=1&cid=AC24AF69F4B79B3C!417">Trail 366</a></span></span><span class="street-address"></span></p><p><span class="street-address">University Mall</span></p><p><span class="street-address">Back parking lot</span></p><p><span class="street-address">10673 Braddock Rd</span><br /><span class="locality">Fairfax</span>, <span class="region">VA</span> <span class="postal-code">22032</span><br /></p>', ''),
(368, 'Apparently it\'s Have You Seen My Precious\' birthday on the 30th, but who really gives a crap. We just want to run trail and drink beer. ', 'From 66 or Dulles Toll Road, take Rt28 north. From Rt28 take the Waxpool exit towards Ashburn, take a left onto Loudoun County Parkway, go past the greenway and make a left onto Hillsboro Hunt Drive, next left onto Lucketts Bridge Circle and follow it around to the parking lot at the Softball/Soccer field.', '<p>Precious\' hobbit house</p><p>22560 Scattersville Gap Ter<br />Ashburn, VA 20148</p>', '<p>Bring running gear, a change of clothes, Tikki repellant, Ivy Block, Flashlight, a birthday cake and the Lord of the Rings Trilogy.</p>', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00046d31b571c68cab46b&safe=on&ll=38.992521,-77.488396&spn=0.011958,0.019248&t=h&z=16">Trail 367</a></p>', ''),
(369, '<p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">At least I feel like one after last week’s trail, when I thought the S.H.*.T. H3 had just moved to Thursday (EWH3) because the average aged dropped TEN YEARS on the average… this week’s trail is for the adults!! I have never seen our sign-in(s) (“Screws on First” AND her sidekick… who’s NOT “Cradle 2 Dreidel”) ‘card’ so many people!! I think she covered half the pack (and the hares)!!</span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">It was also a young hare crew… all TEN of them!! You could tell by the: 1) Miss markings on trail (apparently… they should have attended the ‘chalk talk’ first!!); 2) Neglecting to mark the ‘Beer Check’ and the ‘Beer Near’ (aren’t those the most important markings on trail?); 3) Neglected to instruct the ‘Brew Meister’ to where finish was. 4) Bag Vehicle? HA!! 5) Lost the majority of the pack on trail.</span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">I could go on… but I really think… I’m suppose to give directions here!!<br /></span></p>', '<p><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Metro…<br /></span></b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Why do you people keep reading this part!?! How often is S.H.*.T. H3 ever ‘metro acceptable’? What wankers!!</span></p><p><b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></b></p><p><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Driving:</span></b></p><p><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">From the Sterling/Herndon/Reston…<br /></span></b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Get yourself onto <b><i>Route 28, Sully Road, South</i></b> heading towards <span style="COLOR: red">Chantilly/Centerville</span>. Take the <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT</span></b> for <b><i>Route 50, Lee Jackson Memorial Highway, East</i></b> toward <span style="COLOR: red">Fairfax</span>. Get all the way into the FAR <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> lane and take a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Centerview Drive</i></b>. Continue on Centerview Drive to 3855 Centerview Drive </span><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">(if you get to Skyhawk Drive… you’ve gone too far)</span></i></b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Park and look for wankers milling around.</span></p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Should you miss Centerview Drive (most do!!) then you can take a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Centreville Road</i></b> then a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Skyhawk Drive</i></b> and then immediate <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Centerview Drive</i></b>. Park and look for wankers milling around.</span></p><p><b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></b></p><p><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">From the Beltway…<br /></span></b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Get yourself to the <b><i>Beltway (I-495)</i></b>. Take <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT 49C</span></b> (from the innerloop) or <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT 49</span></b> (from the outerloop) onto <b><i>I-66, West</i></b> towards <span style="COLOR: red">Front Royal/Vienna</span>. Continue on I-66 for approx. 6½ miles and take <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT 57B</span></b> for <b><i>Route 50, Arlington Boulevard, West</i></b> towards <span style="COLOR: red">Winchester/Fair Oaks</span>. Continue on Route 50, West (ignoring the pre-laid flour… OH WAIT!! This is Tuesday’s trail!! Forgot… ‘live’ trail!!) for approx. 4½ miles and turn <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT</span></b> onto <b><i>Centreville Road</i></b> then a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Skyhawk Drive</i></b> and then immediate <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Centerview Drive</i></b>. Park and look for wankers milling around.</span></p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></p><p><b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Otherwise… if you’re cumming from the South:</span></b></p><p><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Get yourself onto <b><i>Route 123, North</i></b>. Take the ramp for <b><i>Fairfax County Parkway</i></b><b><i>, Route 7100, North…</i></b> and continue on Fairfax County Parkway for approx. 8.2 miles and take the second <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT</span></b> for <b><i>Route 50, Arlington Boulevard, West</i></b> towards <span style="COLOR: red">Winchester</span>. Continue on Route 50, West (ignoring the pre-laid flour) for approx. 3 miles and turn <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT</span></b> onto <b><i>Centreville Road</i></b> then a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Skyhawk Drive</i></b> and then immediate <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Centerview Drive</i></b>. Park and look for wankers milling around.</span></p>', '<p><span><b><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">Bungalow Billiard &amp; Brew Co.</span></b></span></p><p><span><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Arial">13891 Metrotech Drive, Chantilly, VA ~ 703.502.325<span style="BORDER-TOP-WIDTH: 1pt; BORDER-LEFT-WIDTH: 1pt; BORDER-LEFT-COLOR: windowtext; BORDER-BOTTOM-WIDTH: 1pt; BORDER-BOTTOM-COLOR: windowtext; BORDER-TOP-COLOR: windowtext; BORDER-RIGHT-WIDTH: 1pt; BORDER-RIGHT-COLOR: windowtext"></span></span></span></span></p>', '<font face="Georgia">Dog Friendly Factor: If it’s hot out… leave the little creatures at home!!<br /><br />Miscellaneous: Trail is A to A’ <b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">(meaning… that it’s long enough that I have to move the ‘Beer Vehicle’ but short enough for you to leave your sh*t in the cars!! Translated… NO BAG VEHICLE and NO SHUTTLES!!)</span></i></b></font><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. The days are long enough… need not to BRING A FLASHLIGHT!!</span><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Final disclaimer… bring dry clothes and shoes and any FEMALE RUSSIAN VIRGINS you have in your closet!! </span></p>', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?hl=en&ie=UTF8&split=0&gl=us&ei=qu5MSrGPCoSltgeX66CmBA&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00046dbea871e240126c4&safe=on&t=h&z=17">Trail 368</a> </p><p>3855 Centerview Drive</p><p>Chantilly, VA</p>', ''),
(370, 'Looks like the hares have out done themselves this time.  Since we seem to have 2 options for the On On On, there will probably be 6 trails and 10 beer checks as well.', 'Take 66 and enter the rest in Google maps.', 'Sweetwater Tavern, Centreville<br /><a href="http://www.greatamericanrestaurants.com/sweetMainCen/" target="_blank"><font color="#2a5db0">http://www.<wbr />greatamericanrestaurants.com/<wbr />sweetMainCen/</font></a> <p /><div class="im"><font face="Tahoma" color="#000000" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma">14250 Sweetwater Lane</span></font><br /><font face="Tahoma" color="#000000"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma">Centreville</span></font><font face="Tahoma" color="#000000"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma">, VA 20121</span></font><br /><font face="Tahoma" color="#000000"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma">Phone: (703) 449-1100<br />Fax: (703) 449-1108</span></font><br /><font face="Tahoma" color="#000000" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"> </span></font><br /></div><font face="Tahoma" color="#000000" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma">or </span></font><br /><font face="Tahoma" color="#000000" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma"> </span></font><br /><font face="Tahoma" color="#000000" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma">The Blue Iguana</span></font><br /><font face="Tahoma" color="#000000" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma">12727 Shoppes Ln</span></font><br /><font face="Tahoma" color="#000000"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma">Fairfax</span></font><font face="Tahoma" color="#000000"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma">, VA 22033</span></font><br /><font face="Tahoma" color="#000000"><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Tahoma">(703) 502-8108</span></font>', 'Bring a tent and a sleeping bag, we may be on trail all night long.', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&safe=on&msa=0&ll=38.871055,-77.40469&spn=0.047779,0.07699&t=h&z=14&msid=114946079815076584162.00046e4674511736edca0">Trail 3<strong><font size="5">69</font></strong></a> </p><p><font face="Tahoma">Trail start: Commuter parking lot on Stringfellow Rd.</font></p><p><font face="Tahoma">4928 Stringfellow Rd, Centreville,  Virginia 20120</font></p>', ''),
(371, '<p>On 21 July 1969, Neil Armstrong became the first man to walk on the moon. And considering the recent death of the original &quot;moonwalker&quot; Michael Jackson, our next trail will be dubbed the Moon trail. So, even though Hermie is gone if you want to wear adult diapers in honor of astronauts, feel free. Or pull out your best sparkly glove to honor Michael. Or just bring some moon pies. <br /></p>', 'Click on link above.', '<p>Sign of the Whale</p><p><span>7279 Arlington Blvd</span><br /><span>Falls Church, VA 22042-3200</span><br /></p>', 'Sounds like there will be a lot of single glove and moon action, so bring your favorite jelly (Smuckers, KY, etc), face mask, leather pants, a red jacket and children.  A flashlight might a good idea in case this ends up being another colonoscopy trail. ', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00046ec2107554030f529&safe=on&t=h&z=16">Trail 370</a></p><p>7119 Camp Alger Ave. (Go through side gate to back)<br />Falls Church, VA 22042</p>', ''),
(372, '<p>Apparently, the Ancestral homeland of the SH*T is at Bowl America.  One of the dangers of starting at the bowling alley is that many of us may just go bowling instead of running.  It takes much less effort, it\'s air conditioned and they offer pitchers of beer!  </p>', '<p>Get to route 7.  Turn on to Dranesville Road.  If you\'re<br />coming from the west, it\'ll be a right.  Otherwise it\'ll be a left.<br />Make the right on Woodson, Bowl America will be on your right.<br /><a href="http://edm.micron.com/cgi-bin/mtgetdoc.exe?itemID=090007da809b38c0"></a></p>', 'Glory Days.  About 1/2 mile up the street at the corner of Dranesville<br />and route 7', 'Bring ivy block, insecct repellant, a bowling ball and pepper spray (in case we get into a scuffle with the bowling league).', '<a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&safe=on&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00046f6160c32252b2eee&ll=39.015182,-77.375314&spn=0.011921,0.019248&t=h&z=16">Trail 371</a>', ''),
(373, 'There must have been another request to frolick under Rt28 and through the tick infested area of Ellanor C Lawrence Park.  Sweet!!!!!!!!!!!!', 'Take I-66 and exit 53B if heading west or 53 (towards VA-28 Centreville) if heading east. This will put you on Sully Road/Route 28. Head (who said head) north past the Walney/Braddock Road intersection. After 0.6 mile past Walney/Braddock Road, take the left entrance at the light and pull in to the parking lot. Look for wankers.', '<div>Texas Road House <span> </span></div><div><span dir="ltr">4993 Westone Plz</span><a style="TEXT-DECORATION: underline" href="http:///" target="_blank"><span></span></a></div><div><span dir="ltr">Chantilly, VA 20151-2294</span></div><div><span dir="ltr"></span><span dir="ltr">(703) 378-9887</span></div>', '<div><span dir="ltr">A to A, shiggy, PI factor, dog friendly (just please clean up after them), not stoller friendly. A change of clothes or a hazmat suit is recommended.</span></div>', '<a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&safe=on&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00046fee7964158d0c095&ll=38.864673,-77.439623&spn=0.023892,0.038495&t=h&z=15">Trail 372</a>', ''),
(374, '<span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">The bus is running<br />It\'s time to leave<br />The summer\'s gone<br />And so are we<br />So come on baby,<br />Let\'s go shut it down……..</span><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni"></span></font><p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni"> </span></font></p>', '<font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni"><p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><b><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">D-erections:</span></font></b></p><p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><b><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">(Metro)</span></font></b></p><p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><b><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">This is the S.H.*.T. get real. </span></font></b></p><p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni"> </span></font></p><p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><b><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">(Driving)</span></font></b></p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.0004707ada65514f61a0e&safe=on&ll=38.822323,-77.223501&spn=0.047812,0.07699&t=h&z=14"></a></span></font><p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">Make your way to the Beltway</span></font></p><p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">Take the Little River Turnpike (Rt. 236) exit west. </span></font></p><p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">Make your first left onto Pineridge Dr. (this will come up very quickly!)</span></font></p><p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">Make an immediate left (less than 15’ from the intersection) onto Accotink Pkwy</span></font></p><p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">Take you first left into the ball field parking lot. </span></font></p><p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">Look for wankers milling about in a confused and disheveled fashion. </span></font></p><p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">Join them.</span></font></p><p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">Hash.</span></font></p>', '<p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><span><font face="Bodoni" color="#000000" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">Kilroy\'s Restaurant</span></font></span><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni"><br />5250 Port Royal Rd # A</span></font></p><p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">Springfield</span></font><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">, VA 22151-2117</span></font><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni"></span></font></p><p style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" align="center"><font face="Bodoni" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">+1 703-321-7733</span></font></p>', '<span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Bodoni">Blah, Blah, Blah, come prepared. Blah, Blah flashlight, change of cloths, Blah. </span>', '<a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.0004707ada65514f61a0e&safe=on&ll=38.822323,-77.223501&spn=0.047812,0.07699&t=h&z=14">Trail 373</a>', '');
