(375, '<p>What better way to start the hunting season by going out west.  This is close to Hillbilly territory so we might as well call this the SH*Tbilly hash.  </p>', '<p>Driving:</p><p>Click on the link above and ask googlemaps for direction. *Important* Park outside the main gate!</p><p>Metro:</p><div>Clifton is actually metro accessible! Take the metro to Union station then take any VRE train towards Frednecksburg and when the engineer blows his whistle for the Clifton road crossing jump off!  I would suggest trying to roll when you hit the ground \'cause the train doesn\'t stop until Manasshole...</div><div>Once you\'re in Clifton, You are on your own.  Hire a rickshaw or bring a skate board.  </div>', '<p>The Polo Pub in Clifton </p><p>7145 Main Street Clifton, VA </p><p>Across from the General Store behind the Heart in Hand. </p>', 'A to B. Walkers is &quot;Strong Dog Friendly&quot; which probably means don\'t bring a chihuahua. High shiggy/P.I. content.  Wear bright orange camo in case we run into the local militia.', '<a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.000471183c3c29346455c&safe=on&ll=38.777774,-77.401772&spn=0.047842,0.07699&t=h&z=14&iwloc=0004716cea096525b0735">Trail 374</a>', ''),
(376, '<p>After some near death experiences with the VRE railroad track last week, the hares are going to test their luck with the runways in Dulles airport.  Same rules apply, if you see a light coming towards you then dodge, duck, dip, dive and dodge!</p>', 'From the toll road: Take exit 10 then left on Centerville Rd.  At the fourth or fifth light turn right onto Coppermine (PNC bank is on the corner).  Follow road for less than a mile and turn into parking lot before the turn onto Horse Pen.<br />', 'TBD', 'We won\'t lie to you so guys plan for desert, woods &amp; shrubs.  Ladies plan for wetness.', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&safe=on&msa=0&ll=38.952801,-77.424045&spn=0.007693,0.013754&t=h&z=16&msid=114946079815076584162.000471aa0e305da28240a">Trail 375</a></p><p>Parking lot on the corner of Coppermine Road and Horse Pen Rd <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&safe=on&msa=0&ll=38.952801,-77.424045&spn=0.007693,0.013754&t=h&z=16&msid=11494607"></a></p>', ''),
(377, '<p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Tysons Corner, Va. (March 10, 2009)</span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> — Leaders of TysonsTunnel, Inc. today commended the federal government for awarding $900 million for phase one of the 23-mile extension of the Metrorail system through Tysons Corner and onto Dulles International Airport, but also said that the group will continue the fight for a tunnel.</span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Thanks for the ‘Stimulus Package’!!</span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">All those who are tired of hearing about ANY kind of ‘Stimulus Package’… please raise your hands!!</span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Oh… and to offer a better trail for you this week… the hares have provided a ‘Stimulus Package’!! For only five dollars… you get cheap beer at the ‘Beer Check’ and more cheap beer at ‘Finish’. Stimulate that, you wankers!!</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Now… get me off this ‘soap box’… Oh… and… Here are the directions!!<br /></span></p>', '<p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Directions:</span></b></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Metro…<br /></span></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Of course… the <a href="http://www.docstoc.com/docs/10156272/Tysons-metro-rail-stop-plan-map" target="_blank"><font color="#2a5db0">Tyson West Station</font></a>... On the “Silver Line”!! However… it may not be open until about 2013!!</span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></b></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Driving:</span></b></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">From the Sterling/Herndon/Reston…<br /></span></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Get yourself onto <b><i>Route 7, East or Route 267, Dulles Toll Road </i></b>heading towards <span style="COLOR: red">Tysons Corner</span>. After you pass over Route 267, Dulles Toll Road (or take the Route 7, East exit, if coming from the Toll Road) and take the first <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT</span></b> onto <b><i>Westwood Center Drive</i></b>. </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Continue to the end of the cul-de-sac</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> of Westwood Center Drive, park and look for wankers milling around.</span></p><p style="MARGIN: auto 0in"><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">From the Beltway…<br /></span></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Get yourself </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">to the <b><i>Beltway (I-495)</i></b>. Take <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT 45</span></b> for the <b><i>Route 267, Dulles Toll Road</i></b>. As soon as you go through the main toll plaza… take the first <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT</span></b> for Route 7. On the ramp to Route 7… stay on your <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> and turn <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Route 7, East</i></b>. You will pass back over the Dulles Toll Road and take your first <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT</span></b> onto <b><i>Westwood Center Drive</i></b>. Continue to the end of the cul-de-sac</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> of Westwood Center Drive, park and look for wankers milling around.</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Alternate direction from the <b><i>Beltway (I-495)</i></b>. Take <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT 47B-A</span></b> for the <b><i>Route 7, West</i></b>. Continue on Route 7 for approx. 2½ miles and turn <b><span style="COLOR: blue">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Westwood Center Drive</i></b> (Tyco Road will be on your right). Continue to the end of the cul-de-sac</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> of Westwood Center Drive, park and look for wankers milling around.<b><span style="COLOR: red"></span></b></span></p>', '<p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">O Malley’s Pub (located behind the Crown Plaza (in between Crown Plaza and the Marriott at Route 123 and International Drive) </span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">1960 Chain Bridge Rd, Mclean, VA 22102-4001</span></p>', '<p style="BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: medium none; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: medium none"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Dog Friendly Factor: If it’s hot out… leave the little critters at home!!<br /><br />Live Trail, as usual, and it’s A to A’ </span><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">(meaning… that it’s long enough that I have to move the ‘Beer Vehicle’ but short enough for you to leave your sh*t in the cars!! Translated… NO BAG VEHICLE and NO SHUTTLES!!)</span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. </span></p><p style="BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: medium none; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: medium none"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></p><p style="BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: medium none; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: medium none"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">If you haven’t noticed yet… it’s getting DARK!! Regardless of that… that means… BRING A FLASHLIGHT!! If you’re an EWH3 hasher… forget it… you’ll never survive this trail!!</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p style="BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: medium none; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: medium none"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></p><p style="BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: medium none; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; PADDING-TOP: 0in; BORDER-BOTTOM: medium none"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Final disclaimer… bring dry clothes and shoes and any FEMALE RUSSIAN VIRGINS you have in your closet!! (hummm… WAIT!! </span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Okay… the virgin(s) can be ‘wet’!!)</span></p>', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00047237cc5590073878e&safe=on&ie=UTF8&ll=38.925029,-77.235904&spn=0.023938,0.038495&t=h&z=15">Trail 376</a> </p><p><span style="COLOR: #660000; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">8699 Westwood Center Dr, Vienna, VA 22182-2235</span></p>', ''),
(378, '&nbsp;', '<span lang="EN"><a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps?city=Reston&state=VA&address=1800+Michael+Faraday+Ct" target="_blank"><font color="#0068cf"><br /></font></a></span>', '<span style="font-size: 13.5pt; color: rgb(196, 18, 0); font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';"><strong>Jackson\'s Mighty Fine Food &amp; Lucky Lounge</strong></span><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 3.75pt; margin-left: 3pt; line-height: 16.5pt; margin-right: 3.75pt;"><span style="font-size: 10pt; color: rgb(196, 18, 0); font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';">4.75 drafts (Itï¿½s Reston)</span></p><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal" style="margin-bottom: 1.5pt;"><span class="EC_EC_street-address"><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(85, 85, 85); font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';">11927 Democracy Dr</span></span><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(85, 85, 85); font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';"><br /><span class="EC_EC_street-address">Reston Town Center</span><br /><span class="EC_EC_locality">Reston</span>, <span class="EC_EC_region">VA</span> <span class="EC_EC_postal-code">20190</span></span></p><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><span class="EC_EC_tel"><b><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(85, 85, 85); font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';">(703) 437-0800</span></b></span><span style="font-size: 9pt; color: rgb(85, 85, 85); font-family: \'Arial\',\'sans-serif\';">ï¿½</span></p>', 'Live A-A trail. <span lang="EN">If you haven\'t figured it out by now, it\'s getting dark really quick so bring a freaking flashlight!!Â  Dry clothes, bug spray, compasses and a bottle of your best Irish for Luck is also recommended! </span><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><span lang="EN">ï¿½</span></p>', '<a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.000472fdd92a1c9cd8cd8&ll=38.953335,-77.344823&spn=0.015552,0.038581&t=h&z=15&iwloc=000472fdeaaf8cf3e1799">Trail#377</a><br /><br />mountain bike trailhead located at:<p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><span lang="EN">Michael Faraday Ctï¿½ </span></p><p class="EC_EC_MsoNormal"><span lang="EN"><a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps?city=Reston&state=VA" target="_blank"><font color="#0068cf">Reston</font></a>, <a href="http://www.mapquest.com/maps?state=VA" target="_blank"><font color="#0068cf">VA</font></a> 20190-5303 </span></p>', ''),
(379, '<p>Ok kids it is time once again to come together as a clan and see if we can finish all the beer and mount both virgins (we know who you are!) in Northern Virginia. We would have done it last year if it weren\'t for that damn hurricane that decided to <span class="squiggly" title="To see spelling suggestions, click this word" word="F" state="new" splc="splc">F</span> with us! We survived that (barely) and have become all the drunkard for it. Well, we can\'t promise that Mother Nature won\'t bare down on us again but we sacrificed Queerly I am Straight to her last night to avoid her vengeful wrath this year in an attempt to appease her. We will have a great trail, beer, food, DJ Tour De Whore all night long, Camp Fire musings, and plenty of camping space so come early(by early we mean show up between 1 &amp; <span class="squiggly" title="To see spelling suggestions, click this word" word="2PM" state="new" splc="splc">2PM</span>) and stay late!(and by late we really don\'t care if you leave because Fire is an a$$hole).</p>', '<table class="barlink" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" border="0"><tbody><tr><td><font face="Georgia"><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Carpool if you can!</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Route 66 West to Exit 40 (Route 15 south).<span style="mso-spacerun: yes"></span></span></p></font></td></tr><tr><td> </td></tr></tbody></table>', 'Barbaque at Fire\'s place', 'Live A to A mostly shiggy trail. Cum prepared for tics, sun burn, PI, hornets, emus, lamas, poisonous spiders, snakes, and seagulls,  black bears, black beans, and black babies, children of the corn, children of the sun, and bastard children, rednecks, yellownecks, and fat chics with no necks.....and kankles!', '<p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&safe=on&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00047338c35235eaf66f0&ll=38.787944,-77.678511&spn=0.011992,0.019248&t=h&z=16">Trail 378</a></font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">Fire in The CornHole\'s place.</font></p><p><font face="georgia,times new roman,times,serif">7708 Cerro Gordo Road Gainesville, VA</font></p>', ''),
(380, '<span>Well, we played musical chairs with the SHIT mismanagement positions again and now you get to see who the lucky ones were that couldn\'t find a seat. Those who were unlucky enough to find a seat get the dubious honor of having to serve another year on SHIT mismanagement.  As a penance for their &quot;racist&quot; behavior in running to find a seat we\'re making them hare the first trail of the new administration. Come on out and see who the (un)lucky wankers were and see if they can lay a trail any better than last year\'s gaggle of misfits.</span>', '<p><span>Get to Route 66 West however you can from wherever you are</span><span></span></p><p><span>Take Exit 53B Sully Rd (Rt 28) North toward Chantilly.</span></p><p><span>Follow Route 28 north for about 1.7 miles then exit onto Westfields Blvd West.</span></p><p><span>Follow Westfields Blvd for about 1 mile and turn left at light onto Sequoia Farms Dr.  Take first left into shopping center parking lot and drive behind the building until you see wankers.  Park. Hash.</span></p>', '<span>The Bungalow</span> <p><span>13891 Metrotech Dr</span></p><p><span></span><span>Chantilly, VA 20151</span></p><p><span></span><span>703-502-3925</span></p>', '<span>Live A to A trail with a good combination of shiggy and pavement. Bring bug spray, flashlight and a change of clothes!!!!  </span>', '<span><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00047380c464d6153dfb4&ll=38.933375,-77.431126&spn=0.051677,0.110378&t=h&z=13">Trail 379</a><br /><br />Behind what use to be a Safeway at:</span><span><br />5111 Westfield Blvd.</span><span><br />Centreville, VA 20120</span>', ''),
(381, '<p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Talk about some ‘old fart’ hares: And How’s Her Bush (96+), The Udder Ho (55+) and (Dixie Queen 26+)!! And maybe I can convince another ‘old’ wanker to come out of retirement… 14K (45+). Just imagine the terrain they must have found!! You probably won\'t need to look for flour, since most of these old farts will be crop dusting along the trail!   So… come on out, follow your nose and catch yourself some ‘old fart’ hare.  Just remember though… your reward for catching a ‘hare’ is to de-pants them! </span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p>', '<p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">From Sterling:</span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Find your way to </span></strong><strong><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Route 7, East</span></i></strong><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Take the </span></strong><strong><span style="COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">EXIT</span></strong><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> for </span></strong><strong><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Algonkian Parkway</span></i></strong><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> (that would be a </span></strong><strong><span style="COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">LEFT…</span></strong><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> a </span></strong><strong><span style="COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">RIGHT</span></strong><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> would be toward Fairfax County Parkway. Continue on Algonkian Parkway for approx. 2.0 miles. Take a </span></strong><strong><span style="COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">LEFT</span></strong><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> onto Lowes Island Boulevard into the Great Falls Plaza Shopping Center. Park in front of Velocity Five and look for deviants. </span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">From Herndon/Reston:</span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Find your way to </span></strong><strong><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Route 7100, Fairfax County Parkway, North</span></i></strong><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Continue on Fairfax County Parkway, North over Route 7. Fairfax County Parkway turns into </span></strong><strong><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Algonkian Parkway</span></i></strong><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">. Continue on Algonkian Parkway for approx. 2.0 miles. Take a </span></strong><strong><span style="COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">LEFT</span></strong><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> onto Lowes Island Boulevard into the Great Falls Plaza Shopping Center. Park in front of Velocity Five and look for deviants. </span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">From the Beltway:</span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Take the <b><i>Dulles Toll Road (267)</i></b>. Pass through the first set of tolls </span><b><i><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">($.75 pre-hash contribution)</span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> and take the first <b><span style="COLOR: blue">EXIT</span></b> for Route 7. At the end of the ramp… take a <b><span style="COLOR: blue">RIGHT</span></b> onto <strong><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Route 7, </span></i></strong><b><i>West</i></b>. Go through a million lights… for like a million miles (or… approximately 8 ½ miles). Take the <strong><span style="COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">EXIT</span></strong><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> for </span></strong><strong><i><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Algonkian Parkway</span></i></strong><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> (that would be a </span></strong><strong><span style="COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">RIGHT…</span></strong><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> a </span></strong><strong><span style="COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">LEFT</span></strong><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> would be toward Fairfax County Parkway. Continue on Algonkian Parkway for approx. 2.0 miles. Take a </span></strong><strong><span style="COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">LEFT</span></strong><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> onto Lowes Island Boulevard into the Great Falls Plaza Shopping Center. Park in front of Velocity Five and look for deviants. </span></strong></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Metro:</span></strong><strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></strong><b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">[ </span></b><b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">BECAUSE… “It’s still not OVER until it’s UNDER!!</span></b><b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> ]</span></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">If you’re waiting for metro… you’ll never get there!! Bye a car!! We are BIG KIDS… WE DRIVE.</span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><strong><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Or check the old fashioned way… GET A MAP!!</span></b></span><b><span style="COLOR: red; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><br /></span></b><b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; COLOR: blue; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">(</span></b><b><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Velocity Five; <span><span style="COLOR: black">20789</span></span><span style="COLOR: black"> <span>Great Falls Plaza</span>, <span>Sterling</span>, <span>VA</span></span><span style="COLOR: blue">)</span></span></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></p>', '<a href="/maps?ie=UTF8&hl=en&vps=1&jsv=176c&safe=on&cid=1550713007828963191"><font color="#0000cc">Velocity Five Sports Restaurant &amp; Bar</font></a><br /><span>20789 Great Falls Plaza</span><br /><span>Sterling, VA 20165</span><br /><span>(703) 444-8666</span><br />', '<p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Live trail (as usual)… As if you can’t tell… it’s dark even before you get into your car!! (well… close to it!!) What does that mean… it means… <b><i>BRING A FLASHLIGHT, you dumbass!!  </i></b></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Other info… well… it’s dark… you won’t see the PI (poison ivy) anyway. It’s dark… you won’t see any water, if any, anyway. It’s dark… you won’t know if you are on road or shiggy. So… what does that mean? It means… ‘just in case’ bring dry clothes and shoes. Best bet… bring one of those… ‘Beautiful Young Female Virgins’ in case you DO get LOST!! That way… at least you won’t even remember trail.  Some febreeze may also help during circle!!</span></p>', '<p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 12pt"><span style="COLOR: #660000; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&safe=on&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.000473db3be16fc697832&ll=39.044619,-77.359028&spn=0.023898,0.038495&t=h&z=15">Trail 380</a></span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 12pt"><span>In front of… <strong><font color="#0000ff">Velocity Five</font>;<br /></strong></span><span><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">20789</span></span><span style="COLOR: black; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> <span>Great Falls Plaza</span>, <span>Sterling</span>, <span>VA</span></span><b><span style="COLOR: #660000; FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span></b></p>', ''),
(382, '<p>Our Hareraiser does talk a lot of smack about how he was going to have all the open slots filled for the next few weeks, but low and behold we have no trails.  As a result, MM is supplying another fun trail so we can continue our habitual drinking on Tuesday nights. So, if anyone has a great trail in mind, please please please contact our hareraiser!  Making fun of him every week for not doing his job is already getting old and it\'s only been 2 weeks!</p>', '<p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Verdana">Get your A$$ on I-66, and head to exit <b>55</b> for <b>7100 (FFX Co. PKWY)</b> toward <strong>Reston/Herndon. </strong>After about .5 miles on 7100, turn left on to Fair Lakes Parkway. Turn left at the very first light you come to on Fair Lakes PKWY. Make an immediate right after the McDonalds, and look for the shopping center with The Blue Iguana on the left side.</span></font></p>', 'The Blue Iguana (duh) Tuesday nights are Karaoke night, so warm your ass (in other words, mouth) up, and get on the mic!!!', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"> <font size="3">There is no chance that any one will get wet and run through shiggy on this trail. Nor will it get dark when trail starts. But bring dry clothes, a flashlight and bug spray anyway.</font></span></font></p>', '<p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font size="3"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&safe=on&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.0004743f692023e662056&ll=38.863671,-77.387395&spn=0.01198,0.019248&t=h&z=16">Trail 381</a></font></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><font size="3">The Blue Iguana</font></span></font></p><p class="EC_MsoNormal"><font face="Arial" size="2"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial"><span dir="ltr"><span>12727 Shoppes Ln</span>, <span>Fairfax</span>, <span>VA</span></span></span></font></p>', ''),
(383, 'The misfits of EWH3 is going to grace SH*T with their version of a shiggalicious trail.  Their Graffiti trail supposedly had a shiggy factor of 70%.  I guess they can make that claim if leaves on the ground qualifies as shiggy.  In case the title and image on the main page doesn\'t provide a hint, it\'s going to be a Toga hash! ', '<p>Metro: Take the metro to Huntington Metro Station. Look for wankers wearing toga\'s at the lot across the street from the Park &amp; Ride..</p><p>Driving: Take 495 to exit 176A for VA/241 Telegraph Rd.  Turn right at Telegraph Rd then left at Burgundy Rd.  Then Right in the parking lot across the street from the Huntington Metro Park and Ride.  Look for Wankers wearing toga\'s.</p><p><a href="http://www.howtomakeatoga.info/">How to Make a Toga</a><br /></p><p />', '<p>Pilar\'s Restaurant:</p><p><span>2249 Huntington Ave</span><br /><span>Alexandria, VA 22303-1509</span><br /><span>(703) 317-9295</span><br /></p>', '<p>This is going to be a Toga Hash, so break out your best 400 thread count Egyptian cotton sheets and flippy floppys!   Other recommendations: A flashlight, bug spray, another set of sheets (in case the one you wear on trail gets wet), sneakers and based on our hashmaster\'s performance at the Blue Iguana, a set of ear plugs for Karoake night at Piler\'s </p><p>News Update: There will be large amounts of EWH3\'s version of an Arnold Palmer (Sweet Tea and lemonade vodka shots).  Now that\'s Southern Hospitality!</p>', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.000474cc3317ef5a51078&safe=on&ll=38.792585,-77.073405&spn=0.005996,0.009624&t=h&z=17">Trail#382</a></p><p>Parking lot <strong>across the street</strong> from the Huntington Metro Station Park &amp; Ride</p>', ''),
(384, 'With Christmas almost upon us, Dixie has decided do a hash at the mall.  This is perfect since I\'m sure many of us would like to return that red dress purchased at Forever 21.  Just remember, if we get caught by mall security tell them we\'re from Great Falls H3!', '<p class="MsoNormal"><strong style="COLOR: rgb(255,0,0)"><span>From Arlington, Alexandria, Springfield:</span></strong><span></span></p><strong style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal"><span>Find your way to </span></strong><strong style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal"><i><span>I-495 Capital Beltway, North(West)</span></i></strong><strong><span><span style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal">. Get onto I-495 (Inner Loop) heading toward the Tyson’s Corner/American Legion Bridge.  Take Dulles Airport Exit - #45 and follow the Dulles Toll Road (VA-267 W) approximately 12 miles to the Sterling Exit #9B (Sully Road – Rt 28 N).  Follow Rt 28 north for a bit less than 5 miles and turn right onto Nokes Blvd.  Go .3 miles and turn left onto Atlantic Blvd.  Make the first right into the Dulles Town Center and turn left onto Dulles Town Circle.  Look for Mimi’s Café on left then find wankers, park and shop or hash.</span><br /><br /></span></strong><p class="MsoNormal"><strong style="COLOR: rgb(255,0,0)"><span>From Fairfax:</span></strong><span></span></p><strong style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal"><span>Find your way to </span></strong><strong style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal"><i><span>I-66, West</span></i></strong><strong style="FONT-WEIGHT: normal"><span>. Get onto I-66 W heading toward Centreville / Manassas.  Take Exit #53B – Sully Rd North and follow it approximately 13 miles and turn right onto Nokes Blvd.  Go .3 miles and turn left onto Atlantic Blvd.  Make the first right into the Dulles Town Center and turn left onto Dulles Town Circle.  Look for Mimi’s Café on left then find wankers, park and shop or hash.</span></strong><br />', '<p>Mimi\'s Cafe and Restaurant</p><p><span class="adr" id="adr" dir="ltr"><span class="street-address">21015 Dulles Town Cir</span>, <span class="locality">Sterling</span>, <span class="region">VA</span></span> - <span class="nw" dir="ltr"><span class="tel">(571) 434-0162</span></span></p>', 'Bring a flashlight in case you get lost at the Victoria Secret\'s fitting room.  We may be running through the fountain at the center of the mall, so bring dry cloths to change into.<br />', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&safe=on&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.000475c0557a86f8a313f&ll=39.031519,-77.424538&spn=0.011951,0.019248&t=h&z=16">Trail 383</a></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Bookman Old Style\',\'serif\'"><span class="adr" id="adr" dir="ltr"><font face="Times New Roman"><span class="street-address">21015 Dulles Town Cir</span>, <span class="locality">Sterling</span>, <span class="region">VA</span></font></span></span></p>', ''),
(385, 'Word on the street is that these hares have changed the start location about 69 times and have gotten lost while scouting for the past 4 days.  The FRBs will have to be smart about this one!  <br />', 'Get a map!', '<span jsvalues="$title:i.title;$laddr:m.laddr;$addrurl:i.addressUrl;lkgal:m.ss.lkg.addresslines;$features:features;$lkgal:m.ss.lkg.addresslines" __jsvalues_parsed="true" lkgal="undefined" jsdisplay="m.b_s!=4" jstcache="131"> Champs<div jsselect="i.addressLines" jsinstance="0" jsvalues="$addrline:$this;" __jsvalues_parsed="true" jstcache="147"><span jsvalues=".innerHTML:$addrline;dir:bidiDir($addrline,true)" __jsvalues_parsed="true" jsdisplay="$title||!$laddr||!$addrurl" jstcache="156" dir="ltr">11694 Plaza America Dr</span><a jsvalues="href:$addrurl" jsdisplay="$features.embed&&!$title&&$laddr&&$addrurl" jstcache="157" target="_parent" style="display: none; text-decoration: underline;"><span jsvalues=".innerHTML:$addrline;dir:bidiDir($addrline,true)" jstcache="162"></span></a></div><div jsselect="i.addressLines" jsinstance="*1" jsvalues="$addrline:$this;" __jsvalues_parsed="true" jstcache="147"><span jsvalues=".innerHTML:$addrline;dir:bidiDir($addrline,true)" __jsvalues_parsed="true" jsdisplay="$title||!$laddr||!$addrurl" jstcache="156" dir="ltr">Reston, VA 20190-4700</span><a jsvalues="href:$addrurl" jsdisplay="$features.embed&&!$title&&$laddr&&$addrurl" jstcache="157" target="_parent" style="display: none; text-decoration: underline;"><span jsvalues=".innerHTML:$addrline;dir:bidiDir($addrline,true)" jstcache="162"></span></a></div><div jsdisplay="$features.embed&&!i.title&&!m.laddr&&i.addressLines&&i.dtlsUrl" jstcache="148" style="display: none;"></div></span><span jsvalues=".innerHTML:i.realestate_data.attr_html" jsdisplay="m.b_s==4&&i.realestate_data" jstcache="132" style="display: none;"></span><div jsselect="i.phones" jsinstance="*0" jsvalues="$type:$this.type" __jsvalues_parsed="true" jstcache="116" class="phone"><span jscontent="$this.numb