(390, 'It seems like the SH*T hash has crossed into a parallel universe during the month of November since none of the trails have been in SH*T territory.  You can call it expanding our horizon or taking over the world, who the heck cares as long as the beer shows up and we have a trail to run/walk. ', '<p>Automobile: 395 to the Duke Street exit, 236 Eastbound towards Landmark.  Look for Ben Brenman Park.  Go to the parking lot at the back and look for wankers loitering the area.</p>', '<p>Mango Mikes</p><p>4580 Duke St</p><p>Alexandria, VA 22304-2504</p>', '<p>Flashlights, Change of Clothes, Flashlights and Change of clothes.</p>', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&safe=on&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.0004787fec414a222041b&ll=38.814115,-77.113788&spn=0.01157,0.019248&t=h&z=16">Trail 389</a></p><p>Ben Brenman Park</p><p>5000 Duke St</p><p>Alexandria, VA 22304</p><p>Go to the Parking lot in the back of the park</p>', ''),
(391, '<p>Captain Awesome himself, Air Spanker One is going to hare all by his lonesome. You may ask &quot;Why would anyone lay both Walkers and Runners trail without the assistance of other half minds?&quot;. Well, if you look at the image on the main page, it will be quite obvious. AS1 wants everyone to aspire to his level of awesomeness.</p>', '<p>D\'Erections: Get to 495, Inner Loop or Outer towards Tyson\'s Corner. Take Exit 46 B (123, Dolley Madison/Chain Bridge) Towards McLean. Once you go under the first underpass (Where the Dulles Toll Road goes above you). Get in the Far Left lane. Make the next left at the light onto Lewinsville Road (near the police substation). After the left, make the next right onto Balls Hill Road. Go down on Balls......hhhahahahha...for about 3 or 4 blocks.Â  Look for the Legion on the right hand side past the &quot;McLean School.&quot;<br /></p><p>Metro Sexual Station: West Fall Church is about 5 miles away.</p>', '&quot;The Pub&quot; or &quot;Tim\'s&quot;, whichever will give the best deal.', 'Trail is A to whatever. There will be a bag vehicle so bring a bag. Flashlight and dry clothes may help.', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.000478cf60041d9987519&z=19">Trail#390</a></p><p>McLean American Legion, Post 270</p><p>1355 Balls Hill Road</p><p>Mclean, VA 22101</p>', ''),
(392, '<p>It\'s Nub\'s birthday and we are going to help him celebrate!  Since Nub is close to being eligible for a Senior Citizen\'s discount, he\'ll be getting a rectal exam at the Colon and Rectal Surgery Center before the start of the trail.  The Udder Ho is going to be holding his hand during the exam, so he might actually show up on time to hare the trail.  Tikki will also be there for moral support. </p>', '<p>Automobile:</p><p>From the East</p><p>66W to 495 South, take exit 50A for US-50 W/Arlington Blvd toward Fairfax/US-29.  Keep Right and follow the signs towards Gallows Rd.  Turn right onto Gallows, then left onto US-29.  Make a right at Prosperity Ave. Turn left into 2710 Prosperity and go towards the back lot.  Look for Wankers milling about!</p><p>From the West</p><p>66E to Exit 62 towards Fairfax.  Make a Left onto Route 29. About 1.5 miles, make a left at Prosperity Ave.  Turn left into 2710 Prosperity and go towards the back lot.  Look for Wankers milling about!   </p><p>Metro</p><p>Approximately 0.5 miles from the Dunn Loring station!!!! </p>', '<p>Grevy\'s</p><p><span>8130 Arlington Blvd</span><br /><span>Falls Church, VA 22042</span><br /></p>', '<p>Bring a flashlight, change of clothes and Preparation H.</p><p><strong><font color="#ff0000">Make sure that you are dressed appropriately to go to Grevey\'s!  Guys, that means NO Sleeveless shirts!  Ladies, tank tops are encouraged!!!</font></strong></p>', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.0004799733d52be233f8a&safe=on&ll=38.871222,-77.227879&spn=0.023956,0.038495&t=h&z=15">Trail#391</a></p><p>Parking lot behind the Colon and Rectal Surgery Center!</p><p>2710 Prosperity Ave</p><p>Fairfax, VA 22031</p>', ''),
(393, 'According to legend, when Running Bare hares a trail, there is no scouting involved.  He will randomly pick suckers out of the crowd on the day of the hash, show them where the BC/BN is and send them on their merry way.  INCONCEIVABLE!', '<p><span style="COLOR: #7f007f; FONT-FAMILY: \'Bookman Old Style\',\'serif\'"><font color="#000000">From 95, take exit 173 towards VA-613/Van Dorn St/Franconia.  Turn right at S Van Dorn St (0.7miles). Left at Franconia Rd (0.7miles). Left at Westchester St.</font></span></p>', '<span style="COLOR: #7f007f; FONT-FAMILY: \'Bookman Old Style\',\'serif\'"><font color="#000000"><p class="MsoNormal">King Street Blues</p><p class="MsoNormal">5810 Kingstowne Center</p><p class="MsoNormal">Kingstowne, VA 22315</p><p class="MsoNormal">(703) 313-0400</p></font></span>', '<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="COLOR: #7f007f; FONT-FAMILY: \'Bookman Old Style\',\'serif\'"><font color="#000000">Dog friendly if they’re leashed, bring flashlights, dry shoes and change of clothes.<br /><br />Gluhwein (hot mulled wine) and fire provided if the weather calls for it?</font></span></p>', '<span style="COLOR: #7f007f; FONT-FAMILY: \'Bookman Old Style\',\'serif\'"><font color="#000000"><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #1f497d"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00047a238b92d97ee1717&safe=on&z=15">Trail#392</a></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #1f497d">Bush Hill Elementary School</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #1f497d">5927 Westchester St.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #1f497d">Alexandria, VA 22310</span></p></font></span>', ''),
(396, 'I\'m not sure what these two love birds owe each other, but they have a 15 minute head start before the rest of us come after them so whatever they plan on doing in the bushes prior to that, it better be quick!', '66 East or West to exit 55 to 7100 South.  Take the exit for Route 29, Lee Highway from 7100 and make a right.  Drive about 2 miles and make a left to Union Mill road. Look for the shopping center on your right and the Giant Supermarket.', 'Sweetwater Tavern<br /><span>14250 Sweetwater Lane</span><br /><span>Centreville, VA 20121-5336</span><br /><br />', 'Bring the usual change of clothes, shoes, flashlight and the not so usual lubrication for the love birds cause no one wants to see them walk like a penguin after laying trail or each other.', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00047bcb1816fa7199476&ll=38.830414,-77.423058&spn=0.029888,0.055189&z=14">Trail 395</a> </p><p>Start is behind the Giant Food at</p><p><span>5740 Union Mill Road</span><br /><span>Clifton, VA 20124-1130</span></p>', ''),
(395, 'Wa What? Are we really heading out of the beltway and back into SH*T territory or are we just making a cameo appearance.  And of all the places to chose from, the hares decided on Centreville, the 2nd highest concentration of mullets in Virginia!  I guess it could be worse, we could be in Front Royal.  Oh wait, is that a Hillbilly Hasher haring for us?  Wow, this trail is going to be full of surprises.', 'D\'Erections<br />', 'TBD', ' ', '5615 Stone Rd<br />Centreville VA 20120<br />', ''),
(394, 'Chuck Norris\' chin maybe his third fist, but 14K has 14 fart numbing chins. No one including his doctor can get close enough to determine the locations of all his chins, but I\'m sure one of them is tucked in his fanny pack!  There has also been an overwhelming request for 14K to show up with his Santa outfit and Nubs to be his Elf for this XXXmas trail<br />', 'D\'Erections:<br />From the South:<br />From the Beltway (you can find that, right?), take the VA-620 W/BRADDOCK<br />RD WEST exit- EXIT 54A.<br />Go to the first light and Turn LEFT onto PORT ROYAL RD.<br />Go to the right rear on shopping center behind Kilroys<br />Find Wankers and Hash.<br /><br />From the North:<br />Take the Beltway to VA-620W/Braddock Rd., exit 54A.<br />', 'Kilroy\'s!', '<p>Bring some XXXmas attire, change of clothes, shoes, flashlight, and a Red Ryder BB gun<br /></p>', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00047aa42e45d508064cd&ll=38.809818,-77.223287&spn=0.014982,0.027595&z=15">Trail#393</a></p><p>Parking lot behind Kilroy\'s in Ravensworth Shopping Center (Braddock and<br />495/Port Royal Road)<br /><br />5250 Port Royal Rd<br />Springfield, VA 22151<br />(703) 321-7733<br /></p>', ''),
(399, '  &quot;Do you know how I know you\'re Gay?&quot; That\'s the question everyone will be asking the hares when we catch them on trail since they can\'t seem to keep their hands off each other. ', '  From all points VA, MD, DC, take 495 to exit 46B and merge onto Dolley Madison Blvd/VA-123 N toward Chain Br Rd/McLean (.8 mi), turn right at the third traffic light onto Anderson Rd. (.3 mi) turn right into the Safeway parking lot and look for wankers.  If you run into trouble or just for a good time call 978.399.8220.  Passion of the Dumbass is standing by with his uber-sexy voice ready to please you', '  Mark\'s <span style="COLOR: #1f497d">P</span>ub<br />2190 Pimmit Dr # E <br />Falls Church, VA<br /><br />From Start, take a right onto Anderson Rd. (.8 mi), turn left at Frieden Rd. (144ft), take first right onto Pimmit Dr. (.9 mi), go straight through the traffic light at the RTE 7 and Pimmit intersections (obviously waiting for the signal to turn green) and make your first right into the shopping plaza with the Chevy Chase Bank and exercise equipment store.', '  Bring a dry bag, clothes, shoes and some mormon underwear.', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00047d76f7f6177bb1f55&safe=on&ll=38.914411,-77.210884&spn=0.060239,0.108318&z=13">Trail 398</a>  </p><p>Safeway<br />7401 Colshire Dr<br />McLean, VA<br /></p>', ''),
(397, '  Separated at Birth or are they just 2 dudes representing Micheal Jackson from the 80\'s and 90\'s.  Either case, the resemblance is uncanny!  The only way to tell them apart is from the amount of facial hair.', '<span style="COLOR: black">From DC area: Take the toll road towards Dulles, take the Fairfax County Parkway exit toward Herndon.  continue on Parkway for a few miles then take a left onto Weihle Ave.  Take a left at the dead end onto Drainsville Road.  Go about 3/4 mile and turn left onto Bennett and the church is on the immediate right.</span>', '<span style="COLOR: #1f497d">Jimmy’s Old Town Tavern</span><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="COLOR: #1f497d">697 Spring St.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="COLOR: #1f497d">Herndon, VA 20170</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="COLOR: #1f497d">(703) 435-5467</span></p>', ' ', '<p><span style="COLOR: #1f497d"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00047c068e86f62086fe7&safe=on&z=15">Trail 396</a></span></p><p><span style="COLOR: #1f497d">Address for the Methodist Church is:</span><span style="COLOR: #1f497d"> </span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="COLOR: #1f497d">701 Bennett St</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="COLOR: #1f497d"></span><span style="COLOR: #1f497d">Herndon, VA 20170</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="COLOR: #1f497d">(across the street from Herndon HS)</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="COLOR: #1f497d">Parking lot in rear of church</span></p>', ''),
(398, '', '<p>Get a GPS!</p>', '<div>Blue Water Grille </div><div>5127 Westfields Boulevard<br />Centreville, VA 20120<br />(703) 803-1040</div>', 'Bring the usual, dry bag, shoes and flashlight.', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00047cf8a60e5d0307536&safe=on&ll=38.880143,-77.453442&spn=0.047907,0.07699&z=14">Trail#397</a></p><p>Cub Run Recreation Center</p><p>4630 Stonecroft Blvd. </p><p><em><span>Chantilly</span></em>, VA 20151</p>', ''),
(400, 'Narcolingus has been busy eating 5 meals a day, drinking and basting in the sun on a Carribean Cruise.  At least, that what he claims!  This &quot;cruise&quot; sounds more like a drug run, so don\'t be surprised if he starts to poop coke pellets out of his ass as we\'re chasing him down on trail. ', 'From 495 Beltway take Little River Tpke West (Exit 52A) then make the first left onto Pineridge Dr. (this will come up very quickly!) Make an immediate left (less than 15\' from the intersection) onto Accotink Pkwy Take the first left into the ball field parking lot, look for wankers, park and hash.', '<p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">The Sunset Grille<br />7520 Columbia Pike<br />Annandale, VA</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">703-658-0928</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'"><a onclick="function anonymous()\r\n{\r\nfunction anonymous()\r\n{\r\nreturn top.js.OpenExtLink(window,event,this)\r\n}\r\n}" href="http://www.thesunsetgrille.com/" target="_blank">www.thesunsetgrille.com</a></span></p>', 'I gather that we would need the usual change of clothes, shoes and flashlight.', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00047dc2743d7ba35b214&safe=on&ll=38.833657,-77.220991&spn=0.011985,0.02738&t=h&z=16">Trail 399</a></p><p />', ''),
(401, '<p class="MsoNormal">Nuclear Jism, Porn To Fail and She Fingered Me have decided that Gobbler’s Knob and Punxatawney Phil are amateurs when it comes to tunnels. I mean, who REALLY believes that we’re going to have 6 more weeks of winter if Phil sees his shadow? Now, 6 more weeks of shiggy, yep, that we can believe. The only thing we’re really worried about is that we might have to keep repeating this damn trail. So, come on out and join the SHIT on Groundhog Day and help the hares see their shadow so we get (at least) 6 more weeks of shiggy.<span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'"> </span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span></p>', '<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" border="0"><tbody><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"><b>D\'Erections:</b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u> </u></b><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">From DC</span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Take your favorite route to I-395 South  (Shirley Highway) and take exit 7 for Shirlington/Glebe Rd. Stay to the left on the exit ramp and follow the sign toward Shirlington. After crossing under Glebe Rd stay in the right lane and follow the sign for Shirlington exit on the right. At the traffic light at the end of the ramp, continue straight onto S. Arlington Mill Dr. Make a left onto Campbell Avenue and look for the Randolph Square garage. Enter the parking garage and drive to the 5th level. Look for wankers, park and hash.</span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"> <span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">From Points South and anywhere but DC</span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Take your favorite route to I-395 North  (Shirley Highway) and take exit 6 for Shirlington. Stay to the left on the exit ramp and follow the sign toward Shirlington. As you get to the top of the ramp, follow the sign for I-395 South toward Richmond, but get into the right lane and prepare to exit. Take the first right onto Campbell Ave. Look for the Randolph garage to your left after you pass the S. Randolph St. Head up to the 5th level, look for wankers, park, drink and hash</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table>', '<p class="MsoNormal"><br /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Bungalow Billiards and Brew Co.<br />2766 South Arlington Mill Dr<br />Arlington, VA 22206</span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">703-578-0020</span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'"><a href="http://www.bungalow4u.com/" target="_blank"><font color="#2a5db0">www.bungalow4u.com</font></a></span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal"><b>Notes:</b><br /><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">This is an A to B trail and a bag vehicle will be provided – don’t be misled by the fact that the On-On-On is just a few yards away from start. Bring a <b><u>FLASHLIGHT</u></b>, dry bag, clothes, shoes and a furry rodent for the harriettes. Bring a <b><u>FLASHLIGHT!!</u></b></span><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span></p>', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00047e8cf5d270b332eb7&safe=on&ll=38.840995,-77.08894&spn=0.005992,0.009624&t=h&z=17">Trail 400</a></p><p>5th level of the Randolph Square parking garage behind the office building on S. Randolph and Campbell.</p><p>Li<a href="http://www.villageatshirlington.com/FRIT_Shirl_ParkingMap_0933849_V3_hi.pdf">nk with Garage location</a></p>', ''),
(402, '<p>Just Johnny claims to be the Mayor of Arlington. Well, at least his little section of Arlington off of Columbia Pike on 14<sup>th</sup> St. He’s decided that Arlington’s Travel and Tourism folks are doing his little fiefdom a huge disservice since none of the tourists ever come to visit and/or bring beer. Since Johnny is <b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Monotype Corsiva\'">not the type to sit around and bitch about something without trying to fix it</span></b>, he’s decided to direct a walking tour of his little duchy. Snatchosnorous, Porn To Fail and Cradle To The Dreidel have decided that Mismanagement participation might keep the pack from being arrested – but there are no guarantees.<span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'"> </span></p>', '<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" border="0"><tbody><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u> </u></b><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">From DC</span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Take your favorite route to I-395 South  (Shirley Highway) and take exit 7 for Shirlington/Glebe Rd. Stay to the right on the exit ramp and follow the sign toward Glebe Rd. Turn right onto Glebe Rd north and follow it for approximately 1 mile then turn left onto 14<sup>th</sup> Street South. Arrive at 3810 on the left, look for wankers, park and hash.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">From Points South</span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Take your favorite route to I-395 North  (Shirley Highway) and take exit 7B for Glebe Rd. North. Follow Glebe Rd for approximately 1 mile then turn left onto 14<sup>th</sup> Street South. Arrive at 3810 on the left, look for wankers, park and hash.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'"><span style="TEXT-DECORATION: none"> </span></span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">From Points West</span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Take I-66 East to Exit 71 - Fairfax Dr/Glebe Rd., merge onto Fairfax Dr then turn right onto Glebe Rd.  Follow Glebe Rd for approximately 2.3 miles and turn right onto 14<sup>th</sup> Street South. Arrive at 3810 on the left, look for wankers, park and hash.</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table>', '<span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">L.A. Bar and Grill</span><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">2530 Columbia Pike, Arlington, VA 22204</span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">703-685-1560</span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'"><a href="http://www.thelabarandgrill.com/" target="_blank"><font color="#2a5db0">www.thelabarandgrill.com</font></a></span></p>', 'Bring a flashlight, dry clothes/shoes, a redneck, a sheep and your best WV accent.', '<span style="COLOR: #670000"><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="COLOR: red">Start of trail will be at the same location – 3810 14<sup>th</sup> St. South, Arlington, VA – parking for start has changed</span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal">Parking is moved to Randolph Elementary, at Quincy and 14th st s. One block down from the Chevy Chase Bank. Walk down 14th st to start. Questions? Call just Johnny @ 571-329-2825.<br /></p></span><p><span style="COLOR: #670000"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&safe=on&t=k&msa=0&msid=108613836288051853627.00047e39379391693f14b&ll=38.859945,-77.090313&spn=0.007786,0.013797&z=16" target="_blank"><font color="#2a5db0">Trail 401</font></a></span><span style="COLOR: #660000; FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">  </span></p><p>3810 14<sup>th</sup> St S.</p><p>Arlington, VA</p>', ''),
(403, 'What\'s better then Beads, Jugs, Beer and Jugs of Beer on Fat Tuesday? Nothing!  So come on out to the annual S.H.I.F.T Trail and help us celebrate what could be the best trail ever.  Yes, even better then the 400th trail!', 'Get to the Beltway. Take the outer loop to the exit for Telegraph Rd. North. Merge on to Duke St. east. Take a left at Callahan Dr. continue leftish on to Russell Rd. turn right at W. Rosemont Ave. Continue across the boulevard (slight left) to stay on W. Rosemont Ave. Turn right on Mt. Vernon Ave. Go to the end of the street and find the wankers.', '<div class="maxtitle title" jstcache="4" __jsproperties_parsed="true" jsdisplay="i.title||m.laddr" jsvalues="className:(i.place_url?\'maxtitle \':\'\')+\'title\'"><span jstcache="8" __jsproperties_parsed="true" jsdisplay="i.title" jsvalues="lkgtitle:m.ss.lkg.title" lkgtitle="undefined"><span jstcache="17" jsdisplay="!features.embed"><span dir="ltr" jstcache="32" __jsproperties_parsed="true" jsdisplay="!i.linkback||(i.lba&&i.lba.cr8Line1)" jsvalues="innerHTML:i.title;dir:bidiDir(i.title,true)"><b jstcache="0"><div jstcache="0"><span jstcache="53" __jsproperties_parsed="true" jsdisplay="m.b_s!=4" jsvalues="$title:i.title;$laddr:m.laddr;$addrurl:i.addressUrl;lkgal:m.ss.lkg.addresslines;$features:features;$lkgal:m.ss.lkg.addresslines" lkgal="undefined"><span jstcache="8" __jsproperties_parsed="true" jsdisplay="i.title" jsvalues="lkgtitle:m.ss.lkg.title" lkgtitle="undefined"><span jstcache="17" jsdisplay="!features.embed"><span dir="ltr" jstcache="32" __jsproperties_parsed="true" jsdisplay="!i.linkback||(i.lba&&i.lba.cr8Line1)" jsvalues="innerHTML:i.title;dir:bidiDir(i.title,true)"><b jstcache="0">O\' Shaughnessy\'s</b> Pub (formerly Laughing Lizard Lounge</span></span></span><div jstcache="71" __jsproperties_parsed="true" jsvalues="$addrline:$this;" jsinstance="0" jsselect="i.addressLines"><span dir="ltr" jstcache="80" __jsproperties_parsed="true" jsdisplay="$title||!$laddr||!$addrurl" jsvalues=