(405, '<p>SFM is going to celebrate his birthday by giving us the gift of Trail! He has also agreed to hare his SFMirthday trail in a girl scout outfit and fullfill the fantasies of many fellow hashers.  Let\'s hope for some Samoas at the end of trail.</p>', 'Take 66 to 28 north. Take the <b>Westfields Blvd</b> exit toward <strong>Co Rd 662. </strong>Keep <strong>left</strong> at the fork to continue toward <strong>Westfields Blvd.</strong><strong> </strong>Turn <b>right</b> at <strong>Stonecroft Blvd. </strong>Turn <strong>left</strong> at <strong>Conference Center Dr. </strong>Look for wankers in the parking lot of the 2 office buildings that are under construction, park &amp; hash!', '<font face="Tahoma" size="2">Blue Water Grille</font><div dir="ltr"><font face="Tahoma" size="2">5127 Westfields Boulevard<br />Centreville, VA 20120-4366<br />(703) 803-1040</font></div>', '<p>Bring a SFMirthday cake with 69 candles and the usual sh*t! flashlight, dry clothes/shoes/bag.  </p>', '<p><font face="Tahoma" size="2"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.0004806db9c757fe7f2ed&safe=on&ll=38.873828,-77.456188&spn=0.023956,0.038495&z=15">Trail 404</a></font></p><p><font face="Tahoma" size="2">Meet at 6:30pm, hares away at 6:45pm (yeah right).</font></p><p><font face="Tahoma" size="2">15148 Conference Center Dr. Chantilly, VA </font></p><div dir="ltr"><font face="Tahoma" size="2">Start will be in the parking lot of the two office buildings that are currently under construction.</font></div>', ''),
(406, '<p>Apparently, there\'s a theme to this weeks hash: Lebowski (white Russian) - True Grit (eye patches).  Not sure what the &quot;white Russain&quot; is all about, but do we really want to do a Bare trail with 2D vision? </p>', '<p><em><font face="Bookman Old Style" color="#007f40">D\'erections: I-495, Take exit 52A-52B for VA-236/Little River Tpk</font></em><span><em>e toward Fairfax/Annandale 0.2 mi<br />Follow signs for Little River Turnpike/Annandale and merge onto Little River Turnpike/VA-236 E 1.3 mi<br />Make a left at the 2<sup>nd</sup> light (Woodland Rd) and immediately turn left onto the service road in front of McDonalds. Destination will be on the right 0.1 mi</em></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Bookman Old Style\',\'serif\'">.<i><span style="COLOR: #007f40"><br /></span></i></span><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00048111572f1e9f5eba4&safe=on&ll=38.839574,-77.204447&spn=0.015142,0.026135&z=15"></a></p><p />', '<font face="Bookman Old Style" color="#007f40"><em>Sunset Grille<br />7250 Columbia Pike<br />Annandale, VA 22003-3145<br /></em></font><a href="http://thesunsetgrille.com/" target="_blank"><em><font face="Bookman Old Style" color="#2a5db0">thesunsetgrille.com</font></em></a>', '<em><font face="Bookman Old Style" color="#007f40">A to AB Trail, finish is either start or no more than one mile from there (which basically means we\'re f*cked!). Dry bag vehicle provided, so bring some dry clothes. Dogs would be risky, so bring a flashlight instead. White Russian/eye patch or grow a beard and wear a bowling outfit instead.<br />Weather: 54/40 with no chance of snow.</font></em>', '<p><em><font color="#007f40"><font face="Bookman Old Style"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00048111572f1e9f5eba4&safe=on&ll=38.839574,-77.204447&spn=0.015142,0.026135&z=15">Trail#405</a></font></font></em></p><p><em><font color="#007f40"><font face="Bookman Old Style">7620 Little River Turnpike<br />Annandale, VA 22003-2620<span style="COLOR: #1f497d"></span></font></font></em></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN-BOTTOM: 12pt"><span style="COLOR: #007f40; FONT-FAMILY: \'Bookman Old Style\',\'serif\'"><em>Go behind the 2<sup>nd</sup> building behind the Wachovia Bank and park as far from the road as possible</em></span></p>', ''),
(407, '<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Porn To Fail has been ruminating on his Irish heritage in preparation for St Patrick’s Day (because he has nothing else better to do).  Specifically, he’s been wondering about the stories regarding Leprechaun’s that he was told by his mum as a wee lad all those many years ago (50 to be exact). Do they REALLY have a pot of gold or is that just folklore?  Are they REALLY at the end of the rainbow, or was that a Rainblow? (it would appear that his mum introduced him to porn) So He decided to test out his personal theory about whether it’s really gold they’re hiding in those pots by inviting 4 of the cutest Leprechauns he could find to set trail with him.  So, come on out to help Porn and the SHIT Pre-Lube St Patrick’s Day and maybe we’ll find out exactly what those Leprechaun’s are hiding after all (a spoon full of jism).</span></p>', '<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" border="0"><tbody><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Metro</span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Blue or Orange lines to Rosslyn Metro then walk down N Moore St to the Continental and take the stairs up to the parking deck. Look for wankers and hash</span><b><u></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">From DC</span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Take your favorite route to I-66W across the Roosevelt Bridge and follow the exit to Arlington Blvd/US 50W.  Take the first exit toward Rosslyn/Key Bridge and turn right onto N. Lynn St.  Turn left onto 19<sup>th</sup> St N and get into the far right lane as you cross N. Moore St. Follow the service road to your right and enter the first parking lot on your right (BB&amp;T) then continue up ramp to parking deck. Look for wankers, park and hash.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">From Points South</span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Take your favorite route to I-395 North  (Shirley Highway) and take exit 8B for VA 27 S/S Washington Blvd toward Columbia Pike. Follow Rt 27 past the entrance to Ft Myer and take the next exit to Arlington Blvd/Rt 50E toward Washington. Take the exit for Rosslyn/Key Bridge, merge onto N. Meade St. and continue onto N. Lynn St.  Turn left onto 19<sup>th</sup> St N and get into the far right lane as you cross N. Moore St. Follow the service road to your right and enter the first parking lot on your right (BB&amp;T) then continue up ramp to parking deck. Look for wankers, park and hash.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'"> </span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">From Points West</span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Take I-66 East to Exit 73 – Rosslyn/Key Bridge then stay straight onto Rt 29 N/Lee Highway.  As you cross N. Nash St get into the rightmost lane and prepare to exit right toward N. Moore St and N. Lynn St immediately after crossing N. Ft Myer Drive. Turn right onto N. Moore St then right again onto 19<sup>th</sup> St N. Stay in the far right lane, follow the service road to your right and enter the first parking lot on your right (BB&amp;T) then continue up ramp to parking deck. Look for wankers, park and hash..</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table>', '<span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Kitty O’Shea’s</span><p>2403 North Wilson Boulevard<br />Arlington, VA 22201<br />(703) 522-5295<span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'"></span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'"><a href="http://www.kittyosheasva.com/" target="_blank"><font color="#2a5db0">www.kittyosheasva.com</font></a></span></p>', '<span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Bring a flashlight, dry bag, clothes, shoes and a butterfly net to catch a Leprechaun or a PTF.</span>', '<p><span style="COLOR: #670000"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=108613836288051853627.00048184753d328042f6b&ll=38.897446,-77.080078&spn=0.01356,0.038581&t=h&z=15" target="_blank"><font color="#2a5db0">Trail 406</font></a></span><span style="COLOR: #660000; FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">  </span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Parking deck above the Continental</span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">1911 North Fort Myer Drive<br />Arlington, VA 22209</span></p>', ''),
