(410, '<p>Meet between 6:30-7pm. Hares away at 7pm sharp!</p><p>Just for clarification, Fairfax Corner is at the corner of Fairfax otherwise it would simply be called &quot;Fairfax&quot;. The minorities are running the show for this upcoming trail to bring out the highest level of politically incorrectness (is that a word) that SH*T has to offer.  We\'ve got Tikki the eggroll eating Asian, Narco of the Spanish inquisition and Davy the potato farmer from Idaho.  </p>', '<p>From 66 E or W(non-HOV). Take the exit for 7100 N (exit 55). Make the first available right onto FairLakes Pkwy.  At the 3rd stop light, make a right onto Monument Drive.  Stay on the left lane and make a left onto Government Center Pkwy (after going over the 66 overpass). Look for wankers in the parking lot immediately to your left, park &amp; hash!</p><p>For you HOVers coming in on 66 west bound, you can take the Monument Drive exit from the HOV lane, make a left onto Monument then another left onto Government Center Pkwy. Look for wankers in the parking lot immediately to your left, park &amp; hash!</p>', '<p>Uncle Julio\'s</p><p><span>4251 Fairfax Corner Avenue</span><br /><span>Fairfax, VA 22030</span><br /><span>(703) 266-7760</span><br /><span class="msiwpdehp"><font color="#008000">unclejulios.com</font></span></p>', '<p>Bring a Flashlight, Dry bag, shoes, clothes, bug spray sunscreen and your 2010 Census report! </p><p>Dog and stroller Unfriendly for parts of the trail.</p>', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.000483313d9dde10ab126&safe=on&ll=38.857764,-77.358105&spn=0.00599,0.009624&z=17">Trail#409</a></p><p>Parking lot at Fairfax Corner Shopping center. Click the link above for the exact location.</p>', ''),
(411, 'Meet between 6:30-7pm. Hares away at 7pm sharp!<br />PTF is on parole (for tax evasion) and is only allowed to hash once a week which is why the location is not too far from the Fairfax parole board and jail.  Unfortunately for us, he decided to fulfill his other responsibility as our SH*T Harerazor and show up this week to hare a trail. ', 'From 66 E or W take the exit 60 Fairfax/Vienna onto Chain Bridge Rd (Rt 123) South toward Fairfax. Follow Rt 123 for approximately 2 miles and turn left onto Whitehead St. Go one block and turn right onto University Drive. Just before you get to the traffic light at North St turn right into the parking garage, navigate to the 2nd level, look for wankers, park &amp; hash!', 'The Auld Shebeen<br />3971 Chain Bridge Rd <br />Fairfax, VA 220320<br />(703) 293-9600<br />The Auld Shebeen', 'Bring a Flashlight, Dry bag, bug spray, bail money and your IRS Form 4868 (Application for Automatic Extension)!', 'Trail#410<br />Parking garage at the corner of North St and University Drive in Fairfax City. Click the link above for the exact location.', ''),
(412, '<p>Meet at 6:30pm, Hares away around 6:50pm </p><p>The Jews of SH*T will be showcasing the ultimate display of White Flour! Not sure who the mystery hare might be, but I would like to nominate Cradle to the Dradle to complete the family!! </p>', '<p>Jewish D\'erections</p><p>Get to Reston, get going North on Reston Parkway<br />Turn Right onto Lake Newport Road (or left if you are going South)<br />Make your first right (it\'ll have a sign saying something about a pool)<br />Go to the back of the lot, and look for Wankers.</p>', '<p><span>CarPool</span><br /><span>208 Elden Street #100</span><br /><span>Herndon, VA 20170</span><br /><span>(571) 203-7995</span><br /><span class="msiwpdehp"><font color="#008000">carpoolweb.com</font></span><br /></p>', '<p>Friendlies: short people, pot enthusiasts, brave dogs, <br />Unfriendlies: strollers, shiggy-fearful, claustrophobics, acrophobics, hydrophobics</p><p>Stuff: flashlight, dry clothes, shoes, bag and a Yamulka!</p>', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00048460de5039ee4507a&safe=on&ll=38.9861,-77.356024&spn=0.030222,0.052271&z=14">Trail#411</a> </p><p>11601 Lake Newport Rd </p><p>Reston, VA 20194 </p>', ''),
(413, '<p>Since Udder claims that nobody ran his trail or drank his beer out in Herndon earlier this year, he has graciously decided to recycle this trail and see if anybody will show up to run.  Anybody? Anybody? Bueller? Bueller? </p>', '<span style="COLOR: black">From DC area: Take the toll road towards Dulles, take the Fairfax County Parkway exit toward Herndon.  continue on Parkway for a few miles then take a left onto Weihle Ave.  Take a left at the dead end onto Drainsville Road.  Go about 3/4 mile and turn left onto Bennett and the church is on the immediate right.</span>', '<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="COLOR: #1f497d">Carpool</span></p>', '  Short, Wet and Sweet!', '<p><span style="COLOR: #1f497d">Trail 412</span></p><p><span style="COLOR: #1f497d">Address for the Methodist Church is:</span><span style="COLOR: #1f497d"> </span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="COLOR: #1f497d">701 Bennett St</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="COLOR: #1f497d"></span><span style="COLOR: #1f497d">Herndon, VA 20170</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="COLOR: #1f497d">(across the street from Herndon HS)</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="COLOR: #1f497d">Parking lot in rear of church</span></p>', ''),
(417, 'Normally, a negative and a negative makes a positive.  But when we combine PTF and POTD, these 2 negatives still makes a negative! ', 'Get a GPS or an iPhone!', '<p class="MsoNormal">Clare and Don’s Beach Shack</p><p class="MsoNormal">130 North Washington Street<br />Falls Church, VA 22046<br />(703) 532-9283</p>', 'Bring a flashlight, bug spray, ivy block, change of clothes, shoes and a dry bag. A sliderule or a HP reverse Polish calculator, we have to math our way outta this one!', '<p class="MsoNormal"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.0004868ecc9eaddddc2bc&safe=on&ll=38.882226,-77.170774&spn=0.002994,0.004812&z=18">Trail#416</a></p><p class="MsoNormal">Start – parking deck behind Ireland’s 4 Provinces in Falls Church</p><p class="MsoNormal">105 West Broad Street<br />Falls Church, VA 22046</p><p class="MsoNormal">Meet at 6:30pm, Hares away at 6:52pm</p>', ''),
(415, 'It\'s Cinqo de Mayo minus 1 as we kickoff the festivities with a barcrawl.', '<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" border="0"><tbody><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u> </u></b><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">From DC</span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Take your favorite route to I-395 South  (Shirley Highway) and take exit 7 for Shirlington/Glebe Rd. Stay to the right on the exit ramp and follow the sign toward Glebe Rd. Turn right onto Glebe Rd north and follow it for approximately 1 mile then turn left onto 14<sup>th</sup> Street South. Arrive at 3810 on the left, look for wankers, park and hash.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">From Points South</span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Take your favorite route to I-395 North  (Shirley Highway) and take exit 7B for Glebe Rd. North. Follow Glebe Rd for approximately 1 mile then turn left onto 14<sup>th</sup> Street South. Arrive at 3810 on the left, look for wankers, park and hash.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'"><span style="TEXT-DECORATION: none"> </span></span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">From Points West</span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Take I-66 East to Exit 71 - Fairfax Dr/Glebe Rd., merge onto Fairfax Dr then turn right onto Glebe Rd.  Follow Glebe Rd for approximately 2.3 miles and turn right onto 14<sup>th</sup> Street South. Arrive at 3810 on the left, look for wankers, park and hash.</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table>', '<p>TBD</p>', 'Bring your best drinking face, cause this trail is going to get crazy!', '<p>Snatch a Dreidle\'s house</p><p> 3810 14th St S, Arlington, VA  22204</p>', ''),
(416, 'Don\'t say the harerazor never warned us that this is what happens when nobody signs up to hare a trail! Get ready to do some 90 degrees turns (like football practice) cause these halfminds will using Zen Power rather then White Flour!', 'I-495, take exit 54A-54B for Braddock Rd W/VA-620 0.6 mi<br />Slight right at Braddock Rd/VA-620 W 1.0 mi<br />Turn left at Southampton Dr 1.2 mi<br />Turn left at Rolling Rd 0.2 mi<br />Take the 1st right onto Burke Rd<br />The VRE lot will be on the right<br />', 'Kilroys, I-495 &amp; Braddock Rd', 'It\'s a Bare Trail so bring the a flashlight, a compass, tent, sleeping bag, change of clothes, shoes &amp; bag!', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.0004863fbc299e493f158&safe=on&ll=38.800654,-77.239981&spn=0.02398,0.038495&z=15">Trail#414</a></p><p>The Rolling Road (VRE station) located at 9016 Burke Rd in Burke, Virginia </p><p>Meet at 6:30pm Hares away by 6:52pm</p>', ''),
(418, 'Summer is upon and to celebrate this momentus occasion, we are going to do a trail in Vienna. Don\'t get premature and blow your load, I have a feeling Old Man Winter is going to F*ck us over for the next few months!', '<p>D\'Erections from Sterling (yes, you would have to start your trip from Sterling!):  </p><p>Get to Rte. 7 (South and East) towards Vienna.  Take a right turn on Towlston Rd. Towlston turns into Trap Rd and crosses the Toll Road.  Keep trucking on Trap Rd. to a 4 Way stop.  Go straight through to Beulah Rd.  and keep going until you make a right onto Clark\'s Crossing.  Go all the way until the end of Clark\'s Crossing Rd to the park.</p>', 'Vienna Inn, its already cheap', 'You will get wet, bring a dry bag, good humor, and no dignity.  Dog\'s are ok if Rover can swim.  Parking is on the limited side, however plenty of street parking is available on and around the parking lot and off Batton Hollow Rd (just next to the park).', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00048757618aeb5843815&safe=on&ll=38.911472,-77.273369&spn=0.023943,0.038495&z=15">Trail#417</a></p><p>Start:</p><p>Clarks Crossing Park, 9832 Clarks Crossing Rd., Vienna, Virgina (GPS 38.92111,-77.285401)</p><p>Meet at 6:30, Hares away at 6:53</p><p>Bring $5</p>', ''),
(421, 'Porn To Fail is taking a break from the city of brotherly love to spread some brotherly love at the Tour Duh Hash.  Sounds gay if you ask me, but acceptable Hash behavior! ', '<p>Metro: Take the Orange Line to the Dunn Loring Metro Station and walk to 2710 Prosperity Ave.</p><p>From the West. Take 66 to the Nutley (Veinna Metro exit towards Fairfax), make a left onto Route 29 (Lee Highway).  Go a few miles and then make a left onto Prosperity after pass the BMW dealership.  Look for wankers hanging out at 2710 on your left, park &amp; hash.</p><p>From 496 N or S, take the exit for Route 50 towards Fairfax and stay on Route 50 (do not get onto gallows).  Make a right onto Prosperity Ave, go pass the BMW dealership and across rt29. Look for wanders hanging at at 2710 on your left, park and hash</p>', '<p>PTF\'s favorite establishment, Grevy\'s Restaurant</p><p><span>8130 Arlington Boulevard</span><br /><span>Falls Church, VA 22042-1025</span><br /><span>(703) 560-8530</span><br /></p>', 'Dry bag, shoes, clothes, flashlight, ivy block, 100 DET and your best gay outfit.', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00048904b199ead244176&ll=38.873895,-77.231827&spn=0.017474,0.038409&z=15">Trail#420</a></p><p>Parking lot behind 2710 Prosperity Ave Fairfax, VA. (about a half mile walk from the Dunn Loring Metro Station).</font /> </p><p /><p>$5 to play.  6:30 sign in/Happy Hour. Hare away at 7pm </p>', ''),
(419, 'The mind tends to shut down for a long weekend so I can\'t think of a ridiculous/insulting/dumbass name for this trail.  I had considered &quot;The Retard (pronounced like in the Hangover) Trail&quot; or &quot;The Three Incontinent Hares Trail&quot;, but none of them seem to click.  So we\'re stuck with a boring title and the only thing to look forward to is beer/trail/karoake and sex.', 'Take I-66 to the exit for Rt. 50 west. Get over to the right, and get on the exit for West Ox Rd south. In about a 1/4 mile over the bridge you will see the Fairfax Town Center shopping complex on your right. Turn into there, and drive to the bakc of the shopping center to find the wankers parked and libating in true SH*TTY fashion.', '<p>The Blue Iguana</p><p><span>12727 Shoppes Lane</span><br /><span>Fairfax, VA 22033-3834</span><br /><span>(703) 502-9877</span><br /><span class="msiwpdehp"><font color="#008000">theblueiguana.com</font></span><br /></p>', 'Dry shoes, clothes, bag, ivy block, Insect spray (10000 DET)', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.000487a7e416278e6ca97&safe=on&ll=38.86758,-77.372203&spn=0.023958,0.038495&z=15">Trail#418</a></p><p>Fairfax Towne Center</p>', ''),
(420, 'Half the hares on this list is broken in some way, shape or form and the other half is mentally challenged. I wouldn\'t be surprised if the trail just runs around in circles like a hamster that visited a microwave for about 5 seconds. ', '<p>From 66, take the exit for Route 50 west towards Chantilly.  Take the exit for West Ox Road North (Rt 608), this exit will be on your right and will come up quickly after getting onto Route 50 so employ those Formula 1 driving skills!  Take Rt 602 when the road splits.  Make a left onto Fox Mill Rd and look for the shopping center on your left.  Find Wanker roaming about, park &amp; hash!</p>', 'Glory Days, Fox Mill Shopping Plaza', 'Bring a change of clothes, shoes, bag, Ivy blok, insect repellent, crutches and prozac for the hares.', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.0004880ccd3cc4e57912b&safe=on&ll=38.928451,-77.376645&spn=0.011969,0.019248&z=16">Trail#419</a></p><p>Fox Mill Shopping Plaza, off of Reston Pkwy.  </p><p>2579 John Milton Drive, Herndon, VA</p><p>Bring 5 dolla.  Meet between 6:30-7pm. Hare away at 6:58:23</p>', ''),
(422, '<p />', '<table style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" border="0"><tbody><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">From DC</span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Take I-395 South for about 9 miles once you get into Virginia, then take Exit 1-B toward Springfield.  Stay slightly left on the exit ramp toward Old Keene Mill Rd and follow it approximately 3 miles to Rolling Rd.  Immediately after crossing Rolling Rd turn right into the shopping center, look for wankers, park and hash.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">From Points South</span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Take I-95 North toward Washington and take Exit 169B to merge onto Franconia Rd (Va 644W) toward Springfield. Franconia Rd becomes Old Keene Mill Rd once you pass to the other side of I-95. Follow Old Keene Mill Rd for approximately 3 miles to Rolling Rd.  Immediately after crossing Rolling Rd turn right into the shopping center, look for wankers, park and hash.</span></p></td></tr><tr><td><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'"> </span></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><u><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">From Points West</span></u></b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Take your favorite route to the 495 Beltway headed East/South and take Exit 57A for Va 644. Take Exit 169B for Old Keene Mill Road (Va 644W) and follow it approximately 3 miles to Rolling Rd.  Immediately after crossing Rolling Rd turn right into the shopping center, look for wankers, park and hash.</span></p></td></tr></tbody></table>', '<span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Hard Times Cafe</span><p>6362 Springfield Plaza<br />Springfield VA 22150 <br />(703) 913-5600</p>', 'Bring a change of clothes, shoes, bag, ivy block, 100DET.  ', '<p><span style="COLOR: #670000"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&ll=38.781856,-77.207193&spn=0.026763,0.077162&z=14&msid=109641920061106691785.0004895505c955f5deaf1" target="_blank"><font color="#2a5db0">Trail 421</font></a></span><span style="COLOR: #660000; FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">  </span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Parking lot in front of:</span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">Washington Sports Club</span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: \'Georgia\',\'serif\'">8430-C Old Keene Mill Road <br />Springfield, VA 22152</span></p>', ''),
(423, 'Let\'s get retodded, let\'s get retodded in here! Come out to what is sure to be a shiggy laden trail as Coppus\' hums his way to the tune of the Black Eyed Peas and brings us back to the town Herndon. Our own Tikki Tooki Timbo No See Nimbo Booey Hooey Bushy Fooey Pom Pom Nikki Nomi Echo Fooey-O has collaborated with Glory days to bring everyone the Tikki Tooki Triple Sliders!  I\'m sure it\'s what everyone\'s been yearning for, a piece of Tikki in their mouth!', '<p>No Metro, just Auto! </p><p>From 66, take the exit for Route 50 west towards Chantilly.  Take the exit for West Ox Road North (Rt 608), this exit will be on your right and will come up quickly after getting onto Route 50 so employ those Formula 1 driving skills!  Take Rt 602 when the road splits.  Make a left onto Fox Mill Rd and look for the shopping center on your left.  Find Wanker roaming about, park &amp; hash!</p>', '<font color="#1f497d">Glory Days, Fox Mill Plaza </font><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt; COLOR: #1f497d">(Featuring the Tiki Tooki Triple Sliders!!!!) </span></p>', '<font color="#1f497d">Bring a Dry Bag, flashlight, really good bug spray with DEET, a machete, rosary beads, and a Sherpa or two.   Oh and one last thing, bring lots of DEET!</font>', '<p><font color="#1f497d"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.0004880ccd3cc4e57912b&safe=on&ll=38.925838,-77.374831&spn=0.005985,0.009624&z=17">Trail#422</a></font></p><p><font color="#1f497d">Happy Half Hour 6:30, Hares away at 6:59:59</font></p><font color="#1f497d"><p>Fox Mill Shopping Plaza, off of Reston Pkwy.  </p><p>2579 John Milton Drive, Herndon, VA</p></font>', ''),
