(426, 'Passion of a Dumbass was playing around with Google one day and saw that today’s date is when Neil Armstrong became the first man to step on the moon in 1969.  Since he fancies himself to be as badass as an astronaut, he attempted to “Go Around the World” with his Oh-So-Hot girlfriend Toona-Piano. Once she had stopped laughing about his delusions of grandeur, she reminded him of how she got the 2nd part of her hash name. Passion hung his head in shame and slunk off to be comforted by his boy-toy/man-slave Wreath Around. Regardless of the Passion Play, come on out to a trail that is bound to be “Out of This World”!', '<p> From DC<br />Take your favorite route to I-66W across the Roosevelt Bridge and follow it for a damn long time then take Exit 62 - Va 243N/Nutley Street SW toward Vienna. Turn right onto Rt 123N/Maple Ave W and drive 1 mile to Glyndon Street NE. Turn left onto Glyndon Street NE  and arrive at Glyndon Park on your right after .2 mile.  Look for wankers, park and hash.</p><p><br /> <br />From Points West<br />Take I-66 East to Exit 62 - Va 243N/Nutley Street SW toward Vienna.  Turn right onto Rt 123N/Maple Ave W and drive 1 mile to Glyndon Street NE. Turn left onto Glyndon Street NE  and arrive at Glyndon Park on your right after .2 mile.  Look for wankers, park and hash.</p>', 'Vienna Inn<br />120 Maple Ave East<br />Vienna, VA 22180<br />(703) 938-9548', 'Trail is A to A’ with a Bag Vehicle provided by your esteemed Hares because, gosh, we care so much about you it’s almost creepy.  Bring a flashlight, change of: clothes, bag, shoes, Ivy Block, and Bug Spray.  PI factor is low.  Shiggy factor is low.  You will encounter water, possibly up to mid-thigh.  Technology on trail is not recommended (READ: Wreath, quit takin’ your damn phone with you!)', '<p><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=109641920061106691785.0004895505c955f5deaf1&ll=38.904176,-77.25764&spn=0.011271,0.019205&z=16">Trail#425</a></p><p>Glyndon Park<br 