(428, 'It\'s time for another Fingerless trail and he has turned over a whole new leaf (This doesn\'t even make sense!).  Fingers has acquired a bi-ped machinery and is going to lay the trail with it!  It has become the love of his life and rides it everyday, if you know what I mean!', '<p>Automobile:</p><p>From the East: Take 66W to exit 57B Route 50 towards Chantilly.  Go 4.43752 miles and make a left onto Walney Rd.  Go 0.5 mile and make a right at Willard Rd.  Go another 0.5 mile and make a right at Daly Dr.  Look for Wankers in the parking lot, pay $5 and hash!</p><p>From the West: Take 66E to exit 53 and head onto 28 North. Go 3.2 miles and exit onto Willard Rd.  Go 0.2mile and make a left at Daly Dr.Head straight to the Chantilly Shopping  Ctr.  Look for Wankers in the parking lot, pay $5 and hash!</p>', 'Bungalow Billiards<div>13891 Metrotech Drive<br />Chantilly, VA 20151-3245<br />(703) 502-3925</div>', 'Bring the usual stuff, dry bag, shoes, clothes, 1000 DET, a guitar and fast acting Tinactin', '<p><span style="font-size: 11pt; "><font face="Times New Roman" size="3"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00048cd85e7f643318b64&safe=on&ll=38.894039,-77.437563&spn=0.024016,0.038495&z=15">Trail#427</a></font></span></p><p><span style="font-size: 11pt; "><font face="Times New Roman" size="3">Dulles Expo Center parking lot</font></span></p><p><span style="font-size: 11pt; ">4368 Chantilly Shopping Ctr<br />Chantilly, VA 20153</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 11pt; ">Happy Half hour at 6:30pm, Hares away at 7pm</span></p>', ''),
(429, 'We know that the S.H.*.T. likes it\'s shiggy and normally we would agree. Designer Bush didn\'t like to run though, because she didn\'t want to spill her beer. In honor of her this week, we are having a &quot;Pretty in Pink&quot;, no frills, limited shiggy trail. We will have toe tags available for a mininum $5.00 donation (that\'s in addition to Hash Cash!) and all proceeds will go to a breast cancer charity. So... wear your prettiest pink outfit and come drink a beer in rememberance of one of the hash\'s finest.', '<p>METRO ACCESSIBLE!! Exit the King Street Station and follow marks to start.</p><p>Driving: From the Beltway... Take EXIT 177 for U.S. Route 1, North. Turn LEFT onto King Street. Turn RIGHT onto Commonwealth Avenue. Turn RIGHT onto W. Rosemount Avenue. Turn RIGHT onto Mt. Vernon Avenue. Go to the end, park, and hash.</p>', '<p>Murphy\'s ~ 713 King Street, Alexandria, VA</p>', 'Trail will be A-B, minimal shiggy, but yes... there will be SOME shiggy, so be prepared.', '<p>The park at the end of the <a title="Cul-de-sac" href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&q=20+Mt+Vernon+Avenue,+Alexandria,+VA+22301&um=1&ie=UTF-8&hq=&hnear=20+Mt+Vernon+Ave,+Alexandria,+VA+22301&gl=us&ei=2x1cTIScBMGB8ga0x6nNAg&sa=X&oi=geocode_result&ct=title&resnum=1&ved=0CBcQ8gEwAA">cul-de-sac on Mt. Vernon Avenue</a>, Alexandria, VA. Same start as our Mardi Gras Hash earlier this year. </p>', ''),
