(432, '<span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-fareast-font-family: "><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">Okay… so… this WAS going to be “Just” Another BUSH Trail, however, it IS “Porn-to-Fails” 60<sup>th</sup> Birthday trail!!</span></p><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt"></span></p><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">WHOA!! How can anyone be so old!?! (sorry “Spinal Tap”, “Mellow…” et al)</span></p><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt"></span></p><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">Hummm… I remember when some un-named female hasher was turning 30 and she was so ticked... that when she laid her 30th birthday trail… she had three back-check 30s!! She figured that since she was so pissed about getting old… she might as well make everyone else pissed off!!</span></p><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt"></span></p><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">However… the good thing this week is that this wanker is so old… I don’t think he’ll be able to get in one back-check 60!! But… I wouldn’t put it past him. He IS, however, a good one for wanting to get everyone wet!! So… in that case… I’d come prepared!!</span></p><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt"></span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: ">But… the ‘real’ questions is… what will it say to those wankers that can’t catch a couple of old-farts haring a live trail?</span></p></span>', '<p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">From Sterling/Herndon/Reston (and Points West): </span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold">Find your way to the beltway via Route 7 East or Dulles Toll Road (Route 267) East or a combination thereof. Take Interstate 495 South (Outerloop) toward Alexandria/Richmond. Take <b>EXIT 54A</b> for <b><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Braddock Road </i></b><b><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">(Route 620) West</i></b> and follow either of the 2 options below:</span></p><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold"></span><strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">Option One:</span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold"> Go 1 mile and take a <b>LEFT</b> at the light for <b><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">South Hampton Drive</i></b>. Continue on <b><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">South Hampton Drive </i></b>for 1.2 miles and take a <b>LEFT</b> onto <b><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Rolling Road</i></b>. Cross over the railroad tracks and take your <b>1<sup>st</sup> LEFT</b> onto <b><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Morriessette Drive</i></b>. Take the <b>1<sup>st</sup> RIGHT</b> into the <b><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Union Bank &amp; Trust Co.</i></b> parking lot and look for wankers milling around.</span></p><p /><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold"></span><strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">Option Two:</span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold"> Otherwise known as… if you miss South Hampton Drive!! Take a <b>LEFT</b> at the light for <b><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Burke Lake Road</i></b>. Take a <b>LEFT</b> at the <b>1<sup>st</sup> light</b> onto <b><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Rolling Road </i></b>and continue on <b><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Rolling Road </i></b>until you cross over the railroad tracks. After you cross over the railroad tracks… take your <b>1<sup>st</sup> LEFT</b> onto <b><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Morriessette Drive</i></b>. Take the <b>1<sup>st</sup> RIGHT</b> into the <b><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Union Bank &amp; Trust Co.</i></b> parking lot and look for wankers milling around.</span></p><p /><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"></span><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">From the Beltway I-495…<br /></span></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">From the Beltway… Same as above… except… you’re NOT cumming from Sterling/Herndon/Reston!!</span></p><p />', '<p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"><a href="http://www.google.com/maps?f=l&hl=en&q=kilroys&near=Morrissette+Dr,+Springfield,+VA+22152,+USA&sll=38.799066,-77.242148&sspn=0.007124,0.014462&ie=UTF8&latlng=38809261,-77219905,7910600826728563109&ei=3MNlRqioF43grQKdvKWHCg&cd=1"><b>Kilroys</b></a><span class="detls2">: </span></span>5250 Port Royal Road</street />, <city w:st="on" />Springfield</city />, <state w:st="on" />VA</state /><span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span><postalcode w:st="on" />22151-2117 ~ <span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">703.321.7733</span></p><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"></span></p><p style="MAR