(433, '<p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">OH MY!! ANOTHER Watergate Birthday? Trail!?!</span></p><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt"></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">Hey… “Lube…” here’s your chance of getting back at Watergate!!</span></p><p /><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt"></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">Let’s Celebrate Watergate!! On Tuesday!! She is even bringing us back toward Sh*t Hash House territory!! Hummm… interesting… two of her co-hares also live in <place w:st="on" />Reston</place /> and then there is some wanker (that’s NOT “Corn on the C*ck”) from Herndon!!</span></p><p /><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt"></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-fareast-font-family: ">Last week… we celebrated “Porn-To-Fail’s” 60<sup>th</sup> Birthday… this week… it’s… “Watergate, what number was that again?”</span> </p><p />', '<p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">From Sterling/Herndon (and Points West):</span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold"></span></p><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold">Find your way to Route 7 East towards Tysons/Falls Church. Take a <b>RIGHT</b> onto <street w:st="on" /></span></p><address w:st="on"><b>Baron Cameron Road</b>. Continue past Wiehle Avenue and turn <b>RIGHT</b> onto <b><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Village Road/Brown Chapel Road</i></b>. Take your immediate <b>RIGHT</b> and “head” towards the back parking lot. Park and look for wankers milling around. </address><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold"></span><strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">From DC Area (and Points East):</span></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold"> <br /></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">From the Beltway… Take the <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">EXIT </b>for the <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Dulles Toll Road</i></b><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">/Route 267</i></b> (contribute to the bins as you go through the main toll plaza). Continue on the <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Dulles Toll Road</i></b><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">/Route 267</i></b> for approx. 9.5 miles and take the <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">EXIT</b> for <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Wiehle Avenue </i></b>(additional contributions needed!!). Turn <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">RIGHT</b> onto <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Wiehle Avenue</i></b> and continue for approx. 2.0 miles. Turn <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">LEFT </b>onto </span><b><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt">Baron Cameron Road </span></i></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold">and then your first <b>RIGHT</b> onto <b><i style="mso-bidi-font-style: normal">Village Road/Brown Chapel Road</i></b>. Take your immediate <b>RIGHT</b> and “head” towards the back parking lot. Park and look for wankers milling around.</span></p><p />', '<p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; COLOR: black; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Somewhere in <place w:st="on" />RESTON</place />!!</span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"></span></p><p /><div style="BORDER-BOTTOM: windowtext 1pt solid; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; PADDING-BOTTOM: 1pt; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: medium none; BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-TOP: 0in; mso-element: para-border-div; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid windowtext .75pt"><p style="BORDER-BOTTOM: medium none; BORDER-LEFT: medium none; PADDING-BOTTOM: 0in; MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt; PADDING-LEFT: 0in; PADDING-RIGHT: 0in; BORDER-TOP: medium none; BORDER-RIGHT: medium none; PADDING-TOP: 0in; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid windowtext .75pt; mso-padding-alt: 0in 0in 1.0pt 0in" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt"></span></p><p /></div><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-fareast-font-family: ">Specials: TBA</span>', '<p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Miscellaneous:</span></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"> Trail is A to A, A to A’, A to B, but I wouldn’t rule out A to Z!!</span></p><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"></span></p><p /><p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial">Final Disclaimer:</span></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-family: Arial"> Bring dry clothes and shoes, bug spray, sunscreen, condoms, your grandmother’s underwear and because it is that time of the year… should we remind you of… shiggy-socks and/or PI Block.</span></p><p /><p> </p>', '<p style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" class="MsoNormal"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; COLOR: #660000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&ie=UTF8&q=Brown%27s+Chapel,+Reston,+VA+20194&fb=1&gl=us&hq=Brown%27s+Chapel,&hnear=Reston,+VA+20194&view=map&cid=7772952644292550143&iwloc=A"><font color="#800080">Brown’s Chapel</font></a></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-bidi-font-weight: bold">: <place w:st="on" /><city w:st="on" /><span style="COLOR: #780000">Reston</span></city /><span style="COLOR: #780000">, <state w:st="on" />VA</state /> <postalcode w:st="on" />20194</postalcode /></span></place /></span><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; COLOR: #780000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt"></span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia; COLOR: #660000; FONT-SIZE: 11pt; mso-fareast-font-family: ">Trail will be… <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal">A to A or A to A’ or A to B, but I wouldn’t rule out A to Z!!</b> </span></p>', ''),
(434, '<div><strong><font color="#0080ff" size="5">Sunny day,</font></strong></div><div style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: \'times new roman\', \'new york\', times, serif"><div style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; FONT-FAMILY: \'times new roman\', \'new york\', times, serif"><div style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt; COLOR: rgb(0,0,0); FONT-FAMILY: \'times new roman\', \'new york\', times, serif"><div><strong><font color="#0080ff" size="5"><font color="#0000cc">S.H.I.T.in</font>\' our days away,<br />On my way to where the trails are shiggy! <br /><br />Can you tell me how to get <br />How to get to So Happy It\'s Tuesday <span class="il"><font style="BACKGROUND-COLOR: rgb(255,255,136)" color="#222222">AGM</font></span>!!!</font></strong></div><p><strong></strong> </p><p><strong>In just six short weeks from now So Happy It\'s Tuesday will be turning EIGHT YEARS OLD!!! Come celebrate this momentous occasion.</strong></p></div></div></div>', 'GPS', ' ', '<strong>The cost of registration will be $30 to pre-register, and a $35 fee for day-of\'s. This will get you a trail, beer, more trail, beer (beer), a fantastic t-shirt designed by Poonskin Cap and Stick It In My Socket (that you will probably spill beer on), BEER, <font size="1">beer, </font><font size="3">some other crap that we will try to pawn off on you, cause we haven\'t been able to all year, and some beer too!</font></strong>', '<p><strong>American Legion Post #139 on N. Washington Blvd. in Arlington, VA.</strong></p><p><strong>Sign-In will begin at 600PM... Happy half hour at 630PM... Hares away at 700PM... Pack away shortly thereafter.</strong></p>', ''),
(435, '<p>What\'s the good thing about welcoming in a new MisManagement? EVERYTHING IS LATE!! The hareline... directions to the next trail... the website. But just remember... it gets BETTER after this!! After all... IT HAS TO!! There\'s no place to go but up!!</p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b>(Metro)</b></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Not without some serious dedication but if you feel like a 4 mile run before trail Franconia <span class="yshortcuts" id="lw_1284385251_3" style="CURSOR: hand; BORDER-BOTTOM: #366388 2px dotted">Springfield</span> is about as close as we are getting</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" /><p> </p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b>(Driving)</b></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b>From inside the Beltway:</b></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Get yer butt to 395 and head south</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Take exit 1B for I-95 N/I-495 E toward Baltimore</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Take exit 169B for </p><address>Old Keene Mill Rd</address>toward Springfield <p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Slight right at </p><address>Old Keene Mill Rd</address><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Take a right onto </p><address>Hanover Ave.</address><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Turn left at </p><address>Highland St</address><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Right at </p><address>Accotink Park Rd</address><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Continue past Accotink Park entrance on Southern Dr</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Where road comes to a fork bear left </p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Wankers will be in the back corner of the parking lot by <span class="yshortcuts" id="lw_1284385251_4" style="CURSOR: hand; BORDER-BOTTOM: #366388 2px dotted">Iron Mountain</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" /><p> </p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b>From the West</b></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Get yer butt to the Beltway (495) and head south</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Take exit 57A for I-95 S toward Richmond</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Take exit 169B for </p><address>Old Keene Mill Rd</address>toward Springfield <p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Slight right at </p><address>Old Keene Mill Rd</address><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Take a right onto </p><address>Hanover Ave.</address><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Turn left at </p><address>Highland St</address><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Right at </p><address>Accotink Park Rd</address><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Continue past Accotink Park entrance on Southern Dr</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Where road comes to a fork bear left </p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Wankers will be in the back corner of the parking lot by Iron Mountain</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt" /><p> </p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b><span class="yshortcuts" id="lw_1284385251_5" style="CURSOR: hand; BORDER-BOTTOM: #366388 2px dotted">From the South</span></b></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Get yer butt to 95 North</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Take exit 169A-B toward Springfield</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Merge onto </p><address>Franconia Rd</address><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Continue on </p><address>Old Keene Mill Rd</address><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Take a right onto </p><address>Hanover Ave.</address><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Turn left at </p><address>Highland St</address><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Right at </p><address>Accotink Park Rd</address><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Continue past Accotink Park entrance on Southern Dr</p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Where road comes to a fork bear left </p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt">Wankers will be in the back corner of the parking lot by Iron Mountain</p>', '<p>Hard Times Cafe<br /><span class="yshortcuts" id="lw_1284389229_0" style="BACKGROUND: none transparent scroll repeat 0% 0%; CURSOR: hand; BORDER-BOTTOM: #366388 2px dotted">6362 Springfield Plz<br />Springfield, 22150-3431</span><br /><span class="yshortcuts" id="lw_1284389229_1" style="CURSOR: hand; BORDER-BOTTOM: #366388 2px dotted">1 (703) 913-5600</span></p>', ' ', '<p>Springfield (Sorry Watergate!!)</p><div class="title" dir="ltr" align="left"><a title="Trail 434" href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&msid=100897786795564762528.00049024e1abdeb5b5211&ll=38.789081,-77.211871&spn=0.03141,0.030384&t=h&z=15">Trail 434</a></div><div class="description" dir="ltr" align="left">Iron Mountain Parking Lot <br />7726 Southern Dr <br />Springfield, VA 22150</div><span style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt"></span>', ''),
(436, '  <p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">To borrow a piece of ransom musing from “Lube Me Up Scottie’s” 30<sup>th</sup> Birthday trail (held not to far from this week’s location):</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">“Trail is guaranteed to be short (I\'m old now and can\'t run far), flat (I\'m old now and can\'t run hills), dry (I\'m old now and hate running with wet feet), and poison ivy free (I\'m old now and don\'t heal very quickly)”.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> </span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">That being said… I have two things to offer:</span></p><ol style="MARGIN-TOP: 0in" type="1"><li class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">How do you lay a trail that’s NOT effed up? You hare it yourself and…</span> </li><li class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">What happens if you get caught? You call it a “Pick-Up Trail”!!</span></li></ol>', '  <strong><font face="Georgia">From Sterling/Reston: </font></strong><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">Take <b>Route 267/Dulles <span class="yshortcuts" id="lw_1284643352_4" style="BACKGROUND: none transparent scroll repeat 0% 0%; CURSOR: hand; BORDER-BOTTOM: medium none">Toll Road EAST</span></b>. Pass under (or over… which ever is your choice) the beltway. Take the <b>FIRST EXIT</b> onto <b><i><span class="yshortcuts" id="lw_1284643352_5">Chain Bridge Road</span></i></b> towards Tyson\'s Corner. Take a <b>RIGHT</b> onto <b><i>Route 123/Dolly Madison Boulevard</i></b> (or it could be called <b><i>Chain Bridge Road</i></b> ). Take your <b>1<sup>st</sup> LEFT</b> onto <b><i>Colshire Drive</i></b> and then your <b>1<sup>st</sup> LEFT</b> into the parking lot at the corner of Colshire Drive and Route 123. Proceed to the back parking lot and look for wankers, park and hash.</span><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span> </p><p><b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">From 66:</span></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> Take 66 East and bear <b>RIGHT</b> onto <b><i>Route 267/Toll Road Extension</i></b>. Take <b>EXIT 19A</b> for <b><i>Route 123/Dolly Madison Boulevard</i></b> (or it could be called <b><i>Chain Bridge Road</i></b>) towards Tyson’s Corner. Take your <b>2<sup>nd</sup> LEFT</b> onto <b><i>Colshire Drive</i></b> and then your <b>1<sup>st</sup> LEFT</b> into the parking lot at the corner of Colshire Drive and Route 123. Proceed to the back parking lot and look for wankers, park and hash. </span></p><p><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"></span> </p><p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia">From Points South:</span></b><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"> Find your way to the beltway… Take <b><i>I-495</i></b> toward Tyson\'s Corner. Take <b>EXIT 46B</b> for <b><i>Route 123/Dolly Madison Boulevard</i></b> (or it could be called <b><i>Chain Bridge Road</i></b> toward McLean . Take your <b>2<sup>nd</sup> RIGHT</b> onto <b><i>Colshire Drive</i></b> and then your <b>1<sup>st</sup> LEFT</b> into the parking lot at the corner of Colshire Drive and Route 123. Proceed to the back parking lot and look for wankers, park and hash.</span></p>', '  <p class="MsoNormal" style="MARGIN: 0in 0in 0pt"><span style="FONT-FAMILY: Georgia"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&expIds=17259,24472,24815,25901,26094,26206,26446,26512,26563,26565&sugexp=ldymls&tok=GW9qtE0I2YO2PgrSzP0rug&xhr=t&q=6827+Redmond+Drive,+McLean,+VA&cp=30&wrapid=tljp128458485228810&um=1&ie=UTF-8&sa=N&tab=wl" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"><font color="#800080"><span class="yshortcuts" id="lw_1284643352_6">“The Pub”</span></font></a>: 