(437, 'So apparently And How\'s Her Bush got worried that The Udder Ho was going to catch up to his hare count, since he was haring a lot over the summer. Soooooo, AHHB has taken it upon himself to hare every single trail for So Happy It\'s Tuesday in the Hash Calendar Year 2011.... YOU KNOW WHAT THIS MEANS!!!! Actually I don\'t either... hopefully no more shorty shorts with winter coming, though!', '<p>From the west:</p><p>~Get on I-66 towards the beltway (east you dummy).</p><p>~Take exit 64A to merge onto I-495 S toward Richmond 1.5 mi </p><p><br />~Take the US-50 E/Arlington Blvd exit toward Arlington 0.5 mi </p><p><br />~Slight left at US-50 E/Arlington Blvd 1.1 mi</p><p /><p>~Turn right at Graham Rd 0.7 mi </p><p><br />~Turn right at Camp Alger Ave Destination will be on the left 466 ft </p><p>End at: 7119 Camp Alger Ave Falls Church, VA 22042<br /></p>', '<p> Greveys Restaurant and Bar<br />  8130 Arlington Blvd, Falls Church, VA 22042 <br />  (703)560-8530 </p><p><font size="5">KARAOKE!!!</font></p>', 'Trail is A2A... It is hasher friendly, runner friendly, walker friendly, human friendly, stripper friendly, octopus friendly... <font size="1">but not idiot friendly</font>', '<p><a title="Trail 436" href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?oe=UTF-8&ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&ll=38.858357,-77.196207&spn=0.062759,0.059566&t=h&z=14&msid=100897786795564762528.000490edca4d0e1b44f12">Trail 436</a> </p><p><span class="yshortcuts" id="lw_1285250269_0" style="CURSOR: hand; BORDER-BOTTOM: #366388 2px dotted">7119 Camp Alger Ave., Falls Church, VA 22042</span></p>', ''),
(438, 'We have been in and around the beltway for the last handful of trails... All The Way in decided that it was time to put a little country bumpkin back into the SH*T hashers! That\'s right, pack your bags, and fill up the gas tank, cause we are gonna go ALL THE WAY to the far side of Centreville!', '<p>From Da East:</p><p>~Get on I-66 and head towards the sunset (west, do I really have to spell it out every time?)</p><p>~Take exit 52 for US-29 toward Centreville 0.3 mi </p><p>~Turn right at US-29 S/Lee Hwy 2.1 mi </p><p>~Turn right at Bull Run Post Office Rd/State Route 621 2.5 mi </p><p>~Stay straight on Bull Run Post Office Rd where it meets Sudley Rd 0.3 mi</p><p>~Take left on to Glory Creek... drive to the end, which is the Cul-De-SACK</p>', '<p>Fast Eddie\'s Centreville</p><p>14114 Lee Hwy<br />Centreville, VA 20120-1913<br />(703) 266-8888<br /></p>', 'It is highly suggested that you bring pants or long socks.... But since we bein all redneck, Ima sure everyone is gonna be wearin them some overalls!', '<p><a title="Trail 437" href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?oe=UTF-8&ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&ll=38.856269,-77.516999&spn=0.01569,0.014892&t=h&z=16&msid=100897786795564762528.000490ee38cfbe18482bb">Trail 437</a></p><p>Post Office Rd. and some back woods dirt road Cul-De-SACK!</p>', ''),
