(465, '<p class="MsoPlainText" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; "><font face="Consolas">~Okay… so… how many times have you heard that “START” is in the “parking lot behind the office building”? Once? Twice? Many? Yes… MANY times!! So… it wouldn’t be such a surprise to hear that last week’s trail was starting in the “parking lot behind the office building”!!</font></p><p class="MsoPlainText" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; " /><p><font face="Consolas">As a matter of fact… that ‘parking lot’ was so well hidden… that many hashers had trouble finding it!!</font></p><p class="MsoPlainText" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; " /><p><font face="Consolas">However… you just may want to check… just what ‘office building(s)that (those) is (are)!! ~ Just saying!!</font></p><p class="MsoPlainText" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; " /><p><font face="Consolas">This week’s “START” will be at the Federal Prison... ***HEY BUSH… THAT IS NOT FUNNY!!***</font></p><p class="MsoPlainText" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; " /><p><font face="Consolas">“Oops… My Bad!!” ~AHHB</font></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; "><b><span>FROM <city w:st="on"><place w:st="on">STERLING</place></city>:</span></b><span> Find your way to the Beltway (that was easy!!)…</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; "><b><span>FROM I-495 (Beltway):</span></b></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; "><b><i><span>Take I-66 West</span></i></b><span> (and traffic SUCKS during that time!!) and take the <b>EXIT 57A</b> for <b><i>Route 50, East</i></b> (the second exit for Route 50 towards <place w:st="on"><city w:st="on">Fairfax</city></place>). Continue on Route 50 for approx. 1½ miles and turn <b>RIGHT</b> onto <b><i>Route 29</i></b>. Continue past the Shell station (on your right) and Next Day Blinds (on your left) and turn <b>RIGHT</b> into the office buildings at:</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p><p><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(102, 0, 0); "><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&sugexp=ldymls&xhr=t&q=11096+Lee+Highway,+Fairfax+VA&cp=27&bav=on.2,or.r_gc.r_pw.&wrapid=tljp1302190002032050&um=1&ie=UTF-8&hq=&hnear=11096+Lee+Hwy,+Fairfax,+VA+22030&gl=us&ei=wdedTcHdFJLAgQf_0e3RBA&sa=X&oi=geocode_result&ct=title&resnum=1&sqi=2&ved=0CBoQ8gEwAA"><font color="#800080">Fair Oaks Square</font></a></span><span style="font-size: 12pt; ">: 11092 (front) – 11096 (rear) </span></p><p /><p /><address w:st="on"><street w:st="on">Lee Highway</street>, <city w:st="on">Fairfax</city>, <state w:st="on">VA</state><span>&nbsp;</span><postalcode w:st="on">22030</postalcode></address>', '<p><span>John’s Place (speaking of ‘dive’ bars… you’ll love this place!!) </span></p><p><span></span><span>11104 Lee Highway</span><br /><city w:st="on"><span>Fairfax</span></city><span>, <state w:st="on">VA</state> <postalcode w:st="on">22030</postalcode></span></p><span>703.352.7222</span>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; "><b><span style="font-size: 11pt; ">Final Disclaimer:</span></b><span> Bring dry clothes and shoes, bug spray, sunscreen (NOT!!), condoms (as always… be safe!!), your grandmother’s underwear (why… we don’t know. Hummm… or is it… you never know?), and your appetite for some fine beers from all over the world!! And… finally… should we remind you… shiggy-socks and/or PI Block.</span></p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; "><span></span></p><p>&nbsp;</p><p /><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-top: 0in; margin-right: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-left: 0in; "><span>Oh… and please don’t forget those beautiful, young Russian female virgins!!</span><span></span></p><p /><p /><p>BierMeister: ??? (maybe there won\'t be beer ***sadface***) </p><p />', '<p><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(102, 0, 0); "><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?oe=UTF-8&ie=UTF8&hl=en&msa=0&ll=38.852442,-77.328343&spn=0.001934,0.002615&t=h&z=19&msid=200158719398624397366.0004a057ff904a3760ba3">Trail 464</a></span></p><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(102, 0, 0); "><p><span style="color: rgb(102, 0, 0); ">Parking lot behind the office building(s) located at: <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&sugexp=ldymls&xhr=t&q=11096+Lee+Highway,+Fairfax+VA&cp=27&bav=on.2,or.r_gc.r_pw.&wrapid=tljp1302190002032050&um=1&ie=UTF-8&hq=&hnear=11096+Lee+Hwy,+Fairfax,+VA+22030&gl=us&ei=wdedTcHdFJLAgQf_0e3RBA&sa=X&oi=geocode_result&ct=title&resnum=1&sqi=2&ved=0CBoQ8gEwAA"><font color="#800080">Fair Oaks Square</font></a>: 11092 (front) – 11096 (rear) </span></p><address w:st="on"><street w:st="on">Lee Highway</street>, <city w:st="on">Fairfax</city>, <state w:st="on">VA</state>, <postalcode w:st="on">22030</postalcode></address><p /><p><span style="font-size: 12pt; color: rgb(102, 0, 0); ">“START” is in the triangle created by Route 29 ~ Route 50 and <street w:st="on" /></span></p><p /><address w:st="on">Jermantown Road</address>. </span>', ''),
