"MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-family: Georgia;">However… you can put this into your GPS: <span style="color: rgb(102, 0, 0);"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&q=7600+Colshire+Drive,+Mclean,+VA&wrapid=tlif12845743746272&um=1&ie=UTF-8&sa=N&tab=wl">7600 Colshire Drive</a>, <city w:st="on">McLean</city>, <state w:st="on">VA</state> (rear parking lot)<p /></span></span></p><p><font face="Consolas">Anyone wearing WH4 Hab will get a WH4 trail credit from this trail!!</font></p><p><br /></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><b><span style="font-family: Georgia;">Directions:</span></b><b><span style="font-family: Georgia;"><br />From Sterling/Reston: </span></b><span style="font-family: Georgia;">Take <b>Route 267/Dulles Toll Road EAST</b>. Pass under (or over… which ever is your choice) the beltway. Take the <b>FIRST EXIT</b> onto <street w:st="on"><address w:st="on"><b><i>Chain Bridge Road</i></b></address></street> towards Tyson\'s Corner. Take a <b>RIGHT</b> onto <b><i>Route 123/Dolly <place w:st="on"><city w:st="on">Madison</city></place> Boulevard</i></b> (or it could be called <street w:st="on"><address w:st="on"><b><i>Chain Bridge Road</i></b></address></street>). Take your <b>1<sup>st</sup> LEFT</b> onto <street w:st="on"><address w:st="on"><b><i>Colshire Drive</i></b></address></street> and then your <b>1<sup>st</sup> LEFT</b> into the parking lot at the corner of <street w:st="on"><address w:st="on">Colshire Drive</address></street> and Route 123. Proceed to the back parking lot and look for wankers, park and hash.<p /></span></p><p><b><span style="font-family: Georgia;">From 66:</span></b><span style="font-family: Georgia;"> Take 66 East and bear <b>RIGHT</b> onto <b><i>Route 267/Toll Road Extension</i></b>. Take <b>EXIT 19A</b> for <b><i>Route 123/Dolly <place w:st="on"><city w:st="on">Madison</city></place> Boulevard</i></b> (or it could be called <street w:st="on"><address w:st="on"><b><i>Chain Bridge 