(494, '', '<div id="yui_3_2_0_1_131782597722188">From the East:</div><blockquote style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 0px; MARGIN: 0px 0px 0px 40px; PADDING-LEFT: 0px; PADDING-RIGHT: 0px; PADDING-TOP: 0px" id="yui_3_2_0_1_131782597722194"><div>Take Rt 7 West</div><div id="yui_3_2_0_1_131782597722193">Turn right onto Colvin Run Rd</div><div>Make an immediate right</div><div>Follow that road for about 200 yards to a parking lot</div></blockquote>From the West:<br /><blockquote style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 0px; MARGIN: 0px 0px 0px 40px; PADDING-LEFT: 0px; PADDING-RIGHT: 0px; PADDING-TOP: 0px"><div><div>Take Rt 7 East</div><div>Turn left onto Colvin Run Rd</div><div>Make an immediate right</div><div>Follow that road for about 200 yards to a parking lot</div></div></blockquote>From anywhere else:<blockquote style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 0px; MARGIN: 0px 0px 0px 40px; PADDING-LEFT: 0px; PADDING-RIGHT: 0px; PADDING-TOP: 0px"><div>Find Rt 7</div><div>Follow the above directions</div></blockquote><b />', 'Near By', '<p>Bring water wings, a small raft, head lamps, tick and ivy block, a machete, and of course an entire change of clothes. Trail will be A to A, and not friendly to anyone, in typical Parents style.<br /></p>', '<strong><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?msid=200153348770417974908.0004ae8e88057fe6e4472&msa=0">Trail #493:</a> The lot by the abandoned building by the old mill on Colvin Run Rd (38.967643,-77.288797)</strong></trail />', ''),
(495, '<p />', 'Take <span id="lw_1318630557_7" class="yshortcuts">Lee Hwy</span> (route 29) to Chain Bridge Road (VA 123 South) and take a right if traveling northeast, a left if traveling southwest. Follow 123 south for 2.3 miles. Make left on Braddock Road (VA 620 east). Turn in to the University Mall on your right. Look for wankers (or a big bald black dude in Marine green).<br />', '<div>Brion’s Grill</div><span id="lw_1318630557_8" class="yshortcuts">10621 Braddock Road<br />Fairfax, VA 22032-2200</span><br /><br />', 'A to A, dog friendly if on a leash, and stroller friendly. Bring a flash light or head lamp. If you are lost, annoyed, or just need an ear to whine into, call Private Snowball at <a rel="nofollow"><u><font color="#234786">202-689-4150</font></u></a>.<br />BeerMeister will be Little C*ck<br />', '<a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?msid=200153348770417974908.0004af4ae893bbac31bc5&msa=0&ll=38.826277,-77.31387&spn=0.00341,0.006947&t=h&z=18&vpsrc=6">Trail 494:</a> Near the M&amp;T Bank at 10697 Braddock Road Fairfax, VA 22032-2237', ''),
