(497, 'The first pub on the list is a real winner. It has 2 out of 5 stars on Yelp, and here are some excerpts from the reviews: <br />&quot;I\'m the duke of Bistro Bistro. It was once a great place frequented by all of the Shirlington locals and regulars -- now it\'s a last resort.&quot;<br />&quot;Poor Bistro Bistro. The waitstaff are eager, solicitous, even desperate for customers, but nonetheless the place remains identity-less, overpriced, and cavernously empty.&quot;<br />&quot;If Bistro Bistro were an abortion of a restaurant it\'d be a step up.&quot;<br /><br />So then why are we going there? SIMPLE – they have a killer Happy Hour!<br />$1.99 domestic drafts<br />$4 premium drafts<br />$4 house wine<br />$4 rail drinks<br />So, shake off those Halloween costumes, Febreze the beer and vomit smell out of them, and come on down to Shirlington to keep the party going with your favorite SH*T wankers!<br />', 'from 395 North, take the Shirlington exit. Keep left at the fork towards N. Quaker Ln. Slight left onto S Shirlington Rd, then right onto Campbell and you\'re there.<br />From 395 South, take Exit 7 and keep left at the fork, following signs toward Shirlington. Turn left onto S Shirlington Rd and then right onto Campbell and you\'re there.<br />From somewhere else, figure it out your own damn self', '', 'Parking: Garages are all free. Park either in the garage on S. Quincy between Campbell and Arlington Mill or in the garage on S. Randolph St south of Campbell (building says 2901)<br />Bring cash for your Pub Crawl drinking needs', 'Bistro Bistro, at <span id="lw_1319667097_2" class="yshortcuts">4021 Campbell Ave; Arlington, VA 22216</span> (part of the Village at Shirlington)<br />', ''),
(498, 'Trail is A to A and not friendly to strollers or pups. <font face="Calibri">Bring the usual - dry bag, condoms, lube, tetanus shot, Band-Aids, flash light and your hash mug.<span style="mso-spacerun: yes">  </span></font>', 'From Beltway inner loop, take exit 51 for Gallows rd and turn left onto Gallows, then left onto woodburn and immediately into the parking lot on the left. From outer loop, take exit 51 and keep left at fork following signs to woodburn, then slight right onto woodburn and left into the parking lot. <br />', 'TBD', 'Brew crew is Fatboy Slim', '<a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?msid=200153348770417974908.0004b0fe149c0e7a839ee&msa=0&ll=38.853854,-77.225003&spn=0.001704,0.003473">Trail start:</a> 3301 Woodburn Rd, annandale, VA.', ''),
