(559, 'It\'s Christmas, so let\'s all celebrate with a few drinks, and some shiggy trails.<div>Feel free to show as early as 3 to enjoy some prelube. Afterall, we need to honor Santa\'s big day somehow.</div>', 'This is a end unit town house. Go around back, and find the pack.<div><br /></div><div>Get to either 286 (the old 7100) Fairfax County Parkway or Reston Parkway</div><div>Take this road towards Reston Town Center</div><div>Find Lake Newport (just North of RTC)</div><div>Turn onto Lake Newport heading towards the opposite road mentioned above</div><div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">&nbsp;</span>i.e. if on FFCP turn onto Lake Newport heading towards Reston Parkway</div><div>Turn onto Autumn Ridge Cir</div><div>Go back to the circle, find a spot (that doesn\'t say reserved) and park. Overflow can park along the street where it is not yellow.</div><div>Walk along the side of house, swing around back. Find wankers. Hash</div>', '&nbsp;', 'Bring warm clothes, and a change of them. No more PI, but some water crossings for sure.', 'Out back of 1497 Autumn Ridge Cir<div><br /></div><div><a href="http://goo.gl/maps/FF8fQ">http://goo.gl/maps/FF8fQ</a></div>', ''),
(558, '<span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">Gotta love Wikipeadia… but not this time!!</span>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">In an effort find something funny and\r\nentertaining about “December 18</span><sup style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">th</sup><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">”… </span><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">I did not have to go any further that our own ‘Hare\r\nLog’!! Apparently… the last December 18</span><sup style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">th</sup><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;"> (Tuesday, December 18, 2007)\r\ntrail was hared by 14K and was the “Third Anal Buffa-Ho-Ho-Ho Trail”.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">Hummm… was this “Buffa-Ho-Ho-Ho” thing so\r\nGREAT that we needed an anal trail for?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">And… what is a “Buffa-Ho-Ho-Ho?</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">W</span><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">ell… if it was in some reference to the\r\nBuffalo Bills (because “Bitch, Where’s My Money” was a co-hare and we ALL know\r\nhe was a big Buffalo Bill fan), then it’s ironic that we can offer you the “Remember\r\nthe Buffa-Ho-Ho-Ho” Trial!! Why, you ask? Because the OnOnOn chosen for this\r\ntrail (Grevey’s) was if in the past, if not still… a ‘Buffalo Bill’ bar?</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">(I’ve been meaning to ask Mr. Grevey, who was a long\r\ntime Washington Bullet, why he made his bar here in the D.C. area… a Buffalo\r\nbar?)</span></p>', '<b>D’ERECTIONS:</b>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b>METRO:</b> <b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;">DUNN LORING METRO</span></b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;">: Exit metro station and turn <b>RIGHT</b> onto <b><i>Prosperity Avenue</i></b>…\r\ncontinue for approx. ½ mile and turn <b>RIGHT</b>\r\nwhen you reach:  <b><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&q=2710+Prosperity+Avenue,+Fairfax,+VA&bav=on.2,or.r_gc.r_pw.r_qf.&bvm=bv.1355325884,d.dmQ&bpcl=39967673&biw=1115&bih=967&wrapid=tlif135566626088210&um=1&ie=UTF-8&sa=X&ei=TtPNUPmrFqvH0AHBs4HYBg&ved=0CAgQ_AUoAA">2710\r\nProsperity Avenue</a>, Fairfax, VA 22031.</b></span><o:p /></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b>DRIVING:</b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p /></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b>From the WEST:\r\n(Sterling/Herndon/Reston): </b>Take <b><i>Route\r\n7, East (or Route 267, Dulles Toll Road, East to Route 7, East</i></b>)… Turn <b>RIGHT</b> onto <b><i>Gallows Road</i></b> and continue\r\nfor approx. 2½ miles. After you pass the entrance for Dunn Loring Metro… turn <b>RIGHT</b> onto <b><i>Prosperity Avenue</i></b> and\r\ncontinue to: <b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&q=2710+Prosperity+Avenue,+Fairfax,+VA&bav=on.2,or.r_gc.r_pw.r_qf.&bvm=bv.1355325884,d.dmQ&bpcl=39967673&biw=1115&bih=967&wrapid=tlif135566626088210&um=1&ie=UTF-8&sa=X&ei=TtPNUPmrFqvH0AHBs4HYBg&ved=0CAgQ_AUoAA">2710\r\nProsperity Avenue</a>, Fairfax, VA 22031</span></b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;">.\r\nPark in the “rear” parking lot and look for wankers milling around.</span><o:p /></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b>From the BELTWAY:\r\n</b>Find your way to the Beltway and take <b>EXIT 50A-B</b> <b><i>Route 50, Arlington Boulevard</i></b>\r\ntowards <span style="color: red;">Fairfax</span>.\r\nFollow signs for <b><i>Route 29/Merrifield</i></b> and merge onto <b><i>Gallows Road</i></b> (<b>RIGHT</b>). Turn <b>LEFT</b> onto <b><i>Route 29, Lee Highway</i></b> and continue\r\nfor approx. ½ mile and turn <b>RIGHT</b>\r\nonto <b><i>Prosperity\r\nAvenue</i></b>. Continue to: <b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&q=2710+Prosperity+Avenue,+Fairfax,+VA&bav=on.2,or.r_gc.r_pw.r_qf.&bvm=bv.1355325884,d.dmQ&bpcl=39967673&biw=1115&bih=967&wrapid=tlif135566626088210&um=1&ie=UTF-8&sa=X&ei=TtPNUPmrFqvH0AHBs4HYBg&ved=0CAgQ_AUoAA">2710\r\nProsperity Avenue</a>, Fairfax, VA 22031</span></b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;">\r\n(on your <b>LEFT</b>). Park in the “rear”\r\nparking lot and look for wankers milling around.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p /></p>', '  <b><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">On-On-On: </span></b><b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;"><a href="http://www.greveys.com/">Grevey’s Restaurant &amp; Sports Bar</a>: <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&bav=on.2,or.r_gc.r_pw.r_qf.&bvm=bv.1355325884,d.dmQ&bpcl=39967673&biw=1920&bih=985&wrapid=tlif135570980647710&q=8130+Arlington+Boulevard,+Fairfax,+VA++22042&um=1&ie=UTF-8&sa=X&ei=VX3OUIT4B8jr0QGW5YCABQ&ved=0CAgQ_AUoAA">8130\r\nArlington Boulevard</a>, Fairfax, VA  22042\r\n~ 703-560-8530</span></b><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;"><o:p /></span></b></p>', '<p class="MsoNormal"><b>ADD’L INFO: BRING\r\nA FLASHLIGHT!!</b> You know… just in case!! And\r\nneed I remind you of the standard disclaimers?<o:p /></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: 0.5in;"><b><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Miscellaneous:</span></b><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"> Trail will be… A to A’: </span><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 11pt; text-indent: 0.5in;">(translated… the </span><b style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 11pt; text-indent: 0.5in;">OTHER</b><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 11pt; text-indent: 0.5in;"> end of the parking lot!!)</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: 0.5in;"><b><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Dog Friendly Factor:</span></b><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"> Tough Dogs Only…<o:p /></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: 0px;"><span style="text-indent: 0.5in;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">&nbsp;</span><b>Stroller Friendly Factor:</b></span></span><span style="text-indent: 0.5in; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"> Tough Strollers\r\nOnly…</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 0.5in;"><b><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">Final Disclaimer:</span></b><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;"> Bring dry clothes and shoes, bug\r\nspray, sunscreen (NOT!!), condoms (as always… be safe!!), your grandmother’s\r\nunderwear (why… we don’t know. Hummm… or is it… you never know?), and your\r\nappetite for some fine beers from all over the world!! And… finally… should we\r\nremind you… shiggy-socks and/or PI Block.<o:p /></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">Oh… and please don’t forget those beautiful, young female virgins!!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p><b>QUESTIONS:</b> Contact And How’s Her Bush: <a href="mailto:AndHowsHerBush@yahoo.com"><span style="color: blue;">AndHowsHerBush@yahoo.com</span></a></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p /></p>', '<b>WHERE:</b> <span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;">“START” location for this week’s So Happy It’s Tuesday trail is in the parking lot behind:<b> <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&q=2710+Prosperity+Avenue,+Fairfax,+VA&bav=on.2,or.r_gc.r_pw.r_qf.&bvm=bv.1355325884,d.dmQ&bpcl=39967673&biw=1115&bih=967&wrapid=tlif135566626088210&um=1&ie=UTF-8&sa=X&ei=TtPNUPmrFqvH0AHBs4HYBg&ved=0CAgQ_AUoAA">2710 Prosperity Avenue</a>, Fairfax, VA 22031 </b><i>(about a half mile walk from the Dunn Loring Metro Station)</i>.</span><br /><div><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p /></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>COST:</b> $5.00 (the preferred form of currency would be (1) Abraham Lincoln or (5) George Washington’s, however, we’ll make due otherwise<b>!!</b>)</p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p /></p><p class="MsoNormal"><b>TIME:</b> Sign-In: 07:00pm ~ Hares Away: 07:15pm</p><p /></div>', '');
