(560, '<span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">Okay…</span><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">You were up late last night… you walked,\r\nslugged, crawled home of fell asleep in the nearest gutter, bathroom or someone\r\nelse’s bed.<o:p /></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">Well… time to get out and shake off those\r\nNew Year’s Eve improprieties and what better way but to come out to the hash!!</span></p>', '<b>D’ERECTIONS:</b>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b>METRO:</b> Sorry… not <b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;">METRO ACCESSIBLE</span></b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;"> at this time. Check back in\r\n2013!! LATER in 2013!!</span><o:p /></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b>DRIVING:</b></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p /></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b>From the WEST:\r\n(Sterling/Herndon/Reston): </b>Take <b><i>Route\r\n7, East (or Route 267, Dulles Toll Road, East to Route 7, East</i></b>)… <b>EXIT</b> onto <b><i>Route 123, North/Chain Bridge  Road</i></b> towards <span style="color: red;">McLean</span>. Chain Bridge Road\r\nturns into <b><i>Dolly Madison Boulevard</i></b>. Turn <b>RIGHT</b> onto <b><i>Great Falls Street</i></b> and take your\r\nfirst <b>LEFT</b> onto <b><i>Chain Bridge Road</i></b> (1<sup>st</sup>\r\nlight). Continue to: <b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&q=1515+Chain+Bridge+Road,+McLean,+VA&bav=on.2,or.r_gc.r_pw.r_qf.&bvm=bv.1355534169,d.dmQ&bpcl=40096503&biw=1920&bih=985&wrapid=tlif135696122773210&um=1&ie=UTF-8&sa=X&ei=_pXhUKDdPOy20AHth4CoAQ&ved=0CAgQ_AUoAA">1515\r\nOld Chain Bridge Road</a>, McLean, VA 22031</span></b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;">. Park\r\nin the “rear” parking lot and look for wankers milling around.</span><o:p /></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b>From the BELTWAY:\r\n</b>Find your way to the Beltway and take <b>EXIT 46B</b> <b><i>Route 123, North/Chain Bridge\r\nRoad</i></b> towards <span style="color: red;">McLean</span>. Chain Bridge Road turns into <b><i>Dolly Madison Boulevard</i></b>.\r\nTurn <b>RIGHT</b> onto <b><i>Great Falls Street</i></b> and take\r\nyour first <b>LEFT</b> onto <b><i>Chain\r\nBridge Road</i></b> (1<sup>st</sup> light). Continue to: <b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;"><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&q=1515+Chain+Bridge+Road,+McLean,+VA&bav=on.2,or.r_gc.r_pw.r_qf.&bvm=bv.1355534169,d.dmQ&bpcl=40096503&biw=1920&bih=985&wrapid=tlif135696122773210&um=1&ie=UTF-8&sa=X&ei=_pXhUKDdPOy20AHth4CoAQ&ved=0CAgQ_AUoAA">1515\r\nOld Chain Bridge Road</a>, McLean, VA 22031</span></b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;">. Park\r\nin the “rear” parking lot and look for wankers milling around.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p /></p>', '  <b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;">The Pub: (next to the\r\nPeking Restaurant: <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&q=6827+Redmond+Drive,+McLean,+VA&bav=on.2,or.r_gc.r_pw.r_qf.&bvm=bv.1355534169,d.dmQ&bpcl=40096503&biw=1115&bih=965&wrapid=tlif135696200815810&um=1&ie=UTF-8&sa=X&ei=4JjhUKzlMqW80AHbzICQDA&ved=0CAgQ_AUoAA">6827\r\nRedmond Drive</a>, McLean, VA  22101 ~\r\n703-448-0928</span></b>', '<p class="MsoNormal"><p class="MsoNormal"><b>ADD’L INFO: BRING\r\nA FLASHLIGHT!!</b> You know… just in case!! And\r\nneed I remind you of the standard disclaimers?<o:p /></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: 0.5in;"><b><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Miscellaneous:</span></b><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"> Trail will be… A to A’:<o:p /></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: 0.5in;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">(translated… the <b>OTHER</b> end of the parking lot!!)<o:p /></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: 0.5in;"><b><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Dog Friendly Factor:</span></b><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"> Tough Dogs Only…<o:p /></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="text-indent: 0.5in;"><b><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Stroller Friendly Factor:</span></b><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"> Tough Strollers\r\nOnly…<o:p /></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin-left: 0.5in;"><span style="font-size: 11pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"><br />\r\n</span><b><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">Final Disclaimer:</span></b><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;"> Bring dry clothes and shoes, bug\r\nspray, sunscreen (NOT!!), condoms (as always… be safe!!), your grandmother’s\r\nunderwear (why… we don’t know. Hummm… or is it… you never know?), and your\r\nappetite for some fine beers from all over the world!! And… finally… should we\r\nremind you… shiggy-socks and/or PI Block.<o:p /></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">Oh… and please don’t forget those beautiful, young female virgins!!</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b>QUESTIONS:</b> Contact And How’s Her Bush: <a href="mailto:AndHowsHerBush@yahoo.com"><span style="color: blue;">AndHowsHerBush@yahoo.com</span></a><o:p /></p></p>', '<b>WHERE:</b> <span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;">“START” location for this week’s\r\nSo Happy It’s Tuesday trail is in the parking lot behind:<b> <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&q=1515+Chain+Bridge+Road,+McLean,+VA&bav=on.2,or.r_gc.r_pw.r_qf.&bvm=bv.1355534169,d.dmQ&bpcl=40096503&biw=1920&bih=985&wrapid=tlif135696122773210&um=1&ie=UTF-8&sa=X&ei=_pXhUKDdPOy20AHth4CoAQ&ved=0CAgQ_AUoAA">1515\r\nOld Chain Bridge Road</a>, McLean, VA 22031</b>.</span><p class="MsoNormal"><o:p /></p>\r\n\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><b>COST:</b> $5.00 (the preferred form of currency would be (1) Abraham\r\nLincoln or (5) George Washington’s, however, we’ll make due otherwise<b>!!</b>)</p><p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;">TIME:</span></b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif;"> Sign-In: 07:00pm ~ Hares\r\nAway: 07:15pm</span></p>', ''),
(561, '<div><span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">Another year and more old people thinking they can do the same SH*T they did a year ago.  To prove this one birthday boy and one soon-to-be birthday bot will brave the cold of Ashburn and lay a trail in hopes of not getting caught.  A collective birthday spanking at these Hare age could take up into the Spring!</span></div><div><br /></div>It\'s a birthday trail, so be sure to come out in your birthday suites....wait, scratch that. Just show up and be prepared for a quick trail so we can get to the drinking and celebrating quicker', '&nbsp;', '<span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">O\'Malley\'s Pub</span><br style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);" /><a href="http://www.omalleyspub.com/dulles/" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">http://www.omalleyspub.com/<wbr />dulles/</a>', '<span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">A to A cold but manageable for most</span> ', '<span style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font size="2">Commuter lot of Ox Road and Moran - Herndon/Ashburn</font></span>', ''),
