(564, 'When we don\'t get enough hares, we\'re stuck back out in Reston again. Show up and enjoy trail, or bitch about the location and volunteer. There is no other option!', '<b>From 66:</b><div>Take West Ox Road (exit 57) North</div><div>Turn right onto South Lakes Drive</div><div>Go about a quarter mile</div><div>See the park on the right</div><div><br /></div><div><b>From 267:</b></div><div>Take Reston Parkway (exit 12) South</div><div>Go about 2/3 of a mile</div><div><div>Turn left onto South Lakes Drive</div><div>Go about a quarter mile</div><div>See the park on the right</div></div><div><br /></div><div>Find Wankers</div><div>Celebrate</div>', 'TBD', 'It\'ll probably be another cold one, so dress warmly. We\'ll try to stay dry, but no promises. There\'s a bad vehicle, so bring a bag!', '<a href="http://goo.gl/maps/SWLHp">South Lakes Drive Park</a><div>11851 S Lakes Dr.</div><div>Reston, VA 20194</div>', ''),
(566, '<div style="text-align: center;"><font size="6"><b>You don\'t know Jack Schitt?</b></font></div><div style="text-align: center;"><b style="font-size: xx-large;">Who is Jack Schitt?</b></div><div><br /></div><div>For some time many of us have wondered just who is Jack Schitt? We find ourselves at a loss when someone says, &quot;You don\'t know Jack Schitt!&quot; Well, thanks to my genealogy efforts, you can now respond in an intellectual way.</div><div>Jack Schitt is the only son of Awe Schitt.</div><div><br /></div><div>Awe Schitt, the fertilizer magnate, married Miss O. Needeep They had one son, Jack.</div><div><br /></div><div>In turn, Jack Schitt married Noe Schitt. The deeply religious couple produced six children: Holie Schitt, Giva Schitt, Fulla Schitt, Bull Schitt, and the twins Deap Schitt and Dip Schitt.</div><div><br /></div><div>Against her parents\' objections, Deap Schitt married her cousin Dumb Schitt, a high school dropout. After being married 15 years, Jack and Noe Schitt divorced.</div><div><br /></div><div>Noe Schitt later married Ted Sherlock, and, because her kids were living with them, she wanted to keep her previous name. She was then known as Noe Schitt Sherlock.</div><div><br /></div><div>Meanwhile, Dip Schitt married Loda Schitt, and they produced a son with a rather nervous disposition named Chick N. Schitt.</div><div><br /></div><div>Two of the other six children, Fulla Schitt and Giva Schitt, were inseparable throughout childhood and subsequently married the Happens brothers in a dual ceremony.</div><div><br /></div><div>The wedding announcement in the newspaper announced the Schitt-Happens nuptials.</div><div><br /></div><div>The Schitt-Happens children were Dawg, Byrd, and Hoarse. Bull Schitt, the prodigal son, left home to tour the world. He recently returned from Italy with his new Italian bride, Pisa Schitt.</div><div><br /></div><div>Now when someone says, &quot;You don\'t know Jack Schitt,&quot; you can correct them.</div>', '  METRO: BALLSTON METRO: EXIT the metro station and turn RIGHT on N. Fairfax Drive and then immediate LEFT onto N. Stafford Street. Continue on N. Stafford Street and cross Washington Boulevard and past Washington-Lee High School. After you pass over I-66, turn RIGHT into the Parking Deck and look for wankers milling around.<div>&nbsp;</div><div>DRIVING:</div><div>From the WEST: (Sterling/Herndon/Reston): Take Route 267, Dulles Toll Road, East (or Route 7 to Dulles Toll Road)… and continue onto Dulles Connector to I-66, East towards Washington, DC. Continue on I-66, East and take EXIT 71 for N. Glebe Road/N. Fairfax Drive and continue straight onto N. Fairfax Drive. Turn LEFT onto N. Stafford Street and continue across Washington Boulevard and past Washington-Lee High School. After you pass over I-66, turn RIGHT onto the N. 15th Street to the Parking Deck: (use: 4052 15th Street North, Arlington, VA for your GPS…). Park and look for wankers milling around.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>From the BELTWAY: Find your way to the Beltway and take EXIT 49B for I-66, East towards Washington, DC (if coming from Rockville… it will be the LEFT EXIT 45B for the Dulles Connector to I-66, East).  Continue on I-66, East and take EXIT 71 for N. Glebe Road/N. Fairfax Drive and continue straight onto N. Fairfax Drive. Turn LEFT onto N. Stafford Street and continue across Washington Boulevard and past Washington-Lee High School. After you pass over I-66, turn RIGHT onto the N. 15th Street to the Parking Deck: (use: 4052 15th Street North, Arlington, VA for your GPS…). Park and look for wankers milling around.</div>', 'TBD', 'BRING A FLASHLIGHT!! You know… just in case!! And need I remind you of the standard disclaimers?<div>&nbsp;</div><div><b>Miscellaneous</b>: Trail will be… A to A’:</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><b>Dog Friendly Factor</b>: Tough Dogs Only…</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><b>Stroller Friendly Factor</b>: Tough Strollers Only…</div><div><br /></div><div><b>Final Disclaimer:</b> Bring dry clothes and shoes, bug spray, sunscreen (NOT!!), condoms (as always… be safe!!), your grandmother’s underwear (why… we don’t know. Hummm… or is it… you never know?), and your appetite for some fine beers from all over the world!! And… finally… should we remind you… shiggy-socks and/or PI Block.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Oh… and please don’t forget those beautiful, young female virgins!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>QUESTIONS: Contact And How’s Her Bush: AndHowsHerBush@yahoo.com</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>AHHB ( or “Busch InBev” for short)</div><div>703.622.8697</div>', '“START” location for this year’s So Happy It’s Tuesday Fat Tuesday trail is the I-66 Parking Garage ~ N Quincy St &amp; 15th St N, Arlington: This is the parking lot behind: Washington-Lee High School: (use: <a href="http://maps.google.com/maps?hl=en&q=4052+15th+Street+North,+Arlington,+VA&bav=on.2,or.r_gc.r_pw.r_qf.&bvm=bv.42080656,d.dmQ&biw=1920&bih=985&wrapid=tlif136042429508710&um=1&ie=UTF-8&sa=X&ei=Ym0WUc2vEubp0gHZ7YDABQ&ved=0CAgQ_AUoAA">4052 15th Street North, Arlington, VA</a> for your GPS…).\r\n<div><br /></div><div><br /></div>', ''),
