(565, '&nbsp;', 'From Wiehle Ave:  Go to Wiehle and Sunrise Valley Dr., take a left at the stop light.  Go about 1.5 miles and turn left onto Robert  Fulton Drive (if you pass the WO&amp;D turn around).  Go up the drive pass Access National Mortgage and take a right into 1801.  Look for wankers at the rear lot neat the high, yet safe, tension wires.<div><br /></div><div>From Fairfax Country parkway: Follow onto Sunrise Valley Drive towards Wiehlie and follow the above directions.</div>', 'Lakeside Inn\r\n<div><div>11150 S Lakes Dr</div><div>Reston, VA 20191</div></div>', 'Dry wet and flat like many young hashers', '<font color="#222222" face="arial, sans-serif" size="2">Rear parking lot at 1801 Robert Fulton Drive</font>', ''),
(571, '<div>Don yOur green and jOin us to cure that hangOver you still have from  St. Patty\'s  day! There will be plenty O\' bOOze and beer. RumOr has it - even some tOe tags.  </div><div><br /></div><div>Runners and walkers trails with beer and shOt checks.</div><div><br /></div><div>Why dO we drink in St. Patricks day, you ask?  (Like we need an excuse to drink) but as legend has it...The custOm O\'  imbibing alcOhOl On St. Patrick\'s Day cOmes frOm an Old Irish legend. As the stOry gOes, St. Patrick was served a measure O\' whiskey that was cOnsiderably less than full. St. Patrick tOOk this as an OppOrtunity tO teach a lessOn O\' generOsity tO the innkeeper. He tOld the innkeeper that in his cellar resided a mOnstrOus devil whO fed On the dishOnesty O\' the innkeeper. In Order tO banish the devil, the man must change his ways. When St. Patrick returned tO the hOstelry sOme time later, he fOund the Owner generOusly filling the patrOns\' glasses tO OverflOwing. He returned tO the cellar with the innkeeper and fOund the devil emaciated frOm the landlOrd\'s generOsity, and prOmptly banished the demOn, prOclaiming thereafter everyOne shOuld have a drOp O\' the &quot;hard stuff&quot; On his feast day. </div><div><br /></div><div>Feck the misspellings, I\'m still drinking!</div>', '<div>Accessible by metrO bus 29E and 29X frOm the PentagOn.</div><div><br /></div>', '<div>The Auld Shebeen</div><div>3971 Chain Bridge Rd.</div><div>Old TOwn Fairfax</div>', '&nbsp;', '<div>RutherfOrd Park</div><div>4798 Guinea ROad</div><div>Fairfax, Va 22032</div>', ''),
