(584, '<div>So Happy It’s Tuesday Hash House Harriers was founded by a handful of wankers that lived in the Sterling-Herndon-Reston area but would frequent trails by the Over The Hump Hash House Harriers (OTH4) in the Woodbridge-Dale City area (our Mother Hash).</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Therefore… S.H.*.T. adopted a lot of the OTH4 markings: “L” arrow for ‘Long’ trail (runners), “W” arrow for ‘Walkers’ trail, flour in a ‘Triangular Shape” for ‘intersection’, three “Parallel” lines for ‘false trail’, “B w/check mark” for ‘Beer Check’, plus some of the traditional markings. A S.H.*.T. trail is NOT COMPLETE until “Finish” is written at or near the ultimate “BN” (Beer Near)!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>After discussion of what days the other DC Area kennels where running… it was determined that Tuesday was the ideal date. And rumors told… it was “Tupperware’s” mother that came up with SH*T for So Happy It’s Tuesday!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>We honor the traditional analversaries (25, 50, 69, 75, 100…), but our recurring analversaries occur every seventh trail, so if you’ve never made it out to a S.H.*.T. trail EXCEPT for Tour d’Hash… you will be making your seventh this year!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>So Happy It’s Tuesday H3 began with the goal of surviving the first three years. We pride ourselves on (mostly) off-road trails that are conducted LIVE (w/fifteen minute head start). There is nothing better than running through the woods in the middle of winter with just a flashlight!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>This week’s trail is within one (1) mile of the start of one its first trails ever and it should offer a true traditional off-road experience. So… cum on out to S.H.*.T. H3 and learn more about this amazing kennel.</div>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif; color: red;">Metro…<br /></span></b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Of course… the <a href="http://www.fairfaxcounty.gov/connector/routes/dullesrail/springhillstation.htm" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204);">Spring Hill Station</a> (</span><a href="http://www.docstoc.com/docs/10156272/Tysons-metro-rail-stop-plan-map" target="_blank" style="color: rgb(17, 85, 204);"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif; color: rgb(42, 93, 176);">Tyson West Station</span></a><u><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif; color: rgb(42, 93, 176);">)</span></u><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">... On the “Silver Line”!! However… you’ll have to WALK IT… the trains won’t be running on it until later this year!!<u><u /></u></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif; color: red;">&nbsp;</span></b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif; color: red;">Driving:</span></b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif; color: red;">From the Sterling/Herndon/Reston…<br /></span></b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Get yourself onto <b><i>Route 7, East or Route 267, Dulles Toll Road </i></b>heading towards <span style="color: red;">Tysons Corner</span>. After you pass over Route 267, Dulles Toll Road (or take the Route 7, East exit, if coming from the Toll Road) and take the first <b><span style="color: blue;">RIGHT</span></b> onto <b><i>Westwood Center Drive</i></b>. Continue to the end of the cul-de-sac of Westwood Center Drive, park and look for wankers milling around.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif; color: red;">From the Beltway…<br /></span></b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Get yourself to the <b><i>Beltway (I-495)</i></b>. Take <b><span style="color: blue;">EXIT 45</span></b> for the <b><i>Route 267, Dulles Toll Road</i></b>. As soon as you go through the main toll plaza… take the first <b><span style="color: blue;">EXIT</span></b> for Route 7. On the ramp to Route 7… stay on your <b><span style="color: blue;">LEFT</span></b> and turn <b><span style="color: blue;">LEFT</span></b> onto <b><i>Route 7, East</i></b>. You will pass back over the Dulles Toll Road and take your first <b><span style="color: blue;">RIGHT</span></b>onto <b><i>Westwood Center Drive</i></b>. Continue to the end of the cul-de-sac of Westwood Center Drive, park and look for wankers milling around.</span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Alternate direction from the <b><i>Beltway (I-495)</i></b>. Take <b><span style="color: blue;">EXIT 47B-A</span></b> for the <b><i>Route 7, West</i></b>. Continue on Route 7 for approx. 2½ miles and turn <b><span style="color: blue;">LEFT</span></b> onto<b><i>Westwood Center Drive</i></b> (Tyco Road will be on your right). Continue to the end of the cul-de-sac of Westwood Center Drive, park and look for wankers milling around.</span></p><u><u><u>&nbsp;</u></u></u>', '<div>O Malley’s Pub (located behind the Crown Plaza (in between Crown Plaza and the Marriott at Route 123 and International Drive)</div><div>1960 Chain Bridge Rd, Mclean, VA 22102-4001</div>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Dog Friendly Factor: If it’s hot out… leave the little critters at home!!<br /><br />Live Trail, as usual, and it’s A to A’ </span><b><i><span style="font-size: 10pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">(meaning… that it’s long enough that I have to move the ‘Beer Vehicle’ but short enough for you to leave your sh*t in the cars!! Translated… NO BAG VEHICLE and NO SHUTTLES NEEDED!!)</span></i></b><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">.<u><u /></u></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><u><u><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"> <u><u /></u></span></u></u></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><u><u><u><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">I would suggest… BRING A FLASHLIGHT!! If you’re an EWH3 hasher… forget it… you’ll never survive this trail!!<u><u /></u></span></u></u></u></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><u><u><u><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;"> <u><u /></u></span></u></u></u></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0px; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><u><u><u><span style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Georgia, serif;">Final disclaimer… bring dry clothes and shoes and any FEMALE RUSSIAN VIRGINS you have in your closet!! (hummm… WAIT!! Okay… the virgin(s) can be ‘wet’!!)</span></u></u></u></p><u><u><u>&nbsp;</u></u></u>', '<div>8699 Westwood Center Dr, Vienna, VA 22182-2235</div><div><a href="http://maps.google.com/maps/ms?msa=0&msid=114946079815076584162.00047237cc5590073878e&safe=on&ie=UTF8&ll=38.925029,-77.235904&spn=0.023938,0.038495&t=h&z=15">The Map</a></div>', ''),
(585, '\'If you\'re going to be something, be a good one\' - Abraham Lincoln', 'Closest Metro is Braddock Rd with bus transfer or a good walk after.', 'Haute Dogs and Fries <div>610 Montgomery Street Alexandria, Va</div>', 'A-A; No bag vehicle so if you bring a bag just leave it in your car.', 'Start will be 500 Slaters Lane Alexandria, Va and there\'s street parking\r\n<div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/preview#!q=500+Slaters+Ln%2C+Alexandria%2C+VA+22314&data=!1m4!1m3!1d3930!2d-77.0412269!3d38.8218069!4m11!1m10!4m8!1m3!1d49719!2d-77.4407885!3d38.8448844!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!17b1">I\'m The MAP!!!</a></div>', ''),
(587, 'It\'s that time, finally. Getting some justs their first hare trail. Come on our and laugh your ass off at these 2 dumbies. And the real kicker, Parent\'s is teaching them the ropes. This can only end disastrously, and you won\'t want to miss it (if you can find your way back).', 'Get to Duke St (236).<div>Head towards Port City Brewery (if you are unfamiliar with that landmark, then....sigh....)</div><div>Turn onto S Gordon St</div><div>When it dead ends into Wheeler, turn right</div><div>Go behind that first building.</div><div>Find wankers and CELEBRATE</div>', 'TBD', 'It\'ll be a relatively short/fast trail, as we may have a squeeze a naming in. Urban shiggy, so bring some spray.', 'Back lot of Walmer Enterprises<div><div>4307 Wheeler Avenue</div><div>Alexandria, VA 22304</div></div><div><br /></div><div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/mm?authuser=0&hl=en">https://www.google.com/maps?q=4307+Wheeler+Avenue+Alexandria,+VA+22304&amp;hl=en&amp;sll=37.0625,-95.677068&amp;sspn=45.014453,135.263672&amp;t=h&amp;hnear=4307+Wheeler+Ave,+Alexandria,+Virginia+22304&amp;z=16</a></div>', ''),
(588, 'Enjoy stumbling through the woods chasing these bastards. It\'s gonna be a true SH*T trail for all you shiggy loving wankers!', '&nbsp;', 'Bowl America (don\'t worry, they have beer)\r\n<div>Free shoes to go along with $9.99 unlimited bowling after 9pm. And a few lanes are set aside for us!</div>', 'Trail is A to A\', with plenty of shiggy abounding. Headlamps are a good idea, Sunscreen may also be helpful, but Off is a must, as well as a dry bag. Sound confusing, well, then you\'re not too bright. Have you seen the weather recently? It is going to be a very wet trail. a very muddy very wet trail.', 'Side Lot Of Bowl America<div>5615 Guinea Rd </div><div>Fairfax, VA 22032</div>', ''),
(590, 'It\'s National Cow Appreciate Day, so come on out and enjoy the coweriffic trail planned.', '<b>From 66 West Bound:</b><div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="font-weight: bold; white-space: pre;">&nbsp;</span>Take Exit 53B for 28N</div><div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">&nbsp;</span>Keep Left, follow signs for Braddock</div><div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">&nbsp;</span>Turn Right onto Sully Rd</div><div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">&nbsp;</span>Turn Left onto Braddock Rd</div><div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">&nbsp;</span>After 1.3 miles, turn Left into Shopping Center</div><div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">&nbsp;</span>Find wankers and hash!</div><div><b>From 66 East Bound:</b></div><div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">&nbsp;</span>Take exit for 29S and go Left</div><div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">&nbsp;</span>After half mile, turn Right onto Stone Rd</div><div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">&nbsp;</span>Turn Right at Stone Range Dr</div><div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">&nbsp;</span>Turn Left into Shopping Center</div><div><span class="Apple-tab-span" style="white-space: pre;">&nbsp;</span>Find wankers and hash!</div>', 'TBD', 'Bring the usual, flashlight, bug/tick/PI spray/block, sun screen, floaties, and some dry underwear', '<div>Behind the Village Center Shopping</div><div><div>5675 Stone Road</div><div>Centreville, VA 20120</div></div>38.85403,-77.452951', ''),
(592, 'Strokin\' is getting older, so come cheer him on as he lays trail with his walker and hearing aide. Luckily the young spry Doc will be there to help out!', '&nbsp;', '<div>Vienna Inn</div><div>120 East Maple Ave</div><div>Vienna, VA</div>', '&nbsp;', '<div>Church of the Holy Comforter</div><div>543 Beulah Rd NE  Vienna, VA 22180</div>', ''),
(593, 'Because you wankers won\'t sign up for trail, you\'re stuck with the glorious PW laying trail for you all', '&nbsp;', '<div>Red Rocks Cafe &amp; Tequila Bar</div><div>13850 Braddock Rd</div><div>Centreville, VA 20121</div>', '&nbsp;', 'The back lot at the Stringfellow park and ride<div><div>Park-&amp;-Ride</div><div>4600 Stringfellow Rd</div><div>Chantilly, VA 20151</div></div><div><br /></div><div>This lot is on the West side of Stringfellow, just North of 66</div>', ''),
(596, '&nbsp;', 'Cumming soon', 'General Store<div>7140 Main St, Clifton, VA 20124<br /><div><br /></div><div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004e5f60db8264bf927a&msa=0&ll=38.767038,-77.405629&spn=0.003643,0.008256">I\'m the map</a></div></div>', 'It will be a wet trail, bring a change of clothes. A to B trail. Strong dog friendly etc.', 'The entrance to Hemlock overlook park:<div>13220 Yates Ford road, Clifton Va. 20124-4354</div><div><br /></div><div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004e5f60db8264bf927a&msa=0&ll=38.767038,-77.405629&spn=0.003643,0.008256">I\'m the map</a></div>', ''),
(595, 'Break out those star spangled stovepipe hats and sparkled stilts. It\'s time to honor Uncle Sam, and we\'re doing it the only way we know how. With beer and trail. ', 'Coming Soon', 'Anthony\'s Restaurant Inc, 7234 Centreville Rd, Manassas, VA &#8206; (Across the street from start)', '&nbsp;', '<div>“START” location for this week’s So Happy It’s Tuesday trail is: Behind Memories Antiques,  7217 Centreville Road,</div><div>Manassas, VA 20111</div>', ''),
(594, '<div>Okay… So… I promised Parent’s Weekend… “no chiggers” on Tuesday.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>However… whst “is” a “chigger”?</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Chigger Bites: Itching from chigger bitees is most intense 1 to 2 days following the bite (see… so you won’t have it on Tuesday).</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>This is when the chigger falls off and can leave red welts that may resemble a blister or pimple (however… you won’t see them over the briar scratches).</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Scratching can lead to a secondary infection, so treatment is directed at relief of itching symptoms. Use over-the-counter antihistamine creams to help relieve itching and prevent scrathing. Consult your doctor (And How’s Her Bush) if you have concerns.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Now can we get on with trail, Parent’s Weekend?</div>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><b>METRO:</b> Sorry… not <b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;">METRO ACCESSIBLE</span></b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;"> at this time, however, it is 92% complete!! Hope they don’t run out of money to finish it!! Besides… </span><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;">This is S.H.*.T… remember? We’re BIG KIDS… WE DRIVE!!<u><u /></u></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><u><u><u><u><b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;"><u> <u /></u></span></b></u></u></u></u></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><u><u><u><b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;">DRIVING:</span></b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Sty