(607, '<div>Humm...</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Scientific evidence has been found that the first ever Northern Virginia Hillbilly Hash was actually performed by S.H.*.T. H3!!</div><div>Don\'t let those imposters on Sunday tell you anything different!!</div><div>On Tuesday, May 17th 2005... the "Oh Brother, Where Art Thy Beer? Hillbilly Hash" was established. The culprits "Cum of a Sailer", "I\'d Rather F*** My Sister", "Gets Off Easy" and a hasher not to be named.</div><div>On this official document... it was written: (quote) Please join the So Happy Its Tuesday gang for its first ever Hillbilly Hash. Hasher not to be named, a native WV\'er has brought his family\'s annual hash out of the mountains and put it right where it belongs in Reston!!</div><div>This is a themed hash, please come dressed in Hillbilly getups - no city slicker doodads, or (I) reckon y\'ll gonna be tarred and feathered! (unquote)</div><div>So... in honor of this finding... the So Happy It\'s Tuesday Hash House Harriers will reinact the first EVER Hillbilly Hash... Same Location... Same Time... Different hares!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>AHHB</div>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><b>METRO:</b>&nbsp;Sorry... not&nbsp;<b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;">METRO ACCESSIBLE</span></b><span style="font-family: \'Bookman Old Style\', serif;">&nbsp;at this time. Check back in 2013!! LATER in 2013!! In 2014?</span><u></u><u></u></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><u></u>&nbsp;<u></u></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color: rgb(34, 34, 34);"><b>DRIVING:</b><u></u><u></u></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt; font-size: 12pt; font-family: \'Times New Roman\', serif; color