(608, 'It\'s&nbsp;(almost)&nbsp;Thanksgiving. So come out to trail, and show us everything your thankful for.<div>Good(?) beer, interesting conversations, fun trails (we can\'t even attempt trying to call them good).</div>', '<div>From route 7 take Drainsvilel Road for about 3 miles then turn right onto Herndon Parkway. &nbsp;Follow Herndon Parkway for about 2 miles, pass under the back 9 overpass then turn right onto Crestview at the light. &nbsp;Park entrance on right.</div><div><br></div><div>From 28: Take the Ox Road/Herndon exit and continue to Herndon Parkway. &nbsp;Turn left onto Herndon Parkway, drive to the next stoplight and turn left onto Crestview. &nbsp;park is on right.</div>', 'O\'Sullivan\'s Irish Pub (across from Jimmy\'s Tavern)<div><br></div><div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004eb9c88bc0f4aac592&amp;msa=0&amp;ll=38.970201,-77.387022&amp;spn=0.001902,0.00408">I\'m The Map</a></div>', '<div>Should be people and dog friendly, end circle is dog friendly but try to keep muddy shoes outside.</div><div>A to Z but walking distance from finish</div><div>Bag vehicle provided and it may be dark, cold and wet so prepare accordingly.</div>', 'Trailside Park in Herndon on the corner of Herndon Parkway and Crestview Drive<div><br></div><div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004eb9c88bc0f4aac592&amp;msa=0&amp;ll=38.970201,-77.387022&amp;spn=0.001902,0.00408">I\'m The Map</a><br></div>', ''),
(609, 'It\'s cold out, so wear plenty of layers. And while you\'re at it, make one of those a sweater, an ugly one at that.<p>That\'s right, it\'s an ugly sweater hoe down. Come out with your gaudiest, brightest. best holiday sweater you can manage.</p>', '<b>From 66:</b><p>Take exit 53 for Rt 28 North</p><p>Go 1.3 miles, and turn left at the traffic light into the park.</p><p>Find the wankers and hash!</p>', '<p>Buffalo Wing Factory &amp; Pub</p><p>13067 Lee Jackson Memorial Hwy</p><p>Fairfax, VA 22033</p><p><br></p><p><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004ec17fd858a2d45bc3&amp;msa=0&amp;ll=38.880473,-77.399218&amp;spn=0.003808,0.008256">I\'m the Map</a></p>', 'It\'s dark, bring a light.<p>It\'s cold, dress warmly</p><p>It\'s an ugly sweater trail, wear an ugly sweater</p>', 'Ellanor C Lawrence Soccer Fields<p>No real address, use the map below or GPS:&nbsp;38.858805,-77.436619</p><p><br></p><p><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 255); text-decoration: underline;">I\'m the Map</span></p>', ''),
(610, 'It\'s a solar eclipse out tonight, so make sure to bring an extra light, as it\'ll be extra dark.<div>On the plus side, there is no need to worry about werewolves, without moon, and clearly the serpents and demons are otherwise occupied devouring this shiny object.</div><div>But then again, I do hear a lack of a moon spells the end of the world...</div>', '<div><b>From Dulles Toll Rd:</b></div><div>Take Hunter Mill Rd exit</div><div><div>Go south on Hunter Mill Rd</div><div>Turn left at T intersection to stay on Hunter Mill where Sunrise Valley Dr goes right&nbsp;</div><div>Make 2nd left onto Brittenford Dr&nbsp;</div><div>In 200 yards, turn right into pool parking lot.&nbsp;</div><div>Look for wankers.</div></div>', '', 'Bring a light, and some dry shoes! Maybe even some tick spray, as they\'re not quite dead yet. A few of us had to pull some off after last weeks trail!', '<div><div><font color="#222222" face="arial, sans-serif" size="2">Hunter Mill Swim and Racquet Club.</font></div><div><font color="#222222" face="arial, sans-serif" size="2">10339 Brittenford Dr</font></div><div><font color="#222222" face="arial, sans-serif" size="2">Vienna, VA</font></div></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;"><br></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px;"><a href="http://goo.gl/maps/l2OM3"><font color="#222222" face="arial, sans-serif" size="2">I\'m the Map</font></a></div>', ''),
(611, 'Remember that one time Parent\'s laid a trail way too long, with way too little flour?<div>One time? Really? Try almost every trail he\'s ever laid.</div><div>We\'ll, it\'s about time we showed him how a trail should be. With that in mind, Fallen has taken it upon himself to put Parent\'s to shame...or something like that...</div>', 'From 66 take Fairfax County Parkway (286) south.<div>About 4 miles make left on Burke Center Parkway.</div><div>About a mile later, the shopping center is on the Northwest corner of Burke Center Parkway and Ox Road.</div><div><br></div><div>Once we determine WHERE in the shopping center we\'ll be, we\'ll post some more detailed directions.</div>', 'Fat Tuesdays at the University Mall<div><div>10673 Braddock Rd</div><div>Fairfax, VA 22032</div></div><div><div><span id="gc-number-0" class="gc-cs-link" title="Call with Google Voice">(703) 385-5717</span></div></div><div><span class="gc-cs-link" title="Call with Google Voice"><br></span></div><div><span class="gc-cs-link" title="Call with Google Voice"><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004ed9a5c06d2c0feef9&amp;msa=0&amp;ll=38.814633,-77.313194&amp;spn=0.04006,0.084543">I\'m the Map</a><br></span></div>', 'It\'s dark out early, some bring a light. And for f*ck\'s sake, it\'s icy and cold, so dress warmly, and bring a change of clothes for when you slip and fall', '<div>The parking lot behind CVS (Not Safeway)</div><div>5711 Burke Center Parkway</div><div>Burke, VA 22015</div><div><br></div><div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004ed9a5c06d2c0feef9&amp;msa=0&amp;ll=38.814633,-77.313194&amp;spn=0.04006,0.084543">I\'m the Map</a></div>', ''),
(612, 'It\'s the most wonderful time, of the year...Christmas. But oh wait...Some of us don\'t celebrate Christmas.<div>And some of us don\'t have a lovely family to hang out with.</div><div>Whatever shall we do. Luckily Christmas Eve falls on a Tuesday. So while we can\'t wipe away the Christmas Day blues, we can at least ensure you\'re not crying alone by yourself waiting for Santa Clause.</div>', '<b>From the (South) East:</b><div>Get to 66.</div><div>Take it West</div><div>If you are HOV 2+ (or are running late and it is after 7pm)</div><blockquote style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;"><div style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Take the Stringfellow Exit (the left exit right after exit 55).</div></blockquote><blockquote style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;"><div style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Go Left at the light on Stringfellow</div></blockquote><blockquote style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;"><div style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Turn Left onto Autumn Willow Dr</div><div style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Make your first Left into the Soccer Fields</div></blockquote>If you are <b>NOT</b> HOV compliant and on time)<div><blockquote style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;"><div style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Take exit 55, and head South on Fairfax County Parkway</div><div style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Turn Right onto Route 29 (Lee Highway)</div><div style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Turn Right onto Stringfellow Rd</div><div style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Turn Right onto Autumn Willow Dr</div><div style="margin: 0 0 0 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Make your first Left into the Soccer Fields</div></blockquote><b>From the (South) West:</b></div><div>Get to 66.</div><div>Take it East</div><div>Take exit 52 for Route 29 (Lee Highway) East</div><div>Turn Left onto Stringfellow Rd</div><div>Turn Right onto Autumn Willow Dr</div><div>Make your first Left into the Soccer Fields</div>', 'TBD', 'It\'s dark, so bring a light. It\'s cold, so dress warmly. It\'s Christmas, so dress up all perty for us', 'The&nbsp;Stringfellow Soccer Park in Sully, VA.<div><br></div><div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004edcef52bdca7c8178&amp;msa=0&amp;ll=38.846294,-77.4013&amp;spn=0.007186,0.016512">Checkout this hot Map</a></div>', ''),
(613, 'It\'s a special trail on a special day, at a special time. PLEASE NOTE THE TIME CHANGE.<div>Trail starts at 4:00pm. SPECIAL START TIME.</div>', '<div dir="ltr" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: HelveticaNeue, \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, \'Lucida Grande\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px;"><div><u>Directions From the West (Leesburg-ish)</u></div><div>Follow Route 7 East to Sterling</div><div>Exit onto Cascades Parkway North</div><div>Travel 1.8 miles on Cascades Parkway</div><div>Turn right onto Broadmore</div><div>Turn left onto Westover Terrace</div><div>Immediate left onto Ashmere Square</div><div>Look for parking along a curb or an open spot</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><u>Directions From the South (Centerville-ish)</u></div><div>Follow Route 28 North to Route 7</div><div>Follow the "From the West" directions</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><u>Directions From the East (Tysons-ish)</u></div><div>Follow Route 7 West to Sterling</div><div>Turn right onto Potomac View Road</div><div>Travel 1.4 miles on Potomac View Road</div><div>Turn left onto Broadmore Drive</div><div>Turn right onto Westover Terrace</div><div>Immediate left onto Ashmere Square</div><div>Look for parking along a curb or an open spot</div></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: HelveticaNeue, \'Helvetica Neue\', Helvetica, Arial, \'Lucida Grande\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px;"></div>', 'TBD', '', '<div>VAGINA\'s place</div><div>46681 Ashmere Square</div><div>Sterling, VA 20165</div><div><br></div><div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004eeb46daf63211351b&amp;msa=0&amp;ll=39.047619,-77.384627&amp;spn=0.009982,0.021136">I\'m the Map</a></div>', ''),
(614, '', '<div>Make your best way to Fairfax County Parkway Rte 286.</div><div><br></div><div>From the North, travel south on the Parkway and turn right on Fred\'s Oak Rd, which is the first right after passing the exit for Ox Rd, Rte 123. &nbsp;Go 300 yards on Fred\'s Oak, turn right at the T-intersection with Sydney Rd. &nbsp; Go 200 yards and make the first left onto Rice Field Place. &nbsp; Drive to the end and park on the left just before the cul-de-sac.</div><div><br></div><div>From the South, travel north on Fairfax County Parkway, and make a left on Fred\'s Oak Rd. (1/4 mile before the exit for Ox Rd). &nbsp; &nbsp;Note, there is no traffic light at this intersection, so be careful. &nbsp; Follow directions as above.</div>', 'At the house, or we\'ll make an ad hoc decision after the circle as to whether to repair to a local bar.', '<div>Guaranteed to be the best trail of 2014 so far.</div><div>Bring dry shoes and socks.</div><div>OK to bring your dog(s)</div><div>Warm, indoor circle location.</div>', '10970 Rice Field Place, Fairfax Station, VA<div>(use this address for navigation systems or mapquest directions)</div><div><br></div><div><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004ef03a85d8a54712d0&amp;msa=0&amp;ll=38.782402,-77.326224&amp;spn=0.006523,0.013078">I\'m the Map</a></div>', ''),
(615, '<div>Yes... it&apos;s true!!</div><div>The Washington Redskins have found themselves a new coach for their team... It&apos;s Jay Gruden. Or did they?</div><div>Jay Gruden, who was the offensive Coordinator for Cincinnatti, was also being pursued by Minnesota, Detroit and Houston.</div><div>However, the frigid weather must have gone to his head for he accepted the job with the Washington Redskins.</div><div>It was rumored that he was on his way to Redskin park, but as the frost started to thaw... he began to have second thoughts and is now thought to be lost in the woods and rough terrain in Ashburn.</div><div>Good thing that the So Happy It&apos;s Tuesday Hash House Harriers are doing trail within walking distance to Redskin Park. Therefore... when on trail... if you happen to see a forty-some year old in a dark suit and Redskin cap... please provide your OnOnOns to get him home!!</div><div>With that being said... this week&apos;s trail will "START" at: "21301 Beaumeade Circle, Ashburn VA"</div>', '<div><b><span style="\\&quot;font-size:" 24px;\\"=""></span></b></div><span style="\\&quot;font-size:18px;\\&quot;"><div style="\\&quot;font-size:" 18px;\\"=""><b style="\\&quot;font-size:" 18px;\\"=""><span style="\\&quot;font-size:" 18px;\\"=""></span></b></div></span><span style="\\&quot;font-size:16px;\\&quot;"><span style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""><div style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""><b style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""><span style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""></span></b></div></span></span><span style="\\&quot;font-size:16px;\\&quot;"><span style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""><span style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""><div style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""><b style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""><span style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""></span></b></div></span></span></span><span style="\\&quot;font-size:12px;\\&quot;"><span style="\\&quot;font-size:" 12px;\\"=""><span style="\\&quot;font-size:" 12px;\\"=""><span style="\\&quot;font-size:" 12px;\\"=""><div style="\\&quot;font-size:" 12px;\\"=""><b style="\\&quot;font-size:" 12px;\\"=""><span style="\\&quot;font-size:" 12px;\\"=""></span></b></div></span></span></span></span><span style="\\&quot;font-size:16px;\\&quot;"><span style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""><span style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""><span style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""><span style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""><div style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""><b style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""><span style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"="">METRO:</span></b></div><div style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""></div></span><div style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""></div></span><div style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""></div></span><div style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""></div></span><div style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""></div></span><div>METRO? Did someone say, METRO? Coming to Ashburn sometime in the next five years!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><b></b></div><span style="\\&quot;font-size:16px;\\&quot;"><div style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""><b style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"="">DRIVING:</b></div><div style="\\&quot;font-size:" 16px;\\"=""></div></span><div><b>From the WEST:</b> (Sterling/Herndon/Reston): "Head" West-ish!! From the intersection of Route 7 &amp; Route 28... Take Route 28, South towards Dulles Airport. Take the RAMP for Waxpool Road towards Ashburn. Turn RIGHT onto Beaumeade Circle (this is the first right after you pass Broderick Drive and the Golf Course Club House). Take your 1st RIGHT onto Beaumeade Circle (yes again!!). Turn RIGHT into the first parking lot at: 21301 Beaumeade Circle, Ashburn VA &nbsp;20147.</div><div>Look for wankers milling around.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><b>From the BELTWAY:</b> Find your way to the Beltway and take the EXIT for the Dulles Toll Road towards Reston/Herndon/Sterling. Take the EXIT for Route 28, North Sully Road. Continue on Route 28, North Sully Road past the exit for Sterling Boulevard and take the LEFT EXIT for Waxpool Road towards Ashburn. Turn RIGHT onto Beaumeade Circle (this is the first right after you pass Broderick Drive and the Golf Course Club House). Take your 1st RIGHT onto Beaumeade Circle (yes again!!). Turn RIGHT into the first parking lot at: 21301 Beaumeade Circle, Ashburn VA &nbsp;20147.</div><div>Look for wankers milling around.</div>', 'Buffalo Wild Wings:&nbsp;<div>21980 Colorado Drive,</div><div>Dulles 28 Centre,</div><div>Sterling, VA &nbsp;20166</div><div><span class="\\&quot;gc-cs-link\\&quot;" title="\\&quot;Call" with="" google="" voice\\"=""><br></span></div><div><span id="\\&quot;gc-number-0\\&quot;" class="\\&quot;gc-cs-link\\&quot;" title="\\&quot;Call" with="" google="" voice\\"=""><span id="gc-number-0" class="gc-cs-link" title="Call with Google Voice">703-444-3048</span></span></div><div><span class="\\&quot;gc-cs-link\\&quot;" title="\\&quot;Call" with="" google="" voice\\"=""><br></span></div><div><span class="\\&quot;gc-cs-link\\&quot;" title="\\&quot;Call" with="" google="" voice\\"=""><a href="\\&quot;https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004ef9ea0c149c36dbcc&amp;msa=0&amp;ll=39.013349,-77.441554&amp;spn=0.012138,0.026157\\&quot;">I&apos;m the Map</a></span></div><div><br></div><div><div>D&apos;ERECTIONS:</div><div>FROM "START":</div><div>Take a RIGHT onto Beaumeade Circle ~ Turn LEFT onto Loudoun County Parkway ~ Turn LEFT onto Waxpool Road toward Route 28. After you pass Broderick Drive and the Golf Course Club House, Take your 1st LEFT onto Pacific Boulevard, then your &nbsp;1st RIGHT onto Colorado Drive, then 1st LEFT toward Buffalo Wild Wings: 21980 Colorado Drive, Dulles 28 Centre, Sterling, VA</div></div>', '<div>BRING A FLASHLIGHT!! You know... just in case!! And need I remind you of the standard disclaimers?</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Miscellaneous: Trail will be... A to A&apos;:</div><div>(translated... the OTHER end of the parking lot!!)</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Dog Friendly Factor: Tough Dogs Only...</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Stroller Friendly Factor: Tough Strollers Only...</div><div><br></div><div>Final Disclaimer: Bring dry clothes and shoes, bug spray, sunscreen (NOT!!), condoms (as always... be safe!!), your grandmother&apos;s underwear (why... we don&apos;t know. Hummm... or is it... you never know?), and your appetite for some fine beers from all over the world!! And... finally... should we remind you... shiggy-socks and/or PI Block.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Oh... and please don&apos;t forget those beautiful, young female virgins!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>QUESTIONS: Contact And How&apos;s Her Bush: AndHowsHerBush@yahoo.com</div>', '"START" location for this week&apos;s So Happy It&apos;s Tuesday trail is in the back parking lot (as usual...): 21301 Beaumeade Circle, Ashburn VA &nbsp;20147.<div><br></div><div><a href="\\&quot;https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004ef9ea0c149c36dbcc&amp;msa=0&amp;ll=39.013349,-77.441554&amp;spn=0.012138,0.026157\\&quot;">I&apos;m the Map</a></div>', ''),
(616, '', '', '', '', '<div>Due to incliment weather... and family issues beyond our hare&apos;s (Little C*ck) control... the So Happy It&apos;s Tuesday Hash House Harriers have decided that in the best interest of our wankers... that we postpone today&apos;s trail.</div><div>Today was to be a pub crawl in Clifton... therefore later this week we will provide something for our dedicated wankers. Possible a &apos;S.H.*.T. Happy Hour and the first couple of pitchers are on us!!</div><div>We know wankers, especially Bad Dog, will be disappointed of this postponement, but we are only looking for the safety of our kennel, visitors and virgins.</div><div>Stay home... or don&apos;t stay home and go out and enjoy the snow. Check out the website later this week &nbsp;for more details on what we&apos;re planning next... and next week&apos;s trail.</div><div>We really do appreciate your patronage... and look forward to seeing each and every one of you each week!!</div><div>By the way... today, January 21st is "National Hug Day", which was launched on January 21, 1986 in Clio, Michigan. The idea of "National Hug Day" is to encourage everyone to hug family and friends more often. Therefore... hug your wife (husband), girlfriend (boyfriend), neighbor, dog (good or bad), neighbor&apos;s cat, an Otter... whatever your little heart desires!!</div><div>We will see you soon!! OnOn!!</div><div>"The MisManagement"</div>', ''),
(617, 'Details Cumming Soon!', '<div>DRIVING:&nbsp;</div><div>From the North/West: (Ashburn/Sterling/Herndon/Reston): Head southeast on VA-7 E/Leesburg Pike and take the Virginia 28 S /Sully Rd for about 14 miles. &nbsp;Take the Interstate 66 W ramp and merge onto I-66 W for 5.7 miles. Take exit 47A to merge onto VA-234 BUS S/Sudley Rd toward Manassas for 1.3 miles and turn left onto Sudley Manor Dr. &nbsp;After 2 miles turn left onto Ben Lomond Park Rd. &nbsp;Start will be on the right, look for Wankers in the parking lot. &nbsp;</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>From the BELTWAY: Head southwest on I-66 W for about 17.2 miles. Take exit 47A to merge onto VA-234 BUS S/Sudley Rd toward Manassas for 1.3 miles. &nbsp;Turn left onto Sudley Manor Dr. for about 2 miles and turn left onto Ben Lomond Park Rd. &nbsp;Start will be on the right, look for Wankers in the parking lot.</div>', 'Hard Times Cafe<div><div>7753 Sudley Rd</div><div>Manassas, VA 20109</div></div><div><div><span id="gc-number-0" class="gc-cs-link" title="Call with Google Voice">(703) 365-8400</span></div></div><div><br></div>', 'A to Hard B.<div>B prepared. Heh!</div><div>Dog-friendly</div><div>Please not it&apos;s really cold outside:&nbsp;WEATHER @ 7PM:High "18?" Low "10?" ~ Overcast w/ 0% Chance of Rain ~ Wind North at 4 mph ~ 38% Humidity.</div><div>Dress appropriately (skirts and tank tops obviously)</div><div>It&apos;s dark when we start, so bring a light you wankers.</div><div><div><br></div><div>And need I remind you of the standard disclaimers?</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Dog Friendly Factor:Tough Dogs Should Be Fine...</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Stroller Friendly Factor:Not A Chance!!</div><div><br></div><div>Final Disclaimer: Bring dry clothes and shoes, bug spray, sunscreen (NOT!!), condoms (as always... be safe!!), your grandmother&apos;s underwear (why... we don&apos;t know. Hummm... or is it... you never know?), and your appetite for some fine beers from all over the world!! And... finally... should we remind you... shiggy-socks and/or PI Block.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Oh... and please don&apos;t forget those beautiful, young female virgins!!</div></div>', '<div>Splashdown Water Park</div><div>7500 Ben Lomond Park Drive</div><div>Manassas VA 20109</div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004f0e385377382dd154&msa=0&ll=38.791858,-77.496657&spn=0.020036,0.042272'),
(699, '', '', '', '', '', ''),
(618, '<div>Since Goundhog Day is on Sunday, February 2nd 2014... and there can be twelve thousand miles of cloud cover... that... that dang groundhog is STILL going to see it&apos;s shadow and cause us to have six more weeks of winter!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Well... I don&apos;t know about you, but... I&apos;m tired of letting this rodent deciding our fate and delaying our Spring!! So... we&apos;re going to &apos;hunt&apos; for this imp!! I don&apos;t care how many tunnels, caves, drain pipes, creeks we have to go through!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>So... come on out and let&apos;s get our flashlights (because it&apos;s STILL going to be winter...) and &apos;hunt&apos; this little sucker!!</div>', '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; width: 1369px;"><tbody><tr><td style="font-family: arial, sans-serif; margin: 0px; padding: 0in;"><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><b>METRO:</b>&nbsp;<b><span style="font-family: &apos;Bookman Old Style&apos;, serif;">METRO? Did someone say, METRO?</span></b><span style="font-family: &apos;Bookman Old Style&apos;, serif;">&nbsp;Coming to Ashburn sometime in the next five years!!<u></u><u></u></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><span style="font-family: &apos;Times New Roman&apos;, serif;"><u></u>&nbsp;<u></u></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><b>DRIVING:</b><u></u><u></u></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="margin: 0in 0in 0.0001pt; font-size: 11pt; font-family: Calibri, sans-serif;"><b><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">From Sterling:&nbsp;</span></b><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">Take&nbsp;<b><i>Dranesville Road/VA-228</i></b>&nbsp;toward&nbsp;<span style="color: red;">Herndon