(626, '', '<div><b>METRO:</b> About a 30 minute walk from Vienna Metro station South on Nutley to make a left on the southern access road paralleling Arlington Blvd for .7 miles and turn right on Guysborough Dr for .1 miles to get to Eakin Court.&nbsp;</div><div><b>DRIVING:</b></div><div><b>From Sterling:</b> &nbsp;Head south on VA-28 S/Sully Rd &nbsp;for 11.8 miles. &nbsp;Turn left onto the Interstate 66 E ramp and merge onto I-66 E for 8.2 miles. &nbsp;Take exit 62 for VA-243 S/Nutley St for just over a mile and a half. &nbsp;Turn left onto Arlington Blvd for .2 miles and a right at Covington St and an imeadeate right onto Guysborough Dr &nbsp;and after .1 miles turn left onto left onto Guysborough Dr . &nbsp;After .1 miles you will arrive at Eakin Park Court. &nbsp;Look for wankers milling around.</div><div><b>From I-495:</b> Find your way to: I-495: Take EXIT 50A to merge onto onto Arlington Blvd for 2.2 miles and a left at Covington St and an imeadeate right onto Guysborough Dr &nbsp;and after .1 miles turn left onto left onto Guysborough Dr . &nbsp;After .1 miles you will arrive at Eakin Park Court. &nbsp;Look for wankers milling around.</div>', 'Grevey&apos;s Restruant &amp; Sports Bar<div>8130 Arlington Blvd</div><div>Falls Church, VA &nbsp;22042</div><div><span id="gc-number-0" class="gc-cs-link" title="Call with Google Voice">(703) 560-8530</span>&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><div>D&apos;Erections from "START" to On-On-On:</div><div>Turn right on Arlington Blvd for 1.5 miles.</div><div>Turn left onto Gallows Road for 453 feet.</div><div>Turn right and Grevey&apos;s will be on the left.</div></div><div><br></div>', '<div>BRING A FLASHLIGHT!! You know... just in case!! And need I remind you of the standard disclaimers?</div><div><b>Final Disclaimer:</b> Bring dry clothes and shoes, bug spray, sunscreen (NOT!!), condoms (as always... be safe!!), your grandmother&apos;s underwear (why... we don&apos;t know. Hummm... or is it... you never know?), and your appetite for some fine beers from all over the world!! And... finally... should we remind you... shiggy-socks and/or PI Block.</div><div>Oh... and please don&apos;t forget those beautiful, young female virgins!!</div>', 'Eakin Park Court, Fairfax VA &nbsp;22031<div><br></div><div>Use&nbsp;8600 Tobin Rd. Annandale, VA 22003 as address for getting directions</div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004f5875a00da1a23538&msa=0&ll=38.868232,-77.226892&spn=0.007192,0.016512'),
(627, '<div>Well, &nbsp;He gave you all a subtle warning, and no one listened... soooo here it comes! &nbsp; All The Way In is setting the trail because no one else wanted to sign up for hareing and he plans on making this trail as close to hell as he can manage. &nbsp;Bring your Flashlight, shiggy socks, shiggy pants, shiggy shirts, shiggy thong or boxers, bug spray, PI Block, machettie, First Aid Kit, Towel, change of shoes, socks, dry clothes, and a replacement soul for the one you may loose on trail!!</div>', '<div><b>From Sterling (North/West):</b></div><div>Take VA-28 South and take the US-50 exit towards Fairfax for about 7 miles. &nbsp; Turn right onto VA-665/Waples Mill Rd for about 1.6 miles before turning right onto Mattie Moore Ct. &nbsp;Start will be at the end of Mattie Moore Court. &nbsp;Look for Wankers.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><b>From Arlington (East):</b></div><div>Go west on US-50 W/Arlington Blvd. and make the slight left onto Fairfax Blvd for another 3 miles. Continue onto Lee Hwy/US-29 S for under a mile before turning left onto VA-665/Shirley Gate Rd for just over a mile before turning right onto Mattie Moore Court. &nbsp;Start will be at the end of Mattie Moore Court. &nbsp;Look for Wankers.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><b>From Woodbridge (South):</b></div><div>Go North on I-95 and take exit 160B for VA-123 North. &nbsp;Go about 13 miles and turn left onto VA-620 W/Braddock Road for about a mile and a half before turning right onto VA-665/Shirley Gate Rd . &nbsp;After a few hundred yards take the 1st left onto Mattie Moore Court, and start will be at the end of Mattie Moore Court. &nbsp;Look for Wankers.</div>', '<div>Brion&apos;s Grille</div><div>10621 Braddock Road, Fairfax VA 22032</div><div><br></div><div><i>D&apos;ERECTIONS to ON-After from "START":</i></div><div>Turn right onto VA-665/Shirley Gate Rd for a few hundred feet and turn left onto VA-620 E/Braddock Rd</div><div>For about 1.8 miles and Brion&apos;s Grill will be on the right.</div>', '<div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Calibri; font-size: medium; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><font size="3"><font face="Times New Roman"><b>BRING A FLASHLIGHT!!</b>&nbsp;</font><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">Trail will be... A to A: (translated... If you get lost or too tired to continue go back to Start and wait for us to return.)</span></font></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Calibri; font-size: medium; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;"><font size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Calibri; font-size: medium; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><font size="3"><b><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">Dog Friendly Factor:</span></b><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;Tough Dogs Only as there is lots of Shiggy,&nbsp;and we may cross a heavy traffic road on this expedition.</span></font></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Calibri; font-size: medium; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><b>&nbsp;</b></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Calibri; font-size: medium; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><font size="3"><b><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">Stroller Friendly Factor:</span></b><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;NO strollers unless you want to carry it on your back for 4 miles.</span></font></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Calibri; font-size: medium; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><font size="3" face="Times New Roman">&nbsp;</font></div><div style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: Calibri; font-size: medium; margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><font size="3"><b><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">Final Disclaimer:</span></b><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;Bring dry clothes, extra shoes,&nbsp;</span><b><font face="Times New Roman">A FLASHLIGHT,</font></b><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif;">&nbsp;bug spray, sunscreen, condoms, Water Wings,&nbsp;</span><b><font face="Times Ne