(634, 'Dr. Strangelove, Cheap A$$ Gigilo', '<div>From Sterling: Take VA-28 South for about 12 miles and merge onto I-66 East for about 2 miles. Take Exit 55 onto VA-286 Fairfax County for about 10 miles and turn right onto Reservation Dr. Look for wankers milling around.</div><div><br></div><div>From I-495: Find your way to: I-95S and take exit 166B for Virginia 286 N toward Heller Road/Fairfax County Parkway . Stay on VA-286 N/Fairfax County Pkwy for about 2.5 miles and take exit ramp to stay on VA-286 for another 3.5 miles. Turn left onto Reservation Dr. Look for wankers milling around.</div><div><br></div><div>From the South: Find your way to I-95 Northbound: Take exit 160B for VA-123 N. Merge onto VA-123 N/Gordon Blvd for 6.0 miles and turn right onto State Rte 643 for 1.1 miles. Turn right onto State Rte 641/VA-286 S for about a third a mile and take the 1st right onto Reservation Dr. Look For Wankers milling around.</div>', 'TBD', '<div>NOTES: Thistrail won&apos;t be the ball buster that last years was, but it&apos;ll still be a decenthike. Bring your PI block, bug spray, and of course a headlamp!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>ADD&apos;L INFO: BRINGA FLASHLIGHT!! You know... just in case!! Andneed I remind you of the standard disclaimers?</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Miscellaneous: Trail will be... A to A&apos;:</div><div>(translated... the OTHER end of the parking lot!!)</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Dog Friendly Factor: Tough Dogs Only...</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Stroller Friendly Factor: Tough StrollersOnly...</div><div><br></div><div>Final Disclaimer: Bring dry clothes and shoes, bugspray, sunscreen (NOT!!), condoms (as always... be safe!!), your grandmother&apos;s underwear(why... we don&apos;t know. Hummm... or is it... you never know?), and your appetite forsome fine beers from all over the world!! And... finally... should we remind you...shiggy-socks and/or PI Block.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Oh... and please don&apos;t forget those beautiful, young female virgins!!</div>', 'South Run Recreation Center<div>7550 Reservation Drive</div><div>Springfield, VA 22153</div><div><span id="gc-number-0" class="gc-cs-link" title="Call with Google Voice">(703) 866-0566</span></div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004f9e953858967cdc8b&msa=0&ll=38.751188,-77.274313&spn=0.007639,0.016512'),
(635, 'What&apos;s this? PW is doing a trail without Herpicles.<div>Thank the hash gods, we might actually have a trail that is half decent (the other half will obviously still be crap since PW is doing it).</div><div>Come on out and help Pink celebrate her 20th birthday. Yay old people...</div><div><br></div><div>Also, if anyone has or can get a hold of an otter mug/cup/thong, be sure to bring it out as a birthday present for Pink. She&apos;s been looking for one for quite a while.</div><div>AND...<b>be sure to come out in your shiniest pink apparel to stand strong with Pink</b></div>', '<b>From the Beltway:</b><div>Take exit 52 to 236 (Little River Turnpike) West.</div><div>Make your first Left onto Pineridge Dr.</div><div>Make an immediate Left onto Accotink Parkway</div><div>Make your first Left into Americana Park</div><div><b>From the West:</b></div><div>Get to 236 (Little River Turnpike) and take it East</div><div>Just before the Beltway, turn Right&nbsp;onto Pineridge Dr.</div><div>Make an immediate Left onto Accotink Parkway</div><div>Make your first Left into Americana Park</div>', 'TBD', '<div><b>Wear Pink:</b> How else could/should you celebrate her birthday?</div><div><br></div><div><b>Trail:</b>&nbsp;A to A&apos;</div><div><br></div><div><b>ADD&apos;L INFO:</b> BRING A FLASHLIGHT!! You know... just in case!! And need I remind you of the standard disclaimers?</div><div><br></div><div><b>Dog Friendly Factor:</b> Tough Dogs Only...</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><b>Stroller Friendly Factor:</b> Tough StrollersOnly...</div><div><br></div><div><b>Final Disclaimer:</b> BRING DRY CLOTHES and shoes, bugspray, sunscreen (NOT!!), condoms (as always... be safe!!), your grandmother&apos;s underwear(why... we don&apos;t know. Hummm... or is it... you never know?), and your appetite forsome fine beers from all over the world!! And... finally... should we remind you...shiggy-socks and/or PI Block.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Oh... and please don&apos;t forget those beautiful, young female virgins!!</div>', 'Americana Park<div>Annandale VA</div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004fa60865c98dbd9ca3&msa=0&ll=38.83359,-77.220626&spn=0.030521,0.066047'),
(636, 'Something amusing later will be placed here. For now just think of elephants playing with monkey feces', '<div>From Washington DC (east): Find your way to: I-66W and take exit 57B for US-50 W. Stay on US-50 W for 4.6 miles and turn right onto Centerview Dr, after 1/3 mile turn left onto Thunderbolt Place. Start will be immediately on the Right. Go behind 14000 Thunderbolt Place and look for wankers milling around.</div><div>From Sterling (north): Take VA-28 South for about 6.5 miles and merge onto US-50 E for about 1/2 mile. Take a left onto Centerview Dr, after 1/3 mile turn left onto Thunderbolt Place. Start will be immediately on the Right. Go behind 14000 Thunderbolt Place and look for wankers milling around.</div><div>From the South: Find your way to I-95 Northbound: Take exit 152A for VA-243 N. Merge onto VA-234 Dumfries Rd for about 14 miles and turn right onto VA 294E for 2 miles. Continue onto Liberia Ave for about 1.5 miles and turn right onto VA-28 N for almost 10 miles. Take the US-50 E exit then the first left onto Centerview Dr, after 1/3 mile turn left onto Thunderbolt Place. Start will be immediately on the Right. Go behind 14000 Thunderbolt Place and look for wankers milling around.</div>', '<div>The Bungalow</div><div>13891 Metrotech Drive</div><div>Chantilly, VA 20151</div><div><span id="gc-number-0" class="gc-cs-link" title="Call with Google Voice">(703) 502-3925</span></div>', 'OH GOD! So much PI! So many ticks. Be sure to bring repellent of all types for trail!<div><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">Trail will have some poison ivy for both walkers and runners so be prepared!</span></div><div><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 19px;">Runners will have a Turkey/Eagle option and headlamps would be a nice touch</span></div><div><span style="font-family: arial, helvetica, clean, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; line-height: 1