(637, '<div>WHERE: "START" location for this week&apos;s So Happy It&apos;s Tuesday trail is in the Giant Food parking lot at 13330 Franklin Farm Rd, Herndon, VA.</div><div><br></div><div>COST: $5.00 (the preferred form of currency would be (1) Abraham Lincoln or (5) George Washington&apos;s, however, we&apos;ll make due otherwise!!</div><div><br></div><div>TIME: Sign-In starts: 06:30pm ~ Hares Away: 07:00pm</div>', '<div>From the North/West: (Ashburn/Sterling/Herndon/Reston):</div><div>Head south on VA-28 S and take the Virginia 608/Frying Pan Rd exit. &nbsp;Turn right onto VA-608 S/VA-657 for about 1.5 miles before turning right onto VA-286 S for another 1.1 miles. &nbsp;Turn right onto Franklin Farm Rd. and your destination will be immediately on the right, just look for Wankers.</div><div><br></div><div>From the BELTWAY:</div><div>Head southwest on I-66 W and take exit 57B for US-50 W toward Fair Oaks/Winchester. Continue onto US-50 W and take the Fairfax Co Pkwy N &nbsp;for about 2.7 miles Turn left onto Franklin Farm Rd. &nbsp;Your destination will be on the right, just look for Wankers.</div><div><br></div><div>From the South:</div><div>Take I-95 North to exit 160B and merge onto VA-123. &nbsp;After about 10 miles take ramp right onto VA 286 North Fairfax County Parkway. &nbsp;Go about 10 miles and Turn right onto Franklin Farm Rd. and your destination will be immediately on the right, just look for Wankers.</div>', 'Dogfish Head AleHouse<div>13041 Lee Jackson Memorial Hwy</div><div>Fairfax, VA 22033</div><div>(703) 961-1140<div><br></div><div>Take the 1st right onto VA-286 S/Fairfax County Pkwy for 2.2 miles then turn right onto Rugby Rd for about .3 miles. Turn right onto US-50 W for about .5 mile and the Alehouse will be on the left.</div></div>', '<div>BRING A FLASHLIGHT!! You know... just in case!! And need I remind you of the standard disclaimers?</div><div><br></div><div>Dog Friendly Factor: Tough Dogs Should Be Fine...</div><div><br></div><div>Strolle