(649, 'To fit in with the Catholic church crowd, please wear your best school girl outfit', '<div>From Dulles Toll Rd:</div><div><br></div><div>Take Reston Parkway exit, going south on the Parkway</div><div>Go 2 miles and turn left onto Lawyers Rd</div><div>Immediately stay left where Fox Mill Rd goes to the right</div><div>Go 0.8 miles to the Church on the left.</div><div><br></div><div>We will try to gather in the rightmost parking lot.</div>', '<div>&nbsp;Glory Days at Fox Mill Center</div><div>2567 John Milton Dr, Herndon, VA 20171</div>', '', '<div>St. John Neuman Catholic Church</div><div>11900 Lawyers Rd</div><div>Reston</div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.00050251eb3881f42c111&msa=0'),
(650, '<div><b><span style="font-size:20px;">NOTE THE SPECIAL TIME AND DATE!</span></b></div><div><span style="font-size:24px;">Sign-In starts: 11:69 ~ Hares Away: 12:30-ish</span></div><div><br></div>Lets chase some hares, have some Beers and Shots and celebrate another shitty year!<div><br></div><div>PRELUBE/ON ON ON: CAMPING AVAILIABLE! &nbsp;Come on out Sat night and bring your best Shot cunt-cock-tion to share on a 10PM tent/shot crawl!? &nbsp;The shitty hares are orginizing some food for a Pot Luck at the end. &nbsp;Feel free to bring a dish to share with your fellow wankers after trail on Sunday.</div>', '<div><b>From the East/Beltway:</b></div><div>From I-495 take exit 49 for Interstate 66 W toward Manassas/Front Royal &nbsp;for about 6.3 miles. &nbsp;Take exit 57B for US-50 W toward Fair Oaks/Winchester for about 16 miles. &nbsp;At the traffic circle, take the 1st exit onto State Rte 860 for about 2 miles. &nbsp;Destination will be on the right; look for Wankers park and pitch a tent if you are going to stay overnight.</div><div><br></div><div><b>From the West:</b></div><div>Make your way to Head east on I-66 E and take exit 40 for US-15 toward Haymarket/Leesburg for 10.3 miles; at the traffic circle, take the 1st exit onto Howsers Branch Dr. for about  1/2  mile. &nbsp;At the next traffic circle, take the 1st exit onto US-50 for about  1/2  mile. &nbsp;At the next traffic circle take the 2nd exit onto State Rte 860. &nbsp;Destination will be on the right in just over 2.1 miles. Look for Wankers park and pitch a tent if you are going to stay overnight.</div><div><br></div><div><b>From the South:</b></div><div>Go North on I-95 and take exit 152B to merge onto VA-234 N toward Manassas for 22.4 miles. &nbsp;Follow signs for Interstate 66 W/Front Royal and merge onto I-66 W for 4.5 miles. &nbsp;Take exit 40 for US-15 toward Haymarket/Leesburg for 10.3 miles; at the traffic circle, take the 1st exit onto Howsers Branch Dr. for about  1/2  mile. &nbsp;At the next traffic circle, take the 1st exit onto US-50 for about  1/2  mile. &nbsp;At the next traffic circle take the 2nd exit onto State Rte 860. &nbsp;Destination will be on the right in just over 2.1 miles. Look for Wankers park and pitch a tent if you are going to stay overnight.</div>', '', '<div>Dog Friendly Factor: Tough Dogs Should Be Fine...as long as they have a fresh tick/flee collar.</div><div>Stroller Friendly Factor: Not A Chance!!</div><div>Final Disclaimer: Bring BUG SPRAY, headlamps, dry clothes, dry shoes, BUG SPRAY, sunscreen, condoms (as always... be safe!!), and your appetite for some beer, and...finally...should we remind you... shiggy-socks and/or PI Block and uhmm... BUG SPRAY.</div><div><br></div><div>Oh... and please don&apos;t forget those beautiful, young female virgins!!</div><div>QUESTIONS: Contact And How&apos;s Her Bush @ <span id="gc-number-0" class="gc-cs-link" title="Call with Google Voice">(703) 622-8697</span> or All The Way In @ (240) 993-6474</div>', '22620 Watson Road, Leesburg, VA<div>GPS: 38.991771, -77.59594</div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.000502b5e1e4e48494e6e&msa=0&ll=38.99141,-77.59592&spn=0.007797,0.015814'),
(651, 'It&apos;s "Get Ready Day" so we&apos;re going with a Mad Max theme this week.<div>Other than that...details are forthcoming</div>', '<div>From Dulles Toll Rd:</div><div><br></div><div>Take Reston Parkway exit, going south on the Parkway</div><div>Go 2 miles and turn left onto Lawyers Rd</div><div>Immediately stay left where Fox Mill Rd goes to the right</div><div>Go 0.8 miles to the Church on the left.</div><div><br></div><div>We will try to gather in the rightmost parking lot.</div>', 'Dogfish Head in Fairfax<div><div jsinstance="0" class="cards-text-truncate-and-wrap" jsl="$x 7;" jstid="94" style="max-width: 100%; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif; line-height: 18px;"><div jsinstance="0" class="cards-text-truncate-and-wrap" jsl="$x 7;" jstid="94" style="max-width: 100%; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif;">13041 Lee Jackson Memorial Highway</div><div jsinstance="0" class="cards-text-truncate-and-wrap" jsl="$x 7;" jstid="94" style="max-width: 100%; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif;">Fairfax, VA 22033</div><div jsinstance="0" class="cards-text-truncate-and-wrap" jsl="$x 7;" jstid="94" style="max-width: 100%; vertical-align: top; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis; font-family: Roboto, Arial, sans-serif;"><span id="gc-number-0" class="gc-cs-link" title="Call with Google Voice">(703) 961-1140</span></div></div></div>', '', '<div>St. John Neuman Catholic Church</div><div>11900 Lawyers Rd</div><div>Reston</div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0005031cfe6866b6484bd&msa=0&ll=38.923384,-77.363169&spn=0.007804,0.015814'),
(652, '<div>This week we have a more family oriented theme, but maybe not quite family &apos;friendly&apos;</div><div>What happens when you don&apos;t clean your room? You get grounded we all know that, but some parents are tougher than others.</div><div>The theme is "Falling family falling apart. &nbsp;Progeny AWOL for being grounded"</div><div>Falling decided the appropriate grounding punishment is to forbid the hash, can you imagine anything worse?</div><div>I personally can not.</div><div>So we&apos;re down from three to two hares this week. Come on out and see what the remaining Fallings can do with trail!</div>', '', '<div>Brion&apos;s Grille</div><div>10621 Braddock Rd</div><div>Fairfax, VA 22032</div><div>or</div><div>Kilroy&apos;s</div><div>5250A Port Royal Rd</div><div>Springfield, VA 22151</div>', '', 'Behind Cafe Rio in Burke<div>6003 Burke Centre Pkwy</div><div>Burke, VA 22015</div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0005032eb9da384adbe73&msa=0&ll=38.809483,-77.305727&spn=0.062535,0.126514'),
(653, 'Last time TWH laid a 7 mile trail loop that no one made it to. I guess he really wanted us to do that section, as here we go again.<div>Let&apos;s all hope he has the common sense not to actually make us do 7 miles.</div>', '<div><b>From South:</b>&nbsp;Take 286 Fairfax County Parkway North and exit onto</div><div>Braddock Road heading west. Turn right at the First light (Sign for</div><div>Willow Springs Elementary) Softball fields will be on the right.</div><div><b>From East:</b>&nbsp;Get to Braddock Road however suits you best. Head West.</div><div>once you pass the FFx County Parkway, Turn right at the First light</div><div>(Sign for Willow Springs Elementary) Softball fields will be on the</div><div>right.</div><div><b>From North or West:</b>&nbsp;Get to Fairfax County Parkway, take it Braddock</div><div>Rd. Head West on Braddock - Turn right at the First light (Sign for</div><div>Willow Springs Elementary) Softball fields will be on the right.</div>', 'TBD', 'Dress inappropriately...all else is up to you.<div><br></div><div>But as always, remember to bring out those beautiful young virgins</div>', 'Softball Fields at Willow Springs Elementary<div><div>5400 Willow Springs School Rd</div><div>Fairfax, VA 22030<br><br><br><div>At the Softball fields just before Willow Springs Elementary (off of</div><div>Braddock Road) You cannot see them from Braddock Road. Meet at the</div><div>back Softball Field.</div></div></div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.000504219e84d374bc550&msa=0&ll=38.831019,-77.37917&spn=0.007631,0.016512'),
(655, 'Since no one is filling out the harelog, Parent&apos;s will hare instead of getting super drunk like he should on his birthday...<div>Or he might just do both!</div>', 'Cumming Soon', 'TBD', '', '<div>Centreville Metro Free Park and Ride</div><div>6195 Stone Rd</div><div>Centreville, VA 20120</div>', ''),
(654, '<div><b></b></div><span style="font-size:24px;"><div style="font-size: 24px;"><b style="font-size: 24px;">Vicious Great White MILF Battle Caught on Camera</b></div><div style="font-size: 24px;"></div></span><div>Great white MILFs don&apos;t fight each other often, but when they do, it&apos;s no-teeth-barred.</div><div>It&apos;s even rarer because great whites will usually avoid conflict with each other -- but in this case, the smaller MILF went straight in for the attack, without hesitation. It&apos;s fascinating to see -- not least because MILFS only have their teeth with which to inflict damage. It doesn&apos;t last long, though - The Great White MILF has a clear size advantage.</div><div>Spotted in walking distance from the Vienna Metro...</div><div>Now... onto more important information!!</div>', '<div>METRO: VIENNA METRO" EXIT Metro to the North of Route 66 (LEFT) and turn LEFT onto Virginia Center Boulevard (toward Oakton High School). Continue through the high school parking lot on the LEFT and turn RIGHT onto Blake Lane. Turn RIGHT onto Tipperary Pass and then LEFT onto Cashel Lane to: "2935 Cashel Lane, Vienna, VA &nbsp;22181".</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>DRIVING:</div><div>From the WEST: (Ashburn/Sterling/Herndon/Reston):</div><div>Take Route 7, East... (or the Dulles Toll Road toward the beltway) From Route 7... take a RIGHT onto Baron Cameron Avenue and then LEFT onto Hunter Mill Road (from the Dulles Toll Road... take the EXIT for Hunter Mill Road and then RIGHT onto Hunter Mill Road). Continue on Hunter Mill Road and then turn LEFT onto Hunter Mill Road (yes... again!!). Continue on Hunter Mill Road until it ends at Route 123, Chain Bridge Road... and turn RIGHT onto Route 123, Chain Bridge Road. Turn LEFT onto Jermantown Road... Jermantown Road turns into Blake Lane. Turn LEFT onto Tipperary Pass and then LEFT onto Cashel Lane to: "2935 Cashel Lane, Vienna, VA &nbsp;22181".</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Look for wankers milling around...</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>From the BELTWAY:</div><div>Find your way to the Beltway and take the EXIT for the Route 66, West towards Winchester. Take the EXIT for Route 243, Nutley Street. Turn RIGHT onto Route 243, Nutley Street and then LEFT onto Virginia Center Boulevard. At the stop sign turn LEFT onto Sutton Road (just in front of Oakton High School). Turn RIGHT onto &nbsp;Blake Lane and then RIGHT onto Tipperary Pass and then LEFT onto Cashel Lane to: 2935 Cashel Lane, Vienna, VA &nbsp;22181".</div>', 'Glory Days is the closest bar/restaurant, however, Vienna Inn isn&apos;t that much further away!!', '', '<div>2935 Cashel Lane</div><div>Vienna, VA &nbsp;22181</div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.00050486429bc86973ea8&msa=0&ll=38.870913,-77.263927&spn=0.007025,0.012381');
