(657, 'It&apos;s that time of year again! Halloween!!!!<div>So cum on out and help Falling celebrate his birthday in style...with some costumes!</div><div>We hope to see a very stinky Big Bird, another sexy Lana, and all sorts of other crazy costumes</div>', '<div>Get to 495. If you are coming from Braddock, just jump to the Braddock section of these directions (head towards 495)</div><div>Take the Braddock Road West exit from 495.</div><div>Immediately turn left at the first light to the strip mall across the street.</div><div>Drive around to the back parking lot behind the bar somewhere.</div><div>Find Wankers</div><div>Celebrate (er...Hash)!</div><div><br></div><div>Start is behind Kilroys in Fairfax.</div><div>Ravensworth Shopping Center off Braddock Rd</div>', '<div>Kilroys Restaurant and Sports Bar</div><div>5250 Port Royal Rd, Springfield</div>', '', '<div>Behind Kilroys Restaurant and Sports Bar</div><div>5250 Port Royal Rd, Springfield</div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.0004f56d50d2889eb558e&msa=0&ll=38.808681,-77.22201&spn=0.007633,0.016512'),
(658, 'Celebrate ATWI making it one more year, and have a few shots', '<div>From the WEST: (Ashburn/Sterling/Herndon/Reston):</div><div>Head south on VA-28 S, Take the US-50 exit toward Winchester/Fairfax. Keep left at the fork to continue toward US-50 E, Keep right at the fork, follow signs for Fairfax/US-50 E and merge onto US-50 E for about 6.7 miles and turn right onto Jermantown Rd. Cross over 29 and go in the WalMart Parking Lot.&nbsp;</div><div>Look for wankers milling around...</div><div><br></div><div>From the BELTWAY:&nbsp;</div><div>Find your way to the Beltway and take the Exit 50 A, follow signs for U.S. 50 W/Fairfax and merge onto US-50 W/Arlington Blvd. Continue to follow US-50 W for about 5.8 miles then continue straight onto US-29 S about  1/2  mile and turn Left onto Jermantown Rd into the WalMart Parking Lot.&nbsp;</div><div>Look for wankers milling around...</div>', 'Primetime Sports Bar &amp; Grille ,11250 James Swart Cir Fairfax, VA 22030, (703) 352-0260, primetimesportsandgrill.com', '<div>This trail won&apos;t be the ball buster that last years was, but it&apos;ll still be a decent hike. Bring your PI block, bug spray, and of course a headlamp!</div><div><br></div><div>ADD&apos;L INFO: BRING A FLASHLIGHT!! You know... just in case!! And need I remind you of the standard disclaimers?</div><div><br></div><div>Dog Friendly Factor: Tough Dogs Only...</div><div>Stroller Friendly Factor: This is an ATWI trail... get real.</div><div>Final Disclaimer: Bring enough dry clothes and shoes to stay warm in 40 deg weather, and your appetite for some beers!! And... finally... should we remind you... shiggy-socks/pants and PI Block.</div><div><br></div><div>Oh... and please don&apos;t forget those beautiful, young female virgins!!</div>', 'Walmart Supercenter, 11181 Lee Hwy, Fairfax, VA 22030', 'https://www.google.com/maps/ms?msid=208291817849788313232.000506bcc3f2fcf3807e2&msa=0&ll=38.849716,-77.332224&spn=0.007812,0.015814'),
(659, 'We all have someone we want to remember, and today&apos;s trail is dedicated to remembering those persons at their very best. Doc Cock&apos;s Day of The Dead trail in memory of his Colombian Abuela, Marta Lucia, who recently passed. She had a dedicated sense of hospitality and a decidedly wicked sense of humor. Guests in her home were entertained with hilarious conversation, fabulous food, and were always offered cafe con leche in the mornings---and aguardiente in the evenings! So why not come out for a trail featuring coffee and liquor the way Doc Cock&apos;s Abuela used to like them? Make a toast and down a shot in memory of someone awesome in your life!&nbsp;', '', 'Kalypso&apos;s Sports Tavern<div>Washington Plaza North</div><div>Reston, VA</div>', '', 'Behind Paisano&apos;s<div>Tall Oaks Village Center</div><div>Reston, VA</div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/edit?mid=z8oA6gJ-rfLo.kQe4rWm6Ovjo'),
(660, 'Join us to celebrate the life of one of our favorite harriettes, Poonskin Cap. &nbsp;We&apos;ll share some stories, drink some drinks, and eat copious amounts of orange food. &nbsp;Technology on trail highly encouraged - let&apos;s tweet, Facebook and Instagram our way through trail just like Poon always did! &nbsp;The more selfies, the better! &nbsp;:-) &nbsp;Paraphrasing Watergate, "The afterlife better have an unlimited data plan now that Poon&apos;s there!"', '<div>Driving: We&apos;re inside the beltway! &nbsp;Take 66 EAST to exit 69 (woot!). &nbsp;Turn right on US-29 south (Lee Highway) go 0.6 miles. &nbsp;Cross Broad St. (Rt. 7) and make a quick right into the parking garage, drive to the top. &nbsp;Circle the block if you miss it.</div><div>Metro: Yep - get off at East Falls Church</div><div><br></div>', '<div>Clare &amp; Don&apos;s Beach Shack</div><div>130 N Washington St</div><div>Falls Church, VA 22046</div>', 'Short-ish walking trail including 2 bars (pay as you go), Flabongo shots, and beer! &nbsp;Bring ID!', 'top of the parking garage behind<div>Ireland&apos;s Four Provinces</div><div>105 W Broad St</div><div>Falls Church, VA 22046</div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/edit?mid=z8oA6gJ-rfLo.kOA4bxrrm-yU'),
(661, '<div>Come on out and get your turkey on! Drunk Turkey that is! Shots and</div><div>Beer will greet you on trail so come dressed as a sexy pilgrim, or</div><div>sexy native American, or sexy turkey and come get basted with your</div><div>favorite hashers. Fire Pit at the Circle location!</div>', '<b>From the (South) East:</b><div>Get to 66.</div><div>Take it West</div><div>If you are HOV 2+ (or are running late and it is after 7pm)</div><blockquote style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;"><div style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Take the Stringfellow Exit (the left exit right after exit 55).</div></blockquote><blockquote style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;"><div style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Go Left at the light on Stringfellow</div></blockquote><blockquote style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;"><div style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Turn Left onto Autumn Willow Dr</div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Make your first Left into the Soccer Fields</div></blockquote>If you are&nbsp;<b>NOT</b>&nbsp;HOV compliant and on time)<div><blockquote style="margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;"><div style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Take exit 55, and head South on Fairfax County Parkway</div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Turn Right onto Route 29 (Lee Highway)</div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Turn Right onto Stringfellow Rd</div><div style="margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 40px; border: none; padding: 0px;">Turn Right onto Autumn Willow Dr</div><div style=