(667, 'The first SHIT trail of 2015 is going to be wicked!<div><br></div><div><div>To make sure trail is HOT enough, All The Way In will provide some Spicy shots and Spicy snacks on trail!</div><div>There will be toe tags for the first 30 people to sign in.</div></div>', '<div><b>METRO</b>: Get of at East Falls Church Station and look for marks to go across the street to Start.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><b>DRIVING D&apos;ERECTIONS</b>: (all directions provided by Mr. Google - If you do not like them... blame him)</div><div><br></div><div><b>From the WEST:</b> (Ashburn/Sterling/Herndon/Reston):</div><div>Head south on Route 7. Take the ramp onto I-66 East, and go about 1.7 miles on I-66 and use exit #69 (go straight at the light at the top of the ramp) to merge onto Fairfax Drive/VA 237 eastbound. After 1/3 mile turn right onto North Sycamore Street, for about 1/2 mile and turn left onto North 17th Street. Take the 1st left onto Roosevelt Street, and look for wankers at the end of the road.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><b>From the DC</b>:</div><div>Find your way to I-66 W and use exit #69. Turn left onto North Sycamore Street and after 1/3 mile turn left onto North 17th Street. Take the 1st left onto Roosevelt Street, and look for wankers at the end of the road.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><b>From the BELTWAY:</b></div><div>Find your way to I-66 E and use exit #69 (go straight at the light at the top of the ramp) to merge onto Fairfax Drive/VA 237 eastbound. After 1/3 mile turn right onto North Sycamore Street, for about 1/2 mile and turn left onto North 17th Street. Take the 1st left onto Roosevelt Street, and look for wankers at the end of the road.&nbsp;</div>', 'Dogfish Head Alehouse<div>6220 Leesburg Pike</div><div>Falls Church, Virginia 22044</div>', '<div>Bring enough dry clothes and shoes to stay warm in 40 deg weather, and your appetite for some beers!!</div><div><div>And... finally... should we remind you... shiggy-socks/pants and a Flashlight!</div><div><br></div><div>Oh... and please don&apos;t forget those beautiful, young female virgins!!</div></div>', 'Across the street from the East Falls Church Metro Station at<div>1798 Roosevelt Street<div>Arlington, VA</div></div>', ''),
(668, '<p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="&apos;color:" black;="" font-family:="" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font size="3">Hummm...</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3"></font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="&apos;color:" black;="" font-family:="" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3"></font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="&apos;color:" black;="" font-family:="" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font size="3">It seems to me... that LAST YEAR at this time (second Tuesday of 2014, January 14</font><sup><font color="#000000" face="Georgia" size="2">th</font></sup><font size="3"> 2014 to be exact), we did a trail just a stones throw away from Redskins Park (The "Search for Gruden" Trail).</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3"></font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="&apos;color:" black;="" font-family:="" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3"></font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="&apos;color:" black;="" font-family:="" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font size="3">However... we did not find the new Redskins Head Coach, Jay Gruden, nor did we get to see the lights on that the Washington Redskins indoor practice facility.</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3"></font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="&apos;color:" black;="" font-family:="" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3"></font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="&apos;color:" black;="" font-family:="" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font size="3">Well... even though Jay Gruden DID show up for some of the Redskins&apos; games... he still may be lost in the woods surrounding Redskins Park. To add to our list of non-hashing half-minds, The Washington Redskins have hired Scot (with one "t") McCloughan as their new General Manager for the next four years!!</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3"></font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="&apos;color:" black;="" font-family:="" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3"></font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="&apos;color:" black;="" font-family:="" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font size="3">Just like Jay Gruden last year, the frigid weather must have gone to their heads for he accepted any kind of job with the Washington Redskins!!</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3"></font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="&apos;color:" black;="" font-family:="" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3"></font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="&apos;color:" black;="" font-family:="" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font size="3">So... as good harriers that we are... we once again begin our search in Ashburn... knowing that when you lost, cold and hungry... that you&apos;re not very far from home.</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3"></font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="&apos;color:" black;="" font-family:="" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3"></font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="&apos;color:" black;="" font-family:="" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font size="3">Therefore... when on trail... if you happen to see a forty-some year old in a dark suit and Redskin cap... please provide your OnOnOns to help him get back to Redskin Park!!</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3"></font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="&apos;color:" black;="" font-family:="" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font size="3">&nbsp;</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3"></font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 0pt;"><span style="&apos;color:" black;="" font-family:="" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font size="3">With that being said... this week&apos;s trail will "START" at:</font> <b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><font color="#000000" face="Georgia" size="3">"</font></b></span><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><a href="https://www.google.com/maps/place/21800+Beaumeade+Cir,+Ashburn,+VA+20147/@39.013682,-77.451713,699m/data=!3m2!1e3!4b1!4m2!3m1!1s0x89b638df5e5e9637:0x5e5805cb85ee9337"><span style="&apos;font-family:" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font color="#0000ff" size="3">21800 Beaumeade Circle</font></span></a></b><b style="mso-bidi-font-weight: normal;"><span style="&apos;color:" black;="" font-family:="" "georgia","serif";="" mso-bidi-font-family:="" arial;="" mso-no-proof:="" yes;&apos;=""><font size=