(677, 'Cum get your Irish on with SHIT this St. Patrick&apos;s Day.<div>Don your kilts or at least your green and get ready for a night of shenanigans, tomfoolery and a little ballyhoo!</div><div>Shot checks, Irish beer checks, runners and walkers trail.</div>', '<div>Get on the beltway (that would be 495) from wherever you are. You&apos;ll want to go either North, South, East or West (depending on where you are)</div><div>Get off on Gallows Road. &nbsp;Follow Gallows Road North a few miles (towards Tysons). Cross over Lee Highway. Make a U-turn at Park Tower. &nbsp;Hotel will be on your right. &nbsp;Turn right at Black Finn - there are two parking garages in that area. &nbsp;Park in one of those.</div><div>OR....just use your GPS and type in the address - everyone has one anyways. &nbsp;It&apos;s called Waze...download the app.</div>', '<div>Black Finn Ameripub</div><div>2750 Gallows Rd</div><div>Vienna, VA 22180</div>', 'Pub Crawl/Bring Money&amp;ID, Dog friendly, Stroler Friendly, A-A or A-B', 'Small park in front of the Courtyard Marriott in Dunn Loring - &nbsp;Look for benches and wankers in front of the hotel.<br><div>Courtyard Mariott Dunn Loring - Fairfax,</div><div>2722 Gallows Rd</div><div>Vienna, VA 2218</div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/edit?mid=z1yVFofA7i34.kpxsEZ1vJo8s'),
(678, 'Cumming soon, I&apos;m still sober over here', '<div>METRO: METRO? Did someone say, METRO? Coming to Herndon sometime soon... NOT!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>DRIVING:</div><div>From the WEST: (Sterling/Herndon/Reston): From Route 7...</div><div>Take Route 228, Dranesville Road towards Herndon. Continue bearing RIGHT on Route 228 and take a LEFT onto Elden Street. After you see the Safeway on your right keep going, then make your second RIGHT onto Herndon Parkway. Then turn RIGHT onto Spring Street, and an immediate RIGHT into the parking lot: "220 Spring Street, Herndon VA &nbsp;20170".</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Look for wankers milling around.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>From the BELTWAY: Find your way to the Beltway and take the EXIT for the Dulles Toll Road towards Reston/Herndon/Sterling. Take the EXIT for Route 7100 (however they may call it: Route 286) Fairfax County Parkway. Turn RIGHT onto Fairfax County Parkway towards Herndon. Take the RAMP for Baron Cameron/Elden Street and turn LEFT onto Elden Street. Turn LEFT onto Herndon Parkway. Then turn RIGHT onto Spring Street, and an immediate RIGHT into the parking lot: "220 Spring Street, Herndon VA &nbsp;20170".</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Look for wankers milling around.</div>', '<div>Carpool</div><div>208 Elden Street</div><div>Herndon, VA &nbsp;20170</div><div><span id="gc-number-0" class="gc-cs-link" title="Call with Google Voice">571-203-7995</span></div>', '<div>ADD&apos;L INFO: BRING A FLASHLIGHT!! You know... just in case!! And need I remind you of the standard disclaimers?</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Miscellaneous: Trail will be... A to A&apos;:</div><div>(translated... the OTHER end of the parking lot!!)</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Dog Friendly Factor: Tough Dogs Only...</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Stroller Friendly Factor: Tough Strollers Only...</div><div><br></div><div>Final Disclaimer: Bring dry clothes and shoes, bug spray, sunscreen (NOT!!), condoms (as always... be safe!!), your grandmother&apos;s underwear (why... we don&apos;t know. Hummm... or is it... you never know?), and your appetite for some fine beers from all over the world!! And... finally... should we remind you... shiggy-socks and/or PI Block.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Oh... and please don&apos;t forget those beautiful, young female virgins!!</div>', '<div>The large parking lot behind 220 Spring Street</div><div>Herndon VA 20170</div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/edit?mid=zTf66a6BrZws.kfxsIqtv2Yps'),
(679, 'Everyone lookout. Herp is haring solo on Tuesday.<div>That&apos;s what happens when you wanks don&apos;t sign up for trail in a timely manner.</div><div>YOU DID THIS TO YOURSELVES</div>', 'Cumming Soon', 'Red Rocks Cafe &amp; Tequila Bar<div>Old Centreville Crossing, 13850 Braddock Rd</div><div>Centreville, VA 20121</div><div>(703) 815-6900</div>', '', 'In front of the soccer fields at<div>Ellanor C Lawrence Park</div><div>5040 Walney Rd, Chantilly, VA 20151</div>', ''),
(680, 'Why is Easter so early this year? It must be those fucking Jews!<div>That&apos;s right. We wanted to get the cracker holiday over with already, so we decided to drop a month, and speed up the whole process.</div><div>Come on out to enjoy all ten plagues in the best way possible, shot form!</div>', 'Go&nbsp;<a href="http://goo.gl/maps/l2viM">here</a><div>Enter your address</div><div>Click get directions</div><div>Follow them!</div>', 'TBD, wherever Mani is on tap', 'Trail is A to A&apos;.<div>There will be a walkers, and runners with a Turkey Eagle split, but only the Eagles will get all 10 plagues, so come pumped for the full trail!</div><div>Like usual, this will be a long trail for eagle, so either be prepared for a long trail, or take the turkey/walkers shortcut</div><div>BRING LIGHTS!!!</div>', '<div>The back lot of</div><div>St Matthews United Methodist</div><div>8617 Little River Turnpike</div><div>Annandale, VA 22003</div>', ''),
(681, 'Come out and share the micro-brews, home-brews, hidden gems and precious pints of the beer spectrum<div>Bring&nbsp;$1 and a 6-pack of the Strangest beer you can find (I.E. not from a local gas station -&nbsp;</div><div>In fact we are starting just a block away from a Total Wine &amp; more at 6801 Bland Street that carries a huge stock of foreign, micro-brew and specialty beers and ciders)</div>', '<div><b>From the West</b>: Make your way into the beltway and take I-495 South towards Richmond. Take exit 57A toward Interstate 95 S/Richmond/Virginia 644 for 1/2 mile. Keep right to continue on Exit 169B, follow signs for VA-644 W/Old Keene Mill Road for 1.1 mile. Keep left, follow signs for Old Keene/Springfield, continue onto Old Keene Mill Road for 0.2 miles and Start will be on the right.</div><div><br></div><div><b>From the North</b>: Make your way to I-395 South towards Richmond. Take exit 1B toward Springfield for 1.3 miles. Continue onto Old Keene Mill Road 0.2 miles. and Start will be on the right.</div><div><br></div><div><b>From the South</b>: Get on I-95 North. Take exit 169A-169B to merge onto VA-644 W/Franconia Rd toward Springfield. Continue to follow VA-644 W for 1.7 miles and Start will be on the right.</div><div><br></div>', 'Hard Times Caf?<div>6362 Springfield Plaza</div><div>Springfield, VA 22150</div><div><span id="gc-number-0" class="gc-cs-link" title="Call with Google Voice">(703) 913-5600</span></div>', 'A-Aish Trail, Bring your bottle openers and flashlights, Hosehead (Dog) OK on trail but will be in a very street traffic heavy area and not allowed at On-After.&nbsp;', 'Springfield Plaza Shopping Center<div>7206 Old Keene Mill Road<div>Springfield, VA</div></div>', ''),
(682, 'It&apos;s National Kindergarten Day! Lucky for us hashers, as most of our minds never progressed much farther.<div>Bring your usual attitude, and be prepared for a trail with the usual half mindedness (maybe even less this time)</div>', '<div><b>From Dulles Toll Rd:</b></div><div>Hunter Mill Rd exit</div><div>Go south on Hunter Mill Rd for 0.4 miles</div><div>At "T" intersection, turn R onto Sunrise Valley Dr; go 0.6 miles</div><div>Turn R at light onto Robert Fulton Dr</div><div>follow this up the hill and turn R into parking lot for 1801</div><div>Go the to far back of the parking lot.</div>', '<div>Cosmopolitan Lounge in the Reston Sheraton</div><div>11810 Sunrise Valley Dr</div>', '', '<div>1801 Robert Fulton Dr</div><div>Reston, VA</div>', ''),
