(684, '<div>It is Cinqo de Mayo! &nbsp;And Lube&apos;s birthday!</div>', '<div>From 495:</div><div>Go east on Route 7 for about a mile.&nbsp;</div><div>Turn right at the light onto Pimmit Drive.</div><div>Drive past the Whole Foods parking lot and turn right into the next strip mall. &nbsp;There is a weird 2-story Subway right at the entrance.</div><div>Drive straight back and up the little hill to the upper lot.</div><div>Park and hash.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>From 66:</div><div>Go west on Route 7 for about half a mile.</div><div>Turn left at the light onto Pimmit Drive.</div><div>Drive past the Whole Foods parking lot and turn right into the next strip mall. &nbsp;There is a weird 2-story Subway right at the entrance.</div><div>Drive straight back and up the little hill to the upper lot.</div><div>Park and hash.</div><div><br></div>', '<div>Art&apos;s Tavern</div><div>2190 Pimmit Dr</div><div>Falls Church, VA 22043</div>', '<div>It is Cinqo de Mayo! &nbsp;And Lube&apos;s birthday!&nbsp;</div><div>Bring a headlamp!</div><div>There is green stuff on trail. &nbsp;I have not broken out from scouting so it probably isn&apos;t poison ivy. &nbsp;But I was wearing pants and showered immediately after scouting. &nbsp;So, yeah, green stuff.&nbsp;</div><div>Dog friendly.</div><div>A stroller would be a pain in the ass. &nbsp;Go to a family hash.&nbsp;</div>', '<div>Upper parking lot (drive all the way straight back and up the little hill):</div><div>2190 Pimmit Dr</div><div>Falls Church, VA 22043</div>', ''),
(685, '<div>Hummm...</div><div>A "Great Falls" trail on Tuesday?</div><div>Who woudda thunk it!?!</div><div>Bad Dog is recruiting 24/7... last week in a discussion he had with a Great Falls Hasher, to be identified later, he finds out that this wanker bought a new place and hadn&apos;t yet sold the other (River Bend Road).</div><div>"And How&apos;s Her Bush" and "Dr. C*ckulus" were planning their next trail in Great Falls (see where I&apos;m going here...) Wa&apos;la!!</div><div>A marrage made in heaven!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>With that being said... this week&apos;s trail will "START" at: "509 River Bend Road, Great Falls VA &nbsp;22066".</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>AHHB</div>', '<div><b>METRO:</b> METRO? Did someone say, METRO? In Great Falls? PLEASE!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><b>DRIVING:</b></div><div>From the WEST Via Route 7: (Sterling/Herndon/Reston):</div><div>Take a LEFT onto Georgetown Pike towards McLean (if cumming from Reston take Baron Cameron Avenue across Route 7 which then turns into Springvale Road to Georgetown Pike... Turn RIGHT onto Georgetown Pike). Continue on Georgetown Pike through Great Falls toward Great Falls Park. Turn &nbsp;LEFT onto River Road and continue for approx. 1.2 miles to: 509 River Bend Road, Great Falls VA &nbsp;22066".</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Look for wankers milling around.</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><b>From the BELTWAY:</b></div><div>Find your way to the Beltway and take the EXIT for the Georgetown Pike towards Great Falls. Continue on Georgetown Pike past the entrance for Great Falls Park and take first RIGHT onto River Road and continue for approx. 1.2 miles to: 509 River Bend Road, Great Falls VA &nbsp;22066".</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Look for wankers milling around.</div>', '<div>The Old Brogue Irish Pub</div><div>760 Walker Road</div><div>Great Falls, VA &nbsp;22066</div><div><span id="gc-number-0" class="gc-cs-link" title="Call with Google Voice">703-759-3309</span></div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>D&apos;ERECTIONS:</div><div>FROM "START":</div><div>Take a RIGHT onto Georgetown Pike ~ Continue to the town of Great Falls ~ Continue past Walker Road ~ Turn LEFT into the shopping center to: Buffalo Wild Wings: 21980 Colorado Drive, Dulles 28 Centre, Sterling, VA</div>', 'BRING A FLASHLIGHT!! You know... just in case!! And need I remind you of the standard disclaimers?', '509 River Bend Road<div>Great Falls VA, 22066</div>', ''),
(686, '<div>The SHIT Hash returns to Falls Church, this time, with the challenge to polish off a keg of 40 Mile IPA, navigate through ghost trails (previous hash marks) and stay on a trail that is guaranteed to "exceed standards." Whose standards, you ask? I guess you&apos;ll have to come and find out for yourself!</div>', '<div><b>METRO: </b>&nbsp;</div><div>The start is about a mile (18 Min walk) South East of the McLean Metro Station. &nbsp;</div><div>Take Dolley Madison Blvd North East to Anderson Road.&nbsp;</div><div>Turn right and go almost a mile.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div><b>DRIVING:</b>&nbsp;</div><div><b>From the WEST:</b>&nbsp;(Sterling/Herndon/Reston):</div><div>Take Route 7, East and turn LEFT onto Lewinsville Road (694).&nbsp;</div><div>After about 11 miles the road becomes Great Falls Street.&nbsp;</div><div>Continue another 2 miles and turn RIGHT onto Magarity Road for about 1/3 mile and turn LEFT into Anderson &nbsp;Road.&nbsp;</div><div>After 1/3 mile park near 1808 Anderson Road and come into the back yard.</div><div><br></div><div><b>From the BELTWAY:</b>&nbsp;</div><div>Find your way to the Theodore Roosevelt Memorial Bridge and take the George Washington Memorial Parkway for about 5.7 miles and EXIT onto VA-123 &nbsp;for 5 miles and turn LEFT onto Great Falls &nbsp;Road (694).&nbsp;</div><div>Continue for  1/2  mile and turn RIGHT onto Magarity Road for about 1/3 mile and turn LEFT into Anderson &nbsp;Road.&nbsp;</div><div>After 1/3 mile park near 1808 Anderson Road and come into the back yard .</div><div><br></div><div><b>From the SOUTH:&nbsp;</b></div><div>Find your way to I-95 North.</div><div>Take I-495 towards Tysons Corner and take the EXIT 47A for Leesburg Pike East.&nbsp;</div><div>Take an immediate LEFT onto Lisle Ave for 1.2 miles. Take a RIGHT onto Anderson &nbsp;Road.&nbsp;</div><div>Park in front of 1808 Anderson Road and come into the back yard.</div>', '<div>On-On-On: Some food will be provided at Fingerrrgrgrgrr&apos;s house.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>After that the hash is welcome to go to Lost Dog or Art&apos;s Tavern.</div>', '<div><b>BRING A FLASHLIGHT!!</b> You know... just in case!!</div><div><i>And need I remind you of the standard disclaimers?</i></div><div><b><br></b></div><div><b>Miscellaneous:</b> Trail will be... A to A&apos;:</div><div>Dog Friendly Factor: Tough Dogs Only...</div><div>Stroller Friendly Factor: Tough Strollers Only...</div><div>Final Disclaimer: Bring dry clothes and shoes, bug spray, sunscreen (!?!), condoms (as always... be safe!!), your grandmother&apos;s underwear (why... we don&apos;t know. Hummm... or is it... you never know?), and your appetite for some fine beers from all over the world!! And... finally... should we remind you... shiggy-socks and/or PI Block.</div><div>Oh... and please don&apos;t forget those beautiful, young female virgins!!</div><div><br></div><div><b>QUESTIONS: </b>Contact And How&apos;s Her Bush: AndHowsHerBush@yahoo.com</div>', '<div>Casa De Fingerrrgrgrgr</div><div>1808 Anderson Road</div><div>Falls Church, VA &nbsp;22043</div>', ''),
