INSERT INTO `shit_directions` (`TRL_ID`, `TIDBIT`, `DIRECTIONS`, `ONONON`, `NOTES`, `ADDRESS`, `MAPLINK`) VALUES
(689, '<div>So Happy Its Tuesday Hash House Harriers was founded by a handful of wankers that lived in the Sterling-Herndon-Reston area but would frequent trails by the Over The Hump Hash House Harriers (OTH4) in the Woodbridge-Dale City area (our Mother Hash).</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>Therefore S.H.*.T. adopted a lot of the OTH4 markings: L arrow for Long trail (runners), W arrow for Walkers trail, flour in a Triangular Shape for intersection, three Parallel lines for false trail, B w/check mark for Beer Check, plus some of the traditional markings. A S.H.*.T. trail is NOT COMPLETE until Finish is written at or near the ultimate BN (Beer Near)!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>After discussion of what days the other DC Area kennels where running it was determined that Tuesday was the ideal date. And rumors told it was Tupperwares mother that came up with SH*T for So Happy Its Tuesday!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>So Happy Its Tuesday H3 began with the goal of surviving the first three years. We pride ourselves on (mostly) off-road trails that are conducted LIVE (w/fifteen minute head start). There is nothing better than running through the woods in the middle of winter with just a flashlight!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>This weeks trail is within one (1) mile of the start of one its first trails ever and it should offer a true traditional off-road experience. So cum on out to S.H.*.T. H3 and learn more about this amazing kennel.</div>', '<div><b>Metro</b></div><div>Of course the Spring Hill Station(Tyson West Station)... On the Silver Line!!</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div><b>Driving:</b></div><div><i>From the Sterling/Herndon/Reston</i></div><div>Get yourself ontoRoute 7, East or Route 267, Dulles Toll Roadheading towardsTysons Corner. After you pass over Route 267, Dulles Toll Road (or take the Route 7, East exit, if coming from the Toll Road) and take the firstRIGHTontoWestwood Center Drive. Continue to the end of the cul-de-sac of Westwood Center Drive, park and look for wankers milling around.</div><div><i>From the Beltway</i></div><div>Get yourself to theBeltway (I-495). TakeEXIT 45for theRoute 267, Dulles Toll Road. As soon as you go through the main toll plaza take the firstEXITfor Route 7. On the ramp to Route 7 stay on yourLEFTand turnLEFTontoRoute 7, East. You will pass back over the Dulles Toll Road and take your firstRIGHTontoWestwood Center Drive. Continue to the end of the cul-de-sac of Westwood Center Drive, park and look for wankers milling around.</div><div>Alternate direction from theBeltway (I-495). TakeEXIT 47B-Afor theRoute 7, West. Continue on Route 7 for approx. 2 miles and turnLEFTontoWestwood Center Drive(Tyco Road will be on your right). Continue to the end of the cul-de-sac of Westwood Center Drive, park and look for wankers milling around.</div><div>&nbsp;</div>', '<div>O Malleys Pub (located behind the Crown Plaza (in between Crown Plaza and the Marriott at Route 123 and International Drive)</div><div>1960 Chain Bridge Rd, Mclean, VA 22102-4001</div>', '<p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 12pt;">Dog Friendly Factor: If its hot out leave the little critters at home!!<br><br>Live Trail, as usual, and its A to A&nbsp;</span><b><i><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 10pt;">(meaning that its long enough that I have to move the Beer Vehicle but short enough for you to leave your sh*t in the cars!! Translated NO BAG VEHICLE and NO SHUTTLES NEEDED!!)</span></i></b><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 12pt;">.<u><u></u></u></span></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><u><u></u></u></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><u><u><u><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 12pt;">I would suggest BRING A FLASHLIGHT!! If you&apos;re an EWH3 hasher forget the light and you&apos;ll never survive this trail!!<u style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 12pt;"><u style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 12pt;"></u></u></span></u></u></u></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><u><u></u></u></p><p class="MsoNormal" style="color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: arial, sans-serif; font-size: 13px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><u><u><u><span style="font-family: Georgia, serif; font-size: 12pt;">Final disclaimer bring dry clothes and shoes and any FEMALE RUSSIAN VIRGINS you have in your closet!! (hummm WAIT!! Okay the virgin(s) can be wet!!)</span></u></u></u></p><u>&nbsp;</u>', 'The End of Westwood Center Drive<div><div>8699 Westwood Center Dr</div><div>Vienna, VA 22182-2235</div></div><div><br></div><div>&nbsp;6:30 pm Sign-In, 7 pm Hares Away</div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/d/edit?mid=zTf66a6BrZws.k7FMroIJKu-Q&usp=sharing'),
(690, '<div>Just Alexander has reached the monumental milestone of being one year old. &nbsp;Leave it said one year old to convince Nuke and Udder to finally hare their birthday trail (5 months late). &nbsp;At least it&apos;s not March like And How&apos;s Her predicted. &nbsp;It also means three birthdays, three trail options, three beverage checks, and whatever else the uncreative hares can make into threes. &nbsp;</div><div><br></div><div>Just Alexander will be making his debut as Lead Hare from the comfort of his stroller; so if you have been waiting for an easy trail in warm weather in order for you to show up, this is the one!</div><div><br></div>', '<div>Directions stolen from AHHB. &nbsp;So if they&apos;re wrong blame him.</div><div><br></div><div>DRIVING:</div><div>From the WEST: (Sterling/Herndon/Reston): "Head" West-ish!!From the intersection of Route 7 &amp; Route 28... Take Route 28, South towards DullesAirport. Take the RAMP for WaxpoolRoad towards Ashburn. Turn RIGHTonto BeaumeadeCircle (this is the first right after you pass Broderick Drive and theGolf Course Club House). Take your 1stRIGHT onto Beaumeade Circle. Turn RIGHT into the first parking lot at: 21800 Beaumeade Circle, Ashburn VA</div><div>&nbsp;</div><div>From the BELTWAY: Findyour way to the Beltway and take the EXITfor the Dulles Toll Road towards Reston/Herndon/Sterling. Takethe EXIT for Route 28, North Sully Road.Continue on Route 28, North Sully Road past the exit for Sterling Boulevard andtake the LEFT EXIT for WaxpoolRoad towards Ashburn. Turn RIGHTonto BeaumeadeCircle (this is the first right after you pass Broderick Drive and theGolf Course Club House). Take your 1stRIGHT onto Beaumeade Circle . Turn RIGHT into the first parking lot at: 21800 Beaumeade Circle, Ashburn VA</div><div><br></div>', '<div>Buffalo Wild Wings</div><div>21980 Colorado Drive</div><div>Dulles 28 Centre</div><div>Dulles, VA 20166-2509</div>', '', 'Parking lot behind 21301 Beaumeade Circle, Ashburn, VA', ''),
(691, 'Let&apos;s see if Doc Cock can lay a trail and NOT lose the beermeister. That would be wonderful, wouldn&apos;t it?', 'Get on Rt 7<div>Turn right on to Colvin Mill Road (or Left if coming from the West)</div><div>Take immediate right onto gravel road</div><div>Follow to old water treatment building</div>', 'American Tap Room<div>1811 Library Street</div><div>Reston, VA 20190</div><div>(703) 834-0400</div><div>americantaproom.com</div>', '', '10002 Colvin Run Road<div>Great Falls, VA</div>', ''),
(692, '<div>Because I had so much fun here last time I have decided to revisit this local for the food alone. &nbsp;Prepare for a trail that will tantalize the senses and touch your soul naughtily.</div><div><br></div>', '', '<div>Chuy&apos;s Tex-Mex</div><div>11219 Lee Hwy, Fairfax, VA 22030</div><div><span id="gc-number-0" class="gc-cs-link" title="Call with Google Voice">(703) 364-5933</span></div>', '', '<div>11213 Lee Hwy</div><div>Fairfax, VA 22030</div><div>(Behind Bombay Cafe, Batteries Plus Bulbs, Kumon Me Math &amp; Reading Center)</div>', ''),
(693, 'The SHIT Hash returns to Burke Lake Park, but this time the SOUTH SIDE.', '<div><b>METRO:</b> Nope, Not this time. Hitch a ride with someone.</div><div><br></div><div><b>DRIVING:&nbsp;</b></div><div><b>From the NORTH and WEST:</b> (Sterling/Herndon/Reston): Take I-66 East and take Exit 55A for VA-286 S/Fairfax County Pkwy. After 6.3 miles take exit for VA-123 / Ox Road. Turn Left on Ox Road and Left into the second entrance into Burke Lake Park after 2.6 miles LOOK FOR THE TRUE TRAIL ARROW SIGNS.</div><div><br></div><div><b>From the BELTWAY:</b> Find your way to I-95 South. Take Exit 166B for VA-286 N / Fairfax County Parkway, after 2.6 miles take Right Exit to stay on VA-286 / Fairfax County Parkway for another 3.2 miles. Turn Left onto VA-643 / Lee Chapel Road for 1.1 miles and turn Right on VA-123 / Ox Road for 1.2 miles. Turn Right at the secondary Entrance for Burke Lake Park LOOK FOR THE TRUE TRAIL ARROW SIGNS.</div>', '<div>Glory Days Grill</div><div>Burke Town Plaza</div><div>9526 Old Keene Mill Road</div><div>Burke, VA 22015.</div><div><br></div><div>D&apos;Erections to On-After from Start: Go South on VA-123 Ox Road for 1.2 miles and Turn Left onto VA-643 / Lee Chapel Road. After 2.8 miles turn Right into Burke Town Plaza, and park in front of Glory Days.&nbsp;</div><div><br></div>', '<div>ADD&apos;L INFO: BRING A FLASHLIGHT!! You know... just in case!! And need I remind you of the standard disclaimers?</div><div><br></div><div>Miscellaneous: Trail will be... A to A&apos;:</div><div><br></div><div>Dog Friendly Factor: Dogs welcome on trial, but not in On-After</div><div><br></div><div>Stroller Friendly Factor: No Strollers</div><div><br></div><div>Final Disclaimer: Bring dry clothes and shoes, bug spray, sunscreen (NOT!!), condoms (as always... be safe!!), your grandmother&apos;s underwear (why... we don&apos;t know. Hummm... or is it... you never know?), and your appetite for some fine beers from all over the world!! And... finally... should we remind you... shiggy-socks and/or PI Block.</div><div><br></div><div>Oh... and please don&apos;t forget those beautiful, young female virgins!!</div><div><br></div><div>QUESTIONS: Contact All The Way In: Allthewayin@rocketmail.com&nbsp;</div><div><span id="gc-number-0" class="gc-cs-link" title="Call with Google Voice">(240) 993-6474</span></div>', 'Burke Lake Park Entrance across the road from 7448 Ox Road (VA Route 123), Fairfax Station, VA 22039', ''),
(694, '<div>Puppy friendly trail. At least one beer check. Definitely two walker/runner splits. Shiggy scale: mid-90&apos;s Playboy bush.</div><div>Start location coordinates: 38?50?56? N 77?18?7? W (I&apos;m not converting to MGRS, because my field of fucks is barren and I have none to give)</div>', '<br>', 'The Auld Shebeen<div>3971 Chain Bridge Rd</div><div>Fairfax, VA 22030</div><div><span title="Call with Google Voice" class="gc-cs-link" id="gc-number-0">(703) 293-9600</span></div>', '<div>Bring:</div><div>- Ivy Block (trust me, if I could grow a field of fucks, that meadow of "ivy" is what it would look like)</div><div>- dawn detergent to wash off after trail</div><div>- insect repellant (&apos;cos malaria, West Nile, an&apos; shit)</div><div>- Shiggy socks</div><div>- head lamps</div><div>- water wings/umbrella/ snorkel (might rain)</div><div>- snake bite kit (Water has been high and we&apos;ve been seeing snakes out of the creek beds, apparently they don&apos;t like to drown)</div><div>- your standard dry bag</div><div>AND</div><div>- lock your shit and hide it</div>', '10312 Willard Way<div>Fairfax, VA 22030</div><div><br></div><div><span style="color: rgb(20, 24, 35); font-family: helvetica, arial, sans-serif; line-height: 18.7600002288818px;">Start Location is BEHIND the Safeway off of Plaza Dr</span></div>', ''),
(695, 'This week the Udder Ho presents...a trail.<div>That&apos;s right, you have a be trail, be happy for that much!</div>', '<div>From Toll Road - get onto 123/Dolly Madison Blvd towrs</div><div>Tysons. &nbsp;Go straight through the light and cross over 123 to stay on</div><div>Anderson Rd. &nbsp;Go a bout a mile or less and Safeway will be on the the</div><div>right</div><div><br></div><div>From Rt 7/Tysons - Get on 123/Dolly Madison heading towards Mclean.</div><div>Pass the Mclean Metro then take the next Right onto Anderson. &nbsp;Follow</div><div>for a bit and Safeway is on your Right</div><div><br></div><div>Metro - available but a bit of a walk to start. &nbsp;Hares might be nice</div><div>and mark it for you.</div>', 'Lost Dog Cafe - next door to Safeway', '<div>Expect short dry and flat but plan to be disappointed</div>A to A', 'Safeway 1688 Anderson Rd<div>McLean, VA 22102</div>', ''),
(696, 'In honor of Joseph Bonar-Part, we&apos;ll be celebrating the Penis Ular War: Battle of the Labia.<div>We&apos;ll be taken back to a simpler time, in 1809, where hashers were hashers, and women showed their breasts freely.</div><div>What has happened to our society?!</div>', '<b>From 66:</b><div>Get to 66.</div><div>Take exit 60 for 123.</div><div>Go South</div><div>Turn left into University Mall (corner at Braddock Road)</div><div>Go to the back, and find wanker(s) - just like anal sex</div>', 'Brian&apos;s Grill', '', 'Backside (heh) of University Mall<div><div>10681 Braddock Rd</div><div>Fairfax, VA</div></div>', ''),
(697, 'In honor of August 2nd, National Sister&apos;s Day, Tuesday trail will do it properly. And by do it, I mean do you sister.<div><a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eTDZjQvPW1E">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=eTDZjQvPW1E</a></div>', 'Put these GPS in Ms. Google and follow her to start<div>@38.854095,-77.399447</div>', '', 'The runners will have a measly 3.5 mile excursion with atleast 2 shots and a beer check. The walkers will have a short 2 mile walk with atleast a beer and shot check. Pants are highly recommended for runners and walkers shouldnt need any special gear. Beer check will have the full range of beer from Bitburger light to Horny Goat PB. I am trying to clear my beer fridge for a restocking.', '<div>Start at behind the closed G Mart at Fair Lakes Shopping Center</div><div>13065 Fair Lakes Shopping Center</div><div>Fairfax, VA 22033</div>', 'https://www.google.com/maps/place/Nationwide+Money+Services,+Inc./@38.854095,-77.399447,17z/data=!4m7!1m4!3m3!1s0x89b64596abd00d9b:0x10eadcc9b1185dd7!2sWalmart+Supercenter!3b1!3m1!1s0x0000000000000000:0xf2ccaea7a53781be');
