(710, '<font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3">\n\n</font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"><span style=&apos;line-height: 115%; font-family: "Book Antiqua","serif"; font-size: 14pt;&apos;><font color="#000000">Should we? Shouldn&apos;t we? Should we? Shouldn&apos;t we?</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3">\n\n</font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"><span style=&apos;line-height: 115%; font-family: "Book Antiqua","serif"; font-size: 14pt;&apos;><font color="#000000">Does THAT sound like a MisManagement to you? It does to\nus!!</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3">\n\n</font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"><span style=&apos;line-height: 115%; font-family: "Book Antiqua","serif"; font-size: 14pt;&apos;><font color="#000000">So many years ago (I don&apos;t remember... I&apos;ve ran out of\nfingers) the So Happy It&apos;s Tuesday Hash House Harriers ran its first trail on a\nTuesday evening on September 10<sup><font face="Book Antiqua" size="3">th</font></sup></font><font color="#000000"> 2002. </font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3">\n\n</font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"><span style=&apos;line-height: 115%; font-family: "Book Antiqua","serif"; font-size: 14pt;&apos;><font color="#000000">Yes... we know... it&apos;s October!! That&apos;s why it&apos;s called "MisManagement"!!\nSo... we&apos;re going to celebrate the birth of the hash at the Busch InBev abode in\nAshburn.</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3">\n\n</font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"><span style=&apos;line-height: 115%; font-family: "Book Antiqua","serif"; font-size: 14pt;&apos;><font color="#000000">So come on out... drink some beers... enjoy some food... have\nplenty of debauchery and leave (eventually) knowing that you&apos;ve help celebrate\nanother end of one year and the beginning of another for the So Happy It&apos;s\nTuesday Hash House Harriers.</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3">\n\n</font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt;"><span style=&apos;line-height: 115%; font-family: "Book Antiqua","serif"; font-size: 14pt;&apos;><font color="#000000">Also... &apos;shake the hands&apos;, &apos;give a hug&apos;, maybe it&apos;s a &apos;kiss\non the cheek&apos; to some of those rare individuals that do a lot of the extra work\neach week to ensure that the hash goes on: The Udder Ho, All The Way In, Parent&apos;s\nWeekend, Vaginger Monoloques, Tasters Choice, and Silver Lining to only mention\na few.</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3">\n\n</font><div style="border-width: medium medium 1pt; border-style: none none solid; border-color: currentColor currentColor windowtext; padding: 0in 0in 1pt; border-image: none; mso-element: para-border-div; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid windowtext .75pt;"><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3">\n\n</font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt; padding: 0in; border: currentColor; border-image: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid windowtext .75pt; mso-padding-alt: 0in 0in 1.0pt 0in;"><span style=&apos;line-height: 115%; font-family: "Book Antiqua","serif"; font-size: 14pt;&apos;><font color="#000000">Others that need to be\nthanked are those that come out each week to hare our trails. Each and every one\nneed to be commended. Since the first day I&apos;ve started hashing here with So\nHappy It&apos;s Tuesday Hash House Harriers, And How&apos;s Her Bush, we&apos;ve been known as\na welcoming kennel for all of you who come out and run our trails, drink our\nbeer and eat all our orange and black and white food!!</font></span></p><font color="#000000" face="Times New Roman" size="3">\n\n</font><p style="margin: 0in 0in 10pt; padding: 0in; border: currentColor; border-image: none; mso-border-bottom-alt: solid windowtext .75pt; mso-padding-alt: 0in 0in 1.0pt 0in;"><span style=&apos;line-height: 115%; font-family: "Book